ead the sliced almonds in a pie plate and toast in the oven for about 7 minutes, until golden brown.'),(1398,7,'Let cool.'),(1398,8,'Reduce the oven temperature to 30'),(1398,9,'In a large skillet, heat 1/8 inch of vegetable oil. Season the skate with salt and pepper and dredge in flour, shaking off the excess. Fry 2 pieces of skate over high heat until they are golden brown and crisp, about 3 minutes. Carefully turn and fry the skate until just opaque throughout, about 30 seconds longer.'),(1398,10,'Transfer the skate to a large rimmed baking sheet and keep warm in the oven. Fry the remaining skate.'),(1398,11,'Pour off the oil and wipe out the skillet.'),(1398,12,'Add the remaining 4 tablespoons of butter to the skillet and melt over high heat. Cook the butter until it starts to turn brown, about 1 minute.'),(1398,13,'Add the almonds and shake the skillet.'),(1398,14,'Remove the skillet from the heat and swirl in the lemon juice.'),(1398,15,'Spoon the parsnip puree onto plates and top with the skate.'),(1398,16,'Drizzle the butter-almond sauce over the fish and serve.'),(1709,1,'Heat the oven to 400F. Grate the potato using the large holes of a box grater, but dont apply too much pressureyou want fairly thin shavings. Season with salt and pepper and toss with the oil or melted butter.'),(1709,2,'Spread half the horseradish on each fillet and season with a little more salt and pepper. Gently pat the potato topping on the surface of each fillet, pressing lightly so it sticks.'),(1709,3,'Bake according to the instructions in the recipe at left, but note the lower temperature in this recipe. Cook the fish for 15 to 18 min. If the fish is almost cooked but the potato topping isnt crisp, switch the oven to broil for the last few minutes.'),(1709,4,'Serve immediately.'),(2295,1,'Whisk together the flour, beer, and taco seasoning mix.Wash catfish nuggets and pat dry with paper toweling.In a food processor or blender, process for a few seconds sour cream, cilantro, lime juice and additional taco seasoning mix to taste.You don\'t want to totally liquify the cilantro.Prepare garnishes as you heat about 1/2\" of oil in a cast iron skillet or heavy frying pan to 360F.Dip fish nuggets into batter and place in hot oil with a fork.Turn once after about 1 minute and brown the other side for another minute.Do this in batches.Don\'t crowd the fish.'),(2295,2,'Drain on paper toweling and keep warm in a 200F oven until ready to serve.'),(2295,3,'Heat tortillas in foil in the oven or nuke them wrapped in a clean kitchen towel.'),(3131,1,'Heat the oil in the pan.'),(3131,2,'Add the onion and saute until tender, about 6-10 minutes.'),(3131,3,'Add the garlic and chili pepper flakes and saute until fragrant, about a minute.'),(3131,4,'Add the fennel and red peppers and saute for a few minutes.'),(3131,5,'Add the white wine and simmer for a few minutes.'),(3131,6,'Add the tomatoes, oregano, paprika, salt and pepper, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.'),(3131,7,'Add the fish simmer until cooked, about 5 minutes.'),(3131,8,'Remove and mix in the fresh herbs.'),(4040,1,'Watch how to make this recipe.'),(4040,2,'Pat fish dry and combine in a nonreactive bowl with the white wine, lime juice and garlic. Set aside to marinate about 10 to 15 minutes.'),(4040,3,'When fish is ready, remove it from the marinade, pat dry, and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper.'),(4040,4,'Heat oil in a large nonstick frying pan over medium-high heat. When oil shimmers, place fish skin-side down in skillet. Cook until opaque and firm to touch, about 3 minutes per side.'),(4040,5,'Flake the fish, squeeze one of the lime wedges over the top, and toss to coat. To make a taco, stack 2 tortillas on top of each other and fill with fish, lettuce, salsa, a few avocado slices, and a dollop of sour cream. Repeat to make 6 tacos total.'),(4098,1,'MAKE PORTIONS BY DIVIDING THE MONKFISH IN TWO 100 GRAM SECTIONS. COOK THE WHOLE POTATOES IN THE FISH STOCK. BLANCH THE GREEN BEANS AND 