 to 8 minutes. Season the stew with salt, if needed.'),(8161,5,'For the Crostini: Put an oven rack in the center of the oven and preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.'),(8161,6,'Arrange the bread slices in a single layer on a baking sheet and drizzle with olive oil.'),(8161,7,'Bake until light golden, about 12 minutes. Cool for 2 minutes. Rub the warm toasts with the cut side of the garlic.'),(8161,8,'Ladle the stew into serving bowls and garnish with parsley.'),(8161,9,'Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle a few red pepper flakes on top.'),(8161,10,'Serve with the crostini.'),(8212,1,'Put wine, shallots, and crushed garlic in a large pot. Set a steamer basket in pot, add clams, and cover. Bring to a boil, then simmer briskly over medium-high heat until clams open, 5 to 10 minutes.'),(8212,2,'Transfer clams to a plate and let cool. Strain broth from pot; set aside 3/4 cup plus 2 tbsp. and chill.'),(8212,3,'Remove meat from clams, saving 8 shells; chill meat and shells.'),(8212,4,'Meanwhile, in a large frying pan over medium heat, saut poblano chile, corn, and pepper in oil until chile is tender-crisp, 7 to 8 minutes.'),(8212,5,'Add minced garlic; cook, stirring, 1 minute.'),(8212,6,'Remove about 2 tbsp. of mixture and set aside.'),(8212,7,'Stir masa in a bowl with 2 tbsp. reserved clam broth and 2 tbsp. water. Stir in corn mixture from pan and half of clam meat. Spoon into 8 (4- to 6-oz.) oiled ramekins; smooth tops. Cover each with foil.'),(8212,8,'Put a rack in a roasting pan and fill pan with water to just below rack. Set ramekins on rack. Cover pan tightly with foil.'),(8212,9,'Heat over 2 burners on high heat until a little steam escapes; reduce heat to medium-low and cook until tamales feel fairly firm, 35 minutes.'),(8212,10,'Meanwhile, in a small frying pan over medium-high heat, cook jalapeos until blackened, turning occasionally, 20 to 25 minutes.'),(8212,11,'Let cool, then peel, seed, and dice.'),(8212,12,'Boil reserved 3/4 cup clam broth in a saucepan over medium-high heat until reduced to 1/3 cup, 5 minutes. Stir in jalapeos. A few minutes before serving, whisk in butter a bit at a time until melted. Stir in remaining clams and heat until warm, then stir in shells.'),(8212,13,'Unwrap ramekins; put on plates. Spoon clam sauce on top and set a clamshell on each. Top with reserved poblano chile, cilantro, and Fresno chiles.'),(8212,14,'*Masa for tamales has fat, leavening, and salt added to ground corn. Find it at Latino markets.'),(8261,1,'Place the chicken breasts one at a time in between to pieces of parchment paper or plastic wrap and pound to a -inch thickness. You can use a meat mallet or a rolling pin. The idea is to get the chicken to an even thickness all around.'),(8261,2,'Remove from the paper and place in a glass baking dish and squeeze the juice of 1 lemon on top.'),(8261,3,'Drizzle with an equal amount of olive oil.'),(8261,4,'Sprinkle with  teaspoon sea salt or kosher salt and black pepper to taste. Allow to sit at room temperature for 30-60 minutes.'),(8261,5,'Heat the grill to medium. In the meantime, prepare the salad dressing.'),(8261,6,'Cut the garlic clove in half and rub the inside of a medium bowl with the cut side of the garlic.'),(8261,7,'Add the garlic to the bowl. To the bowl, add 3 Tablespoons lemon juice, Dijon mustard,  teaspoon sea salt, and black pepper to taste.'),(8261,8,'Whisk to combine.'),(8261,9,'Pour  cup olive oil into the bowl, whisking constantly to emulsify. Taste for seasoning and tartness.'),(8261,10,'Add more oil if necessary.'),(8261,11,'Remove chicken from marinade and grill a few minutes on both sides until golden brown.'),(8261,12,'Place on a cutting board. Arrange the arugula on a platter and drizzle with enough of the dressing to coat lightly.'),(8261,13,'Cut the chicken into strips and arrange on top of the arugula. Scatter tomatoes on top and drizzle a little more dressing. Or arrange the chicken on a platter and top with dressed arugula leaves and tomato.'),(8467,1,'