ly.'),(47459,1,'Melt butter in heavy large saucepan over medium heat.'),(47459,2,'Add shallots and celery. Cook until soft, stirring frequently, about 8 minutes.'),(47459,3,'Add wild rice, 4 1/2 cups broth, thyme, and 1/2 teaspoon coarse salt; bring to simmer. Cover, reduce heat to medium-low, and simmer 30 minutes.'),(47459,4,'Add brown rice, cover, and simmer until rice is tender but firm, adding more broth by 1/4 cupfuls if dry, about 40 minutes longer. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cool slightly; cover and chill. Rewarm over medium-low heat before using, adding more broth by 1/4 cupfuls if dry.'),(47459,5,'Meanwhile, preheat oven to 350°F.'),(47459,6,'Place grapes on rimmed baking sheet.'),(47459,7,'Drizzle with oil; toss. Roast grapes until beginning to wrinkle, about 15 minutes.'),(47459,8,'Transfer to bowl; toss with vinegar. DO AHEAD: Can be made 4 hours ahead.'),(47459,9,'Let stand at room temperature.'),(47459,10,'Add grapes and any juices, walnuts, and orange peel to hot rice; toss well. Season to taste with salt and pepper.'),(47590,1,'Preheat oven to 40'),(47590,2,'Place a lightly greased wire rack in an aluminum foil-lined 15- x 10-inch jelly-roll pan. Dip bacon slices in syrup, allowing excess to drip off; press pecans onto both sides of bacon. Arrange bacon slices in a single layer on rack, and bake 20 minutes; turn bacon slices, and bake 5 to 10 more minutes or until browned and crisp.'),(47590,3,'Remove from oven, and let stand 5 minutes.'),(47590,4,'Cut bacon crosswise into 1-inch pieces.'),(47590,5,'Place salad greens on a serving platter.'),(47590,6,'Cut pear and apple into thin slices; toss with salad greens. Top with grapes, cheese, and bacon.'),(47590,7,'Serve salad with Cranberry Vinaigrette.'),(50227,1,'In a heavy saucepan over medium low heat melt the chocolate and the coffee; once melted remove pan from heat and stir in the butter, cream, and cinnamon.'),(50227,2,'Scoop ice cream into serving dishes top with sauce and toppings of you choice'),(52147,1,'Preheat oven to 350°F and butter and flour 9 (1/2-cup) muffin cups (just butter if nonstick).'),(52147,2,'Beat together butter, sugar, and zest until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time. Beat in cream, then flour and salt, on low speed until just combined. Stir in 1/2 cup coconut and gently stir in blueberries.'),(52147,3,'Spoon batter into cups and smooth tops.'),(52147,4,'Sprinkle tops with remaining 3 tablespoons coconut.'),(52147,5,'Bake in middle of oven until a tester comes out clean and edges are golden brown, about 25 minutes. Invert onto a rack and cool.'),(54338,1,'Combine sugar and rum in a microwave-safe bowl. Microwave at HIGH 1 1/2 minutes or until sugar dissolves.'),(54338,2,'Brush rum mixture evenly over pineapple wedges.'),(54338,3,'Melt butter in a grill pan over medium-high heat.'),(54338,4,'Add pineapple to pan; grill 3 minutes on each side or until grill marks form and pineapple is thoroughly heated.'),(54338,5,'Sprinkle with coconut.'),(54338,6,'Serve with ice cream.'),(55578,1,'In a 3- to 4-quart pan over medium-high heat, stir together cranberries, orange peel, orange juice, and sugar. Bring mixture to a boil, then lower the heat to maintain a simmer, and cook, stirring frequently, until the berries have broken open and released their juices, 8 to 10 minutes.'),(55578,2,'Add Port and cook 2 minutes longer.'),(55578,3,'Let cool completely and store airtight up to 2 weeks.'),(57324,1,'Place the dried shiitakes into a small bowl and cover with hot water for about 30 minutes to allow them to re-hydrate.'),(57324,2,'Rinse the chicken to remove any residue and pat dry with paper towels. Rub the mesquite seasoning onto all the chicken parts. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. In a large saute pan, brown the chicken on all sides and place on a baking sheet.'),(57324,3,'Transfer the chicken to the oven and bake until the juices run clear and the chicken is fork tender, about 35 minutes.'),(57324,4,'Remove from oven and let rest.'),(57324,5,'While the chicken is in the oven, prepare the tomato demi-glace.'),(57324,6,'Heat the canola oil in a medium saucepan over medium-high heat and saute the red onion, celery and garlic until they begin to caramelize lightly, being careful not to burn them. Deglaze the pan with the red wine, and when most of the alcohol has evaporated, add the vegetables, stock, tomatoes, parsley leaves, and thyme. Return to a gentle boil and let the liquid reduce by half, then strain into a small bowl.'),(57324,7,'Strain the mushrooms through paper towels to reserve the soaking liquid. Use 1/2 cup of the mushroom soaking liquid in a small saucepan to make the sauce by whisking in the demi-glace.'),(57324,8,'Heat for a few minutes to let the flavors integrate.'),(57324,9,'Remove from heat and fold in the mushrooms.'),(57324,10,'Cut the figs in half lengthwise. Arrange the chicken on serving dish, spoon some sauce on top and garnish with figs.'),(57491,1,'Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F. Line a 24 count regular-size cupcake pan with cupcake liners.'),(57491,2,'In a heavy-duty mixing bowl, cream together the butter and shortening on medium speed.'),(57491,3,'Add the eggs, 1 at a time until, completely combined. Scrape down the sides of the bowl with a rubber spatula.'),(57491,4,'Add the superfine sugar with the mixer set to low speed. Once combined, set the mixer to medium speed and mix for 5 minutes.'),(57491,5,'Sift together the cake flour, almond flour, salt, and baking powder. Begin to add the sifted dry ingredients to the batter, alternating with the warm milk. Fold in the sliced almonds.'),(57491,6,'Fill the cupcake liners two-thirds of the way and bake for 16 to 20 minutes. Use a toothpick to poke in the center of the cupcake and if it comes out clean then the cupcakes are done.'),(57491,7,'Remove from the pan and place onto a tray to cool.'),(57491,8,'Once the cupcakes are cooled, fill the center of the cupcakes with 1 tablespoon Fig Filling. Using a pastry bag and piping tip, frost the cupcakes with the Maple Buttercream. Pat the sides of the buttercream with the toasted almonds.'),(57491,9,'Put all the ingredients into a blender and blend for 1 minute. Once blended, move the mixture into a microwave-safe bowl and microwave until thick, about 2 minutes.'),(57491,10,'Mix well after microwaving.'),(57491,11,'In a heavy-duty mixing bowl, cream the butter until light and fluffy.'),(57491,12,'Add 3 cups powdered sugar and mix on medium speed for 3 minutes. Scrape down the bowl and pour in the non-dairy whipping cream.'),(57491,13,'Mix on low speed until completely mixed.'),(57491,14,'Add the remaining 4 cups powdered sugar. Fold in the maple syrup.'),(59337,1,'Beat pudding mix and milk in medium bowl with whisk 2 min.  Stir in 1/2 cup COOL WHIP.'),(59337,2,'Stack cake layers on serving plate, spreading pudding mixture between layers.'),(59337,3,'Microwave chocolate and remaining COOL WHIP in microwaveable bowl on HIGH 30 sec.; stir until chocolate is completely melted and mixture is well blended. Spoon over cake. Refrigerate 1 hour.'),(59761,1,'Watch how to make this recipe.'),(59761,2,'Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F.'),(59761,3,'Combine the cranberries, apple, brown sugar, orange zest, orange juice, and 1 teaspoon of the cinnamon in a medium bowl. Set aside.'),(59761,4,'In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, beat the eggs on medium-high speed for 2 minutes. With the mixer on medium, add 1 cup of the granulated sugar, the butter, vanilla, and sour cream and beat just until combined. On low speed, slowly add the flour and salt.'),(59761,5,'Pour the fruit mixture evenly into a 10-inch glass pie plate.'),(59761,6,'Pour the batter over the fruit, covering it completely.'),(59761,7,'Combine the remaining 1 tablespoon of granulated sugar and 1/8 teaspoon of cinnamon and sprinkle it over the batter.'),(59761,8,'Bake for 55 to 60 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in the middle of the cake comes out clean and the fruit is bubbling around the edges.'),(59761,9,'Serve warm or at room temperature.'),(60093,1,'Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Lightly butter pan or ramekins.Caramel rum sauce (make up two weeks ahead)'),(60093,2,'Place sugar and water into a saucepan over medium low heat and stir the until sugar has dissolved. Dissolve any crystals forming on the side with a wet pastry brush.Once sugar has dissolved increase heat to high. Do not stir the mixture directly. Now and then, using the handle, give the pot a swirl to keep the mixture moving. The mixture will start to bubble after a minute or so.After 3-4 minutes the mixture will turn from a light amber to medium amber and then finally to a dark reddish brown color. Once the mixture starts to smoke, add the butter and heavy cream. The mixture will bubble wildly. Allow mixture to cool for ten minutes before adding dark rum.'),(60093,3,'Add dark rum and whisk to combine. Set aside to cool completely.To make banana bread (make up to three days ahead)'),(60093,4,'Place flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a bowl and whisk to combine; set side.In a separate bowl combine eggs and sugar then whisk until well combined and mixture becomes thick and light in color, about 1 minute.'),(60093,5,'Drizzle cooled butter into mixture and whisk to combine.'),(60093,6,'Add oil and buttermilk to mixture then whisk to combine.'),(60093,7,'Add vanilla extract and mashed bananas and whisk to combine.Butter the bottom of a 9x5 loaf pan and pour batter into it.'),(60093,8,'Bake at 350 degrees F or until inserted tooth pick from the center of the loaf comes out clean.'),(60093,9,'Remove from oven and cool completely.Slice and cube cooled banana bread.'),(60093,10,'Spread banana bread cubes on a bake sheet and toast until bread cubes feel dry but not hard. Cool completely on bake sheet. (If making ahead store banana bread cubes in plastic bag).To make pudding'),(60093,11,'Add sugar, eggs and salt to a bowl and whisk to combine; set aside.'),(60093,12,'Add heavy cream and whole milk to a small sauce pan and bring to a simmer. Slowly add egg mixture into cream mixture with one hand while continuously whisking the combined mixture with the other.'),(60093,13,'Add in vanilla bean paste and rum and whisk to combine. Strain mixture.Assembly'),(60093,14,'Place on a single layer of banana bread cubes in pan or ramekins.'),(60093,15,'Place sliced bananas on top and then cover banana slices with half of caramel rum sauce.'),(60093,16,'Place second layer of bread cubes down.'),(60093,17,'Pour custard all over assembled pan or pour evenly among ramekins.'),(60093,18,'Let stand for 15 minutes, occasionally pressing down bread to absorb pudding.'),(60093,19,'Place pan or ramekins in a larger pan with water filled half way up. Cover water-filled pan with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.'),(60093,20,'Remove foil and bake for another 3o minutes for ramekins and another 4o minutes for 9x9 pan.'),(60093,21,'Serve while hot with a light dusting of confectioner sugar and drizzle remaining half of caramel rum sauce top.'),(60145,1,'Heat oven to 350F.'),(60145,2,'Prepare cake batter and bake as directed on package for 24 cupcakes. Cool completely.'),(60145,3,'Beat pudding mix and milk in medium bowl with whisk 2 min.'),(60145,4,'Let stand 5 min.  Meanwhile, use serrated knife to cut cupcakes horizontally in half.'),(60145,5,'Whisk 1/2 cup COOL WHIP into pudding; spoon onto bottom halves of cupcakes, using about 1 Tbsp. for each.  Cover with cupcake tops.'),(60145,6,'Microwave remaining COOL WHIP and chocolate in small microwaveable bowl on HIGH 1-1/2 min. or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring after 1 min.  Stir until chocolate is completely melted and mixture is well blended.'),(60145,7,'Let stand 15 min.'),(60145,8,'Frost cupcakes with chocolate mixture.  Refrigerate 15 min.'),(60995,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).  Grease and flour two 9 inch, round, cake pans; cover bottoms with waxed paper.'),(60995,2,'In a large bowl, combine flour, 2 cups sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.'),(60995,3,'Add eggs, milk, oil, and 1 tablespoon vanilla; beat until well blended.'),(60995,4,'Pour batter into prepared pans.'),(60995,5,'Bake for 35 minutes,  or until wooden toothpick inserted in centers comes out clean. Cool layers in pans on wire racks 10 minutes. Loosen edges, and remove to racks to cool completely.'),(60995,6,'Drain cherries, reserving 1/2 cup juice.'),(60995,7,'Combine reserved juice, cherries, 1 cup sugar and cornstarch in a 2 quart saucepan. Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly. Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla. Cool before using.'),(60995,8,'Combine whipping cream and confectioner\'s sugar in a chilled medium bowl.  Beat with an electric mixer at high speed until stiff peaks form.'),(60995,9,'With long serrated knife, split each cake layer horizontally in half. Tear one split layer into crumbs; set aside.   Reserve 1 1/2 cups Frosting for decorating cake; set aside.  Gently brush loose crumbs off top and side of each cake layer with pasty brush or hands.  To assemble, place one cake layer on cake plate.'),(60995,10,'Spread with 1 cup frosting; top with 3/4 cup cherry topping.  Top with second cake layer; repeat layers of frosting and cherry topping.  Top with third cake layer.  Frost side of cake.  Pat reserved crumbs onto frosting on side of cake.  Spoon reserved frosting into pastry bag fitted with star decorator tip.  Pipe around top and bottom edges of cake. Spoon remaining cherry topping onto top of cake.'),(61750,1,'Heat oven to 350 F. In a medium bowl, combine the butter and crushed gingersnaps. Press the mixture into a 9-inch springform pan, working the crumbs over the bottom and then up the sides.'),(61750,2,'Bake for 20 minutes. In a small bowl, toss the pears and ginger. Line the cooled crust with the pears, overlapping the slices slightly. In a large bowl, with an electric mixer on medium, beat the cream cheese for 2 minutes.'),(61750,3,'Add 1 cup of the sugar and beat for 2 minutes.'),(61750,4,'Add the eggs, 1 at a time, and mix until combined. Stir in 2 teaspoons of the vanilla.'),(61750,5,'Pour the mixture over the pears.'),(61750,6,'Bake until the top is barely set but still slightly wobbly, about 50 minutes.'),(61750,7,'Transfer pan to a wire rack but leave oven on. In a small bowl, combine the sour cream and the remaining sugar and vanilla.'),(61750,8,'Pour over the cheesecake and bake for 8 minutes.'),(61750,9,'Transfer to a wire rack and cool to room temperature. Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours before serving.In Advance: Make the cheesecake and refrigerate for up to 2 days. Slice it just before serving, running the knife under warm water after each cut.'),(61873,1,'In a medium bowl, mix the graham cracker crumbs with the melted butter, cinnamon, 1 tablespoon of the sugar and a pinch of salt. Press the crumbs over the bottom and 1 inch up the side of a 6-inch springform pan that\'s 3 inches deep.'),(61873,2,'In a standing mixer fitted with a paddle, combine the cream cheese with the flour, the remaining 2/3 cup of sugar and 1/4 teaspoon of salt. Beat at medium-high speed until smooth, about 2 minutes. Scrape down the side of the bowl and add the eggs and the almond extract. Beat at medium speed until blended.'),(61873,3,'Add the sour cream and beat until smooth.'),(61873,4,'Pour the batter into the springform pan.'),(61873,5,'Fill a 6- to 7-quart round or oval slow cooker with 1/2 inch of water and position a rack in the bottom. Set the cheesecake on the rack. Cover the slow cooker with a triple layer of paper towels and the lid. Turn the cooker to high and cook for 2 hours without peeking. Turn off the heat and let stand until the slow cooker has cooled, 1 hour.'),(61873,6,'Remove the lid and the paper towels and transfer the cheesecake to a rack to cool to room temperature, about 1 hour. Cover the cheesecake with plastic wrap and refrigerate until chilled, at least 4 hours.'),(61873,7,'Heat a sharp, thin-bladed knife under hot water; dry the knife. Carefully run the knife around the edge of the cheesecake. Release the spring and lift the cheesecake out of the mold.'),(61873,8,'Cut into wedges and serve.'),(62619,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour a 10 inch Bundt pan. Have all ingredients at room temperature.'),(62619,2,'In a large bowl, stir together cake mix and pudding mix. Make a well in the center and pour in eggs, sour cream, oil and water. Beat on low speed until blended. Scrape bowl, and beat 4 minutes on medium speed. Stir in chocolate chips.'),(62619,3,'Pour batter into prepared pan.'),(62619,4,'Bake in the preheated oven for 50 to 60 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean. Allow to cool.'),(64017,1,'Make cupcakes: Preheat oven to 375F. Line a 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners. In a bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt.'),(64017,2,'Cream butter and sugar with a mixer on high speed until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and egg white until well combined. With mixer on low, beat in half of flour mixture. Beat in 6 Tbsp. orange juice, then add remaining flour mixture and beat until combined, scraping down sides of bowl as needed. Gently fold in chopped strawberries.'),(64017,3,'Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups, filling each until almost full.'),(64017,4,'Bake until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean, 20 to 22 minutes.'),(64017,5,'Let cool in pan on a wire rack for at least 5 minutes.'),(64017,6,'Make glaze: In a small bowl, stir together confectioners\' sugar and remaining 2 Tbsp. orange juice until smooth. If glaze is too thick, stir in additional juice, making sure to add only 1 tsp. at a time, until you reach desired consistency. Glaze should be loose enough to spread easily on cupcakes, but not so thin that it drips.'),(64017,7,'Remove cupcakes from pan and top evenly with glaze.'),(64017,8,'Let cool completely on rack, about 1 hour.'),(64017,9,'Garnish each cupcake with a strawberry half, if desired.'),(64369,1,'Stir together gingerbread cake mix, eggs, and 2 1/2 cups stout beer in a large bowl until combined.'),(64369,2,'Pour batter evenly into 2 lightly greased 8-inch square pans.'),(64369,3,'Bake at 350 for 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans on a wire rack 10 minutes.'),(64369,4,'Remove from pans, and let cool on wire rack 1 hour or until completely cool.'),(64369,5,'Beat softened butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy. Gradually add powdered sugar and remaining 1/4 cup stout beer, beating until blended after each addition. Beat 1 minute or until light and fluffy.'),(64369,6,'Spread stout buttercream between layers and on top of cake.'),(64369,7,'Garnish, if desired.'),(64369,8,'Note: For testing purposes only, we used Betty Crocker Gingerbread Cake & Cookie'),(64369,9,'Mix. We used Terrapin Wake-n-'),(64369,10,'Bake Coffee Oatmeal Imperial Stout at one testing and Guinness Extra Stout beer at another.'),(67878,1,'Preheat oven to 35'),(67878,2,'Arrange pecans in a single layer on a baking sheet, and bake 5 to 7 minutes or until lightly toasted and fragrant.'),(67878,3,'Stir together coffee liqueur and coffee.'),(67878,4,'Coarsely chop 1 chocolate bar. Microwave coarsely chopped chocolate and butter in a large microwave-safe bowl at MEDIUM (50% power) 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until melted and smooth, stirring at 30-second intervals.'),(67878,5,'Whisk in 2 cups sugar and eggs, whisking until blended; stir in flour, stirring just until blended. Spoon batter into a lightly greased 11- x 7-inch pan.'),(67878,6,'Bake at 350 for 35 minutes or until center is set.'),(67878,7,'Remove from oven, and cool in pan on a wire rack 10 minutes. Pierce brownie multiple times using the tines of a fork.'),(67878,8,'Pour coffee mixture over brownie.'),(67878,9,'Let cool on wire rack 1 hour or until completely cool.'),(67878,10,'Whisk together remaining 1/4 cup sugar, mascarpone cheese, and vanilla in a large bowl. Beat whipping cream at medium speed with an electric mixer until stiff peaks form. Fold whipped cream into mascarpone mixture.'),(67878,11,'Crumble half of brownies, and divide evenly among 6 (8-oz.) glasses. Spoon half of mascarpone cheese mixture over brownies. Repeat procedure with remaining brownies and mascarpone cheese mixture.'),(67878,12,'Chop remaining half of chocolate bar into thin shreds.'),(67878,13,'Sprinkle chocolate and pecans over mascarpone cheese mixture.'),(67878,14,'Serve immediately, or cover and chill up to 24 hours.'),(67878,15,'Note: For testing purposes only, we used Kahla for coffee liqueur.'),(68547,1,'Heat the oven to 325 degrees F.'),(68547,2,'Split the Keiser rolls favoring the bottom half a little. Scoop a little of the white soft insides out of the bottoms.'),(68547,3,'Season the ricotta with a little salt and pepper. Stir the salami and grated cheese into ricotta. Fill the rolls with the ricotta and salami. Cover the ricotta with mozzarella, tomato and basil. Set covers in place and bake to heat through 10 to 12 minutes.'),(68547,4,'Cut and serve.'),(70187,1,'Preheat oven to 350°F.'),(70187,2,'Toss together all crust ingredients with a fork until crumbs are moistened. Press evenly onto bottom and up side of a 10-inch glass or ceramic pie plate (6-cup capacity).'),(70187,3,'Bake crust in middle of oven 7 minutes, then cool on a rack.'),(70436,1,'Preheat oven to 375  degrees F (190 degrees C).'),(70436,2,'Mix the crushed cookies with 1 tablespoon of melted butter, and press onto a baking sheet.'),(70436,3,'Bake in preheated oven for 5 minutes, then remove, allow to cool completely, then crumble.'),(70436,4,'Melt the remaining 1 tablespoon of butter in a skillet over medium heat.  Stir in the apples, 3 tablespoons sugar, and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.  Cook until the apples have lightly browned, and the sugar has begun to caramelize, about 10 minutes.'),(70436,5,'Remove from the pan, and allow to cool completely.'),(70436,6,'Combine cream, half and half, 1 cup sugar, eggs, vanilla, and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon in a large bowl; mix to blend well.'),(70436,7,'Pour into an ice cream maker and freeze according to manufacturer\'s instructions.'),(70436,8,'When the ice cream has finished, stir in the crumbled cookie, caramelized apples, and walnuts.'),(70436,9,'Add the dulce de leche by the teaspoon while stirring to evenly distribute.'),(73750,1,'Bring ingredients to boil in saucepan on medium-high heat.'),(73750,2,'Simmer on medium-low heat 10 min., stirring occasionally.'),(73899,1,'Heat a paella pan over medium-high heat, and coat with olive oil.'),(73899,2,'Add the chicken, rabbit and garlic; cook and stir until nicely browned. Move the browned meat to the sides of the pan, and add the tomato, butter beans, peas, and green beans. Season with paprika, and mix well.'),(73899,3,'Fill the paella pan almost to the top with water, measuring the water as you put it in. This is to help you to determine how much rice to add, as paella pans come in different sizes. Bring to a boil. Simmer for about 1 hour to make a nice broth.'),(73899,4,'Season with a generous amount of salt, and just enough saffron to make a nice yellow color. Season with thyme and rosemary if desired. The goal is to make a rich tasting broth that will soak into the rice to make it delicious. Stir in half as much rice as the amount of water in the pan. Cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer until all of the liquid has been absorbed, about 20 minutes.'),(76517,1,'Heat olive oil over medium high in a pot large enough to hold all of the mussels.'),(76517,2,'Add shallots and saute for 1 minute, then add garlic and tomatoes and saute for 1 minute more.'),(76517,3,'Add wine to deglaze the pan and bring to a boil.'),(76517,4,'Add mussels, cover pan, and simmer until mussels open, about 5 minutes. Discard any mussels that didn\'t open during cooking. Either serve family style in a large bowl, or divide mussels among 8 bowls. Spoon a ladle of the sauce over each bowl and serve immediately with crusty French bread for soaking up the sauce.'),(76638,1,'Watch how to make this recipe.'),(76638,2,'Working, 1 at a time, scrub any grit from shells under running water. Discard open mussels that do not close with a few taps of the finger and any with cracked shells.'),(76638,3,'Put the mussels in a bowl of cold water.'),(76638,4,'Heat the oil in a large wide pot over medium-high heat and add the chorizo. Using a wooden spoon or potato masher, mash the chorizo into chunks, so it resembles ground beef.'),(76638,5,'Saute until brown, about 8 minutes.'),(76638,6,'Remove chorizo to a bowl. In the same pot, add the onion and garlic and season with salt and pepper, to taste.'),(76638,7,'Saute 3 minutes to sweat. Deglaze the pan with the wine. Pull the mussels from bowl and transfer them and the water to the pot, do not strain, leaving behind any sand and grit that has sunk to the bottom. Stir to coat.'),(76638,8,'Add the chorizo back into the pot and cover. Cook over medium heat until the mussels open, 5 to 10 minutes.'),(76638,9,'Transfer to a large serving bowl, sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately.'),(77751,1,'Mix together the chopped cilantro, lime juice, lime zest, and salt in a medium bowl.'),(77751,2,'Smash the softened butter into the cilantro lime mixture and mix it until the cilantro is well distributed.'),(77751,3,'To save the butter for later, wrap it up in plastic wrap in the shape of a log and refrigerate until stiff. To use, just unwrap and slice from the butter log.'),(77751,4,'Serve with corn-on-the-cob or over your favorite fill-in-the-blank.'),(78501,1,'Beat eggs, 2 tablespoons chives and milk in bowl to blend. Melt butter in heavy large skillet over medium heat.'),(78501,2,'Add onion and sauté until golden, about 15 minutes.'),(78501,3,'Add egg mixture. Cook until almost set, stirring occasionally, about 4 minutes.'),(78501,4,'Mix in salmon. Cook until eggs are cooked through but still moist, about 1 minute longer. Season with salt and pepper.'),(78501,5,'Transfer eggs to platter; sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons chives.'),(81112,1,'Place first 3 ingredients in a shallow serving bowl.'),(81112,2,'Gently stir in sugar and remaining ingredients. Cover and chill for at least 2 hours or overnight, if desired.'),(82486,1,'The chicken should be cut and disjointed into 8 pieces. The breast and thighs can also be cut in half again, if you prefer small pieces. Clean and singe, if necessary. Prepare the meatballs using 1 pound of ground beef and doubling the other ingredients in the recipe.'),(82486,2,'In a 2-quart Dutch oven, slowly saut the chopped onion in 3 tablespoons of the fat until the onion is soft and yellow; do not let it brown.'),(82486,3,'Remove and reserve.'),(82486,4,'Add more fat to the pot if needed and brown the chicken pieces lightly until all sides are pale golden brown. Do this in several batches, as the chicken will not brown if crammed into the pan.'),(82486,5,'Remove the chicken, sprinkle with salt and pepper, and reserve.'),(82486,6,'Return the onions to the pot and sprinkle with paprika. Saut for a minute or two, until the paprika loses its raw smell.'),(82486,7,'Add the tomato juice and 1 cup water.'),(82486,8,'Return the chicken to the pot and add the garlic cloves. The liquid should come about halfway up the chicken. Cover and simmer gently but steadily for 20 minutes. Gently and carefully add the meatballs to the pot, moving the chicken aside to make room and shaking the pot intermittently to separate the meatballs. These will be fragile while raw, but once cooked they will become firm and will not crumble or stick together.'),(82486,9,'Add more liquid to the pot if needed. Simmer, loosely covered, for another 20 to 30 minutes, or until the chicken and meatballs are done.'),(82486,10,'Remove the chicken and meatballs and skim the fat from the gravy. Return the chicken and meatballs and reheat, checking, the seasoning as you do so.'),(82486,11,'Serve the chicken and meatballs with rice or noodles.'),(82486,12,'If you plan to make this in advance, add a little water before reheating.'),(85937,1,'Season the tomatoes and onions with salt and pepper on both sides.'),(85937,2,'Brush the tomatoes and onions with canola oil on both sides.'),(85937,3,'Place tomatoes and onions on a hot grill and grill for 3 minutes per side.'),(85937,4,'Remove from the grill and coarsely chop.'),(85937,5,'Place in a bowl and add balsamic vinegar and thyme. Check for seasoning. Set aside.'),(85937,6,'In a shallow dish, combine cornmeal, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper. Lightly dredge the catfish fillets in the cornmeal, pressing lightly to make the cornmeal stick well.'),(85937,7,'Place a saute pan on the grill and heat. When the pan is hot, add 3 tablespoons of canola oil and heat.'),(85937,8,'Place the catfish in the pan, and pan fry for 3 to 4 minutes per side or until the cornmeal is golden brown.'),(85937,9,'Serve the catfish with the grilled tomato and onion salad.'),(89955,1,'Bring orange juice, chipotles, and vinegar to a boil in a 1- to 1 1/2-quart heavy saucepan, then reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until reduced to a generous 1/3 cup, 15 to 20 minutes.'),(89955,2,'Remove from heat and cool.'),(89955,3,'While sauce cools, prepare charcoal or gas grill for cooking. If using a charcoal grill, open vents on bottom of grill, then light charcoal. Charcoal fire is medium-hot when you can hold your hand 5 inches above rack for 3 to 4 seconds. If using a gas grill, preheat burners on high, covered, 10 minutes, then reduce heat to moderately high.'),(89955,4,'While grill heats, stir together coriander, cumin, chili powder, black pepper, and kosher salt in a shallow bowl.'),(89955,5,'Brush tuna on all sides with 1 tablespoon oil (total), then coat all sides evenly with spice mixture.'),(89955,6,'