tes or until the top turns golden brown.Lastly and most importantly, let the pastitsio rest for an hour or two before eating. The bchamel has to set and solidify a little bit. If you don\'t wait, the sauce will gush out.'),(139914,1,'Using a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment (or a handheld mixer or a wooden spoon), cream the butter until creamy and light, about 2 minutes.'),(139914,2,'Add the granulated sugar and brown sugar and continue to beat on medium speed for about 1 minute, or until combined. Turn the speed down to low and add the flour and mix until well combined. Slowly drizzle in the orange juice and mix for about 30 seconds.'),(139914,3,'Transfer the batter to an airtight container and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or for up to 1 week.'),(139914,4,'When ready to bake cookies, position a rack in the center of the oven, and heat the oven to 350°F. Line a very flat baking sheet with parchment paper. (This batter spreads like crazy, so you have to use an extremely flat baking sheet in order for the cookies to bake in circles and not amoeba-like shapes.)'),(139914,5,'Pinch off rounded tablespoon-size balls of dough and place on the prepared baking sheet, spacing them at least 3 inches apart to allow for spreading.'),(139914,6,'Bake for 16 to 18 minutes, or until the cookies are completely golden brown throughout.'),(139914,7,'Let cool completely (they must be firm to the touch) on the baking sheet on a wire rack. Gently remove the cookies from the parchment.'),(139914,8,'The cookies can be stored, in layers separated with sheets of parchment paper or waxed paper, in an airtight container at room temperature for up to 3 days.'),(140760,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).'),(140760,2,'In a large bowl, beat together the butter, vanilla and sugar until light and fluffy. Sift together the salt and flour and mix into the butter mixture.  Fold in the chocolate chips and nuts.'),(140760,3,'Mix until well blended. Press batter into a 15x10 