y whisk together the eggs, apple cider vinegar, and honey.'),(240308,4,'Make a well in the middle of the dry ingredients, and pour the egg mixture into it.'),(240308,5,'Gently mix with a spatula until a wet, chunky dough forms, and then throw in the apple.'),(240308,6,'Combine the ingredients with your hands, and form a ball of dough.'),(240308,7,'On a sheet of parchment paper or a nonstick surface, gently flatten the ball with your hand. The round of dough should be about 3/4 inch thick. Using a pastry cutter or a sharp knife, cut the dough into 6 equal-sized wedges, and arrange them on the parchment-lined baking sheet.'),(240308,8,'Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, rotating the tray halfway through. The scones are ready when they\'re golden brown, and an inserted toothpick comes out clean.'),(240308,9,'Transfer the scones onto a wire rack to cool slightly before serving.'),(240308,10,'This isn\'t just another subpar substitute for the real thing. It\'s BETTER than scones made with wheat flour!'),(240308,11,'BONUS RECIPE!'),(240308,12,'In the mood for Dark Chocolate Cherry Scones instead? Follow the same recipe, but leave out the cinnamon and apple.'),(240308,13,'Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla extract in step'),(240308,14,'Then, in step 5, add 3 ounces of super dark chocolate, cut into bite-size chunks, and 1/4 cup of dried cherries.'),(240308,15,'Reprinted with permission from Nom Nom Paleo: Food for Humans by Michelle Tam + Henry Fong. Nom Nom Paleo copyright © 2013 Michelle Tam & Henry Fong. Published by Andrews McMeel Publishing, LLC.'),(240528,1,'Preheat oven to 400°F. Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper.'),(240528,2,'Cut stack of phyllo sheets lengthwise into 4 equal stacks.'),(240528,3,'Cover phyllo stacks with 2 overlapping sheets of plastic wrap and then a damp kitchen towel (to keep phyllo moist).'),(240528,4,'Remove 3 strips from 1 stack and place separately on a work surface, then brush each strip with butter. Gather and pleat the long side of each strip to form a 3-inch ruffled fan.'),(240528,5,'Arrange 3 fans to form a 6-inch circle on 1 corner of baking sheet. Make 3 more circles in same manner and arrange on remainder of baking sheet.'),(240528,6,'Sprinkle each circle with 1/2 teaspoon sugar.'),(240528,7,'Repeat twice, adding 2 more layers of ruffled fans to each circle, sprinkling each layer with 1/2 teaspoon sugar. (Each flower will have 3 layers of ruffles.)'),(240528,8,'Arrange pear slices in 1 slightly overlapping layer on phyllo flowers, leaving a 1-inch border.'),(240528,9,'Place 3 raspberries in center of each flower.'),(240528,10,'Sprinkle fruit with remaining 2 tablespoons sugar.'),(240528,11,'Bake flowers in middle of oven until phyllo is golden, 18 to 20 minutes. Using a wide spatula, carefully transfer to a rack to cool.'),(240568,1,'Combine raspberry lemonade, coconut rum, and amaretto liqueur in a large pitcher. Stir well, and serve over ice.'),(241521,1,'Preheat oven to 375°F.'),(241521,2,'Place mushroomsin large bowl. Toss with 4 tablespoonsoil. Scatter mushrooms on rimmed bakingsheet.'),(241521,3,'Sprinkle with coarse salt and pepper.Roast until tender, stirring occasionally, 25to 30 minutes. Cool up to 2 hours.'),(241521,4,'Place large bowl of cool water nearstovetop.'),(241521,5,'Pour additional water into largeskillet to reach depth of 2 inches.'),(241521,6,'Add1 tablespoon lemon juice and generoussprinkling of coarse salt to skillet. Bringwater to simmer over medium heat. Crackeggs, 1 at a time, into water (whites mayspread). Simmer until whites are cookedthrough and yolks are still soft, occasionallyspooning water over, about 3 minutes.'),(241521,7,'Using slotted spoon, transfer eggsto bowl of cool water. Reserve skilletwith poaching water. DO AHEAD:  Can bemade 2 hours ahead.'),(241521,8,'Let stand at roomtemperature. Bring reserved skillet of waterto simmer. Rewarm eggs 1 minute.'),(241521,9,'Whisk remaining 2 tablespoons oil and2 tablespoons lemon juice in another largebowl to blend. Season dressing to taste withcoarse salt and pepper.'),(241521,10,'Add frisée, radishes,and mushrooms and toss to coat. Dividesalad among plates. Top each salad withpoached egg and serve.'),(241521,11,'Per serving: 240.7 kcal calories,'),(241521,12,'2 % calories from fat,    19.8 g fat,'),(241521,13,'7 g saturated fat,'),(241521,14,'0 mg cholesterol,'),(241521,15,'0 g carbohydrates,'),(241521,16,'5 g total sugars,'),(241521,17,'3 g net carbohydrates,'),(241521,18,'Bon Appétit'),(241692,1,'Combine all ingredients in a large stock pot; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 3 hours.'),(241692,2,'Remove oxtails.'),(241692,3,'Remove meat; coarsely chop, discarding bones.'),(241692,4,'Add meat to soup.'),(241692,5,'Ladle soup into individual serving bowls; serve warm.'),(241976,1,'Preheat the oven to 425°F/220°C.'),(241976,2,'Put the pumpkin in a roasting pan with the onion and sage. Season and pour over the olive oil. Cook for around 30 minutes, or until the pumpkin is tender.'),(241976,3,'While the pumpkin is cooking, make your dressing. In a small frying pan on a medium heat, toast the cumin seeds. This should only take a minute, and you will know it\'s ready when the dusk of the cumin is wafting round your kitchen. Cool for a minute, then squeeze the lemon juice into the pan and add the olive oil. Put this into a pitcher or something and leave to the side, stirring in the crème fraîche just before serving.'),(241976,4,'Now, the greens. In a big frying pan, heat the olive oil and garlic. Throw in the greens and cook until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.'),(241976,5,'Take the pumpkin out of the oven.'),(241976,6,'Put the greens on a plate, top with the pumpkin, and cover with the dressing.'),(241976,7,'Recipes by Sophie Dahl. Reprinted with permission from Very Fond of Food: A Year in Recipes by Sophie Dahl, © 201'),(241976,8,'Published by Ten Speed Press, a division of Random House, Inc.Sophie Dahl began her career as a model, but writing was always her first love. In 2003 she wrote an illustrated novella called The Man with the Dancing Eyes, which was a Times bestselling book. This was followed by a novel, Playing with the Grown-Ups, published to widespread praise by Bloomsbury in 200'),(241976,9,'Dahl is a contributing editor at British Vogue. She has also written for US Vogue, Waitrose Food Illustrated magazine, the Observer, the Guardian, and the Saturday Times Magazine, among others.A devoted eater and cook, she wrote a book chronicling her misadventures with food, Miss Dahl\'s Voluptuous Delights, published by Harper'),(241976,10,'Collins in 2009, which was her second Times bestseller. Following the success of Voluptuous Delights, Dahl wrote and presented a popular BBC2 six-part cooking series, The Delicious Miss Dahl, which aired in numberous countries all over the world.Dahl lives in England, where she continues to work on her journalism, fiction, and baking.'),(243494,1,'Preheat oven to 35'),(243494,2,'Weigh or lightly spoon flour into dry measuring cups; level with a knife.'),(243494,3,'Place flour, 1/4 cup powdered sugar, pine nuts, and salt in a food processor; pulse 2 times to combine.'),(243494,4,'Add butter and canola oil. Pulse 3 to 5 times or until mixture resembles coarse meal.'),(243494,5,'Place mixture into the bottom of an 8-inch square glass or ceramic baking dish coated with cooking spray; press into bottom of pan.'),(243494,6,'Bake at 350 for 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Reduce oven temperature to 32'),(243494,7,'Combine granulated sugar and next 5 ingredients (through egg white) in a medium bowl, stirring with a whisk until smooth.'),(243494,8,'Pour mixture over crust.'),(243494,9,'Bake at 325 for 20 minutes or until set.'),(243494,10,'Remove from oven, and cool completely in pan on a wire rack. Cover and chill for at least 2 hours.'),(243494,11,'Sprinkle squares evenly with 2 tablespoons powdered sugar.'),(244029,1,'Stir together orange juice and next 3 ingredients; serve over ice.'),(244029,2,'Garnish, if desired.'),(244548,1,'Heat oven to 375°F with rack in middle.'),(244548,2,'Meanwhile, stir together bread crumbs and milk in a large bowl and set aside.'),(244548,3,'Cook onion, carrot, celery, and garlic in oil with 1 teaspoon salt in a heavy 12-inch skillet over medium heat, covered, stirring occasionally, until tender, 8 to 10 minutes.'),(244548,4,'Remove from heat and cool.'),(244548,5,'Combine beef, pork, ketchup, eggs, Worcestershire sauce, smoked paprika, pepper, 1 teaspoon salt, and cooked vegetables with bread crumbs and mix with your hands until vegetables are well distributed and mixture is cohesive.'),(244548,6,'Form mixture into a 12-inch loaf, about 4 1/2 inches wide, in pan, and lay bacon slices crosswise over it.'),(244548,7,'Roast in oven until an instant-read thermometer inserted into the center registers 160°F, 40 to 45 minutes.'),(244548,8,'If the bacon on top isn\'t crisp, reset oven to broil and broil the meatloaf, 4 to 5 inches from the heat, until bacon is crisp and browned, 2 to 3 minutes.'),(244548,9,'Let meatloaf rest in pan 10 minutes before transferring to a platter.'),(245587,1,'Trim the fat and coat chicken pieces in lemon juice, salt, and herbs: Trim all the fat from the chicken breast and slice it lengthwise. In a small bowl mix the lemon juice, salt, and herbs.'),(245587,2,'Add the chicken pieces and coat all over with the lemon juice mixture.'),(245587,3,'Let the chicken pieces sit in the lemon juice while you heat the water in the next step.'),(245587,4,'Bring a pot of water (2 1/2 quarts of water, 4 quart pot) to a high simmer.'),(245587,5,'Roll up the chicken in plastic wrap: '),(245587,6,'Roll out a long sheet of plastic wrap at least twice as long as the chicken breast slices.'),(245587,7,'Place 1 chicken strip on the plastic wrap, in the middle.'),(245587,8,'Roll up the chicken in the plastic wrap tightly.'),(245587,9,'Compress as much air out of the chicken as you can as you roll it. Once the chicken is rolled up, rotate it on your cutting board or counter several times to tighten the cylinder even more. Tie the loose ends of the plastic wrap together in a double knot. Repeat with the second chicken strip.'),(245587,10,'Poach the chicken in the hot water: Once the water has reached a high simmer, turn off the heat (keep the pot on the burner though) and drop the rolled-up chicken cylinders in the pot. Cover the pot and let the chicken steep for 15 minutes.'),(245587,11,'The chicken should be cooked through by then. (If for some reason the chicken is not cooked through, for example if you are using larger than called for breasts, or if you are using frozen chicken that hadn\'t quite defrosted before starting cooking, you can always put the chicken back in the poaching liquid for a few more minutes.)'),(245587,12,'To serve, snip off the tied ends of the plastic wrap, and unwrap. Note that there will be some juice inside the plastic wrap with the chicken, which has lots of flavor. So you might want to unwrap the chicken pieces over a bowl or something to catch the juice, which you can then pour over the chicken if you want. Or serve the chicken with a sauce of your choice.'),(246013,1,'Heat corn tortillas according to package directions.'),(246013,2,'Cut tortillas into circles with a 3-inch cutter. Put tortilla circles on a plate, and cover with a towel; set aside.'),(246013,3,'Cook pork in a large nonstick skillet in 1 tablespoon hot vegetable oil over medium heat 5 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring constantly.'),(246013,4,'Remove pork from pan, and drain on paper towels. Wipe skillet clean.'),(246013,5,'Saut onion, garlic, and peppers in remaining 1 tablespoon hot oil over medium-high heat 3 to 4 minutes or until onion is tender. Stir in pork, tomato paste, vinegar, pepper, and salt; cook, stirring occasionally, 2 to 3 minutes.'),(246013,6,'Remove from heat, and stir in cilantro.'),(246013,7,'Spoon 2 tablespoons pork mixture evenly down center of each tortilla circle; top evenly with cheese.'),(246013,8,'Roll up, and secure with a wooden pick.'),(246013,9,'Pour vegetable oil to depth of 1 1/2 inches into a large heavy skillet. Fry taquitos, in batches, in hot oil (35'),(246013,10,'over medium-high heat 1 to 2 minutes or until golden brown.'),(246013,11,'Remove wooden picks, and serve immediately.'),(246013,12,'*1 pound of chopped or shredded pork (without sauce) from your favorite barbecue restaurant can be used.'),(246109,1,'Season shrimp with salt and pepper.'),(246109,2,'Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat; add shrimp and fennel seeds to pan. Cook until shrimp are opaque, turning often (about 3 minutes).'),(246109,3,'Remove pan from heat; toss shrimp with 1 tablespoon lemon juice.'),(246109,4,'In a large bowl, combine watercress, fennel, radishes, remaining olive oil, and remaining lemon juice, tossing well.'),(246109,5,'Divide salad among 4 plates; top each evenly with shrimp, mint, and cheese.'),(246851,1,'Combine the ingredients to prepare the dough.'),(246851,2,'Add enough water to form a ball of dough, knead a couple of times and keep it covered for an hour.To prepare the stuffing, add the teaspoon of oil in a frying pan and let it heat for a minute.  Now add the mint leaves and sauteed it for a while until it is wilted.'),(246851,3,'Remove the pan from the stove and keep it aside.Now to the mashed potato add the mint leaves, the remaining ingredients for the stuffing and combine together thoroughly.Divide the paratha dough into lemon size balls and the stuffing into smaller size balls.  I got 5 balls of dough for the above measurement.Now roll each ball of dough into a small circle and place one ball of the stuffing and cover it with the dough and roll it back again.Meanwhile preheat the griddle (tava) and once the tava is hot, cook the parathas on both the sides, by adding little oil.Enjoy it with yogurt and/or your favorite pickle.'),(247322,1,'Preheat oven to 375°F.'),(247322,2,