ut not solid.'),(252465,8,'Spread preserves over bottom of prepared crust. Spoon yogurt mixture evenly over preserves; freeze until set. Cover with plastic wrap; freeze 6 hours or until firm.'),(252465,9,'Place pie in refrigerator 30 minutes before serving to soften.'),(253168,1,'Preheat the oven to 40'),(253168,2,'In a blender, puree the parsley, water, shallots, thyme and 2 tablespoons of the olive oil; season with salt and pepper.'),(253168,3,'In a large cast-iron skillet, heat the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil in the oven for 10 minutes.'),(253168,4,'Add the bacon to the skillet and bake for 12 minutes, or until the fat is rendered and the bacon is slightly crisp.'),(253168,5,'Transfer the bacon to a plate.'),(253168,6,'Add the potatoes to the skillet and turn to coat them with the fat; season with salt and pepper.'),(253168,7,'Bake the potatoes for 15 minutes, or until tender and lightly browned; transfer to the plate with the bacon.'),(253168,8,'Set the skillet over moderately low heat. Crack 4 of the eggs into the skillet and fry for 2 minutes per side, until the whites are set and the yolks are still runny (or until done to your liking).'),(253168,9,'Transfer the eggs to 2 plates and repeat with the remaining 4 eggs. Spoon the bacon and potatoes alongside the eggs and dollop the parsley sauce on top.'),(253168,10,'Serve at once.'),(253168,11,'Make Ahead: The parsley sauce can be refrigerated overnight. Bring to room temperature before serving.'),(253168,12,'Wine Recommendation: A soft, fruity and young Spanish Tempranillo will stand up to the salty bacon and contrast with the difficult-to-match eggs here. Try the 1999 Bodegas Ramon Bilbao Tempranillo Rioja Limited Edition or the 1998 Heredad Ugarte Rioja Crianza.'),(253815,1,'Combine tomatoes and pasta sauce; stir well, and set aside.'),(253815,2,'Combine cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, and pepper; stir well, and set aside.'),(253815,3,'Spoon one-third tomato mixture into bottom of a 13- x 9- x 2-inch