h portion into 10 rectangles, and press 4 almonds into each rectangle. (Wooden cookie molds may be used to press dough into assorted shapes, omitting almonds.)'),(256564,6,'Preheat oven to 425 for 7 minutes; reduce heat to 325, and bake cookies for 25 minutes. Cool slightly on cookie sheets.'),(256564,7,'Remove to wire racks to cool completely. Break cookies apart, and store in airtight containers.'),(256832,1,'Evenly spread walnut oil over bottom of a large, heavy skillet over medium-high heat.'),(256832,2,'Place Brussels sprout halves in skillet cut side down. Cook 5 to 10 minutes, until cut sides are lightly browned.'),(256832,3,'Pour orange juice over sprouts in skillet, and continue cooking 5 minutes or until sprouts are tender.'),(256832,4,'Transfer to a large bowl.'),(256832,5,'Place the walnuts in a small skillet over medium heat. Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until lightly toasted. Gently toss Brussels sprouts with toasted walnuts and orange zest. Season with salt and pepper.'),(256963,1,'Grease a 9x13-inch baking dish.'),(256963,2,'Mix rolled oats, steel-cut oats, rice cereal, dried fruit, and almonds together in a large bowl.'),(256963,3,'Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat; add brown sugar, honey, and vanilla extract.'),(256963,4,'Whisk until sugar is completely dissolved, about 2 minutes.'),(256963,5,'Pour over oat mixture; stir to combine.'),(256963,6,'Spread oat mixture into prepared baking dish. Press chocolate chips into top. Refrigerate until chilled, about 1 hour.'),(256983,1,'Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).'),(256983,2,'Place the potatoes in a single layer in a ceramic casserole dish. Melt the butter in a skillet over medium heat.'),(256983,3,'Add garlic, and cook until golden. Stir in the rosemary, and cook just until fragrant.'),(256983,4,'Pour over the potatoes in the dish. Season with sea salt and pepper.'),(256983,5,'Roast uncovered for about 30 minutes in the preheated oven, until the potatoes are fork tende