ulation. Grill the packets, covered, until the fish is just cooked through, 8 to 10 minutes. Carefully open the packets and slide the fish and vegetables onto plates. Top with more cilantro and serve with lime.'),(286346,3,'Photograph by Antonis Achilleos'),(288015,1,'In a medium skillet over medium heat, brown the ground beef, onion, and green pepper; drain off liquids.'),(288015,2,'Stir in the garlic powder, mustard, ketchup, and brown sugar; mix thoroughly. Reduce heat, and simmer for 30 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.'),(289046,1,'Blend the peas and vegetable broth in a blender until smooth. Take the lid off and, with the motor running, pour in the oil in a steady stream to emulsify the mixture.'),(289046,2,'Add the lemon juice then chill in the refrigerator for 1 hour.'),(289046,3,'To make the spicy crab, whisk the canola oil, chili paste, and lemon juice together in a bowl. Fold in the crabmeat and mint and season with a pinch of salt. Fill espresso or sake cups, about 3/4 full, with the chilled pea soup.'),(289046,4,'Garnish the pea shots with a generous tablespoon of the spicy crab and serve immediately.'),(289161,1,'Place the potatoes into a large pot and cover with salted water. Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.'),(289161,2,'Drain and allow to steam dry for a minute or two. Return the drained potatoes to the pot.'),(289161,3,'Pour the vegetable broth, thyme, rosemary, oregano, basil, onion powder, parsley, sage, and garlic over the potatoes; mash with a potato masher.'),(289709,1,'Watch how to make this recipe.'),(289709,2,'Combine sour cream, juice, zest, salt and pepper in a medium nonreactive bowl. Store, covered in refrigerator until ready to use.'),(289709,3,'Heat a lightly oiled grill pan over medium heat. Meanwhile, brush onions and mushrooms with oil and season well with salt and freshly ground black pepper.'),(289709,4,'When grill pan is heated, add onions cut side down and cook until softened, about 10 minutes.'),(289709,5,'Transfer to a plate.'),(289709,6,'Add mushrooms and grill until charred and soft, about 10 minutes.'),(289709,7,'Serve immediately with sour cream sauce.'),(289867,1,'Quarter and seed tomatoes. Dice the tomatoes and transfer to a bowl. Finely chop enough onion to measure 1/2 cup and chop cilantro. Stir chiles, onion, cilantro, and garlic into tomatoes with sugar and lime juice and season with salt and pepper.;'),(289954,1,'Combine the sake, mirin, soy sauce, sugar, ginger and sesame oil in a dish that you can steep the chicken in, (I use a 23cm square dish, but anything of similar dimensions would do).'),(289954,2,'Add the prepared chicken pieces and leave for 15 minutes.'),(289954,3,'Heat the peanut oil in a large shallow frying pan or casserole (that has a lid) over medium heat. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the chicken pieces from the marinade to the pan.'),(289954,4,'Saute them until they look cooked on the outside.'),(289954,5,'Add the marinade to the chicken pieces and bring to a bubble, then turn down the heat to a gentle simmer, put the lid on and cook for about 5 minutes.'),(289954,6,'Cut into a piece of chicken to make sure it\'s cooked through.'),(289954,7,'Remove the cooked pieces with a slotted spoon (you could keep them in a bowl covered in aluminum foil to keep them warm) and turn the heat up under the pan to let the liquid boil down to a thick dark syrup.'),(289954,8,'Return the chicken pieces back to the pan, stir well so that all the chicken pieces are coated in the sticky savory syrup.'),(289954,9,'Serve with a comforting pile of sushi rice and perhaps some steamed baby bok choy or other veggies of your choice.'),(291394,1,'Cut chicken into 1- x 1 1/2-inch pieces; set aside.'),(291394,2,'Combine next 5 ingredients; mix well. Dip chicken into batter, and fry in hot oil (37'),(291394,3,'until golden brown.'),(291394,4,'Drain on paper towels.'),(291394,5,'Combine honey and mustard, stirring well.'),(291394,6,'Serve with nuggets.'),(291749,1,'Rinse the chicken and remove any organs that may be inside.'),(291749,2,'Place in a pot large enough for the chicken to move around, but not too much room or the broth will be watery.'),(291749,3,'Add the chicken neck if that is included with your chicken. Fill with enough water to cover by about 1 inch. Cover and bring to a boil. When boiling, reduce heat to low and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour, skimming the fat from the top as it collects.'),(291749,4,'When the chicken is done, the meat should pull from the bones easily.'),(291749,5,'Transfer the bird to a large bowl and set aside to cool.'),(291749,6,'Add the rice, and season the broth with salt and pepper. Simmer over low heat for 20 more minutes, or until rice is tender.'),(291749,7,'Whisk the eggs with the lemon juice in a bowl. When the rice is done, turn off the heat.'),(291749,8,'Whisk one ladle full of hot broth into the eggs slowly so the eggs do not curdle. Gradually whisk in more broth until the egg mixture is heated. Then pour the egg mixture back into the pot, whisking briskly. The result should be a creamy, cloudy looking soup. You may season with additional salt, pepper or lemon juice at this point.'),(291749,9,'You may add pieces of chicken to the soup before serving or serve soup with salted chicken on the side.'),(291864,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.'),(291864,2,'In a large bowl, combine the ground chuck and next 8 ingredients, mixing well.'),(291864,3,'In a small bowl, combine the ketchup and mustard. Stir 1/4 cup ketchup mixture into meat mixture, reserving remaining ketchup mixture.'),(291864,4,'Press meat mixture into a 9 by 5 by 3-inch loaf pan, or shape into a loaf and place on a rack in a broiler pan.'),(291864,5,'Spread remaining ketchup mixture over loaf.'),(291864,6,'Bake 40 minutes. Top with French fried onions; bake another 10 to 15 minutes, or until meat is no longer pink.'),(292223,1,'Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add oil.'),(292223,2,'Place over medium-high heat until hot.'),(292223,3,'Add peas and water chestnuts; saute 4 to 5 minutes or until peas are crisp-tender.'),(292223,4,'Combine soy sauce and remaining 3 ingredients, stirring until smooth.'),(292223,5,'Add to vegetable mixture. Bring to a boil, and cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.'),(292497,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 12x18 inch half sheet pan.'),(292497,2,'In a large bowl, using a wooden spoon, mix together the eggs, oil, sugar and pumpkin until well blended.'),(292497,3,'Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and nutmeg; stir into the pumpkin mixture until just blended.'),(292497,4,'Spread evenly into the prepared pan.'),(292497,5,'Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in the preheated oven, until bars spring back when lightly touched. Cool before cutting into bars.'),(292903,1,'Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease 12 muffin cups.'),(292903,2,'Mix 1 1/2 cup confectioners\' sugar, almond meal, butter, flour, egg whites, and xanthan gum together in a bowl until just combined. The mixture will be slightly grainy. Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups. Scatter blueberries onto batter.'),(292903,3,'Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted in the center of a muffin comes out clean, about 25 minutes. Cool muffins in pan for 10 minutes before transferring to a wire rack. Dust with about 2 tablespoons confectioners\' sugar.'),(294447,1,'Preheat oven to 275 degrees F (135 degrees C). Grease two 9 inch tube pans.'),(294447,2,'In a saucepan over medium heat cook apricots in the water until they are mushy. Press them through a sieve and let them cool.'),(294447,3,'Separate the eggs. Beat the egg yolks until lemony colored. Then beat the egg whites until stiff peaks are formed. Set aside.'),(294447,4,'Cream the butter or margarine and sugar together.'),(294447,5,'Add the beaten egg yolks and the apricots, and mix thoroughly.'),(294447,6,'Combine the raisins, candied cherries, candied pineapple, and mixed dried fruits in a bowl coated with one cup of the flour.'),(294447,7,'Combine the remaining flour, baking soda, and salt.'),(294447,8,'Add this flour mixture alternately to the creamed mixture with the apricot juice. Blend this batter into the mixed fruits.'),(294447,9,'Add the chopped pecans or walnuts and fold in the beaten egg whites. Turn the batter into the prepared pans.'),(294447,10,'Bake at 275 degrees F (135 degrees C) for 2 hours.'),(294447,11,'Garnish cakes with candied pineapples and cherries. Makes about 24 servings.'),(294651,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.'),(296094,1,'Place onion, potatoes, and carrots in a 5-quart slow cooker.'),(296094,2,'Combine water, garlic, bay leaf, sugar, vinegar, and contents of spice packet in a small bowl; pour over vegetables. Top with brisket and cabbage.'),(296094,3,'Cover and cook on Low until meat and vegetables are tender, 8 to 9 hours.'),(296094,4,'Remove bay leaf before serving.'),(296607,1,'Heat a Dutch oven over medium heat.'),(296607,2,'Add first 3 ingredients to pan; cook 10 minutes or until onion is tender, stirring frequently.'),(296607,3,'Add broth, chickpeas, oregano, and salt; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 30 minutes or until chickpeas are very tender. Stir in kale; simmer 10 minutes or until kale is tender.'),(296607,4,'Serve with lemon wedges.'),(297171,1,'Watch how to make this recipe.'),(297171,2,'In a large pot with salt, boil pasta for 12 to 15 minutes until cooked. Stir often.'),(297171,3,'Drain and cool. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.'),(297171,4,'In a large pot with a dash of salt, add eggs on medium high heat. Bring to a boil. Cover and remove from heat.'),(297171,5,'Let eggs sit for 6 to 7 minutes.'),(297171,6,'Remove eggs and shock in ice water. Once thoroughly cooled, peel eggs and roughly dice.'),(297171,7,'Place pasta in a large bowl.'),(297171,8,'Add onions, celery, eggs, relish, mayonnaise, salt and pepper, hot sauce and Worcestershire.'),(297171,9,'Mix until well combined.'),(298902,1,'Heat pan over medium high heat.'),(298902,2,'Add oil, garlic and thinly sliced red onion, then mussels. Arrange mussels in a single layer.'),(298902,3,'Add vermouth to the pan and cover. Cook until mussels open. Discard any unopened shells.'),(298902,4,'Transfer mussels to a bowl.'),(298902,5,'Pour juice over mussels and sprinkle with parsley, salt and pepper. You\'ll need a second bowl, for shells.'),(299389,1,'Fill a very large stock pot about halfway with water and bring it to a boil over high heat.'),(299389,2,'Add the stone, if using, and the chicken. Return this to a boil, reduce the heat to medium, and simmer for 30 minutes, skimming any foam that may rise to the top.'),(299389,3,'Add the remaining ingredients and cook until the vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.'),(300052,1,'Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil in a medium saucepan. Stir in couscous and cranberries.'),(300052,2,'Remove from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes.'),(300052,3,'Add pine nuts and parsley; fluff with a fork.'),(300052,4,'Serve immediately.'),(300242,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.'),(300242,2,'In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda, ground ginger, cinnamon, salt, allspice and cloves.'),(300242,3,'Add the shortening, butter and the brown and granulated sugars to the bowl of a standing mixer fitted with a paddle attachment. Beat on medium speed until light and fluffy, 3 to 4 minutes. Slip in the molasses and egg and beat until well incorporated.'),(300242,4,'Add the flour mixture by scoopfuls and beat until combined.'),(300242,5,'Add the turbinado sugar to a small plate or bowl.'),(300242,6,'Roll the dough into balls that are 1 inch in diameter (1/2 ounce in weight), then roll in the sugar.'),(300242,7,'Place 12 balls on a baking sheet 2 inches apart.'),(300242,8,'Bake the cookies 9 to 11 minutes, rotating halfway through 