n the boiling water, stirring occasionally until cooked through but firm to the bite, about 8 minutes.'),(301511,4,'Drain.'),(301511,5,'Spread 1 1/2 cups turkey sauce in bottom of 9x13 baking dish. Arrange 6 noodles lengthwise over sauce.'),(301511,6,'Spread half the ricotta over noodles. Top with a third of the mozzarella cheese slices. Spoon 1 1/2 cups turkey sauce over mozzarella, and sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Repeat layers and top with remaining mozzarella and Parmesan cheese. Cover with aluminum foil; make sure foil does not touch cheese to prevent sticking.'),(301511,7,'Bake in preheated oven until sauce is hot and cheese is melted, about 25 minutes more.'),(301511,8,'Remove foil and bake until cheese is golden brown, about 25 minutes. Cool 15 minutes before serving.'),(301577,1,'Heat the vegetable oil in a large pot over medium heat. Once hot, stir in the sugar and popcorn. Cover, and shake the pot constantly to keep the sugar from burning. Once the popping has slowed to once every 2 to 3 seconds, remove the pot from the heat and continue to shake for a few minutes until the popping has stopped.'),(301577,2,'Pour into a large bowl, and allow to cool, stirring occasionally to break up large clumps.'),(301583,1,'Cut tenderloin crosswise into 12 slices, approximately 3/4-inch thick.'),(301583,2,'Place each slice on its cut surface and flatten with heel of hand to 1/2-inch thickness.'),(301583,3,'Combine crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper; dredge pork slices to coat.'),(301583,4,'Heat oil over medium-high heat in nonstick pan.'),(301583,5,'Saute pork for 2 to 3 minutes per side; remove and keep warm.'),(301583,6,'Add onion, garlic and zucchini or squash to skillet and saute 5 minutes or until tender.'),(301810,1,'Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.'),(301810,2,'Thaw 1 sheet of puff pastry, unwrap it, and brush with beaten egg. Slice pastry into 1-inch wide strips. Weave strips into lattice design, sized to fit the top of a 1 1/2 quart oven-safe medium-sized serving bowl or casserole.'),(301810,3,'Place pastry on a parchment paper-lined cookie sheet and bake until light golden brown.'),(301810,4,'Remove from oven and let stand until needed.'),(301810,5,'Adjust oven temperature to 350 degrees F.'),(302018,1,'Preheat oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Arrange trout fillets in a large baking dish.'),(302018,2,'Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat; cook and stir green onion, parsley, and garlic until fragrant, 1 to 2 minutes. Stir in mushrooms and continue to cook until just softened, 1 to 2 minutes more.'),(302018,3,'Add white wine, lemon juice, salt, and cayenne pepper.'),(302018,4,'Remove from heat and gently stir in artichoke hearts; pour mixture over trout.'),(302018,5,'Bake in preheated oven until fish flakes easily with a fork, about 20 minutes.'),(302018,6,'Remove baking dish from oven and scatter tomatoes over fish.'),(302018,7,'Set oven rack about 6 inches from the heat source and preheat the oven\'s broiler.'),(302018,8,'Return baking dish to oven and broil until fish is browned, 1 to 2 minutes more.'),(302512,1,'In the bowl of an electric mixer with the paddle attachment, beat the butter and confectioners\' sugar until soft, about 2 minutes. Beat in the egg. In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, almond flour, hazelnuts, and salt.'),(302512,2,'Add the flour mixture to the butter mixture in two batches, scraping down the sides of the bowl in between additions.'),(302512,3,'Mix until the dough is well combined. Scrape the dough onto a piece of plastic wrap and form it into a disk. Chill for at least 1 hour, until firm.'),(302512,4,'Preheat oven to 325 degrees F.'),(302512,5,'Roll out the dough into a 12-inch round and fit into a 10-inch tart pan with a removable bottom. Trim excess dough. Use a fork to prick the crust all over to prevent air bubbles from forming.'),(302512,6,'Bake the tart crust until it\'s pale golden all over, about 20 to 25 minutes.'),(302512,7,'Transfer tart to a wire rack to cool. (Tart shell can be made 8 hours ahead.)'),(302512,8,'Triple Creme Filling: In a heavy-bottomed saucepan combine 3/4 cup of the milk and 3 tablespoons of the sugar, and bring the mixture to a simmer. Meanwhile, in a large bowl whisk together the remaining 1/4-cup milk, egg yolks, cornstarch and another 2 tablespoons of the sugar.'),(302512,9,'Remove the milk mixture from the heat and add a little bit of it to the egg yolk mixture to warm it, whisking constantly to keep the yolks from cooking.'),(302512,10,'Pour the egg yolk mixture into the hot milk mixture, whisking the milk constantly as you pour.'),(302512,11,'Return the custard to the stove and cook it over medium heat, whisking constantly until the consistency of pudding (pastry cream).'),(302512,12,'Add the cheese and freshly grated nutmeg, and whisk until smooth. Strain the custard through a sieve into a clean bowl. In a small heavy saucepan, stir and combine the remaining cup of sugar, light corn syrup and water. Cook over medium heat until it reaches (soft ball) 240 degrees F on a candy thermometer. Meanwhile, in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a whip attachment, whip whites until they are opaque and hold very soft peaks. When the sugar syrup is ready, drizzle it into the whites in a slow and steady stream on low speed. Once fully incorporated, increase the speed and whip until stiff, but still warm.'),(302512,13,'Whisk 1/3 of meringue into pastry cream to lighten. Fold in remaining 2/3 in 2 separate additions. Mound into prepared tart shell.'),(302512,14,'Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for approximately 30 minutes or until tart is golden brown and springy to the touch.'),(303191,1,'Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to boil.'),(303191,2,'Add pasta and cook until al dente, about 8 to 10 minutes; drain.'),(303191,3,'Transfer pasta into a large bowl, and mix in 1 tablespoon olive oil; cover, and refrigerate until cool.'),(303191,4,'Place lentils into a small saucepan, co