 salt and pepper to taste.'),(530169,1,'Cook pasta according to package directions and allow to cool.'),(530169,2,'Combine zucchini, tomatoes and red onion.'),(530169,3,'Combine olive oil, balsamic vinegar, garlic and basil in a bowl and then toss with pasta.'),(530169,4,'Combine pasta and vegetables, then add pepitas and Parmesan cheese.Chill for 30 minutes and serve.'),(530415,1,'Combine dressing, preserves and soup mix and place in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Season chicken and place skin side down in pan.'),(530415,2,'Bake 375 for 45 minutes until chicken is done and juices run clear.'),(530470,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.  Grease and flour a 13\"x9\" pan.  In a bowl, combine cake mix, butter, and two eggs.  Batter will be very stiff.'),(530470,2,'Spread in prepared pan.  In another bowl, combine remaining two eggs, cream cheese, and powdered sugar.  Beat until very smooth and pourable.'),(530470,3,'Pour over crust.'),(530470,4,'Bake in preheated oven for about 30 minutes, or until cake is nearly set.  Top will be a light golden brown, and center should jiggle slightly.'),(530470,5,'Let cake cool completely before cutting and serving.'),(531019,1,'Melt unsweetened baking chocolate and butter over medium-low heat, stirring constantly until almost melted.'),(531019,2,'Remove from heat and stir until completely melted.  Set aside.In a large bowl, beat eggs until light yellow in color, approx. 5 minutes.'),(531019,3,'Add sugar and mix thoroughly.'),(531019,4,'Add vanilla and melted chocolate to the egg and sugar mixture.'),(531019,5,'Mix until smooth, then add the flour and mix thoroughly.'),(531019,6,'Pour batter into greased 9\" x 13\" baking pan.  8\" X 8\" pan will work too, but may need to bake longer.  Smooth with a spatula.'),(531019,7,'Sprinkles chocolate chips on top.'),(531019,8,'Bake on the center rack at 300* F for 45-55 minutes.  A clean toothpick placed in the center of the brownies indicates they are done.  Do not overbake.  Cool to room temperature, c