en into the coconut shrimplay in an even layer on the lined baking sheetplace in oven and bake for 15 to 20 min, turning half way throughpour plum sauce into a sauce pan over med heatstir in remaining ingredients and bring to a boillower heat to a simmer for 5 minremove from heat and serve with baked coconut shrimp'),(535723,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. In a large bowl, sift together the flour, salt and baking powder. Using either two knives or a pastry blender, cut the cold unsalted butter pieces into the flour until it looks like small lumps. Stir in the milk and herbes de provence until just combined.Turn the dough out onto a floured board and knead with floured hands until the dough is sticky and smooth.'),(535723,2,'Roll out to 1/2-inch thick with a floured rolling pin. Use a 3-inch biscuit cutter to cut out four biscuits.'),(535723,3,'Place on the baking sheet.'),(535723,4,'Bake the biscuits for 14-16 minutes, until the biscuits have risen and are dry to the touch. Using a pastry brush, bathe the biscuits with the melted butter. Broil for 1-2 minutes, until golden.'),(535723,5,'Remove from the oven immediately.While the biscuits are cooling, cook the eggs (over easy!).'),(535723,6,'Heat a nonstick skillet over medium heat. Cook one egg at a time, flipping once, until the whites are set. Meanwhile, cook the sausage patties according to package directions.To serve, slice open the biscuits and place one sausage patty and one egg over easy on each one. Enjoy!'),(536067,1,'In a large bowl, combine mango, tomato, jalapeño, red onion cilantro, lime juice, honey and salt; set aside. Preheat grill to medium high heat.'),(536067,2,'Add hot dogs to the grill and cook until golden brown, about 3-4 minutes. To assemble the hot dogs, add hot dogs into each hot dog bun, top with mango salsa and avocado.'),(536067,3,'Serve immediately.'),(536184,1,'In a small bowl, whisk together Greek yogurt, mayonnaise, garlic and onion powder, salt and pepper, to taste; set aside in the refrigerator. Preheat oven to 450 degrees F.'),(536184,2,'Place a cooling rack inside a baking sheet and coat rack with cooking spray; set aside. Season chicken strips with salt and pepper, to taste. In a large bowl, combine bread crumbs, garlic and onion powder; set aside. Working one at a time, dredge chicken strips in the flour, dip into the eggs, then dredge in the bread crumbs mixture, pressing to coat.'),(536184,3,'Place breaded chicken strips on top of prepared rack and lightly coat with cooking spray.'),(536184,4,'Place into oven and bake for 8 minutes. Flip each strip over and lightly coat with cooking spray. Continue baking for 8-10 minutes, or until crisp and golden brown.'),(536184,5,'Serve immediately with Greek yogurt ranch, if desired.'),(536320,1,'Put the tomatillos in a food processor and blend for 10 seconds to begin to break them up.'),(536320,2,'Add remaining ingredients and blend until liquified.Taste the salsa and if it is too spicy add more lime juice to taste as well as additional salt to taste.'),(536320,3,'Serve with fresh tortilla chips or on Mexican Dishes or put in a sealed container and keep in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.'),(536333,1,'Whisk together dressing ingredients and set aside. You may not need all of the dressing for the soba.'),(536333,2,'Cook soba according to package. Once done, drain, rinse with cold water, and drizzle with a bit of sesame oil so it doesn\'t stick.'),(536333,3,'Press tofu block under some weight for a few minutes wrapped in paper towels to press out some moisture. Then cube into 1/2 inch cubes. Sear tofu over high heat with a drizzle of oil until it is seared well, about 6 minutes.'),(536333,4,'Add tofu to soba and toss with some of the dressing.'),(536333,5,'Slice mango into two halves, leaving the large seed in the middle. Take each half and cut a grid into it and then turn it inside out.'),(536333,6,'Cut off mango pieces.'),(536333,7,'Add mango pieces to soba and top with red onion slices and fresh cilantro.'),(536333,8,'Drizzle with extra dressing and serve warm or cold.'),(536357,1,'Mix dry ingredients together in a large bowl.'),(536357,2,'Mix wet ingredients (eggs/milk/butter) in a smaller bowl.'),(536357,3,'Whisk wet ingredients into dry ingredients until well combined. The batter should be thick, but not dry or clumpy.'),(536357,4,'Stir in any add-ins that you want.'),(536357,5,'Heat up waffle iron and spray it with nonstick spray or rub it down with some oil.'),(536357,6,'Add batter to iron (1/2 cup is a good start) and cook until waffle is crispy and golden brown, about 5 minutes.'),(536357,7,'Serve with butter, honey, syrup, or jams.'),(536588,1,'Dice ham and rinse and dice chard. Try to cut out any of the large ribs in the chard.'),(536588,2,'Add ham to a large skillet over medium heat with a small drizzle of olive oil. Cook until ham starts to brown slightly, about five minutes.'),(536588,3,'Add chard and sliced red onion and cook until chard starts to wilt, about another 2-3 minutes.'),(536588,4,'Season veggies with salt and pepper and divide between two large bowls.'),(536588,5,'Top with avocado slices, an egg (poached, soft-boiled or over-easy), and a dash of hot sauce.'),(537080,1,'Combine the chopped tomatoes with the minced garlic and basil and drizzle with olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Set aside.'),(537080,2,'Slice baguette on a bias and toast in a 400 degree oven for 5-7 minutes until golden brown around the edges.'),(537080,3,'Bring a medium saucepan full of water and 1/4 Cup of white vinegar to a simmer over medium heat. Slowly roll the eggs into the water being careful not to just DROP the egg in.'),(537080,4,'Let simmer for 3 minutes, very carefully stirring.'),(537080,5,'Remove the eggs with a slotted spoon to a paper towel to drain.'),(537080,6,'Top toasted bread with bruschetta mixture and a poached egg.'),(537080,7,'Drizzle with olive oil and top with basil leaves and a pinch of paprika.'),(537426,1,'In a spice grinder, grind a handful of dried mushrooms for 25-30 seconds until they are powdered. Measure out a Tablespoon of the powder.'),(537426,2,'Use kitchen twine to tie together parsley and thyme sprigs with bay leaf.'),(537426,3,'Melt butter in a large, sturdy pot (dutch oven works well) over medium heat.'),(537426,4,'Add leeks, carrots, celery, white wine and soy sauce, plus a big pinch of salt. Cook until liquid is evaporated and veggies are soft, about 10 minutes.'),(537426,5,'Add water, broth, barley, mushroom powder, herb bundle, and garlic. Increase heat and bring to a simmer. Reduce heat and simmer for 25 minutes, partially covered.'),(537426,6,'Add potatoes, turnips, and cabbage. Cook until tender, about 20 minutes.'),(537426,7,'Remove soup from heat and stir in peas and chopped parsley.'),(537426,8,'Remove herb bundle. Season with salt and pepper.'),(537426,9,'Serve with crusty bread and lemon-thyme butter.'),(537736,1,'In a medium pot, add olive oil, onions, garlic, and red pepper flakes and begin cooking over medium heat. Cook for 5 minutes until onions are soft and fragrant. Be careful not to brown the onions and garlic. You just want them soft.'),(537736,2,'Add in tomatoes and cook for a few minutes.'),(537736,3,'Remove sauce from heat and blend with a stick blender, or normal blender until sauce is fairly smooth. It doesn\'t have to be perfect.'),(537736,4,'Add gin and sugar to sauce and bring to a simmer. Simmer for 20 minutes or so until alcohol cooks off from gin. You\'ll know when it\'s ready because it won\'t smell like strong alcohol.'),(537736,5,'Stir in cream, Parmesan cheese, and basil and season with salt and pepper. Keep warm.'),(537736,6,'Cook pasta according to package. Make sure to pull it when it is al dente or has a slight bite to it still.'),(537736,7,'Drain pasta well and add directly to sauce. Stir together.'),(537736,8,'Serve garnished with Parmesan cheese and fresh basil!'),(537865,1,'Put the olive oil in the tagine and sauté the chopped onion for about 2 mins, followed by adding in garlic.'),(537865,2,'Add all the remaining chopped vegetables, spices, harissa and other ingredients.Cover with the lid and cook over low heat for 40 mins, stirring occasionally. The end result will be a thick, hearty vegetable dish.If you\'re using a skillet/deep dish skillet, use the same process and cover with a lid.'),(537865,3,'Serve over rice, quinoa, or plain with an added protein before enjoying.'),(537865,4,'Garnish with fresh mint and parsley.Keeps well in the fridge for leftovers, simply reheat in the oven or microwave briefly.'),(537993,1,'Start by filling a large salad bowl with the dark leafy greens.Next, top with all the remaining vegetables, sweet potatoes, and hemp seeds; piling them in their own \"spot\" in the bowl (as pictured).You can arrange each ingredient in a pile and then wait to stir everything together, or you can simply top the dark leafy greens with all the remaining ingredients at the same time and stir thoroughly.The nutritional yeast + the hummus + the apple cider vinegar makes for a thick and creamy dressing on it\'s own.'),(537993,2,'Serve and enjoy!'),(538763,1,'Preheat oven to 35'),(538763,2,'Line mini muffin pans with paper liners.'),(538763,3,'Place butter and 4 ounces white chocolate in a large bowl. Microwave on high in 30 second intervals, stirring between each, until mixture is smooth.Stir in brown sugar and granulated sugar. Stir in eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition. Gradually stir in flour. Stir in vanilla. Then, stir in white chocolate morsels and nuts.Spoon batter into muffin pans.'),(538763,4,'Bake for about 15 minutes, until lightly browned. Cool in pans for 5 minutes. Then, remove from pans and cool on wire racks.'),(538859,1,'Preheat oven to 37'),(538859,2,'Butter and sugar 6 6-ounce ramekins.'),(538859,3,'Place butter, 1 tablespoon sugar, Frangelico, and vanilla in the top of a double boiler.'),(538859,4,'Heat over medium heat until butter melts.'),(538859,5,'Remove from heat.'),(538859,6,'Add 3 ounces of chocolate, and let sit until chocolate melts.'),(538859,7,'Transfer chocolate mixture to a pie plate.'),(538859,8,'Place in freezer for 10 minutes.Using a spoon, form the cold chocolate into 6 evenly-sized balls.'),(538859,9,'Place in refrigerator.'),(538859,10,'Place flour in the top of a double boiler. Slowly pour in milk.'),(538859,11,'Add salt.'),(538859,12,'Heat over medium heat, whisking constantly, until thick (about 5 minutes).'),(538859,13,'Add egg yolks. Continue to whisk constantly until mixture is the consistency of mayonnaise.'),(538859,14,'Remove from heat. Stir in 6 ounces of chocolate. Set aside to allow chocolate to melt.'),(538859,15,'Place egg whites and cream of tartar in a large stainless steel bowl. Whip until soft peaks form. Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar. Continue whipping until firm peaks form. Gently fold whipped whites into warm chocolate mixture.'),(538859,16,'Place a ball of the chilled chocolate in the center of each ramekin. Spoon the souffle mixture over the chocolate balls, filling to the rim of each ramekin.*Fill a 9\"x 13\"x 2\" pan about halfway with hot water.'),(538859,17,'Place ramekins in pan.'),(538859,18,'Bake 30-40 minutes, or until souffle has risen and tops are browned.'),(538859,19,'Remove from oven and serve immediately.'),(539059,1,'Mix together cream cheese, garlic and herbs.Stuff each pepper half with about 1 Tablespoon of cream cheese mixture. Chill until serving.'),(539059,2,'Bake potatoes according to package directions.Make dipping sauce: mix together yogurt and hot sauce, set aside.  When potatoes are done baking, sprinkle with taco seasoning and stir together to coat all of the potatoes.  You can sprinkle on the cheese now and put back in the oven until the cheese is melted.  Or if your serving dish is oven safe, you can put the potatoes in the serving dish and then top with cheese and put back into the oven to melt cheese.'),(539059,3,'Sprinkle with cilantro and green onion.'),(539059,4,'Serve immediately with dipping sauce.Cook pasta according to the package directions.In a medium saucepan, melt butter.'),(539059,5,'Whisk in flour, cooking for about a minute.  Slowly add milk, cooking until thickened, stirring often.  Stir in spices and season to taste with pepper.Reduce heat and stir in sour cream.  When smooth, add in cheeses and stir until melted.'),(539059,6,'Pour sauce over pasta, add ham and veggies.  Toss together before serving.Preheat oven to 400 degrees.Toss carrots with olive oil and salt & pepper.Roast in oven for 20 minutes.'),(539059,7,'Mix together olive oil, honey and balsamic vinegar.'),(539059,8,'Drizzle over carrots and place back in oven for 5 minutes.Enjoy!In a food processor, pulse together all salsa ingredients 4 or 5 times.  Chill at least 30 minutes to blend flavors.Preheat oven to 375°.  Line a baking sheet with foil, use wire rack if desired, spray foil and rack with non-stick spray.'),(539059,9,'Cut tilapia into strips. Beat eggs together in a shallow dish.  Open Fresh Take and combine according to the package instructions.Dip each piece of fish into egg and then into Fresh Take mixture.'),(539059,10,'Place on baking sheet and repeat with remaining fish.'),(539059,11,'Bake 13-15 minutes or until fish is cooked through.'),(539059,12,'Spread a tostada shell with 2 Tablespoons of refried beans.'),(539059,13,'Sprinkle with cheese and top with 2 strips of fish.'),(539059,14,'Layer on lettuce and drizzle with salsa.'),(539059,15,'Serve immediately.'),(539059,16,'Combine all veggies in a bowl.  Stir in cilantro and lime juice, season to taste with salt and pepper.'),(539059,17,'Let stand 10-15 minutes before serving.'),(539059,18,'Place beets and carrots into steamer basket in boiling water, steam for approx 8 minutes.'),(539059,19,'Add apples, and cook 2 more minutes.  Allow mixture to cool.'),(539059,20,'Place in blender with juice, puree until smooth.  ENJOY!In a large pot, heat olive oil.'),(539059,21,'Add ground beef and cook until brown.'),(539059,22,'Add carrots, celery, onion, and garlic and cook until vegetables start to soften. Then add tomatoes, beef broth, bay leaves, salt, pepper, and thyme. Bring to a boil and let simmer 15 minutes.'),(539059,23,'Add pasta and cook until al dente. ENJOY!** Keep in mind that the pasta will absorb some of the liquid. If you have leftovers, you may need to add additional broth or liquid the second day.'),(539646,1,'Preheat the oven to 300 degress F. Line a sheet tray with parchment paper. Turn the parchment paper over. Draw or trace 4 (4-inch) circles on the paper. (I traced the lid to my tea jar.) Turn the paper back over so the ink doesn’t come in contact with your food.Beat the egg whites on medium speed to soft peaks, or when the tips curl when the beaters are lifted out of the egg whites.'),(539646,2,'Add the powdered palm sugar one tablespoon at a time while still beating the whites.'),(539646,3,'Add the instant coffee. Beat the whites to stiff peaks, or when the tips stand straight up. Fold in the cocoa powder in two to three additions, taking care not to deflate the whites.Divide the chocolate egg mixture between the four circles, then use the back of a spoon to spread out the meringue making it lower in the center than on the edges.'),(539646,4,'Put the tray into the oven and immediately decrease the oven temperature to 250 degrees F.'),(539646,5,'Bake for 1 hour – 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until meringue is set on the outside. Turn the oven off and leave the door closed for an hour.'),(539646,6,'Remove from oven and if necessary, let cool completely. Carefully remove from parchment paper.Whip the heavy cream to stiff peaks. Stir 1/4 of the whipped cream directly into the Greek yogurt. Fold the remaining whipped cream into the Greek yogurt, adding in the vanilla stevia to taste.Top each pavlova with 1/4 of the whipped cream and 1/4 of the berries just before serving.'),(539681,1,'Prepare your liquid ingredients. Do this by combining milk and heavy cream in a large liquid measuring cup or spouted bowl. Put gelatin and arrowroot in separate, small bowls.'),(539681,2,'Add about 3 tablespoons of milk to each and stir until combined. Set gelatin and arrowroot aside.'),(539681,3,'Add half of remaining milk to a heavy bottomed sauce pan and heat over medium low heat.'),(539681,4,'Add unsweetened baking chocolate and melt chocolate over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally. Once chocolate has melted, add remaining milk, gelatin, cocoa powder, and coffee. For Mexican Chocolate Variation, add cinnamon now.'),(539681,5,'Heat until milk has scalded. Reduce heat to low, taking care not to boil.Get eggs ready to add to the milk. In this step, you beat the eggs in a medium sized bowl for 2 minutes, until light and airy.'),(539681,6,'Add ½ cup agave nectar to eggs and continue to beat on medium for about one minute.'),(539681,7,'Mixture will double in volume.Temper your eggs so that they don\'t scramble when you add them to the hot milk. This simple step involves adding 1/3 cup of scalded milk to egg mixture while whisking.'),(539681,8,'Add the tempered eggs to the milk and whisk in arrowroot. Continue to whisk slowly until milk mixture thickens and coats the back of a spoon. To test, draw your finger across the back of the spoon.'),(539681,9,'Mixture is done when it will hold a line without running.'),(539681,10,'Remove from heat.Strain ice cream mixture into a medium sized mixing bowl using a fine mesh sieve. (Tip: I like to use spouted bowls to make it easier to pour the ice cream base into the ice cream maker.) Cover and chill until mixture thickens, for a minimum 4 – 6 hours, and preferably overnight.Set up your ice cream maker according to the manufacturer\'s instructions.'),(539681,11,'Remove ice cream base from refrigerator and whisk or stir with a large spoon until the mixture is smooth.'),(539681,12,'Add ice cream base to ice cream maker. Stir freeze according to manufacturer\'s directions.When ice cream reaches the consistency you desire, (I always test it with a tasting spoon!) move to a chilled, freezer-safe container and let it harden for about 4 hours.'),(539718,1,'Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F. Line a large baking sheet with aluminum foil. Set a baking rack on the baking sheet.'),(539718,2,'Put the bacon on the baking rack.'),(539718,3,'Bake for 30 minutes, carefully flipping halfway through, or until desired crispness is achieved.'),(539718,4,'Transfer cooked bacon to a paper towel lined plate to cool.'),(539718,5,'Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Rinse the baby spinach and shake lightly to remove some of the water.'),(539718,6,'Put the spinach and chives in the skillet, season with salt and pepper, and cook, stirring, until the spinach is wilted.'),(539718,7,'Remove cooked spinach and chives to a paper towel lined cutting board, removing as much moisture as possible. Discard the paper towels. Chop the spinach and chives roughly. Stir the chopped spinach and chives into the lightly beaten eggs. Return to the skillet and cook until the eggs are set.Divide the cooked eggs into four portions. If desired, spread pesto on the toasted bread, then put the bacon on one slice of bread and top it with one-fourth of the eggs. Top the eggs with microgreens if using. Complete the sandwich with the second slice of bread.'),(539718,8,'Serve with extra pesto on the side if desired. (In my book you can never have enough pesto.)'),(540292,1,'Bring diced rhubarb, 1 cup of strawberries, sugar, corn syrup, water and scraped seeds from vanilla bean up to a simmer.Gently simmer for 10 minutes until rhubarb is tender and colour is extracted.'),(540292,2,'Remove from heat and strain'),(540292,3,'Stir in remaining strawberries while warm and let cool. Syrup can be prepared up to a week in advance and stored in the refrigerator.'),(540292,4,'Whisk flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, lemon zest and salt to combine.In a separate bowl, whisk together buttermilk, oil and egg yolks to combine.'),(540292,5,'Whisk into flour mixture and stir until just blended.Whip egg whites until they hold a soft peak when beaters are lifted and fold gently into waffle batter.Lightly grease a preheated waffle iron and spoon about 1 1/2 cups of batter onto waffle iron (for a Belgian waffle). Close and cook until steam from the waffles dies away, about 6 minutes (depending on your iron).'),(540292,6,'Remove waffles and place on an ovenproof dish, cover, and hold in a low (250 degrees F) oven until ready to serve. Waffles are best served fresh, but if preparing in advance, let waffles cool, freeze, then warm uncovered in a 300 degree F oven for 20 minutes when ready to serve.To assemble, top waffles with a dollop of whipped cream, and drizzle syrup over, top with quartered strawberries and dust with icing sugar.'),(541029,1,'Heat the oven to 180°CMelt the chocolate with butter in a heat proof bowl over simmering water together with butter and sugar.Do not let the bowl touch the water or your chocolate will burn and that’s not welcome in a chocolate cake'),(541029,2,'Mix until the sugar is dissolved then remove from the simmering water and set aside to cool down a bit.Separate the egg yolks from the whites.When chocolate mixture has cooled down a bit, mix a few spoons into the egg yolks, one at a time to temper and prevent the yolks from scrambling. Then mix all the yolks into the chocolate mixture, followed by the flour, a little at the time to avoid lumps. Set aside.'),(541029,3,'Add a pinch of salt to the egg whites and beat them to stiff peaks, then incorporate them into the chocolate mixture in 3 parts. Fold them in gently, this affects the texture of the cake.'),(541029,4,'Pour the batter into lightly buttered form and bake for 30-35 minutes.When the cake is done, set aside to cool down.Bring the cream to boil and pour over the chocolate chips. Leave to soften for a few minutes, then either using a whisk or a hand blender, mix till smooth. Set aside to cool down for 10-30 minutes.Before assembling, make sure your cake is completely cold. Very important! It will allow the ganache to set quicker.'),(541029,5,'Cut the cake in half.'),(541029,6,'Place the bottom layer on the cake stand and pour half of the ganache to the centre of the cake. Then using a knife or spatula gently spread the ganache equally to the sides, but stop about 0.5 cm to the sides, place some cherries on the ganache (to your liking). Then place the top layer of the cake and top it with the remaining ganache.'),(541029,7,'Sprinkle some white chocolate shavings and some extra cherries!'),(542309,1,'In a medium bowl, combine bell pepper, mango, red onion and lime juice.'),(542309,2,'Heat olive oil in a non-stick skillet on medium-high heat. When hot, brown chicken on each sides, about 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Reduce heat and cook until chicken is no longer pink inside. Do not overcook it, you don\'t want a dry meat.'),(542309,3,'Remove from skillet and set aside.  In the same skillet, add bell pepper, mango, red onion and lime. Cook for about 30 seconds.'),(542309,4,'Remove skillet from heat, bring chicken back to the skillet, and mix.'),(542309,5,'Garnish with cilantro or parsley and serve with jasmine rice on the side.'),(542701,1,'Prepare the brownies according to package directions. After baking, cool completely. I baked mine the day before I made the truffles. Once the brownies are cooled, break them up until they are crumbly.Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Shape the brownie crumbles into balls. I used a cookie dough scoop to scoop and press the mixture. Then, using my hands, I patted them into a rounder shape.Melt the candy melts according to package direction. If your candy melts get thin enough, then you should be able to dip the brownie balls into the melts and then remove them and place them back onto the parchment lined baking sheet. If your candy melts are too thick, you can do what I did - I used a knife to \"ice\" the brownie balls. My melts were the consistency of store bought icing so using the method I did worked perfect. It was just a tad bit time consuming.After coating each brownie truffle, top with sprinkles.'),(542701,2,'Place in the refrigerator for 30 minutes to allow the coating to harden.'),(543010,1,'Preheat the oven to 450 degrees.Using either a Silpat with a perforated sheet, or a cookie sheet, assemble your tortilla:Scatter the sausage and any veggies, then carefully break the two eggs towards the center of the tortilla.'),(543010,2,'Sprinkle with grated cheese.'),(543010,3,'Bake in a preheated oven for about 7-8 minutes for soft egg yolks, 10-11 for hard!'),(543010,4,'Remove from oven, and use a pizza cutter to slice your tortilla into wedges.'),(543132,1,'Finely slice or shred your cabbage, toss into a salad bowl along with the other salad ingredients.Make your dressing. Taste and adjust seasoning to your preference.Toss the salad with the dressing, to taste. Start with less, you can always add more!'),(543313,1,'In a mixing bowl, whisk together cake flour, cocoa powder, cornstarch, baking powder and salt until well blended, set aside. In the bowl of an electric stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment whip butter, shortening and sugar until pale and fluffy.'),(543313,2,'Mix in egg, then mix in egg white, vanilla, lemon juice and food coloring. With mixer set on low speed, slowly add in dry ingredients and mix just until combined. Cover bowl with plastic wrap and chill 2 hours. Preheat oven to 375 degrees during last 10 minutes of chilling.Shape dough into about 3 Tbsp balls and transfer to Silpat lined baking sheets. Evenly flatten balls with greased hands to about 1/2-inch.'),(543313,3,'Bake in preheated oven 9 - 11 minutes.'),(543313,4,'Remove from oven and allow to cool on baking sheet 2 minutes then transfer to a wire rack. Cool completely then frost with cream cheese frosting.For the frosting:In the bowl of an electric stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, whip cream cheese and butter until pale and fluffy.'),(543313,5,'Mix in vanilla extract followed by powdered sugar and blend until well combined and fluffy.*I used 1 tsp or red gel food coloring and 1 tsp red liquid food coloring.Recipe Source: Cooking Classy'),(543557,1,'Preheat the oven to 400 degrees.'),(543557,2,'In a bowl, combine the bran flakes and milk and let sit for 5 minutes.'),(543557,3,'Whisk in the egg, oil and sunflower butter.'),(543557,4,'In a separate bowl, mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.'),(543557,5,'Mix the dry ingredients into the wet ingredients until just combined. Fold in the mini chocolate chips, if desired.'),(543557,6,'Bake for 20 minutes, or until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.'),(543662,1,'Cook the chicken breast in a steamer pot over boiling water for 4 minutes.'),(543662,2,'Add the broccoli and yellow squash and steam an additional 4 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and vegetables are fork tender.'),(543662,3,'Place all the ingredients in a food processor and pulse.*'),(543662,4,'Cool and serve.*Its nice to keep this dish a little chunky if youre serving it to alittle one with a few teeth.'),(545254,1,'Add boiling water to gelatin mix in medium bowl; stir with whisk 2 min. until completely dissolved.'),(545254,2,'Beat cream cheese in large bowl with mixer until creamy.  Gradually add gelatin to cream cheese, mixing until well blended.  Gently stir in COOL WHIP.'),(545254,3,'Refrigerate 30 min.'),(546842,1,'Dans un saladier moyen, mettez les ingrédients de la farine à l\'huile, et mélangez bien à la fourchette. Vous pouvez préparez le topping la veille : mettez-le au frais dans un récipient hermétique.Le jour-même, préchauffez le four à 180°C. Pelez les pommes en rayures verticales alternées, de telle sorte qu\'il reste des lanières de peau. Coupez les pommes en quartier, retirez le coeur, et coupez en morceaux.Mettez les morceaux dans un plat à four (celui que j\'utilise en général est un plat carré de 25 cm de côté) et saupoudrez le topping par dessus.Enfournez et laissez cuire 40 minutes, jusqu\'à ce que les pommes soient bien tendres et le dessus brun-doré. Surveillez de temps en temps pour vérifier que ça ne colore pas trop vite ; si c\'est le cas, couvrez d\'une feuille de papier sulfurisé.'),(546842,2,'Servez tiède ou à température ambiante. Vous pouvez cuire le crumble quelques heures en avance, et le réchauffer un peu avant de servir : si le four a servi pour le plat principal, je mets simplement le crumble dans le four éteint pendant qu\'on mange. Les restes sont délicieux froids le lendemain, mangés directement à la sortie du réfrigérateur.'),(547583,1,'Preheat oven to 400* F.  Spray a 3-quart baking dish with cooking spray and set aside.Cook pasta, in salted water, according to package directions to al dente, less 2 minutes.  Reserve 1/2 cup pasta cooking water for  later use.Meanwhile in a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat.'),(547583,2,'Saute onion and zucchini 5 to 6 minutes, until softened.'),(547583,3,'Add garlic, cayenne and herbs within last minute, stirring until combined.'),(547583,4,'Remove from heat and stir in ricotta cheese and pumpkin.'),(547583,5,'Add drained pasta to pumpkin mixture, mixing to combine.'),(547583,6,'Add reserved pasta water by the tablespoonful, as needed, until desired consistency (not too stiff, but you don\'t want it to be too watery)'),(547583,7,'Pour into prepared baking dish.'),(547583,8,'Sprinkle Parmesan over top of pasta and then bake for 10 to 15 minutes, or until the cheese starts to brown.'),(547583,9,'Add crushed red pepper over tops, as desired and serve!'),(547898,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Bring a large pot of water to a boil.'),(547898,2,'Add the salt and cook the lasagna noodles to al dente, according to package directions.'),(547898,3,'Drain and carefully lay the lasagna noodles out flat on a large piece of parchment paper.'),(547898,4,'Let sit to cool.'),(547898,5,'In a medium bowl, combine the ricotta cheese, egg, garlic, spinach, artichoke hearts, parmesan cheese, basil, crushed red pepper, and nutmeg. Stir until well combined. Season with salt and pepper.'),(547898,6,'Spray a 9x13 baking dish with cooking spray. Line the bottom with marinara sauce, about 1/2 cup. Set aside.'),(547898,7,'Take about 1/4 cup of the ricotta spinach mixture and spread it evenly onto each lasagna noodle. Top each noodle with 2 tablespoons of mozzarella cheese and 2 tablespoons of marinara sauce. Carefully roll the noodles up and place them in the prepared pan. Top the lasagna rolls with the remaining marinara sauce and mozzarella cheese. Spray a large sheet of foil with cooking spray and cover the pan.'),(547898,8,'Place the pan in the oven and bake for 35 minutes.'),(547898,9,'Remove the foil and bake for an additional 5 minutes, or until the cheese is melted on top.'),(547898,10,'Remove from the oven and let sit for 5 minutes.'),(547898,11,'Serve warm.Note: To prepare the lasagna rolls in advance, roll them up, add the sauce and cheese and cover with foil and place in the fridge until ready to bake. I\'ve made them a day before baking and they were still great. To freeze, bake and let cool to room temperature.'),(547898,12,'Place in a freezer container and freeze. Reheat in the microwave. You can place a whole pan in the freezer and heat back up in the oven, but I like to freeze the rolls in individual servings for easy lunches and dinners.'),(548107,1,'Preheat grill or grill pan to medium high. Season steak with additional salt and pepper.Grill until cooked to desired doneness, 3 to 5 minutes per side for medium-rare.'),(548107,2,'Let rest for 10 minutes before slicing.Prepare Romesco sauce by combining red peppers, almonds, parmesan cheese, garlic, vinegar and salt & pepper in a food processor. Pulse until smooth.'),(548107,3,'Pour Romesco sauce over steak and serve immediately.'),(548114,1,'Combine all ingredients in a blender and puree until smooth. If Orange Julius is too runny, add more ice and puree again until drink is desired texture.'),(548414,1,'Cook orzo pasta according to package directions.'),(548414,2,'Drain the orzo and rinse with cold water to stop the cooking and to wash away some of the starches. Allow the pasta to cool.'),(548414,3,'In a large bowl, combine orzo, chickpeas, cucumbers, feta, dill, and red onion.'),(548414,4,'In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, dill, salt, and pepper.'),(548414,5,'Drizzle over salad and stir until ingredients are well coated.'),(548414,6,'Serve immediately or chilled.'),(548538,1,'Preheat oven to 350°F. Spray 9-inch pie plate with non-fat cooking spray. Boil 4 cups of water in a medium saucepan. Spray a medium skillet with non-fat cooking spray and put over medium-high heat.'),(548538,2,'Saute onion and garlic until softened, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes. Set aside.'),(548538,3,'Add spinach and cook until spinach begins to wilt. Then, add artichoke hearts, tarragon and parsley, and saute for about 2 minutes.Meanwhile, whisk together Almond Breeze, egg substitute, egg whites, 1/2 cup of cheese, lemon zest, salt and pepper.'),(548538,4,'Pour into prepared pie plate. Scatter garlic & onion mixture evenly over egg mixture.'),(548538,5,'Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup of mozzarella cheese and the parmesan cheese.To bake quiche, create a water bath: Set a large sheet pan with sides on a flat surface.'),(548538,6,'Place pie plate on sheet pan.'),(548538,7,'Pour hot water around pie plate so it goes 1/2 inch up sides of pie plate (do not get water on quiche). Carefully lift sheet pan to prevent splattering water and place in oven.'),(548538,8,'Bake in water bath until quiche is set in center, about 45 minutes.To remove pie plate from water bath, slide 2 large spatulas under pie plate and remove pie plate from oven (make sure to wear oven mitts). Leave sheet pan in oven so water can cool before removing pan from oven.Turn oven to broil. Broil quiche 3 inches from heat until golden brown, about 2 minutes.'),(548538,9,'Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.'),(548974,1,'Preheat  oven to 42'),(548974,2,'Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and lightly mist with non-fat cooking spray. Slice polenta log into 18 equally sized rounds.'),(548974,3,'Place onto baking sheet. Season with a bit of salt and pepper.'),(548974,4,'Place into oven and roast for about 12 minutes, or until edges begin to turn golden brown.Meanwhile, whisk together maple syrup and mustard in a small saucepan over medium heat and bring to a boil. Simmer until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.'),(548974,5,'Remove from heat and set aside. Preheat broiler.Season salmon fillets with salt and pepper and place onto a prepared baking sheet.'),(548974,6,'Brush evenly with about ¾ of the maple glaze and top with pineapple and jalapenos.'),(548974,7,'Place under broiler and cook for about 6-8 minutes or until the salmon flakes easily and is cooked through.'),(548974,8,'Place cooked salmon on top of polenta and drizzle with remaining maple glaze.'),(548974,9,'Serve immediately.'),(549016,1,'Cook pasta in a large pot of boiling, salted water until al dente, 8-10 minutes.Meanwhile, heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.'),(549016,2,'Add garlic, jalapeno and ginger; cook until garlic is soft, about a minute.'),(549016,3,'Add coconut milk, cover and turn up heat to bring to a simmer.'),(549016,4,'Add kale and spinach; cover and cook until just wilted and bright green (depending on the size of your pot, you may need to add it in bunches, letting a handful wilt then tossing in another handful).'),(549016,5,'Add mint and remove from heat. Puree sauce using an immersion blender (or a regular stand blender – just puree in batches or the steam created can blow the lid off).'),(549016,6,'Add salt in big pinches, tasting as you go, until the flavours pop – then it is properly seasoned.When the pasta is cooked, scoop out a cup of the pasta water before draining it. Toss the pasta with the sauce, adding splashes of pasta water if needed to thin out to desired consistency.'),(549055,1,'If using dried chickpeas, rinse in a colander then soak overnight or with the 1 hour quick soak method outlined above.'),(549055,2,'Place soaked, drained chickpeas in 9 cups of salted water. Bring to a boil then reduce to a simmer and cook for 1 hour. Reserve 1 cup of cooking liquid and drain.Meanwhile, in a separate large pot, heat ghee (or butter/oil) on medium high for 1 minute.'),(549055,3,'Add cumin seeds and allow them to sizzle for about 30 seconds.'),(549055,4,'Add onions and cook until golden brown, about 10 minutes.'),(549055,5,'Add garlic and saute 2-3 minutes. Stir in tomatoes, then add jalapeno pepper, garam masala, mango powder, turmeric, fenugreek, salt and cayenne. Reduce heat to medium and cook until oil glistens on top (about 5-8 minutes). Stir in reseved chickpea water or 1 cup fresh water if using canned chickpeas.'),(549055,6,'Add boiled, drained chickpeas (or canned chickpeas, drained). Bring to a boil on medium-high heat, then reduce to low and simmer for 20 minutes or until thickened. Stir in cilantro.'),(549245,1,'Heat the oven to 350 degrees and grease an 8x9\" baking dish.'),(549245,2,'Whisk together the water, mushroom gravy (or substitutes), and milk.'),(549245,3,'Add the mushroom mix, rice, cooked beef and carrots to a bowl and stir to combine. Dump into an 8x9\" baking dish and bake, uncovered for 90 minutes.'),(549245,4,'Add slices of cheese and return to the oven for another couple of minutes or until the cheese is melted.'),(549403,1,'Heat a large dutch oven or soup pot over medium heat.'),(549403,2,'Add a tablespoon of olive oil to the pan and then add the onion and garlic. Lower the heat to medium low and cover pot. Cook, stirring as needed until the onions are translucent and just starting to caramelize. This takes about 30 minutes.'),(549403,3,'Add the chicken, ancho chili powder, smoked paprika, ground cumin, onion powder, garlic powder, brown sugar, chipotle chilies and adobo sauce to the pot and continue to cook for an additional 10 minutes covered so that the chicken gets infused with the aromatics and the spices.Stir in the chicken broth, diced tomatoes, beans (if using), and green chiles. Stir in the dark chocolate cocoa powder.'),(549403,4,'Add salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a slow boil and cook, uncovered, stirring as needed until the liquid has reduced to your level of preference.For serving, pass the cotija cheese and chopped cilantro for topping as desired.This is great with beer bread and a salad.'),(549420,1,'Prepare the dough 1-2 hours ahead of time.Well the dough rises make the honey balsamic glaze.'),(549420,2,'Add the balsamic vinegar and honey to small sauce pan and simmer until reduce by half. This should take about 10 to 15 minutes.'),(549420,3,'Remove from the heat and set aside until ready to use.When ready to grill the pizzas preheat the grill the high heat.'),(549420,4,'Add the blackberries to a bowl and add about half of the basil. Lightly mash the blackberries with a fork.Invert a baking sheet and generously dust with flour.Divide the pizza dough in half and roll each half as thin as you can, but make sure not to rip the dough.'),(549420,5,'Cut the dough into 12 to 16 squares or circles (I did both).'),(549420,6,'Add the olive oil to a small bowl and brush both sides of the pizza rounds with the olive oil and place on the baking sheet. Carefully add half of the pizza rounds to the hot grill and grill for no more the 2 minutes. The dough will bubble up, this is good!'),(549420,7,'Remove the pizzas using tongs and repeat with the remaining pizza rounds. When all the pizzas are grilled, turn the heat on the grill down to medium.Top the grilled side of each of the pizzas with slices of brie, but make sure to leave a 1/2 inch boarder around the edges so the brie does not melt all over the grill. Then top with lightly mashed blackberries and the chopped strawberries. Carefully return the pizzas to the grill and grill another 3 to 5 minutes, our until the brie has melted and the pizzas are crisp. Top with the remaining fresh basil and drizzle on the honey balsamic glaze. To make the American flag pizza place the the blackberries in the left hand corner of a square pizza crisp and then push the strawberries into the brie in rows. Grill as directed above.'),(549616,1,'Heat the oven to 375 degrees. Spray a muffin tin with cooking spray.'),(549616,2,'Roll out the pie dough and using a circle biscuit cutter, cut out circles.'),(549616,3,'Sprinkle evenly with cinnamon sugar, then roll the tinfoil into tight little logs and very gently press the dough around the log like a taco with the cinnamon sugar side facing out. Lean each one against the side of the muffin tin and bake for 10 minutes. Allow to cool and then fill with fresh fruit and a dollop of whipped cream.'),(549782,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 9x13 inch baking dish or line with foil or parchment paper.To make the brownie batter -'),(549782,2,'Add the butter and 2 ounces milk chocolate to a medium size mixing bowl that is microwave safe. Microwave the butter and chocolate on 30 second intervals, stirring after each interval until melted and smooth. This takes me about 1 minute and 30 seconds.To the melted chocolate mixture add the sugar and instant coffee, whisking until completely combined.'),(549782,3,'Add the vanilla and egg and whisk until smooth. Stir in the cocoa powder, flour and salt until smooth and just combined, try not to over mix the batter. It will be thick.'),(549782,4,'Add 1/4 cup of the melted peanut butter (you will use the remaining 1/4 cup later) and gently stir, leaving a few streaks of peanut butter. Stir in the remaining chocolate chips or chunks.To make the oatmeal cookies - In a large mixing bowl or bowl of a stand mixer, add the oatmeal, flour, brown sugar, baking soda, salt, melted coconut oil, eggs and vanilla and beat until combined and the dough holds together (the dough will seem oily, this is good, if not add a tablespoon more of oil).'),(549782,5,'Mix in about 1/2 cup of the chocolate chunks.To assemble drop dollops of about half the brownie batter into the prepared pan.'),(549782,6,'Sprinkle the oatmeal cookie dough around and over the brownie batter. Dollop the remaining brownie batter over top the oatmeal cookie dough. If needed, re-warm the remaining 1/4 cup of peanut butter in the microwave and then drizzle it over the the pan. Use a sharp knife to swirl the peanut butter around the brownie batter (don\'t try to swirl the peanut butter around the oatmeal cookie dough). Now grab the remaining chocolate and scatter it over the pan.'),(549782,7,'Bake for about 25-35 minutes, just do not over bake. Underdone is always better in my opinion. Allow bars to cool in pan for at least 1 hour before slicing and serving.'),(550173,1,'Salt and pepper chicken and grill outside or on a grill pan or frying pan until done, for about 5-7 minutes per side or until heat comes to 165º on meat thermometer inserted in thickest part of chicken halfway in.Slice chicken into thin strips across the grain.'),(550173,2,'Add cornstarch in small bowl with water and whisk until dissolved.'),(550173,3,'Add cornstarch mixture and next 8 ingredients into small sauce pan over medium heat and bring to boil.Reduce and simmer for 2-3 minutes until it thickens up.'),(550173,4,'Remove ½ c. of sauce to add to chicken. Reserve remaining sauce for dipping.'),(550173,5,'Add reserved stir fry sauce to non-stick skillet and heat over medium high heat.'),(550173,6,'Add in chicken and green onions, stir frying just until chicken is coated and warmed about 2-3 minutes.'),(550173,7,'Remove to a cutting board and slice it into thing strips.Spoon into serving bowl on platter line with lettuce, red pepper strips, edamame, shaved almonds, cilantro, green onion and carrots.'),(550173,8,'Serve with remaining stir fry sauce for dipping and Thai Peanut Dipping Sauce (recipe follows).'),(550820,1,' Cook the pasta to the al dente stage in lightly salted water. Toast the pine nuts in a medium pan. '),(550820,2,'Heat the cream, garlic powder and butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat until butter melts. Gradually stir in all grated cheese.Reduce heat to low, and continue stirring just until all cheese is melted.'),(550820,3,'Drain the pasta and reserve some of the cooking water.Put pasta back in the pan, pour in the cheese cream and add salt and pepper. Stir gently to combine adding some of the reserved cooking water if you want to thin the sauce slightly.'),(550820,4,'Sprinkle the top with some cheese, toasted pine nuts and fresh parsley.  '),(550820,5,'Serve immediately. '),(550844,1,'Prepare the cauliflower crust according to the instructions found here'),(550844,2,'While the crust is in the oven, prepare the sun-dried tomato pesto'),(550844,3,'Add the sun-dried tomatoes, garlic, avocado oil, salt, pepper and walnuts to the bowl of a small food processor and process until reduced to a crumbly puree.'),(550844,4,'Add fresh basil leaves and pulse a few times until fully incorporated.'),(550844,5,'Add the water, one tablespoon at a time and process until fully incorporated.'),(550844,6,'Add as much water as necessary to reach the desired, “spreadable” consistency, which should be 3 to 5 tablespoons (depending on how moist your sundried tomatoes were to begin with)After the crust comes out of the oven, spread as much or as little sun-dried tomato pesto as you like over the entire surface of the crust (I used about half the recipe) Top with grated mozzarella cheese, followed by the grilled chicken, walnuts, half the goat and half the blue cheese.'),(550844,7,'Place in the oven and bake for 8-10 minutes, until the cheeses are melted and start to get bubbly and golden around the edge. Take pizza out of the oven and sprinkle with the remaining goat and blue cheeses. Top with a handful of arugula leaves, cut into 4 to 6 slices and serve.'),(550873,1,'Dissolve the fresh yeast in the milk. In a medium sized bowl mix well the butter with flour and salt.'),(550873,2,'Add the eggs and the milk with yeast and mix until well blended. Knead well, cover with plastic and refrigerate for about 1 hour to let the yeast develop. Meanwhile prepare the spinach filling. In a sauce pan put water to boil, wait until water is a bubbling boil, add fresh spinach and cook for 3 minutes, drain immediately. Set aside to cool down. When cold enough cut a little bit in smaller pieces.In a large flat-bottomed frying pan heat oil over medium-high heat. Cook onion and garlic,for about 5 minutes until soft.'),(550873,3,'Add the mushrooms and spinach and cook until any liquid has evaporated.'),(550873,4,'Add salt and pepper and remove from the heat and allow to cool.Preheat the oven to 180 (350F).'),(550873,5,'Cut the dough into 3 equal pieces.'),(550873,6,'Sprinkle flour on the working surface. Using a rolling pin roll out each piece into a rectangular about 12 inches (30 cm) long, 10 high.Cover the dough with 1/3 of the spinach filling.'),(550873,7,'Roll and cut into 1 inch slices. Arrange dough pieces in a baking tray. '),(550873,8,'Brush with egg yolk. '),(550873,9,'Bake for about 25-30 minutes or until nicely browned. '),(550981,1,'To make the overnight starter, in the evening stir down the 100% hydration sourdough starter, and remove 19 g in a bowl. First add the water and stir well.'),(550981,2,'Add flour and stir. Cover with plastic wrap, and let it rest at room temperature for 12-14 hrs (overnight). (For the 100% hydration sourdough - you either make it to have it your own as shown here- or take from a friend who has or buy from a specialized store).In the morning, in a large bowl mix the flours and wheat bran with water and the overnight starter until well combined.'),(550981,3,'Let the dough rest (autolyse) for 30 minutes.'),(550981,4,'Add the salt and knead by hand for 5-8 minutes. Wipe the inside of a wide bowl with a little vegetable oil.'),(550981,5,'Place the dough into this wide bowl so the dough can be stretched and folded without removing it from the bowl. Cover with plastic wrap. '),(550981,6,'Let the dough ferment at room temperature for 2.5 hours with folds at 50 minutes. The folding is shown here.Turn the dough out onto a floured surface. Shape it in form of a loaf.'),(550981,7,'Sprinkle the loaf with flour, cover  and let rest for 15 minutes.Meanwhile prepare 1 bowl with 1 kitchen towel, sprinkled with  flour.'),(550981,8,'Add the dough  seam-side-up, cover with the edges of the towel and proof for 2 or 2.5 hours at room temperature. You will know it\'s done when pressing the dough with the finger the it comes slowly back.Preheat the oven to 475 F (240 C) with baking stone or in case you don\'t have one preheat a baking sheet.'),(550981,9,'Place a small pot with  water at the base of the oven to create steam. Turn the proofed loaf onto a parchment and score it. You can see some tips here. Carefully transfer it to the preheated baking stone or back of the baking sheet.'),(550981,10,'Bake for 15 minutes with steam then remove the pot with water from the oven and bake for another 20-25 minutes without steam. Cool on a wire rack.'),(550981,11,'Let it cool completely before cutting  for at least 2 hrs.'),(551059,1,'In a frying pan heat oil over medium high heat. Cook onions for about 5 minutes until soft. Stir in paprika then add carrots and celery pieces. '),(551059,2,'Add soy sauce, beans, corn kernels and stir. Cook few minutes until soy sauce has evaporated, add pepper and seasonings. Before serving garnish with chopped green onion. '),(551830,1,'Preheat the oven to 500 degrees F and place a pizza stone in the oven to heat. On a piece of parchment paper, roll out (or stretch) the pizza crust into a large 14 inch circle.'),(551830,2,'Brush the pizza crust with 1 tablespoon olive oil and set aside.Meanwhile, heat a skillet over medium heat, and add the butter, sliced crimini mushrooms and sliced shallots. Salt and pepper to taste. Then stir and saute for 10-12 minutes, until the onions and mushrooms are soft and slightly caramelized.Re-stretch the pizza crust and spread a thin layer of spicy mustard over the top of the crust. Then spread the sauteed onions and mushrooms over the mustard.'),(551830,3,'Place pieces of thinly sliced steak over the mushrooms, followed by a sprinkle of parmesan cheese.Using a flat baking sheet or pizza paddle, slide the pizza onto the hot pizza stone and bake for 7-10 minutes until the edges are bubbled and crusty.'),(551830,4,'Remove the pizza from the oven and sprinkle with fresh scallions before slicing and serving.'),(552336,1,'Place the chopped white chocolate in a bowl. Scald the cream. Once it is very hot pour it over the white chocolate and let it sit for 5-10 minutes. Stir until smooth.'),(552336,2,'Add the food coloring, rose water and salt.'),(552336,3,'Mix well, then place in the fridge to cool.Once cool, scoop the ganache into an electric mixing bowl and whip until light and fluffy. (The ganache will have a strong rose flavor. Don\'t worry--the dark chocoalte will mellow it out.)'),(552336,4,'Place the ganache in a piping bag with a large tip. (You could use a plastic bag with the corner cut off.) Pipe the ganache smoothly onto the spoons. Freeze.Once the ganache filled spoons are frozen,'),(552336,5,'Place 8 oz. of the dark chocolate in a double-boiler over medium-low heat. Stir as it melts. Once completely melted, remove from heat and add the remaining chocolate. Stir until smooth.Dip the spoons into the dark chocolate. Wave the spoon a little to remove extra chocolate, then lay on wax paper to dry. DON\'T TAP! You don\'t want to create thin spots in the chocolate.Gently place dried rose petals on each spoon before the chocolate dries, don\'t press down.'),(552668,1,'Bring 1 cup of salted water to boil.  Turn off the heat, add the cous cous and stir.  Cover and let sit for five minutes.Meanwhile, whisk the olive oil, lemon juice and parsley in a medium bowl.'),(552668,2,'Add the tomato, green onion and garlic and mix.  When the cous cous is ready, add to the other ingredients and mix well.'),(552668,3,'Add salt and pepper to taste and garnish with Parmesan cheese.This is best served at room temperature or chilled but can be served warm as well.'),(553254,1,'Preheat oven to 425F. Line two baking sheets with parchment paper.Put water, butter and oil in a medium-size saucepan over medium-high heat and melt. When the butter has melted, add the flour and salt all at once and stir vigorously.  Cook and stir until the mixture forms a ball that doesn’t separate, about 20 seconds.'),(553254,2,'Remove from the heat and cool for about 5-10 minutes.'),(553254,3,'Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each one and until the dough is smooth. I use a wire whisk for this, just like in the picture.Drop heaping tablespoons of dough about 2-inches apart onto a greased baking sheet.  Or transfer the batter to a pastry bag with a round tip and pipe circles about 2-inches in diameter and about 1-inch apart onto baking sheets previously lined with parchment paper (make sure you get rid of the tips on each puff that forms when you pipping them on to the baking sheet, they tend to burn)'),(553254,4,'Bake puffs for about 11-12 minutes at 425 F (medium sized ones, for small ones 10-11 minutes at 425F and 6-7 minutes at 375F). Reduce the temperature to 375 F and bake for an additional 6-8 minutes until they are golden brown and puffy.Turn off the oven and open the door a crack and leave cream puffs inside to cool for 20-30 minutes.'),(553333,1,'Preheat oven to 400F.'),(553333,2,'Roll out the prepared dough into a round, square, rectangle, how ever you may like the pizza pie shape to be.'),(553333,3,'Spread pesto sauce over the dough.'),(553333,4,'Sprinkle goat, and provolone cheese over pie. Arrange veggies and olives over pizza.'),(553333,5,'Sprinkle mozzarella and dry oregano and bake for 20-25 minutes.'),(553541,1,'Beat butter and sugar until fluffy, about 2-3 minutes. Beat in egg, oil, zest and lime juice.'),(553541,2,'Add flours, shredded coconut and baking powder.Divide dough into two and flatten out with a rolling pin like in the pictures. Chill dough for at least 4 hours. I did over night.Preheat oven to 350F and line two baking cookie sheets with parchment paper.'),(553541,3,'Roll out the dough to about 1/4 inch thick and stamp out rounds or squares using a cookie cutter (I roll out the dough in between plastic wrap which I find very easy to do. You can use any other cookie cutter shape you like as well).'),(553541,4,'Bake cookies for 14-17 minutes. Cool on sheets for 2-3 minutes and transfer them to a wire rack and cool.If using the glaze mix ingredients to obtain desire consistency and drizzle over cookies.Tip: Dough can be chilled for up to 5 days or frozen wrapped in a double layer of plastic wrap for up to 1 month. If frozen, thaw dough in the fridge before using.'),(554113,1,'In a large saucepan, melt the butter.'),(554113,2,'Add the onion and garlic and cook 5 minutes. Stir in the flour, salt, and garlic powder until a roux forms.'),(554113,3,'Whisk in the milk.Bring to a boil and add the potatoes. Cook for 10-20 minutes or until the potatoes are done, stirring often (cooking time depends on thickness and the bottom of the pan may burn if not stirred often).'),(554113,4,'Add the cheese and stir until melted.'),(554601,1,'Preheat the oven to 375F. Lightly spray two baked doughnut pans.*In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.In a large mixing bowl, beat together the butter and sugar until creamy, about 2-3 minutes. Beat in the vanilla bean seeds, egg, and vanilla extract until incorporated then add the milk. Gradually beat in the flour mixture until just incorporated.Spoon the batter into a pastry bag** then pipe into each doughnut cavity, being careful not to fill it too full.'),(554601,2,'Bake 8-10 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes then remove from the pan and finish cooling on a cooling rack.In a medium bowl, whisk together the powdered sugar, salt, 3 teaspoons milk, and vanilla until smooth. If it\'s too thick for a glaze, add the extra teaspoon of milk.Once the doughnuts are completely cool, dip the tops of each doughnut into the glaze and let the excess drip off.'),(554601,3,'Let the glaze harden before serving. Store in an airtight container.'),(556178,1,'Preheat oven to 375 degrees.Steam cauliflower in the microwave until very soft, then mash with a fork or use a food processor.In a medium bowl, combine the cauliflower, baked beans, and hotdog pieces.Spray a 9x9 inch baking dish with cooking spray, then spread the cauliflower/baked bean/hotdog mixture in the dish.Evenly distribute the spinach over the hotdog mixture.'),(556178,2,'Sprinkle the cheese over the spinach.'),(556178,3,'Place the tater tots on the top, to form a sort of crust.'),(556178,4,'Bake for about 45 minutes, until hot and bubbly.'),(556917,1,'Melt the coconut oil in a bowl. [Mine takes about a minute in the microwave].'),(556917,2,'Add the stevia and cocoa and stir until completely combined. It will be very loose and soupy. Taste it to see if you want more sweetness.'),(556917,3,'Pour the milk into the chocolate and stir vigorously. It should start becoming more pudding/mousse like.Use a rounded tablespoon or even a coffee scoop to make a ball as best you can.'),(556917,4,'Roll in coconut flakes and set in a small cupcake liner or on a plate.Refrigerate and it will harden perfectly.'),(557330,1,'Add all ingredients into your blender and blend until smooth.If making with frozen spinach you can eliminate the ice.With fresh, add as much ice as needed to make it to your desired consistency.'),(557493,1,'Bring 4 cups of water and farro to a boil.Simmer on low until almost tender about 15 minutes.'),(557493,2,'Add salt and simmer another 5-10 minutes until water is absorbed.'),(557493,3,'Drain water if needed.Allow to cool slightly.'),(557493,4,'Add other ingredients to a serving bowl.In a small bowl whisk dressing ingredients together and toss with farro and vegetables. Makes 6 cups.'),(557493,5,'Serve room temperature or refrigerate and serve chilled.'),(558289,1,'In a large mixing bowl, beat butter and granulated sugar together. Beat in eggs, one at a time.'),(558289,2,'Add flour and cocoa powder. Fold in chopped chocolate bars. Refrigerate one hour.Shape into ball (large tablespoons), and roll in powdered sugar, covering completely. Drop on parchment paper lined cookie sheet and bake in a 350 degree oven for 10-12 minutes. Allow to cool on pan 10 minutes before removing to wire rack.ENJOY.'),(558462,1,'Cook rice according to package directions.'),(558462,2,'Heat the oil to a large, nonstick saute pan, then add the scallions, tomatoes, garlic, oregano, thyme, salt and hot sauce.'),(558462,3,'Saute until the tomatoes start to soften, then add in the rice and beans.'),(558462,4,'Mix well and adjust your seasonings as needed.'),(558519,1,'In a small saucepan, melt 7oz milk chocolate bars with butter, whisking until smooth. In a large mixing bowl, mix sour cream with brown sugar.'),(558519,2,'Add melted chocolate and butter mixture, combining completely.'),(558519,3,'Mix in corn syrup, egg and vanilla.'),(558519,4,'Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, cocoa powder and salt.'),(558519,5,'Combine until fully incorporated. Fold in 1/3 cup mini chocolate morsels and Brookside Chocolate.Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.'),(558519,6,'Place liners in jumbo muffin cups. Fill 3/4 full.'),(558519,7,'Bake for 25 minutes, remove, and immediately sprinkle remaining min chocolate morsels and milk chocolate morsels on top of muffin. Allow to cool in pan 10 minutes. **if making regular sized muffins, bake in a 375 degree oven for 15-18 minutes.'),(558524,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees.'),(558524,2,'Using a mandoline or a sharp knife, thinly slice potatoes and place into your ramekins. (You may have to cut the potatoes in order to fit them if the potato is too large).'),(558524,3,'Place the ramekins on a baking sheet.'),(558524,4,'In a small saucepan, melt 1 tbsp. of butter over low heat; then add the garlic.'),(558524,5,'Saute garlic for 1 minute; then whisk in flour to form a roux.'),(558524,6,'Stir in the heavy cream and mix until the roux has dissolved; then add your cheeses.'),(558524,7,'Simmer the sauce for 5-8 minutes until all of the cheese has melted; then pour the mixture over the potatoes in each ramekin. (Fill as much as you can to the top leaving space to add your topping).'),(558524,8,'While the sauce is cooking, add the potato chips and fried onions to your food processor and pulse until the mixture is crumbly.'),(558524,9,'Melt the remaining 2 tbsp. of butter and add to the topping.'),(558524,10,'Mix well then sprinkle the topping over each ramekin.'),(558524,11,'Place the entire pan into the oven and bake 30-40 minutes until the topping is golden brown and the potatoes are tender.'),(558582,1,'In a large bowl or stand mixer with paddle attachment, mix together coconut oil, coconut sugar, stevia and vanilla.Once blended, add in the egg, lemon lest and lemon juice.'),(558582,2,'Mix until smooth. Next, add in the oat flour, almond flour, baking powder & soda, salt.Dough should be easy to roll. If you find its too sticky, add a couple Tbsp more oat flour till it reaches a roll-able consistency.'),(558582,3,'Roll each dough ball in icing sugar and place on a cookie sheet lined with parchment paper to prevent sticking.'),(558582,4,'Bake at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes.'),(558742,1,'Place all the chicken brine ingredients in a pot and bring to a boil.'),(558742,2,'Let it boil for 1 minute, until the salt dissolves, then chill it completely.  If you\'re in a hurry, you can place the mixture in a bowl and set that in an ice bath.  Otherwise, let it chill to room temperature, then stick it in the fridge.Once the mixture is chilled, place the chicken in the brine for 10 to 12 hours.  Don\'t go beyond 12 hours or the chicken will get too salty.  Discard the brine and pat very dry with paper towels.'),(558742,3,'Let the chicken sit at room temperature for 1 hour while you prep the other stages.'),(558742,4,'Mix the flour with the garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, cayenne, salt, and pepper.  Split this between two bowls.'),(558742,5,'Place the buttermilk in a third bowl, set in between the two spiced flour bowls.Preheat your deep fryer to 320 degrees F, and right before frying, dip the legs and thighs into the flour mixture, the buttermilk, then the flour mixture again.  Fry for 10 minutes until golden brown (be careful not to crowd the fryer with too much chicken), and drain on paper towels.Raise the heat to 340 degrees F and dip the wings and breasts into the flour, then buttermilk, then flour.  Fry for 6 to 7 minutes until golden brown and cooked to 16'),(558742,6,'Enjoy the best fried chicken of your life!'),(558828,1,'In a large bowl or stand mixer with paddle attachment, cream together the butter, coconut sugar, stevia.Once blended, mix in the egg, molasses and applesauce. Once that\'s together, it will look curdled, which is how its supposed to look.Next, to the same bowl add in all the dry ingredients at once...starting with the oat flour, then baking soda, baking powder and all the spices (ginger, cinnamon, allspice).'),(558828,2,'Mix until blended together and forms a dough.Take dough, wrap in plastic wrap and chill for at least 2 hours. I chilled mine for 3 hours. You can chill for even longer, but if you chill it too long, it will just be a bit tougher to roll out.When ready to bake your cookies, preheat your oven to 350 degrees F.'),(558828,3,'Roll out dough between 2 large pieces of parchment paper or plastic wrap.A trick I used to make it easier to roll out is holding the end of the parchment paper by folding the end piece over the counter and holding it with my hips! That way, I could roll it out without the paper moving. Its a stiff dough like regular gingerbread, so it takes a bit of muscle to roll it out.Once the dough is to a thickness you like, cut into shapes. To avoid your cookie cutter from sticking, dip it in a bit of oat flour and shake off the excess.  The amount of cookies you get depend on the shape you use. Once you cut out your shapes, keep rolling out the remaining dough until you have none left.Cooking time will depend on the thickness of the cookies. I baked mine for 10 minutes. I\'d say they were average thickness. If they are fairly thin, I\'d bake for 8 minutes, then check. You just want the cookies firm, and there will be no thumbprint if you press them. You can\'t tell by color on these when you pull them out.Cool on a cookie sheet and transfer to a cooling rack.'),(558828,4,'Add icing with a piping bag if desired. I didn\'t measure the icing I made and I had lots left over, so I can\'t include in nutrition. I added 1.5 Tbsp butter with approx 2 cups icing sugar, pinch of cream of tartar and a bit of unsweetened almond milk. Just whipped to a spreadable consistency. I added it to a piping bag and decorated. Since I didn\'t add too much icing to mine, my guess would be its adding about 30 more calories per cookie and a few grams of sugar.'),(559338,1,'Preheat oven to 375 F degrees.'),(559338,2,'Mix all of the glaze ingredients together, in a large bowl and whisk well.'),(559338,3,'Add the pork ribs and massage the glaze all over the pork ribs thoroughly.'),(559338,4,'Place the ribs in a large roaster and pour the remaining glaze over it.'),(559338,5,'Bake in the oven for about 1 hour and a half and every 20 minutes or so, baste the ribs with the drippings from the pan.'),(559341,1,'Whisk the flour, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl; set aside.In a medium saucepan, add water and 1¾ cups of the granulated sugar and stir over low heat, until sugar has dissolved completely.'),(559341,2,'Add butter and chocolate and continue stirring until all the chocolate has melted and the chocolate is nice smooth.'),(559341,3,'Let cool slightly, then add the Grand Marnier and eggs and stir until just combined.'),(559341,4,'Add the flour mixture and stir until just combined.'),(559341,5,'Transfer to a bowl, cover and refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours.Position rack in the upper and lower thirds of the oven and preheat to 350 F degrees.Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper or silpat.'),(559341,6,'Put the remaining ¼ cup granulated sugar and the confectioners\' sugar in 2 separate shallow bowls. Form the dough into 1-inch balls.'),(559341,7,'Add the dough balls a few at a time, to the granulated sugar and roll to coat, then transfer to the confectioners\' sugar and roll to coat. Arrange about 1½ inches apart on the prepared baking sheets.'),(559341,8,'Bake, switching the pans halfway through, until the cookies are puffed and cracked, about 12 minutes.'),(559341,9,'Let cool 5 minutes on the baking sheets, then transfer to racks to cool completely.'),(559709,1,'For the cake: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Butter and flour two 8-inch round cake pans.In a medium bowl, sift together the flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.In the bowl of an electric mixer, beat the butter and sugars on medium-high speed until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.'),(559709,2,'Add in the vanilla and then the eggs, one at a time. On low speed beat in half the dry ingredients then the sour cream and bananas. Beat in the remaining dry ingredients. Stir in the chocolate chips.Divide the batter among the prepared pans.'),(559709,3,'Bake for 40 minutes, or until the cakes are golden brown and pull away from the edges. Cool in the pans for 15 minutes before flipping onto cooling racks to cool completely. Refrigerate until ready to frost. The colder the cake, the easier it will be to frost. You can even pop the cake in the freezer for 30 minutes to chill.For the frosting: In the bowl of an electric mixer, beat the butter and peanut butter on medium-high speed until light and fluffy.'),(560511,1,'Place flour in a mixing bowl and with 2 knives cut in the butter or margarine till the mixture resembles small peas. Stir in the sour cream and vanilla till the dough holds together. On your floured work surface knead the dough about 10 times. Divide the dough into 3 pieces and wrap in plastic wrap.'),(560511,2,'Roll one piece of the dough at a time into 10 inch circle. This is like making pizza.'),(560511,3,'Spread the dough with 2 tbsp of jam and sprinkle with one third of the chopped white chocolate. Using a pizza cutter cut the dough into 12 wedges. Starting at curved edge, roll up each wedge and place point-side down, on an ungreased baking sheet. Repeat with the remaining dough.In a small bowl stir together the sugar and cinnamon if desired and sprinkle over each cookie. If you are trying to cut back on sugar, you can omit this step.'),(560511,4,'Bake at 375 degrees for 20 to 25 min or until light golden brown.This recipe yields about 3 dozen cookies.'),(560735,1,'Prepare the crust by adding the graham crackers and sugar to a food processor and blending until a fine crumb forms.Next, add the nutella and butter and blend into a coarse crumble.'),(560735,2,'Place the crust in the bottom of a 9 x 13 baking dish.'),(560735,3,'Place in the freezer for 10 minutes.In the meantime, prepare the cheesecake filling by using an electric hand mixer to combine the cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and milk.Blend until creamy, then hand mix in the strawberries.'),(560735,4,'Remove the crust from the freezer then add the cheesecake on top.'),(560735,5,'Place back into the freezer for at least 4 hours.'),(560735,6,'Remove 20 minutes before serving to thaw enough to slice through.'),(560735,7,'Cut into bars and serve.'),(561253,1,'Make the sauce:Find a metal bowl with as round a bottom as possible and then find a pot it will fit inside, leaving enough room underneath for about an ind to an inch and a half of water, making sure the water doesn\'t touch the bottom of the bowl.Melt the butter in a pot or cup with a spout and set aside.'),(561253,2,'Whisk the egg yolks and 4½ teaspoons of water together in the bowl, place the bowl in the pot of water, and place the pot over medium-low heat.'),(562455,1,'Cut cheese in sliced squares, or desire shape.'),(562455,2,'Place flour in a plate; place beaten egg in a shallow bowl.Coat the sliced cheese with flour; dip in the beaten egg, then the bread crumbs; repeat the last two steps as often as desired to achieve the desired thickness of coating.Press the coating into the cheese lightly.Preheat a shallow pan with cooking oil to approximately 350°F; fry until golden brown; transfer to a a paper towel lined plate to drain.'),(562455,3,'Serve warm with cranberry, strawberry, or raspberry sauce or warm jam or plain.'),(562926,1,'Combine the beans and wheat berries in a large pot.'),(562926,2,'Add water to the pot, filling it so that the water is about 2 inches above the beans. Salt the water generously and bring to a boil. Lower to a simmer and cook, covered, until beans and wheat berries are tender, about an hour.'),(562926,3,'Drain and set aside.'),(562926,4,'Heat oven to 400.Toss the cauliflower and asparagus with 2 tbsp olive oil and salt, to taste.'),(562926,5,'Spread on a parchment-lined baking sheet and roast for 20 minutes, or until tender and starting to brown. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, whisk together the red pepper flakes, parsley, basil, capers, and remaining 1/4 cup olive oil. Season to taste with salt.In a large bowl, toss together the beans, wheat berries, cauliflower, asparagus, and dressing. Season to taste with salt and pepper.'),(562938,1,'Blend sugar, gum (if using), vanilla, milk in a mixer until sugar is dissolved, about 1-1/2 minutes.'),(562938,2,'Add whipping cream and mix for about 30 seconds. Do not over mix.Turn on ice cream machine and run per manufacturer’s instructions. I have a 2 quart Cuisinart Ice Cream Machine and this recipes takes about 20 minutes to freeze.'),(563328,1,'Bring cauliflower, celeriac, garlic and chicken stock to a boil over medium-high heat. Cover, reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender, 15-20 minutes.Carefully transfer to Vitamix and puree until smooth.'),(563328,2,'Add ghee, salt & pepper and blend to combine.Top with bacon and chives.'),(565143,1,'Preheat oven to 400ºF.Line a dozen muffin cups with liners or grease.'),(565143,2,'Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.'),(565143,3,'Whisk together the dairy-free yogurt, applesauce, oil, agave, orange zest and orange juice in a separate bowl.'),(565143,4,'Add wet ingredients into dry ingredients, stirring until just combined (do not over mix). Stir in currants.Fill prepared muffin cups and bake 15 minutes, or until just beginning to brown and crack on the top.Cool for several minutes in the pan and them remove onto cooling rack to cool completely.'),(566058,1,'Preheat oven to 350F.'),(566058,2,'Mix together the cake mix, softened butter, egg, and vanilla. Fold in the coconut flakes and chocolate chips. Freeze the dough for at least 15 minutes.On a parchment lined baking sheet, drop the cookie dough by tablespoons with plenty of space in between for spreading.Before baking, insert a couple of the diced Mounds pieces into the top of each cookie, pressing in just past the surface.'),(566058,3,'Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies have set up.'),(566507,1,'After brewing coffee, pour it in a cup and set the cup inside a bowl filled with ice. Chill for 15 minutes.Scoop chocolate ice cream and vanilla ice cream into a tall glass.'),(566507,2,'Pour the cold coffee over the ice cream.Taste for sweetness.'),(566507,3,'Add sugar if needed.Top with whipped cream.'),(566507,4,'Drizzle caramel topping.'),(566507,5,'Serve.'),(566878,1,'In a clay pot saut onion, carrot, celery, parsley, butter and 2 Tbs oil.'),(566878,2,'Add tomatoes, drained beans, salt and enough water to cover vegetables and bring to boil. Reduce the heat, and simmer, covered, until the beans are tender.'),(566878,3,'Transfer about 2 cups beans and their liquid to a food processor and process to a thick puree. Stir the puree back into the beans.'),(566878,4,'Add pasta, cook, stirring constantly, until the pasta is tender.'),(566878,5,'Serve with parmesan cheese.'),(567248,1,'Use your hands to combine first 8 ingredients together in a bowl.'),(567248,2,'Mix well.'),(567248,3,'Place 1 teaspoon of mixture into a gyoza wrapper. Dip your finger in water and run along the outside edge of the wrapper. Fold wrapper over the mixture and pinch closed. Repeat with remaining filling and wrappers.To cook, heat enough oil to lightly coat the bottom of a skillet over medium-high heat.'),(567248,4,'Place pot stickers in the skillet and fry 2 minutes or until bottoms are golden brown.'),(567248,5,'Pour in 1/2 cup water, cover and cook 5-7 minutes or until water has evaporated.'),(567248,6,'Serve hot. To freeze, place uncooked potstickers on a baking sheet in a single layer. Freeze until solid.'),(567248,7,'Transfer to freezer bags. Thaw before cooking.'),(568238,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees.    Rinse artichokes in cold running water. To prep the artichokes, cut the top 1 inch off of each artichoke. Then using kitchen sheers trim the points off the petals. Next cut the artichokes in half lengthwise and remove the inedible fuzzy part and any purple tipped leaves with a spoon. Rub lemon all over the artichokes.    In a small bowl combine salt, garlic powder and black pepper.'),(568238,2,'Sprinkle over the inner and outer leaves of the artichokes.'),(568238,3,'Place artichokes in a baking dish, drizzle with olive oil.'),(568238,4,'Pour water and white wine over the top. Cover with foil and bake for 40 - 50 minutes or until you can remove leaves easily.'),(568238,5,'Transfer to serving platter, squeeze a little lemon over the top if desired and serve with melted butter or mayonnaise for dipping.'),(568916,1,'For the sauce, combine all the ingredients in a medium saucepan and bring to a simmer. Continue simmering for 10-15 minutes.'),(568916,2,'Remove from the heat. While the sauce simmers, in a large pot of boiling, salted water, cook the pasta shells al dente according to package directions.'),(568916,3,'Drain and immediately place them in an even layer on paper towels or parchment. For the filling, in a medium bowl, stir together the cottage cheese, ricotta cheese, salt, pepper, parsley, oregano and basil.'),(568916,4,'Add the spinach and mix until combined. Stir in the cheeses. Lightly grease a 9X13-inch pan with cooking spray and preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Spoon about half of the sauce on the bottom of the prepared pan and spread evenly. Fill each pasta shell with an even amount of the filling (about 1/4 cup per shell, more or less) and place the shells on top of the sauce in the pan - making three rows of eight shells.'),(568916,5,'Pour the remaining sauce evenly over the top of the shells. Cover the dish with aluminum foil and bake for 35-40 minutes. Uncover and bake five or so more minutes.'),(568916,6,'Remove the pan from the oven and let the shells sit for 5-10 minutes before serving.'),(569521,1,'Whisk together all the marinade ingredients in a small bowl.'),(569521,2,'Place the flank steak in a shallow dish (like a 9X13-inch pan) and pour the marinade over the steak. Cover and let marinade for 8-10 hours, flipping the steak once or twice during the marinade time.Grill the flank steak over medium heat for about 7-8 minutes per side, depending on how well done you like your steak.'),(569521,3,'Let the steak rest for about 10 minutes before slicing very thinly against the grain and serving.'),(569562,1,'Lightly coat a deep 9 or 10-inch pie plate with cooking spray and set aside. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F.In a large pot of boiling, salted water, cook the noodles until al dente according to package directions. While the noodles boil, heat a large 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat and add the ground beef or turkey, breaking it into pieces with a wooden spoon.'),(569562,2,'Add the onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally and continuing to break up the meat, until the meat is cooked through, 5-7 minutes.'),(569562,3,'Remove the skillet from the heat and drain the excess grease, if any. Return the skillet to medium heat and stir in the crushed tomatoes, tomato sauce, dried basil and oregano. Simmer the sauce over medium or medium-low heat for 10 minutes.When the noodles are done cooking, drain and return to the pot. Immediately stir in the cream cheese and toss the noodles by lightly lifting them up and over with tongs until the cream cheese is mostly melted. Stir in the cottage cheese, 1/2 cup of the Parmesan cheese and 1/2 cup of the mozzarella cheese. Toss until the noodles are evenly coated. Stir in 2 cups of the red sauce. Keep the remainder of the red sauce warm on the stove.Scrape the noodles into the prepared pie plate and using a flat spatula, press the noodles evenly into the dish so they are tightly pressed together and evenly flat across the top.'),(569562,4,'Sprinkle the remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan and 1/4 cup mozzarella cheese across the top.'),(569562,5,'Bake the spaghetti pie for 20-22 minutes, until it is hot and bubbly and the cheese is golden on top.'),(569562,6,'Let the dish rest for 10 minutes.'),(569562,7,'Cut into slices and serve with remaining red sauce.'),(569783,1,'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.In a large skillet, melt the butter over medium heat and add the barley, nuts (if using), garlic and onions.'),(569783,2,'Saute the mixture, stirring frequently, until the onions are tender and the barley is golden. Scrape the mixture into a 3-quart baking dish and stir in the salt, pepper and chicken broth.'),(569783,3,'Bake uncovered for 60-80 minutes, until the liquid is absorbed and the barley is tender.'),(569783,4,'Garnish with green onions, if desired.'),(571258,1,'Combine all ingredients, excepting the cheese and green onion, in a large bowl.'),(571258,2,'Place ¼ of the mixture on each foil square, then fold up the tinfoil so that the mixture won\'t leak while turning the packet over the fire.'),(571258,3,'Place on a BBQ grill or the grate over a campfire and cook for 20-25 minutes, turning the packets occasionally so that everything is cooked evenly.When the chicken has been cooked thoroughly, remove from the fire and cool slightly.Turn out the foil packets onto a plate, top with cheese and green onion.Enjoy!'),(572491,1,'Preheat oven to 375 degrees.Line a 16x21x1-inch baking pan with foil and spray with non stick cooking spray.'),(572491,2,'Drain all the pineapple juice into a medium saucepan.'),(572491,3,'Add cornstarch and sugar.Cook on medium heat until the pineapple juice mixture starts to bubble and thickens.Set aside. DO NOT ADD PINEAPPLE'),(572491,4,'Add together the cake mixes and oats, stir to combine.'),(572491,5,'Add melted butter, stir until crumbs form.'),(572491,6,'Pour half of the cake mixture into the prepared pan and press to the bottom of the pan.'),(572491,7,'Pour Pineapple Juice mixture over pressed crumbs; evenly spread using an offset spatula.'),(572491,8,'Sprinkle on the pineapple and remaining crumb topping.'),(572491,9,'Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly golden brown.'),(572491,10,'Cut into 35 bars.'),(573835,1,'For the rolls - Dissolve yeast and ¼ teaspoon sugar in the ½ cup warm water. Stir and let stand until foamy, 5-10 minutes.'),(573835,2,'Heat the coconut milk, shortening, sugar, and salt in a small saucepan or large measuring cup in the microwave. Don\'t let it boil, but it should be hot enough to dissolve sugar and salt. Stir and let cool a bit.'),(573835,3,'Place the eggs in the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment. Turn mixer on low and beat eggs for a few seconds.'),(573835,4,'Add the warm milk mixture to the eggs in a slow, steady stream.'),(573835,5,'Add half of the gluten-free flour and mix well.'),(573835,6,'Add the proofed yeast to the bowl and mix well. Scrape down the sides of the bowl, if needed. With mixer running on low, add the remaining flour. The dough will be pretty sticky, and that’s fine.'),(573835,7,'Remove the bowl and paddle from the mixer. Scrape the dough off the paddle and sides of the bowl.'),(573835,8,'Let stand for about 15-20 minutes in a warm place. During this time, the dough will thicken/set up a bit and start to rise.'),(573835,9,'Sprinkle a little rice flour on a clean surface. Turn dough out onto the flour and sprinkle with a little more rice flour. Pat it into a thick disk. This will help with creating evenly sized rolls. Coating your hands with a little flour each time, divide the dough into 15 evenly sized pieces. You can use a knife, but the dough is very, very sticky, so your hands are a bit easier.Gently pat the dough and form into balls. Don’t overwork the dough too much or they won\'t be as light and fluffy after they bake.Grease a 9 by 13-inch glass baking dish.'),(573835,10,'Place the rolls in five rows with three rolls in each row. Cover loosely with plastic wrap and let rise for about 45 minutes.Meanwhile, prepare the coconut syrup.'),(573835,11,'Place coconut milk, sugar, cornstarch (if using), vanilla, and pinch salt in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook for 60 seconds, whisking constantly.'),(573835,12,'Remove from heat and let cool until slightly warm, but not hot. Set aside.Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.'),(573835,13,'Pour the warm syrup over the raised rolls, allowing some to drip over the top of each rolls.'),(573835,14,'Place pan in oven and bake for 25-30 minutes.To serve, let cool slightly and serve from the pan or turn them out onto a serving platter, coconut syrup side up.'),(573998,1,'Cut bacon into small to medium pieces and fry until crisp.'),(573998,2,'Slice hard boiled eggs'),(573998,3,'Combine all non-dressing ingredients and toss well'),(573998,4,'Combine all dressing components and mix well'),(573998,5,'Serve with dressing on the side.'),(574156,1,'Preheat oven to 375 Convection (or 400 regular).'),(574156,2,'Combine dry ingredients: 1 cup AP flour, 1 cup whole wheat flour, ¼ cup sugar, 1 T baking powder, ½ t baking soda, ¾ t salt.'),(574156,3,'Add 4 T of a low fat spread (I used Smart Balance Light) and cut in with a fork until grainy.In another bowl combine 2 egg whites, 1 t vanilla and 1 cup non fat yogurt.'),(574156,4,'Whisk together.'),(574156,5,'Add wet to dry and fold together until combined. Do not over mix.Rinse blueberries and fold into the dough. I used frozen.'),(574156,6,'Place a sheet of parchment paper on a baking sheet.'),(574156,7,'Place dough in the middle and with floured hands, shape into an eight inch round.'),(574156,8,'Cut into eight pieces.'),(574156,9,'Spread the individual scones and then sprinkle with a little white sugar.'),(574156,10,'Bake until golden brown – about 18-20 minutes. Allow to cool on the tray for a few minutes then move to rack to cool.'),(574195,1,'Combine all ingredients except tuna in a 1 gallon zip lock bag and mix well.'),(574195,2,'Add tuna and coat well. Refigerate for 1-4 hours.'),(574195,3,'Preheat grill on high for 15 minutes, clean and  oil well.'),(574195,4,'Grill for 3 minutes per side.'),(575114,1,'Preheat the oven to 350.In a small bowl mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar, melted butter, and lime zest.'),(575114,2,'Mix until completely combined.'),(575114,3,'Place cupcake liners in cupcake tins.'),(575114,4,'Add 2 Tablespoons of the graham cracker mixture and press down in each cupcake liner.'),(575114,5,'Bake for 8 minutes, remove from oven, and let completely cool.In a stand mixer, combine softened cream cheese, salt, and lime zest.'),(575114,6,'Mix until combined.'),(575114,7,'Add low fat sweetened condensed milk and mix until incorporated and no lumps of cream cheese remain.'),(575114,8,'Mix in egg yolk and key lime juice until incorporated.'),(575114,9,'Pour mixture into cooled graham cracker cupcake liners  of the way full.'),(575114,10,'Bake for 15 minutes at 35'),(575114,11,'Remove from oven and place in refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.. Top with fresh lime zest.'),(575114,12,'Serve.'),(575789,1,'In a large pot over medium heat, brown the ground beef.'),(575789,2,'Drain the fat and add the chili seasoning, tomato sauce, and brown sugar. Stir to combine and simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.While the chili is simmering, bring a large pot of water to a boil.'),(575789,3,'Add the macaroni and cook according to package directions.'),(575789,4,'Drain and set return to the pan.'),(575789,5,'Pour the chili into the pan with the cooked macaroni.'),(575789,6,'Add the chili sauce and stir to combine.'),(575789,7,'Serve with cheese, onions, and sour cream.'),(576167,1,'Combine 1 cup of lemon juice with ¾ oz of basil leaves in a blender. Blend 1 minute.'),(576474,1,'Use these ingredients to make English Muffin Pizzas, Broiled Salmon, Salmon Rice Bowl, Cashew Chicken and Fried Rice.'),(576534,1,'Put the vegetable broth in a pot set to medium high heat and bring to a boil.  Reduce heat to low and bring to a simmer.'),(576534,2,'Add in the green onions and kale and cook for about 5 minutes.'),(576534,3,'Add in the tofu and continue to simmer for another 5 minutes.'),(576534,4,'Remove pot from the heat.  Spoon the miso paste into a bowl and add a ladle of the soup (about 1/2 cup).'),(576534,5,'Whisk to mix it and dissolve the miso paste.'),(576534,6,'Add it into the pot and stir well.'),(576534,7,'Add salt if desired.'),(576690,1,'In a large pot, melt the butter and add the oil.'),(576690,2,'Add the onions and peppers and cook for 5 minutes.'),(576690,3,'Add the garlic and cook for a minute more.Stir in the flour and cook and stir for 1 minute.'),(576690,4,'Whisk in the broth.Stir in the cream.Bring soup to a bubble, then reduce the heat to a simmer.Stir in the cheese, chili powder and cumin.Simmer the soup for 10 minutes.Stir in the cooked broccoli.Season with salt and pepper, to taste.'),(576690,5,'Serve with crushed tortilla chips'),(577166,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.In a medium bowl, combine the flour, baking powder and salt, and whisk together to blend.In the bowl of an electric mixer, combine the butter and sugar and beat together on medium high speed, about 3 minutes.'),(577166,2,'Add in the eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition and scraping down the bowl as needed.'),(577166,3,'Add in the vanilla.Reduce the speed of the mixer to low and add in the dry ingredients a little at a time and mixing just until incorporated.Press the dough onto round pizza pan.'),(577166,4,'Bake for 8-10 minutes or until set.'),(577166,5,'Let cool slightly and meanwhile make the cream cheese topping.In a medium bowl or in the mixer, blend together the cream cheese and the confectioners\' sugar until thoroughly mixed.'),(577166,6,'Spread over the top of the cookie.Top the pizza with the fruit.Slice and serve immediately.'),(577318,1,'Add all of the ingredients listed under \"for the buns\" to your bread maker and start the dough program.If your bread machine has a notification to add additional ingredients, add the raisins and orange zest when it beeps. Otherwise, add them when there are about five minutes of kneading left.'),(577318,2,'Remove the dough after the second kneading. Divide it into 12 balls and place in a greased 9\"x12\" pan. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, approximately 30 minutes.'),(577318,3,'Mix the egg yolk and water to make an egg wash and brush on the top of each roll.'),(577318,4,'Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove the rolls from the pan to a wire rack to cool.'),(577318,5,'Mix the confectioner\'s sugar, milk and vanilla to make the icing.'),(577318,6,'Pour the icing into a Ziploc bag and snip off the corner. Use the bag to pipe a cross on each completely cooled bun.'),(577509,1,'Preheat your oven to 375 degrees and line a baking sheet, i.e. a silpat.Sift the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger into a medium bowl and set aside.Cream the butter and dark brown sugar on high speed until light and fluffy {about 1-2 minutes}. On medium speed beat in the egg and molasses, increase the speed to high and mix until it no longer looks curdled.On low speed, gradually add flour mixture, stop once combined. Use a 1/4 cup scoop to measure each cookie and roll them into large balls. Toss each cookie ball into the granulated sugar and place 4 onto the prepared baking sheet {they will spread!}. With dampened fingers, press down the center of each cookie.'),(577509,2,'Bake in your preheated oven for 10-12 minutes.'),(577509,3,'Remove the pan let cool for 5 minutes before removing to a wire rack. Repeat until all are baked.'),(577629,1,'I bought a rice steamer for the purpose of making sushi. If you do not have a steamer, I would use Alton Brown\'s instructions for making the rice.'),(577629,2,'Place rice and water in steamer and set to cook.While rice is cooking, whisk together vinegar, sugar and salt. Once rice is done, stir in vinegar mixture. You may serve this rice warm or cold- top with veggies,I usually sprinkle soy salt and toasted sesame seeds on top!'),(577941,1,'In a large salad bowl, combine'),(577941,2,'Lettuce, Tomato, Ham (or choice of Meat), Swiss Cheese, and Olives.Just before serving, add in the “1905” Dressing, Cheese, Worcestershire Sauce, and the Juice of 1 Lemon.Toss together until salad is covered well with dressing and serve.'),(577941,3,'Mix together the Olive Oil, Garlic, and Oregano in a medium bowl using a whisk.'),(577941,4,'Pour in vinegar, gradually whisking until an emulsion starts to form.Season with salt and pepper to taste.Best if made 1 - 2 days ahead of time and kept refrigerated.Makes 2 full salads or 4 side salads.'),(578096,1,'Heat the oven to 190C (Gas Mark 5 / 375F).Using a mini food processor, blitz the bread into breadcrumbs, and then add to a bowl with the chopped olives and artichoke hearts, and the parsley. Season with plenty of black pepper (you shouldn\'t need any salt, because the olives are already quite salty).'),(578096,2,'Add the egg, and mix until fully distributed through the mixture. Using your hands, form the mixture into four sausage shapes, and place them on a lined baking tray - don\'t worry if the mixture seems quite wet at the moment, as it will firm up a lot when baked.'),(578096,3,'Bake in the oven for around 30 minutes, until firm and golden brown.'),(578096,4,'Serve warm.'),(578364,1,'Melt the butter in the microwave, and pour it into the bottom of your slow cooker.'),(578364,2,'Add the next 6 ingredients, and whisk to combine. Finally add the corn, grated cheese and chopped jalapenos, and mix well.Cook on low for 3-5 hours, until the edges are just beginning to pull away from the sides of the dish and the centre is set. Then, remove the lid and cook for a further 20-30 minutes.'),(578929,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Prepare muffin pan with liners, set aside.In a large bowl, cream butter and sugars.'),(578929,2,'Add wet ingredients, mixing well.'),(578929,3,'Sprinkle in dry ingredients, mixing on low until fully incorporated. Fold in apple chunks.Fill muffin liners 3/4 full with a heaping large cookie scoop of batter.'),(578929,4,'Combine topping ingredients.'),(578929,5,'Sprinkle over the top of each muffin.'),(578929,6,'Bake for 25-30 minutes or until a cake tester comes out clean.'),(578929,7,'Let muffins sit in tray for 2-3 minutes prior to transferring to a wire rack to cool completely. Store in an airtight container for up to several days or may be frozen.'),(579082,1,'Preheat oven to 425°F and spray rimmed baking sheet with non stick spray; set aside.In a small bowl, whisk together maple syrup, olive oil, rosemary and salt and pepper to taste.'),(579082,2,'Place butternut squash in a large bowl and pour 2/3 of the maple syrup mixture over the squash and toss to coat.'),(579082,3,'Spread squash out onto prepared baking sheet and roast for 15 minutes.While squash is roasting, drizzle the pears with the remaining maple syrup mixture and toss to coat.After 15 minutes of roasting, remove baking sheet from oven, stir the squash and add the pears to the baking sheet.Return to the oven and roast for 10 more minutes or until squash and pears are tender, but still hold their shape.'),(579082,4,'Remove and allow mixture to cool slightly. Preheat broiler.Top each piece of toasted bread with 1 tablespoon of ricotta cheese. Divide squash and pear mixture over the top of the ricotta and place tartines onto a clean baking sheet.'),(579082,5,'Place under the broiler until ricotta is warm and beginning to bubble in places, about 3-4 minutes.'),(579082,6,'Remove and sprinkle tartines with chopped hazelnuts. Enjoy! '),(579479,1,'Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.  '),(579479,2,'Add the pasta to the pot and cook until al dente, or according to the package instructions.  Do not drain the water after cooking — you need the cooking water for the sauce.Meanwhile, in a blender, place the avocado halves, olive oil, lemon juice and Parmesan cheese.  Pulse briefly to combine, and then stream in 1/2 - 3/4 cup of the pasta cooking water until a smooth, creamy sauce forms.  Taste and add salt and pepper, if needed.'),(579479,3,'Combine the pasta and avocado sauce and serve with extra Parmesan on top. '),(579655,1,'Preheat oven to 325 degrees F. Beat together eggs and sugar until slightly thickened, about 1 minute.'),(579655,2,'Add flour, milk, oil, baking powder and vanilla and beat for another minute.'),(579655,3,'Pour batter into lined cupcake tins, filling each tin 2/3 full.'),(579655,4,'Bake for 18-20 minutes (or use a cake-tester).   Allow to cool completely, then cut out a cone from the center of the cupcake.  Discard cones and prepare filling.  (For a cupcake filling tutorial, see this link.'),(579655,5,'Combine ingredients in  bowl, and whisk for 2 minutes until mixture starts to thicken.  Refrigerate for 10-15 minutes or until very set.  Fill each cupcake with a generous teaspoon of pudding.Bring a small amount of water to a rolling boil in a large saucepan on the stove top.'),(579655,6,'Whisk together egg whites and sugar in the bowl of your stand mixer.'),(579655,7,'Place the bowl of your stand mixer over rolling water (similar to a double boiler) and whisk constantly until the sugar is dissolved and no longer grainy. Immediately transfer bowl to stand mixer and whisk on medium high speed until the eggs form stiff peaks AND the bowl is cooled to room temperature.  This could take several minutes. Switch to the paddle attachment and add butter, two pieces at a time until incorporated. Continue to beat the mixture until it forms a smooth, silky frosting. If the mixture is runny or begins to curdle, do not fear - just keep beating until it comes together.'),(579655,8,'Add vanilla and beat until incorporated.Using a piping bag fitted with a jumbo round tip, pipe a circle or dollop of frosting onto each cupcake.  This layer should be flat and almost cover the entire top of the cupcake.  Put cupcakes into the freezer to allow the frosting to harden (so it doesn\'t melt when dipped.)While cupcakes are freezing, prepare the chocolate dipping sauce (below.)  Dip each cupcake into the chocolate, working quickly.'),(579655,9,'Sprinkle the edges of each cupcake with a generous amount of rainbow sprinkles, and move back to the freezer to allow the chocolate to harden.Change the tip of your piping bag to a jumbo, closed-star tip.  Pipe a small dollop on the top of each cupcake and top with a maraschino cherry.'),(579655,10,'Combine oil and chips in a microwave safe bowl.'),(579655,11,'Heat for 30-60 seconds or just until chocolate begins to melt and soften.  Stir until smooth.  (You may also use a double boiler.)  Do not overheat chocolate, heat it for 30 seconds and then 10 seconds at a time until desired consistency is met.Store finished cupcakes in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.  Allow to come to room temperature before serving.Enjoy!'),(580973,1,'Begin by prepping the cauliflower: peel off the outside leaves, then cut out the core carefully. Slice the whole head in half, then chop each half into 6 pieces.'),(580973,2,'Place all pieces of cauliflower in a large glass bowl.'),(580973,3,'Add the heavy cream, then cover the bowl with plastic wrap.Microwave for 5 minutes. Carefully, remove from the microwave and peel back the plastic wrap (be careful! The steam is very hot). Stir the cauliflower, then add the salt and pepper. Cover again and microwave another 5 minutes.When ready to serve, mash the cauliflower with a potato masher and the butter. For a very creamy puree, I use an immersion stick blender. A food processor is a great substitute, too.'),(581625,1,'Place the potatoes in a large bowl, sprinkle with two tablespoons of water, cover, and microwave cook for 4 minutes.'),(581625,2,'Combine the carrots, peas, and corn in a bowl, sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of water, cover and microwave cook for 3 minutes'),(581625,3,'In a large pot, heat the oil on medium heat and add the cumin seeds and cinnamon stick.When the cumin is slightly brown and fragrant, turn the heat to low and add the ginger, chili pepper, turmeric and garam masala. Stir for one minute.'),(581625,4,'Add the potatoes and return to medium heat. Stir and cook for 3-4 minutes.'),(581625,5,'Add the rest of the vegetables and cook for another 3-4 minutes.Stir in the lemon juice, salt and sugar.'),(581625,6,'Add the chopped cilantro, let the mixture cool and remove the cinnamon stick.In a small bowl, combine ¼ cup water with the flour and set aside.'),(581625,7,'Cut the spring roll sheets into quarters so that you have four long pieces.Taking the corner of one strip fold it to make a cone shaped pocket and fill the pocket with about a teaspoon of the filling.Continue to fold the strip over to create a triangle shape and seal the remaining edge with a dab of flour water mixture.In a large deep fryer, heat about 1 to 1 ½ inch of vegetable oil to medium heat. To test the temperature, place a small piece of the dough in the oil. If it is ready, it will sizzle and rise to the top.'),(581625,8,'Place the samosas in the pan a few at a time, turn slowly and fry until golden brown.'),(581668,1,'In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with a dough hook, mix the instant yeast with 3/4 cup warm water (105-115°F.) Set aside until yeast has dissolved and is bubbly, about 10 minutes.'),(581668,2,'Whisk together the flour, sugar and salt.'),(581668,3,'Add the flour mixture and lemon zest to yeast.'),(581668,4,'Mix on low just until moistened.'),(581668,5,'Add the egg, butter and lemon oil.'),(581668,6,'Mix until dough forms a soft, smooth ball, about 10 minutes.'),(581668,7,'Place the dough ball into a lightly oiled bowl, turn on all sides to coat and cover with plastic wrap. Set in warm room temperature to rise until puffy but not necessarily doubled in size, about 1 1/2 - 2 hours.Gently deflate dough and transfer to a lightly floured work surface.'),(581668,8,'Roll the dough to a 10-inch by 14-inch rectangle.'),(581668,9,'Spread the lemon curd (and raspberry jam, if using) over the dough evenly, leaving 1/2-inch margin on the long sides.Starting with one of the long sides, gently roll the dough up and end with the seam side down. Use a length of dental floss, cut the log into twelve pieces, each 1 1/2\" wide.'),(581668,10,'Place the rolls, spiral side up into paper cups sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Cover the rolls loosely with plastic wrap and allow to rise again until puffy, about 1 1/2 hours.Preheat oven to 350°F.'),(581668,11,'Removed plastic and bake rolls for 25-30 minutes until golden brown.'),(581668,12,'Transfer rolls to a wire rack to cool completely.Once cooled, combine all the glaze ingredients together in a small bowl. If the consistency is thicker than you\'d like, add another 1/2 - 1 tablespoon heavy cream.'),(581668,13,'Drizzle over the cooled rolls.'),(582149,1,'Bring a large saucepan of water to a boil.'),(582149,2,'Add pasta; cook 7 minutes or until al dente.'),(582149,3,'Drain pasta in a colander over a bowl, reserving 1 cup cooking liquid.'),(582149,4,'Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),(582149,5,'Add sausage to pan; cook 5 minutes or until browned, stirring to crumble.'),(582149,6,'Add 1 cup arugula, onion, oregano, crushed red pepper, and garlic; cook 2 minutes, stirring frequently.'),(582149,7,'Add reserved 1 cup cooking liquid, tomatoes, sugar, black pepper, and salt to pan; bring to a boil.'),(582149,8,'Add pasta; cook 2 minutes. Stir in remaining 1/2 cup arugula. Divide pasta mixture among 4 shallow bowls; top with Parmesan cheese.'),(582620,1,'In a large bowl, mix the sugar, cake flour, dark cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda and salt.'),(582620,2,'Add the eggs, milk, applesauce and almond extract; beat on medium for 2 minutes.Next, stir in the boiling water and mix well.Fill the mini bundt cake pan with chocolate cake batter in each well about ¾ full.'),(582620,3,'Add a Milk Way Simply Caramel Unwrapped Bite into the center of each filled well.'),(582620,4,'Bake at 350 degrees for 18-20 minutes. To test for doneness, insert a toothpick into the side of the cake (avoid the caramel center, because that should be liquidy)Allow to cool for about 5 minutes in the pan after being removed from oven.While they are cooling, prepare the Chocolate Ganache. (directions below)Turn out the mini bundt cakes onto a cooling rack after 5 minutes.In a heatproof bowl, combine the chocolate and butter.In a small saucepan over medium-high heat, bring the cream just to a boil.Immediately pour the cream over the chocolate and butter.'),(582620,5,'Whisk until the chocolate is melted and the mixture is smooth.'),(582620,6,'Drizzle the Chocolate Ganache over the chocolate bundt cakes.Top with some shredded coconut and Easter decorations for a cute, Easter themed mini bundt cake.Boil a pot of water. While it\'s heating to boiling, clean up the end of the asparagus (I cut them off) and then boil them for 3 minutes.'),(582620,7,'Drain them and put them in a cold water bath.In a blender, mix the Parmesan cheese, garlic clove and softened cream cheese together until blended.'),(582620,8,'Add the asparagus and pulse a few times to mix that in. We actually really blended it in, just because I love the green color.'),(582620,9,'Put the asparagus dip into a heat proof dish and sprinkle with some more Parmesan cheese.'),(582620,10,'Bake at 350F for 10 minutes, or until the mixture is hot and bubbly and the top is browned. We pulled ours out just a few minutes early because we were heading out the door, but it was fantastic anyway.Using a vegetable brush, scrub the fruit with a nontoxic, odorless dish soap and hot water.'),(582620,11,'Cut off the tops and bottoms of the oranges deeply enough to remove the solid disks of pith and reveal the flesh of the fruit. Quarter the fruit and cut away the center rib. Flick out the seeds with the end of your knife. Using the disk blade of a food processor, finely slice the orange quarters.'),(582620,12,'Transfer the sliced oranges to a large nonreactive pot, looking out for any large pieces that made it past the blade. Return these larger pieces to the food processor with ½ cup of the water and puree using the chopping blade.'),(582620,13,'Add the puree to the pot with enough water to cover, about another ½ cup or so. (Alternatively, you can slice the oranges thinly by hand and add them to the pot with enough water to cover, about 1 cup). Bring to a boil.'),(582620,14,'Remove from heat, cover, and let sit overnight.The next day, bring to a boil and then let sit overnight again.On the third day, measure the volume of the cooled and softened mixture (you should have roughly about 3 cups), and return to the pot with an equal amount of sugar and the remaining half cup of water. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly to prevent the sugar from burning. Continue cooking until the gel stage is reached. About 20-25 minutes or so.'),(582620,15,'Remove from the heat. Allow the marmalade to rest for 5 minutes, giving it an occasional gentle stir to release trapped air; it will thicken slightly. Skim off any foam.Boil a large pot of water.Ladle the marmalade into clean, hot (submerge the into boiling water) 4-ounce or half pint jars, leaving ¼ inch of headspace between the top of the marmalade and the lid. (I was able to fill 3 jars). Run a bubble tool along the inside of the glass to release trapped air. Wipe the rims clean; center lids on the jars and screw on jar bands until they are just fingertip-tight. Process the jars by submerging them in boiling water to cover by 2 inches for 10 minutes. Turn off the heat, remove the canner lid, and let the jars rest in the water for 5 minutes.'),(582620,16,'Remove the jars and set aside for 24 hours. Check the seals, then store in a cool, dark place for up to 1 year. (ours didn\'t last that long!)'),(582620,17,'Heat the olive oil, in a large skillet over medium heat. Once heated, add the peppers, 1½ tablespoons of garlic, onions and asparagus, stirring occasionally about 5 minutes or until it the vegetables are just starting to get soft. I try not to let them get too soft, because the little bit of crisp is actually really nice in each bite.'),(582620,18,'Remove the vegetables from the heat, and set them aside on a plate. Cover to keep warm.In the skillet, add the remaining garlic and the lemon juice and heat for about 1 minute, stirring frequently.'),(582620,19,'Add the shrimp. Cook for about 2 minutes, stirring frequently.'),(582620,20,'Add the chicken broth and stir. Then add the cornstarch and stir and cook until thickened, about 3-4 minutes or so.'),(582620,21,'Serve this with brown rice, pasta or quinoa.Pile a plate with ½ cup of brown rice. Dish the veggies evenly over each plate. Spoon the shrimp and sauce over the entire thing.'),(582620,22,'Mix together and enjoy!On a pan, place the asparagus pieces and drizzle them with olive oil.'),(582620,23,'Sprinkle with a little salt and pepper and toss to coat.'),(582620,24,'Bake at 425 degrees for about 10 minutes.'),(582620,25,'Remove from oven and allow to cool.'),(582620,26,'Brush each of your baguette slices with a little olive oil. If you want them really toasted, broil them for about 2 minutes on each side.If not, simple stack the asparagus spears on top of the bread. Then add the ham and then top with the cheese.Put in the oven and broil for about 3 minutes or until the cheese is melted.'),(582620,27,'Remove and serve.In a blender, blend the strawberries until pureed.'),(582620,28,'Add the lemon juice, apple cider vinegar and sugar and blend again.'),(582620,29,'Add the olive oil in and blend until the vinaigrette has thickened. Stir in the poppy seeds and you are ready to use it.Stores in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.'),(582620,30,'Layer the baby spinach on a 2 small plates or 1 large plate.'),(582620,31,'Add the strawberries and avocado.Divide the Meyer lemons among the two plates (or all on one).'),(582620,32,'Add the sliced almonds and drizzle with the wonderfully delicious Strawberry Vinaigrette you just made.Enjoy!Preheat oven to 425 degrees F.On a large baking pan, spread out the asparagus and grape tomatoes.'),(582620,33,'Drizzle everything with extra virgin olive oil and sprinkle with some sea salt'),(582620,34,'Boil a large pot of salted water.Cook pasta as directed on package.'),(582620,35,'Drain, reserving 1 cup of pasta water.'),(582620,36,'Mix together pasta and pesto sauce. Stir in the asparagus. Then gently toss in the tomatoes.If you think you need to add the water to make a thinner pesto sauce, add a little at a time until it\'s the right consistency. We didn\'t do this part.'),(582620,37,'Serve sprinkled with ground black pepper and grated Parmesan if desired.Slice the eggs in half lengthwise.'),(582620,38,'Remove the yolks and put the yolks into a small bowl and set the white eggs aside.Take the cooked asparagus and cut off the tips and ends leaving the soft green middle.'),(582620,39,'Put them in a blender and puree. Take the pureed asparagus and put in a towel and twist until all moisture has been removed. First of all, don’t worry – when the moisture is all out, the asparagus scrapes easily off the towel (weird, but oh so true!) and if you just soak the towel with some dish soap at the end, it won’t stain the towel green. I hear you can use cheese cloth, but I didn’t have any and just wanted to get this part done. I used a towel, twisted the top and squeezed and squeezed until I couldn’t get anymore liquid out.'),(582620,40,'Add the asparagus and the egg yolks into a blender and blend together.'),(582620,41,'Add your mayonnaise and scallions or shallot, salt & pepper and your garlic powder if you’re using and again blend until smooth.Fill the white egg halves with the mixture. You can decorate with the removed Asparagus tips.Cover with plastic wrap and chill until ready to serve.ENJOY!'),(583136,1,'Place all ingredients into the blender. Blend until smooth.'),(583136,2,'Serve. Delish!'),(583389,1,'Combine the mayonnaise with a ½ teaspoon of Creole seasoning in a small bowl; Cover and keep cold in the refrigerator until ready to use. The longer is sits the more the flavors mix together.Preheat oven to 375°.Split the french bread in half, slicing only one side, not all the way through.'),(583389,2,'Spread butter on each side of the bread and add some minced garlic. (if you don’t have minced garlic you can sprinkle a little garlic powder instead)'),(583389,3,'Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 5 minutes or until lightly toasted. Set aside.'),(583389,4,'Put the shrimp in a bowl and sprinkle with the Creole seasoning and set aside.In a large skillet, heat the olive oil over med-high heat.'),(583389,5,'Add your sliced onion and saute in olive oil for a few minutes, keep them moving often so they don’t burn.When onions are starting to turn translucent, about 4 minutes or so, add the shrimp and saute the onions and shrimp together for about 5 more minutes.'),(583389,6,'Spread the Creole mayonnaise over both sides of your french bread.'),(583389,7,'Add some shredded lettuce and diced tomatoes.Spoon the shrimp and onions on the sandwich. Don’t be afraid to get some of the liquid from the shrimp and onions on there… it seeps into the bread and tastes like heaven.'),(583389,8,'Serve immediately.'),(585795,1,'In a medium skillet brown the meat with onions, peppers and garlic until meat is down and onions are translucent.'),(585795,2,'Add the spices and stewed tomatoes. Cook until mixture blended. Rice will cook in the pumpkin.'),(585795,3,'Cut a lid out of the pumpkin and clean out the seeds and inside membrane.'),(585795,4,'Layer inside the pumpkin shredded cabbage, green beans, parsnips and meat mixture. Packing it tightly and ending with the meat mixture on top.In the bottom of a roasting pan add all ingredients. '),(585795,5,'Add the rack and place the pumpkin on the roasting rack.'),(585795,6,'Place roasting pan lid on top. If pumpkin lid will not fit cook it to the side.  Cook on high for 3-4 hours until the pumpkin is tender and rice is cooked. (You can use the roasting vegetables to puree as a sauce or stock for a nice beef soup.)'),(585795,7,'Remove from roasting pan and let sit until slightly cooled. Slice wedge pieces of pumpkin to serve.'),(586462,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees.Coat a 13x9 inch baking pan with non-stick spray. Pulverize cookies in food processor until fine crumbs form.'),(586462,2,'Add melted butter, process until crumbs clump together. Press crumbs into prepared pan.'),(586462,3,'Bake 15 minutes or until golden.Melt the peanut butter chips, corn syrup, butter, and vanilla in a saucepan over medium-low heat, stirring until smooth, about 5 minutes.'),(586462,4,'Spread 1/2 C. of the peanut mixture over crumb base.Top with marshmallows and return the pan to the oven.'),(586462,5,'Bake until marshmallows puff up, about 2 minutes, then remove from oven. DO NOT let the marshmallows brown or they will turn crunchy.Toss peanuts and cereal with the remaining peanut mixture to coat. Drop spoonfuls of the topping over the marshmallows, then spread with a spatula (sprayed with non-stick cooking spray to prevent sticking).Cool bars before cutting.'),(586519,1,'In a medium sized bowl stir together cole slaw mix, Dean\'s Dip and vinegar. Cover and keep cold while you prepare the rest of the sandwich.'),(586519,2,'Lay our your pounded chicken breast onto a baking sheet , turn your broiler onto high heat  and move your oven rack second from the top. In a small bowl mix together smoked paprika, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Coat both sides of the breasts with seasoning.'),(586519,3,'Put the chicken under the broiler and with the door slightly cracked let it cook for about 3 minutes and then flip. While the chicken is cooking mix together honey and vinegar. After your chicken has been flipped and cooked for 3 minutes on the other side, flip your chicken again and baste with honey mixture. Cook for another 3 minutes, flip, baste and cook again. At this point the chicken should be fully cooked and slightly sticky and sweet from the honey glaze.'),(586519,4,'Remove from the oven, add 1 chicken piece per bun and top with cold cole slaw.'),(586990,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease light colored baking sheets with non stick cooking spray and set aside.In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy. Whip in vanilla, egg, orange zest and juice. Scrape sides and mix again. Stir in all dry ingredients slowly until just combined, excluding the powdered sugar. Scrape sides of bowl and mix again briefly. Stir in chopped cranberries.'),(586990,2,'Pour powdered sugar onto a large plate.'),(586990,3,'Roll a 2 teaspoon of dough into a ball and roll in powdered sugar.'),(586990,4,'Place on baking sheet and repeat with remaining dough.'),(586990,5,'Bake for 9-11 minutes or until bottoms begin to barely brown and cookies look matte {not melty or shiny}.'),(586990,6,'Remove from oven and cool cookies about 3 minutes before transferring to cooling rack.*If using a non stick darker baking tray, reduce baking time by about 2 minutes.'),(588156,1,'Saute the potato, onion, garlic, ginger and tomato paste in the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until the onions and potatoes are softened. (You don\'t have to do this step and can throw all the ingredients directly into the blender but I think this gives it more flavor).'),(588156,2,'Transfer the mixture to the blender once sauteed.'),(588156,3,'Add the remaining ingredients to the blender and place the lid on.Turn to variable speed 1, increase to 10 quickly and then switch to High and blend for about 5 minutes until you see steam coming out the top of the blender.Once hot, pour into bowls, adjust seasoning to taste and garnish with cilantro.'),(588195,1,'In a small bowl, combine the dried porcini mushrooms and the warm water.'),(588195,2,'Let soak for about 15 minutes. Squeeze the excess water from the mushrooms, saving the water. Chop the porcinis and set aside.'),(588195,3,'Combine the mushroom water and chicken broth in a small sauce pan on the stove. Keep warm over medium-low heat.In a large skillet over medium heat, add ½ tablespoon of the butter, 1 tablespoon of the olive oil, ¼ teaspoon of the thyme and the garlic. Sauté for about 1 minute until fragrant.'),(588195,4,'Add the chopped mixed mushrooms (not the porcinis) and sauté for about 10 minutes, only stirring once or twice until the mushrooms start to caramelize. Set aside.In a large stock pot or dutch oven, add the remaining 1 tablespoon of butter, 1 tablespoon of olive oil and the bay leaf over medium-high heat.'),(588195,5,'Add the squash, onions, chopped porcini mushrooms and ½ teaspoon of the wild porcini sea salt. Cook for about 7 minutes until the squash starts to become tender.'),(588195,6,'Add the rice to the pot and stir \"toasting\" the rice for about 2 minutes.'),(588195,7,'Add the wine to the pot next and cook until it evaporates.Ladle the broth that\'s been keeping warm into the pot until it covers the top of the rice. Lower the heat to medium.'),(588195,8,'Let the mixture cook, stirring occasionally until the broth starts to drop below the top of the rice.'),(588195,9,'Add more broth to cover the top and repeat until all the broth is gone, stirring as you go. With the last ladle of broth, add the cooked mixed mushroom mixture to the pot and stir.Once all the broth is absorbed by the rice, remove from the heat and add the remaining thyme, the sage, the parmesan cheese, black pepper and more wild porcini sea salt to taste.'),(588195,10,'Serve immediately garnishing with thyme, sage and/or more wild porcini sea salt.'),(588337,1,'Preheat skillet or pancake pan to medium heat.'),(588337,2,'Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips in a medium bowl and whisk together.Fold in chocolate chips.Grease pan and pour batter (it will be very thick from the coconut flour) in about ¼ cup measurements onto pan (you might have to shape it into pancake form a bit).Cook for approximately 2 minutes per side.'),(588337,3,'Serve warm, top with a peanut butter & milk sauce and extra chocolate chips if desired.'),(589447,1,'Wash zucchini, peel off skin and use a mandoline or spiralizer to create \"noodles\". (Click here for a tutorial if you are not familiar.)'),(589447,2,'Place \"noodles\" in a mesh strainer and generously salt. Allow to sit for at least 30 minutes, discard liquid and gently squeeze out any remaining liquid from the noodles.Wash tomatoes and remove any stems. Set aside to dry.Grab a handful of fresh basil leaves, place in a flat pile, roll up and thinly slice.'),(589447,3,'Place a large frying pan over medium high heat. Once very hot, add olive oil and then tomatoes. Cook tomatoes, stirring occasionally for 5 to 7 minutes until they are blistered and starting to burst.'),(589447,4,'Sprinkle kosher salt and pepper over tomatoes, add in crushed garlic and a splash of white wine. Continue cooking, stirring constantly, for 1 minute until garlic is fragrant. Use the back of a wooden spoon to crush the tomatoes and release their juices.Toss zucchini \"noodles\" into frying pan, stir to combine and cook until noodles are heated through, about 3 to 4 minutes.'),(589447,5,'Remove from heat, adjust salt and pepper if necessary, toss with fresh basil, serve and Enjoy!'),(589523,1,'For instructions on how to easily break down the cauliflower into florets, click here. Preheat the oven to 450F. Line a baking sheet with tin foil and set aside. Grab a gallon size ziploc type bag and place cauliflower florets into it, add olive oil, seal and gently shake until well coated.'),(589523,2,'Add in Italian seasoning, salt, garlic powder and crushed red pepper flakes. Seal and gently shake until evenly coated. Open bag and pour cauliflower onto lined baking sheet. Shake tray to spread out. Roast for 15 minutes.'),(589523,3,'Remove and turn cauliflower florets, roast for an additional 15 minutes until you see some crispy edges and browning. While cauliflower is roasting, heat marinara sauce.'),(589523,4,'Serve roasted cauliflower florets with marinara for dipping and Enjoy!'),(589892,1,'In a medium bowl or mason jar, combine all ingredients together except for greens, vegetables and accompaniments'),(589892,2,'In bowl, whisk ingredients together well. In mason jar, close lid tightly and shake well until all ingredients are combined'),(589892,3,'Toss into greens, then top with accompaniments.'),(590184,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.'),(590184,2,'Add oil to a medium saucepan and heat over medium-high heat until hot.'),(590184,3,'Add onion and saute until tender, about 5 minutes.'),(590184,4,'Add garlic, tomato paste, crushed red pepper and sugar and stir for 30 seconds.'),(590184,5,'Add diced tomatoes and sun-dried tomatoes. Cook for 1 minute and then reduce heat to medium-low. Simmer for 10-15 minutes, stirring occasionally. You want the tomato mixture to reduce and thicken.'),(590184,6,'Remove from heat when it has reached the desired consistency. Stir in the basil and add salt and pepper to taste.Use a handheld mixer to blend the goat cheese and cream cheese together. Lightly grease a shallow baking dish (a pie plate works well as does an 11 x 7 dish).'),(590184,7,'Spread the cheese mixture into the dish and top with the tomato mixture.'),(590184,8,'Bake for 15-18 minutes or until heated through.'),(590184,9,'Serve with assorted vegetable crudite and/or pita wedges.'),(590915,1,'Preheat oven to 350° F. Grease a mini muffin pan and set aside.Use a food processor to grind graham crackers into a fine crumb.'),(590915,2,'Combine graham cracker crumbs, flour and baking powder in a medium sized bowl. In a microwave proof bowl, heat butter for 20-30 seconds to soften.'),(590915,3,'Combine softened butter with sweetened condensed milk.'),(590915,4,'Whisk until well combined.'),(590915,5,'Add vanilla extract and whisk together until well mixed.'),(590915,6,'Pour wet ingredients over dry ingredients and stir until all ingredients are combined. Dough will be slightly sticky.'),(590915,7,'Add your choice of mix in. I chose chocolate chips, peanut butter chips and walnuts. Spoon 2 tbsp of cookie dough into mini muffin pan.'),(590915,8,'Bake at 350°F for 12-14 minutes. Allow to cool for 5 minutes. Take a tart shaper or the back of a spoon and gently press down in the middle of the cookie to create a crater. Allow to cool in the muffin pan.'),(590915,9,'Cut up cold butter into 1” thick chunks. Beat on medium speed until butter is light and fluffy. You may have to scrape the sides of the bowl.'),(590915,10,'Add cocoa powder and beat to incorporate into butter. In a microwave safe bowl, combine chocolate chips and mini marshmallows. Microwave for 30 seconds. Do not walk away from the microwave, keep an eye on the marshmallows as they increase in size when heated.'),(590915,11,'Remove after 30 seconds and stir. Return to the microwave and heat for another 30 seconds. Stir chocolate and marshmallow until well mixed.'),(590915,12,'Add to the butter. The butter will melt due to the warm chocolate.'),(590915,13,'Add powdered sugar one cup at a time. Frosting will become thicker.'),(590915,14,'Add vanilla extract and milk. Increase speed to medium high and beat for 60 seconds until smooth. Pipe frosting onto cooled cookie cups.'),(591049,1,'Combine first 6 ingredients.'),(591049,2,'Add chicken and marinate for 30 minutes -1 hour. The longer they marinate, the more intense the flavor.Preheat oven to 375 degrees.'),(591049,3,'Remove chicken from marinade and coat in Panko crumbs.'),(591049,4,'Bake for 20 min or until chicken is cooked through.'),(591049,5,'Serve immediately.'),(591076,1,'Cook pasta according to package directions.In a large skillet, sauté the onions over medium-high until slightly translucent - about 3 minutes.'),(591076,2,'Add ground beef and continue cooking with the onions breaking up the meat into small pieces.Once the beef is fully browned, add the garlic, herbs and salt - sauté until fragrant.'),(591076,3,'Add the tomatoes and cook until completely heat stirring frequently.Reduce heat to keep sauce warm if more time is needed for the pasta.Toss the spaghetti with the meat sauce and serve with grated parmesan cheese.'),(591854,1,'Thaw your spinach and squeeze out excess water. I just use the microwave to thaw it (put it in a bowl to catch melting liquid) but you can leave it in your fridge for a day too. You do not need to squeeze out ALL of the water, I think some is fine and it holds a lot of spinach flavor.Finely dice the onion and garlic.'),(591854,2,'Saute until soft and translucent (not browned) in 4 Tbsp of butter over medium heat. This may seem like a lot of butter for half an onion and 2 cloves of garlic but you need 4 Tbsp for the roux to make sure there is enough thickening power for all of the milk.Once the onions and garlic have cooked, it’s time to make the roux. Dump in the 4 Tbsp (or ¼ cup) of flour and stir it into the melted butter well. Continue to cook this paste for 1-2 minute more over medium heat.'),(591854,3,'Add the 2 cups of milk and whisk until all of the flour/butter paste has dissolved.'),(591854,4,'Let the mixture simmer until it is nice and thick (5-10 minutes).'),(591854,5,'Add the salt, pepper and red pepper flakes to taste. The red pepper flakes are not necessary but I think it gives the creamed spinach a nice little kick… Too much and it will over power the fresh, delicate spinach flavor.Stir in your spinach and you’re done! If your creamed spinach is still too liquidy, you can simmer it a little bit longer until the sauce reduces. Just remember that when it cools down it will thicken as well.'),(592411,1,'Preheat your oven to 400 degrees and line a baking sheet with foil.'),(592411,2,'Cut your baguette into the size you want your pizzas. I had a half length baguette so I cut it in half (lengthwise) then sliced it open to make four pieces, each about 8 inches long and four inches wide.Top each pizza with about ¼ cup of sauce and ¼ cup of shredded cheese. I like to sprinkle on a little extra Italian spices at this point to kick up the flavor. I use dried basil, oregano and sometimes red pepper flakes. Follow this up with pepperoni or whatever other toppings you are using (marinated mushrooms? YUM)'),(592411,3,'Bake the pizzas in the oven at 400 degrees for 10 to 15 minutes or until the cheese is melted and bubbly and the edges of your bread are brown and crispy. Every oven is different but mine took between 10 and 15 minutes.'),(592956,1,'In a large mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar until fluffy and pale yellow.'),(592956,2,'Add egg and vanilla, mix to combine.In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, and cinnamon.'),(592956,3,'Add dry ingredients and milk to butter mixture; alternate flour and milk additions, beginning and ending with flour mixture.Chill dough for 30 minutes in the fridge.Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.'),(592956,4,'Place dough on a lightly floured surface, the dough will still be pretty tacky; you\'ll want to keep extra flour close at hand.'),(592956,5,'Roll dough out to about ¼\" thick, add more flour as needed to keep dough from sticking.Using a floured square cookie cutter, cut out cookies and place on a Sil-Pat (or parchment) line baking sheet.'),(592956,6,'Bake for 9 to 11 minutes.'),(592956,7,'Let cookies set on baking sheet for 2 minutes, then remove to wire cooking rack to cool completely. Repeat with remaining dough.Once cookies are completely cool, make the frosting.'),(592956,8,'Combine butter and powdered sugar in a large mixing bowl.'),(592956,9,'Add syrup and vanilla, mix to combine.'),(592956,10,'Add milk ½ tablespoon at a time, mixing after each addition until the frosting is the desired consistency - your want a spreadable frosting, not a drippy icing. If you add too much milk, just add a little extra powdered sugar.Frost cookies and sprinkle with a little cinnamon, if desired.'),(593043,1,'In a medium bow, whisk together oil, ranch, Worcestershire sauce, cayenne, paprika, salt, lemon juice, vinegar, pepper and sugar until combined; set aside.'),(593043,2,'Cut chicken like you’re going to butterfly, but cut breasts all the way through – you want to create thin halves.'),(593043,3,'Place chicken in a gallon Ziploc bag with prepared marinade. Refrigerate for a minimum 30 minutes (2 hours+ is better).Cook pasta according to package directions in salted water, until al dente.'),(593043,4,'Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook chicken in skillet for 8 to 10 minutes, or until cooked through and browned.In a medium saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter.'),(593043,5,'Whisk in evaporated milk, garlic, cayenne, paprika, and Parmesan cheese. Continue whisking for 5 minutes or so, until sauce thickens slightly.'),(593043,6,'Place pasta in serving bowls and top with sliced chicken breasts. Top with more shredded Parmesan cheese, if desired.'),(593148,1,'In a large bowl, microwave peanut butter, peanut butter chips, butter, and marshmallow fluff for 45 seconds to 1 minute. {The fluff will puff up, watch it.}'),(593148,2,'Mix together until the peanut butter chips are smooth, the marshmallow will still have little bits floating around, that\'s okay.'),(593148,3,'Add the cereal to the bowl.'),(593148,4,'Mix until well coated will a wooden spoon.'),(593148,5,'Pour cereal into a gallon sized ziploc bag.'),(593148,6,'Add powdered sugar and bacon. Seal bag. Shake until cereal is coated in sugar. {The bage will turn clear and you\'ll see a white-ish layer on the cereal.}'),(593148,7,'Serve immediately or chill and serve when you\'re ready.'),(593403,1,'Soak the dried mushrooms in the boiling water for 30 minutes to soften.Meanwhile, pre-heat the oven to 150 and chop the other ingredients. Melt the butter in a medium saucepan or wok over medium-low heat.'),(593403,2,'Add the onion and garlic and cook gently for 5 minutes. Now stir in the portabello mushrooms and celery. Leave aside while simmering to prepare the now softened dried mushrooms.'),(593403,3,'Drain the dried mushrooms in a fine strainer over a bowl to reserve the soaking liquid. Squeeze excess liquid from the mushrooms by hand, then chop finely.'),(593403,4,'Add to the other mushrooms and vegetables, and continue to cook gently while the mushroom sweat their juices out  about 20 minutes. While they are cooking, put a large oven-proof casserole dish in the pre-heated oven to warm.'),(593403,5,'Add the rice to the mushrooms and vegetables and stir well to give each grain a coating of butter.'),(593403,6,'Pour in the water, vermouth and the soaking liquid from the dried mushrooms and stir in the salt. Raise the heat to moderately high and bring everything up to the simmering point.'),(593403,7,'Transfer the mixture to the warmed casserole dish and stir only enough to spread evenly over the dish\'s surface.'),(593403,8,'Place uncovered in the centre of the oven and cook for 20 minutes.'),(593403,9,'Remove from the oven and gently stir in the grated Parmesan, being careful not to break the rice grains. Raise the heat to 175 and return the risotto to the oven. Cook until the liquid has evaporated  depending on the size of the casserole dish and the surface area of the risotto, this may take between 15 and 30 minutes.'),(593403,10,'Remove from the oven and stir in fresh ground black pepper to taste. Cover with a dish towel until serving.'),(593403,11,'Serve as soon as possible garnished with shavings of Parmesan cheese.'),(593701,1,'Butter a 8  8 inch baking pan. Melt the butter and chocolate in a saucepan over low heat and set aside.'),(593701,2,'Combine the flour, baking powder and salt in a small bowl. In a large bowl, beat the eggs and sugar until creamy and lightened, then stir in the vanilla.'),(593701,3,'Add the chocolate and dry ingredients.  Stir well to combine.'),(593701,4,'Transfer the mixture to the baking pan, and prepare the topping.Preheat an oven to 35'),(593701,5,'Combine the peanut butter, butter, sugar, flour and egg in a large bowl and beat until combined.  Scoop the topping in spoonfuls over the brownie layer and use a knife to spread in swirls over the top.'),(593701,6,'Bake for 30 minutes or until a cake tester or toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.'),(593701,7,'Let cool for 10 minutes, then cut into squares and serve warm.'),(594205,1,'Preheat oven to 300 degrees.Have a saucepan of boiling water ready.In a small saucepan, add the cream and vanilla bean paste, stir to mix and set the pan over medium-low heat.Warm the cream until bubbles form around the edges and steam begins to rise to the surface.'),(594205,2,'Remove from heat and let steep for 15-20 minutes.While the cream mixture is steeping, in a medium bowl, whisk together the egg yolks, pumpkin puree, pumpkin pie spice, and sugar until the mixture is light orange. This will take about 5 minutes of heavy whisking.Once the mixture is light orange, gradually pour the cream into the egg mixture, whisking until blended. At this point, you will see a lot of white foam form at the top. Take a spoon and skim off the foam.Divide the custard among the ramekins and place the ramekins on a baking pan.Pull out the middle rack of the oven and place your baking pan on top. Then very carefully, pour boiling water to fill the pan almost halfway up the sides of the ramekins.Cover the pan loosely with foil and slowly push the rack back into the oven.'),(594205,3,'Bake until the custards are just set around the edges, about 30-35 minutes, but could be longer depending on how many ounces your ramekins are. Mine were a little deeper so it took about 50 minutes to bake.'),(594205,4,'Transfer the ramekins to a wire rack and let cool to room temperature. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until chilled, at least 4 hours or overnight. They will keep up to 3 days.Before serving, sprinkle a heavy layer of granulated sugar on top of the custard. Using a kitchen torch, melt the sugar. Move the flame gradually in small circles over the surface of the custard, heating the sugar until it is evenly melted and golden. The sugar will harden in a few seconds and your pumpkin crème brûlée is ready to eat!'),(594590,1,'Preheat oven to 35'),(594590,2,'Line two mini muffin pans with paper liners and set aside.In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, and salt. Set aside.In a large bowl or the bowl of a stand mixer, cream butter and brown sugar together on medium speed until well-combined and fluffy, about 2 minutes.'),(594590,3,'Add eggs one at a time, beating each until combined. Beat in vanilla.Turn off the mixer and add the flour mixture. Beat on low speed until just incorporated. Fold in chocolate chips with a spatula.'),(594590,4,'Place about ½ tablespoon of batter in each cup. Dollop about ½ teaspoon of Nutella into the center of each. Then top with another teaspoon or so of batter.'),(594590,5,'Bake for 12-14 minutes, until lightly browned. Cool completely in pans.'),(594603,1,'Turn the boiler on in your oven.In a large bowl, whisk together the 10 eggs. Set aside.In an oven-proof skillet or cast iron pan over medium high heat, brown the ground turkey then add in sundried tomatoes and onions. Cook until onions are tender and translucent, about 5 minutes.Gently add in the kale leaves, little by little. They will wilt down a lot so as soon as one batch wilts down, start adding more.Once all the kale has wilted, season mixture with salt and pepper then pour the eggs into the pan.'),(594603,2,'Let it cook for 1-2 minutes before running a spatula along the edge of the eggs & pan.'),(594603,3,'Let cook for 1-2 minutes more, making sure the top of the frittata is still uncooked.'),(594603,4,'Place the entire skillet carefully into the oven and broil for 3-5 minutes, watching it carefully as you don\'t want the top to burn.Once the top has cooked through and browned a little, carefully (with oven mitts) remove the pan and let cool for 5-10 minutes before serving.You can top with cheese, hot sauce, or whatever you wish.'),(594603,5,'Serve warm.'),(594704,1,'Preheat oven to 375 F. Line or grease a muffin tin and set aside.'),(594704,2,'Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.In a smaller bowl, combine egg and buttermilk and whisk well to combine.Using a pastry cutter or two knives, cut the butter into the flour mixture until the mixture resembles pea-sized crumbs.'),(594704,3,'Pour buttermilk mixture into flour mixture and stir to combine. Fold in currants.Divide batter evenly in muffin cups and bake for 20 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Cool in pan for five minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.'),(595143,1,'Mix all ingredients together.Chill for at least 1 hour.'),(595143,2,'Serve with cooked peeled shrimp.'),(595144,1,'Combine all sauce ingredients in a small bowl. Set aside.In a large pan, heat sesame oil.'),(595144,2,'Add onions and garlic and sauté for one minute.'),(595144,3,'Add fish cakes and carrots and fry for 3 to 4 minutes. Finally, add noodles, cabbage, and sauce mixture. Stir to get all ingredients well mixed, another 3 to 4 minutes.Stir in green onions, turn off heat, and dish onto plate.'),(595144,4,'Garnish with nori strips and beni-shoga.'),(595144,5,'Serve immediately.'),(595770,1,'Lightly grease a 8\"x12\" casserole dish or a 2qt baking dish. Arrange broccoli florets in the dish. Set aside.In a medium mixing bowl, whisk together milk and cornstarch.In a large saucepan, melt butter.'),(595770,2,'Add onion and sautee until soft, about 2 minutes.Gradually, add the milk mixture to the onions.'),(595770,3,'Whisk after each addition.'),(595770,4,'Let the sauce thicken before adding more milk. Repeat until you use all the milk.'),(595770,5,'Add the cheese and stir until melted.'),(595770,6,'Add the corn and stir until coated with sauce.'),(595770,7,'Pour the cheesy corn sauce over the broccoli.Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.In a small measuring cup, mix melted butter and breadcrumb mix.'),(595770,8,'Sprinkle over the casserole.'),(595770,9,'Bake for 25 to 27 minutes, or until the topping is golden brown and the casserole is bubbling.'),(595770,10,'Let sit for 10 minutes before serving.Refrigerate any leftovers for up to 2 days.'),(596614,1,'Remove the stems and pit the cherries.'),(596614,2,'Heat the cherries, water, sugar and lemon juice in a large nonreactive saucepan or skillet or until the liquid starts to boil.Turn down the heat to a low boil and cook the cherries for 25 minutes, stirring frequently for the last 10 minutes of cooking to make sure they are cooking evenly and not sticking.Once syrup is reduced to the consistency of maple syrup, remove the pan from the heat, add the almond extract and let the cherries cool in their syrup.'),(596614,3,'Drain cherries from syrup and coarsely chop them. Set chopped cherries aside with ¼ cup of the syrup (remaining syrup can be reserved for another use).Preheat oven to 350 F°. Grease an 8 inch square pan.In a large saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat.'),(596614,4,'Remove from heat, and stir in vanilla, eggs and sugar until thoroughly combined.'),(596614,5,'Mix in cocoa powder, flour, baking powder and salt until well blended. Gently fold in candied cherries and dark chocolate chunks.'),(596614,6,'Pour batter into prepared pan, spread with a spatula to smooth out top.'),(596614,7,'Bake at 350 for 35-40 minutes.'),(596614,8,'Let cool before slicing and serving.'),(596621,1,'Clean the orange, grapefruit and lemons thoroughly then cut into ¼ inch thick slices.In a large pitcher combine white wine, sliced citrus and limoncello. Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.When ready to serve, stir in the sparking sparkling water (or sparkling wine).'),(596621,2,'Pour into individual glasses. If desired, garnish glasses with sliced fruit from the pitcher.'),(597215,1,'To make the filling, put the cabbage in a food processor and process until cabbage is finely minced.'),(597215,2,'Remove the cabbage to a large bowl and sprinkle with the salt.'),(597215,3,'Let cabbage sit for 10 minutes. In the meantime, return the food processor bowl to the stand and add the ginger, chives, pork, pepper, soy sauce, rice wine and sesame oil. Pulse 4 times to mix the ingredients well. Set aside.'),(597215,4,'Use your hands to grab a handful of the cabbage and squeeze and discard the excess moisture out into the sink. You can also spoon all of the cabbage onto a cheesecloth and then squeeze all the water out.'),(597215,5,'Place the dry cabbage back into the large bowl and add the pork mixture. Fold the cabbage into the pork mixture.'),(597215,6,'Mix together the slurry. Take one dumpling wrapper, spoon scant 1 tablespoon of the pork mixture onto the middle of the wrapper. Dip one finger into the slurry and “paint” the edges of the dumpling wrapper. Bring up the bottom side of the wrapper, fold up and press to shape into a half-moon shape, encasing all of the filling.'),(597215,7,'Place on baking sheet, cover loosely with plastic wrap and repeat with rest of dumplings. Make sure that the dumplings do not touch each other on the sheet.4 When all dumplings assembled, you can cook immediately or cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for up to several hours. To cook, half-fill a large pot with water and bring to boil. When boiling, and gently slide in 1/3 of the dumplings. When water returns to a boil, turn heat to a simmer and gently cook for 6-8 minutes.'),(597215,8,'Remove with slotted spoon and repeat with remaining dumplings.'),(597215,9,'Serve with hot chili sauce.'),(597419,1,'Combine all ingredients except bread, eggs and milk and mix thoroughly.'),(597419,2,'Spread pumpkin mixture on bread and put bread slices together sandwich style.'),(597419,3,'Mix eggs and milk together in shallow bowl'),(597419,4,'Soak sandwiches on both sides in egg/mil mixture.'),(597419,5,'Heat frying pan or griddle over medium-high heat, grease with about 1 tablespoon of butter.'),(597419,6,'Cook sandwiches on griddle until both sides are lightly toasted.'),(597419,7,'Serve with maple syrup and fresh whipped cream. I like to shake cinnamon sugar on the top of mine.'),(597720,1,'In a small bowl, mix together the piri-piri sauce, garlic, salt, and lemon juice.'),(597720,2,'Place the ribs in a 9-by-13-inch baking dish, add the marinade, and turn to coat. Cover and marinate for at least several hours and up to overnight in the refrigerator.'),(597720,3,'Heat a gas or charcoal grill to medium.'),(597720,4,'Place the ribs on the grill and cook, turning often and basting with the remaining marinade, until the meat is tender and richly brown, about 1 1/4 hours. For an extra kick of heat, brush the ribs with fresh molho de piri-piri just before serving. Slice between the bones and arrange on a platter or plate.'),(598224,1,'Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C). Adjust the oven rack to the middle position. Line a 12-cup muffin tin with 10 paper cupcake liners.'),(598224,2,'Dissolve the cornstarch in 1/4 cup milk. Set aside.'),(598224,3,'In a food processor, shred the coconut flakes for 30 seconds.'),(598224,4,'In a large bowl, stir the eggs and sugar together with a wooden spoon. One by one, add the cornstarch mixture, the remaining milk, the coconut, melted butter and lemon extract, stirring well after each addition.'),(598224,5,'Ladle the custard into the paper cups, filling each 1/4 inch from the top. (Make sure to stir the custard frequently to keep the coconut well distributed.)'),(598224,6,'Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until the coconut is nicely toasted. Cool completely in the tin before serving.'),(598242,1,'Make the caramelized onions'),(598242,2,'Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat.'),(598242,3,'Add the garlic, onions, and sugar and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.'),(598242,4,'Add the wine, bay leaf, and thyme. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer briskly for 3 to 6 minutes, or until reduced by half.'),(598242,5,'Add the stock and bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer briskly for 5 to 8 minutes, or until reduced by half again.'),(598242,6,'Stir the butter into the sauce and keep stirring until its incorporated. Season to taste with salt and pepper and finish with a small splash vinegar (1 to 2 teaspoons). Cover and keep warm.Make the veal meatballs'),(598242,7,'Preheat the oven to 350F (175C). Lightly oil a rimmed baking sheet.'),(598242,8,'In a large bowl, combine the bread crumbs and melted butter and mix well with your hands.'),(598242,9,'Add the cheese, milk, eggs, garlic, 1 tablespoon of the parsley, the oregano, olive oil, salt, black and red pepper, and lemon zest and mix well.'),(598242,10,'Add the ground pork and veal to the bowl and mix well. Pinch off small walnut-sized pieces of meat, each about 1/2 ounce, and roll them into mini meatballs. You should have between 32 and 40 meatballs. A few extra are fine.'),(598242,11,'Transfer the veal meatballs to the baking sheet. Arrange them in neat rows, leaving space between them.'),(598242,12,'Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until the meatballs are just barely cooked through. Do not overcook.'),(598242,13,'Divvy the veal meatballs among 4 serving plates. Spoon the warm sauce over the top of the meatballs and garnish each plate with some of the remaining parsley, a little diced tomato, and the basil.'),(598242,14,'Drizzle the remaining vinegar over each plate and serve.'),(598748,1,'Make the caramelized onions'),(598748,2,'Melt the butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium-low heat.'),(598748,3,'Add the onions and toss to coat. Cook until the onions have softened, about 5 minutes, and add the thyme and red pepper flakes, if using. Continue caramelizing the onions, stirring them frequently so they brown evenly, for up to 60 minutes or more. (If the heat is too hot, the onions will burn, so slow it down and take some time to enjoy the process.) Season to taste with salt.'),(598748,4,'Transfer the onions to a large bowl and set aside.Make the mustard aioli'),(598748,5,'Whisk the egg yolk, garlic, lemon juice, and mustard in a medium bowl to thoroughly combine. Start adding the canola oil, just a few drops at a time, whisking constantly, until the mixture begins to emulsify. As it thickens, continue adding the oil in a slow stream, making sure each addition is thoroughly blended before adding more. Season to taste with salt. Cover the aioli and refrigerate until needed.Assemble the sandwiches'),(598748,6,'Position a rack in the center of the oven and preheat to 350°F (176°C). Line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper.'),(598748,7,'Cut each roll in half horizontally. Butter the cut sides of the rolls and place them, cut side down, on the baking sheet. Toast the rolls in the oven for 3 to 5 minutes, until the butter is melted and the rolls are warm.'),(598748,8,'Flip each roll over so that the cut side is up.'),(598748,9,'Spread each side with some mustard aioli.'),(598748,10,'Place equal amounts pastrami on the bottom half of each roll, folding it up to only slightly overhang. Next, divvy the caramelized onions among the sandwiches, layering them on the pastrami.'),(598748,11,'Place the Gruyère on the top halves of the rolls. Return the sandwiches, still open-faced, to the oven for 5 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and the pastrami is warm to the touch.'),(598748,12,'Sandwich the halves together and, if desired, cut on the diagonal with a serrated knife. You can take it from here.'),(598968,1,'Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).  Butter and lightly flour 8 small (3-inch) round cake tins or 8 large muffin tins.'),(598968,2,'Place the butter, granulated sugar, and vanilla in the bowl of an electric mixer and beat until light and creamy.'),(598968,3,'Add the eggs, 1 at a time, and beat well. Sift the flour and baking powder over the butter mixture and gently fold through until no trace of flour remains.'),(598968,4,'Add the sour cream and almonds and mix just until combined.'),(598968,5,'Spoon the mixture into the prepared tins. Top the batter with several nectarine slices and sprinkle with raw sugar.'),(598968,6,'Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until a skewer or toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.'),(598968,7,'Let the cakes cool in the pans for a few minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack.'),(598968,8,'Serve the cakes warm with coffee.'),(598971,1,'Make the aïoli by hand'),(598971,2,'To make by hand, chop the garlic and salt together on a cutting board until a paste forms.'),(598971,3,'Transfer to a deep mixing bowl and wrap a damp towel around the base of the bowl to keep it from sliding around the counter as you work.'),(598971,4,'Whisk in the mustard, lemon juice, and egg yolks. While whisking continuously and vigorously, add the olive oil in a slow, thin, steady stream until all of it has been incorporated and the mixture is thick and completely emulsified.Make the aïoli in a food processor'),(598971,5,'Place the garlic and salt in the work bowl and process to chop as finely as possible.'),(598971,6,'Add the mustard and lemon juice and pulse to combine.'),(598971,7,'Add the egg yolks and, with the motor running, add the olive oil in a slow, thin, steady stream until all of it has been incorporated and the mixture is thick and completely emulsified.'),(598971,8,'Cover and refrigerate for up to 24 hours until needed.Make the steak'),(598971,9,'Place the steak in a small, nonreactive baking dish.'),(598971,10,'Combine the olive oil, rosemary, and black pepper in a small bowl and stir well. Rub the mixture evenly over the tri tip. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 8 hours or up to 24 hours.'),(598971,11,'Remove the tri tip from the refrigerator 1 1/2 hours before cooking.'),(598971,12,'Prepare and light a charcoal grill for direct cooking.'),(598971,13,'Add the olives to the aïoli and season with cayenne. When the grill is at its hottest (when the coals are red and glowing and too hot to hold your hand over the grill for more than a couple of seconds), remove the tri tip from the marinade, wipe off any excess marinade, and season on both sides with sea salt.'),(598971,14,'Place the steak on the cooking grate directly over the coals, cover the grill, and cook, turning once, for about 20 minutes, or until a thermometer inserted into the thickest part reads 130°F (55°C) for medium rare.'),(598971,15,'Transfer to a cutting board and let rest for 5 to 10 minutes.'),(598971,16,'Cut the tri tip into thin slices across the grain and arrange on a platter.'),(598971,17,'Serve with the aïoli.'),(600009,1,'Combine the vinegar, ketchup, ancho chile powder, brown sugar, salt, black pepper, and chile de arbol powder or cayenne pepper in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Cook for 1 minute.'),(600009,2,'Remove from the heat and let cool to room temperature. (The sauce is best when you cover and refrigerate it overnight to allow the flavors to meld. You can, of course, stash it in the fridge for up to a week or so. Bring to room temperature before using.)'),(600009,3,'Rely on the sauce both for mopping pork butt, chicken, or burgers on the grill and for slathering over just about any grilled item just before serving—just be mindful to keep your mopping sauce separate from your slathering sauce, lest you contaminate the latter with cooties from raw meat from the former.'),(600196,1,'Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C). Oil a 9-by-5-inch baking dish, two 4-by-6 baking dishes or six 2-by-3 dishes or ramekins of some sort.'),(600196,2,'Assemble your lasagna in layers, starting with 1/3 of the sauce, then 1/2 the ravioli, followed by 1/2 the cheese. Spoon 1/2 of the remaining sauce over the cheese, then layer the remaining ravioli on top. Dump the remaining sauce over the ravioli and sprinkle with the remaining cheese.'),(600196,3,'Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake until warmed through and bubbling, 10 to 15 minutes more.'),(600196,4,'Let stand about 5 minutes or so before serving.'),(600526,1,'Heat the oil in a pan on medium heat. Once hot add mustard seeds, let them pop. Then add cumin seeds, let them sizzle a bit.Then add curry leaves and green chilies. Sauté for 30 seconds.'),(600526,2,'Add asafetida and turmeric powder.Immediately add cabbage, potatoes and green peas.'),(600526,3,'Mix well.'),(600526,4,'Add salt, coriander powder, chili powder.'),(600526,5,'Mix well.Cover the pan and cook it for 10-12 minutes or until cabbage and potatoes are cooked.Stir in between to make sure that it doesn’t stick to bottom of the pan.'),(600526,6,'Serve hot.'),(601095,1,'Pour lentils, broth, and sweet potatoes into a large pot. Bring to a boil and then simmer on low for 30-45 minutes, or until lentils and sweet potatoes are just barely done cooking.'),(601095,2,'Add the turmeric, tomatoes and ginger to the pot and cook for another 10 minutes.'),(601095,3,'Heat the oil and butter in a large skillet.'),(601095,4,'Add garlic, onions, and jalapenos.'),(601095,5,'Saute for 2-3 minutes.'),(601095,6,'Add the cabbage and cook for 10 minutes, or until cabbage is cooked through.'),(601095,7,'Add cabbage to lentil pot and stir in coconut milk. Top with cilantro.'),(602118,1,'Add chicken wings to a large zipper bag with 2 tbs sea salt. Seal and rub chicken until evenly coated. Refrigerate for 24 hours but up to 48 hours.An hour before cooking, soak 3-4 wood chunks of your choice in water and set aside'),(602118,2,'Remove chicken from fridge, rinse thoroughly and pat dry with a paper towel. Set aside to rest 20-30 minutes'),(602118,3,'Using a charcoal chimney starter, light charcoal and leave in chimney until charcoal starts to ash over'),(602118,4,'While charcoal is preheating, add all seasonings to a small mixing bowl, and mix well'),(602118,5,'Liberally coat chicken on all sides and set aside'),(602118,6,'Spread out hot coals evenly in the bottom of the smoker, there should be enough for 2 layers of charcoal'),(602118,7,'Remove wood chunks from water and add to coals'),(602118,8,'Fill water pan or other high heat resistant container with water and place in smoker'),(602118,9,'Add chicken to cooking grate and cover'),(602118,10,'Smoke chicken for 90 minutes at 230°-260°F. Resist the urge to lift the lid. Each time you open the lid, add 15 minutes to your cook time'),(602118,11,'Remove from smoker and let cool for 15-20 minutes'),(602118,12,'Serve with homemade ranch as a dipping sauce and enjoy.'),(602118,13,'Add all ingredients to a large mixing bowl and combine with a whisk until evenly combined.If ranch is too thick for your tastes, simply add more buttermilk and whisk.'),(602591,1,'Preheat the oven to 375F.In a large bowl, whisk together all the ingredients except for the chicken wings. Set aside half of the sauce mixture to use later.Toss the chicken wings in with the marinade in the large bowl to coat. Line a baking sheet with foil and spread the chicken wings in a single layer.'),(602591,2,'Bake for 30 minutes or until the wings are cooked through.When the wings are done, toss with the reserved sauce mixture.'),(603620,1,'Add the raspberry lime dressing, red pepper flakes and cilantro to a medium bowl.'),(603620,2,'Add the shrimp and toss well to coat.'),(603620,3,'Place in the refrigerator for 15-20 minutes to marinate.Skewer the shrimp with fresh raspberries.Grill over medium heat for 2-3 minutes per side.'),(603620,4,'Serve with lime wedges for squeezing over the freshly grilled skewers.'),(603636,1,'In the bowl of a food processor, combine the almond flour, sugar, salt, and flour. Pulse to combine.'),(603636,2,'Add in the butter and pulse until the mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.'),(603636,3,'Add the egg yolks and 1/4 cup ice water to the food processor and pulse just until the dough starts to come together.'),(603636,4,'Remove to a lightly floured surface and knead until the dough is evenly moistened. Split dough in half and pat each piece into a flat disk. Wrap in plastic and chill for at least 2 hours or overnight.When you are ready to make the pie, preheat oven to 425F.'),(603636,5,'Let the dough sit out for 5 minutes to soften.'),(603636,6,'Roll out each dough half on a lightly floured surface to a 12-inch round.'),(603636,7,'Place on a parchment-lined baking sheet and chill while you prepare the filling.In a large bowl, combine the sugar, lime zest, cornstarch and cherries. Toss to coat.'),(603636,8,'Transfer one pie crust to a 9-inch pie plate. Scrape the cherry filling into the crust. Using a 1/2-inch pastry tip or a cookie cutter, punch out holes in the remaining crust (or just cut slits in it).'),(603636,9,'Place it on top of the filling. Fold the edge of the top crust under the bottom crust and press together to seal. Crimp as desired.'),(603636,10,'Brush the pie with the beaten egg and sprinkle generously with the demerara sugar.'),(603636,11,'Place the pie on a parchment-lined baking sheet.'),(603636,12,'Bake for 30 minutes and then reduce the oven temperature to 350, covering the edges of the pie with foil or more parchment paper if it is browning too quickly. Cook for another 50-60 minutes or until pie is bubbling and crust is deep golden brown. Allow to cool for at least 4 hours before serving.'),(604177,1,'If using wooden skewers make sure to soak them in water for at least 20 minutes.'),(604177,2,'Combine the Avocado Vinaigrette with the cubed chicken in a zip close bag and let marinate for at least 30 minutes. The longer you can marinate the better, so plan ahead.'),(604177,3,'Heat the grill to medium heat, and brush grates with olive oil to prevent sticking.Skewer on the veggies and chicken in a rotating pattern, then grill for 5 to 6 minutes, turning halfway, until chicken is fully cooked.'),(604177,4,'Sprinkle the kabobs with the crumbled feta and serve with additional Avocado Vinaigrette on the side for dipping. Enjoy!'),(604730,1,'Combine ingredients into a small food processor (or use a hand blender like I did.)Puree until smooth.Refrigerate until time to use.'),(605121,1,'Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil.'),(605121,2,'In large saucepan over medium heat, combine pecans, sugar, butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla.'),(605121,3,'Heat to between 234 and 240 degrees F (112 to 116 degrees C), or until a small amount of syrup dropped into cold water forms a soft ball that flattens when removed from the water and placed on a flat surface.'),(605121,4,'Drop by spoonfuls onto prepared baking sheet.'),(605121,5,'Let cool completely.'),(605228,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a 9x5 inch loaf pan with strips of parchment paper or line with foil and spray foil with cooking spray.In a small custard cup, melt the chocolate in the microwave using 50% power and stirring every 30 seconds.In a metal or glass bowl, beat whites with a little of the salt until soft peaks form. Gradually beat in remaining salt and sugar; beat until stiff peaks form. Fold in melted chocolate and extract.'),(605228,2,'Sprinkle flour over meringue mixture, and with a heavy duty silicone scraper, fold it in.'),(605228,3,'Mix together the nuts and chips and fold them. The batter will be light brown, but the biscotti will be darker after they have gone through the whole baking cycle.Spoon the batter into your prepared loaf pan, spreading evenly.'),(605228,4,'Bake on center rack for 35 minutes. Cool loaf in pan for about 20 minutes, then remove from pan and let it cool to room temperature. When it’s almost cool, transfer to the refrigerator and chill until very cold – this makes it easier to slice.Preheat oven again to 250 degrees F.Peel parchment off the cold loaf. With a serrated knife cut loaf crosswise into thin slices – mine are usually between 1/8 and 1/4 inch thick. Arrange slices on 2 baking sheets and bake for about 45 minutes (check at 30 minutes), switching racks halfway through. The goal is to dry them out without letting them get too brown, so keep a close eye on them.'),(605228,5,'Remove from the oven and let cool. If they’re not completely crisp while hot, they should crisp as they cool.'),(605275,1,'Pour the whipping cream, condensed milk, and passion fruit juice into a blender. Blend on low until light and fluffy, 30 seconds to 1 minute.'),(605275,2,'Pour into a serving bowl or dessert dishes, and refrigerate at least 30 minutes before serving.'),(605909,1,'In a pot of boiling salted water, add broccoli florets for 3-4 minutes.'),(605909,2,'Drain and rinse in ice water.'),(605909,3,'Place the salad ingredients together in a serving bowl.In a small bowl whisk together dressing ingredients.Toss dressing with vegetables and refrigerate or enjoy immediately.'),(605947,1,'Place cherries, mint and honey in a tall glass and muddle together with a cocktail muddler or the handle of a wooden spoon until the cherries are smashed and the mint has released it\'s aroma.'),(605947,2,'Add rum and lime juice and stir.'),(605947,3,'Add ice to the glass and top off the drink with club soda.'),(605947,4,'Garnish with additional cherries and mint leaves. Enjoy!'),(606326,1,'Preheat the grill on high heat.'),(606326,2,'Drizzle the bell peppers and onions with oil and 1 tablespoon balsamic vinegar and sprinkle with salt.'),(606326,3,'Place all the veggies on the grill and cook for 3-5 minutes on each side, until the veggies are soft.'),(606326,4,'Remove from the grill and allow to cool slightly.'),(606326,5,'Thinly slice the mushrooms and bell peppers. Separate the onions into thin rings.'),(606326,6,'In a small bowl mix together the yogurt and 1 teaspoon balsamic vinegar.'),(606326,7,'Spread 1 tablespoon of the yogurt sauce onto wrap and divide the veggies evenly between the tortilla wraps, top with the feta cheese and roll up like a burrito.'),(606709,1,'In a large bowl add lamb, garlic, parsley, mint, sherry, oregano, cumin, coriander, crushed red pepper, salt and black pepper. Using your hands mix the meat together and divide into 4 patties. Either grill the patties over medium/high heat or fry the burgers with a little olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Cook until desired doneness. Please keep in mind that you will get the juiciest burger by cooking them medium rare. Baste the inside of the cut open brioche bun with olive oil and lightly toast. Top each bun with burger, 1/4 cup goat cheese and 1/4 cup arugula.'),(606953,1,'View detailed instructions for Cajun Chicken Pasta and other Cajun recipes'),(607283,1,'Cook quinoa according to package directions and set aside to cool.Clean and grate beet root, then set aside'),(607283,2,'For each wrap set out a tortilla on a flat surface.  In the center of the tortilla lay 1/4 cup each of spinach and arugula.'),(607283,3,'Place 1/4 cup quinoa on top of greens, handful of grated beets, 2 whole mushrooms sliced, 4 sliced roasted red peppers and a drizzle of balsamic vinaigrette.Pull up the opposite sides of the wrap over each end of the filling.  Then take one long side and fold tortilla over filling and continue rolling up like a cigar until filling is completely encased in the tortilla.  Now you have a wrap.Slice wrap in half with a knife, plate and serve with fresh fruit, chips, fries, slaw or potato salad.Enjoy!!!'),(607379,1,'Place all the ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth.'),(607782,1,'Prepare brownies per packages instructions.  Cool completely.'),(607782,2,'Remove brownies from pan and place brownies in a food processor and pulse a few times until crumbly.'),(607782,3,'Place crumbled brownies and cream cheese in a large mixing bowl.  Using an electric mixer, mix until well combined.  Chill mixture in the refrigerator for 15 minutes.  Make tablespoon size balls and place on  a large wax or parchment paper lined baking sheet.  Freeze balls for about 45 minutes.  Melt chocolates using a double boiler or microwave in 30 seconds intervals.'),(607782,4,'Let melted chocolate cool slightly.  Insert lollipop sticks into balls.  Dip in chocolate, letting excess drip off, then roll in crushed pretzels.'),(607782,5,'Sprinkle with fleur de sel or sea salt.  Set back on baking sheet.  Repeat until all balls are done then place in the refrigerator until chocolate hardens.  Store in air tight containers until ready to serve.'),(607836,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.  Generously butter a 9 by 13 inch pan.In a large bowl, stir together orange and lemon zest, sugar, flour, and salt until combined.'),(607836,2,'Add butter and work in with your fingers or a pastry cutter until the butter is about the size of peas and has been well distributed.Reserve 1 ½ cups of the shortbread in a small bowl.'),(607836,3,'Pour the remainder of the shortbread into the pan and press it in firmly.'),(607836,4,'Bake 15-20 minutes until light golden brown.While the crust cools, prepare the filling.  In a medium bowl, whisk together eggs, sugar, sour cream, flour, and vanilla bean paste until fully incorporated.  Fold in the cherries.'),(607836,5,'Pour the filling over the baked crust and spread into an even layer.'),(607836,6,'Sprinkle with reserved crumb topping.'),(607836,7,'Place the pan on a baking sheet larger than the pan to catch any drips (mine dripped a lot) and bake for an additional 45-55 minutes, until light golden brown.  Cool at least one hour before cutting.  Bars may be stored in the refrigerator in an airtight container for up to 3 days, or frozen, wrapped individually in parchment and foil and placed in a zipper bag for up to 3 months.  Thaw in the refrigerator about 1 hour.'),(608102,1,'Preparing Cauliflower Florets'),(608102,2,'Firstly chop or break the gobi (cauliflower) in medium size florets.'),(608102,3,'Heat water with salt and boil it. Rinse the cauliflower florets and add them to the hot water. '),(608102,4,'Let them get blanched in the water for 15 to 20 minutes. Later drain and keep aside.'),(608102,5,'Pan Frying Cauliflower Florets'),(608102,6,'In a bowl mix together the ingredients for making the batter - all purpose flour, corn starch, soy sauce, black pepper, kashmiri red chili powder and salt.'),(608102,7,'Add water and whisk to make a smooth batter without any lumps.'),(608102,8,'Dip each cauliflower floret in the batter.'),(608102,9,'Fry the batter coated cauliflower florets in hot oil. I have pan fried and added about 6 tbsp oil. Later I have not added any oil while stir frying the spring onions etc.'),(608102,10,'You can also deep fry or shallow fry. I have fried in batches of three. So depending on the size of your pan, you can fry at once or in batches. The frying takes some time.'),(608102,11,'When one side gets cooked and crisp, turn over each cauliflower florets and pan fry the uncooked sides. '),(608102,12,'Flip for a couple of times more, so that the cauliflower florets are evenly fried and light golden.'),(608102,13,'Drain the fried cauliflower florets on a kitchen paper towel. Fry all the cauliflower florets this way in batches.'),(608102,14,'Making Gobi Manchurian Dry'),(608102,15,'No need to add any oil again. In the same pan, add chopped ginger, garlic and green chilies. Sauté for some seconds till the raw aroma of ginger and garlic go away.'),(608102,16,'Then add the chopped spring onions & capsicum.'),(608102,17,'Add chopped celery if using. Increase the flame and stir fry till the capsicum is half cooked or almost cooked.'),(608102,18,'Add soy sauce, tomato ketchup, black pepper and salt. Stir.'),(608102,19,'Add the pan fried cauliflower florets.'),(608102,20,'Mix very well ensuring that the spiced sauce coats the fried cauliflower florets well.'),(608102,21,'Lastly add vinegar and stir well. Switch off the flame. Check the taste and add more of soy sauce or tomato ketchup as per your taste. '),(608102,22,'Mix in the chopped spring onions greens or garnish with them while serving cauliflower manchurian.'),(608102,23,'Serve Dry Gobi Manchurian as a snack or as a side dish with veg fried rice or mushroom fried rice or veg hakka noodles or veg noodles.'),(608138,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a 8-by-8-inch square pan with parchment. Lightly spray parchment with non-stick baking spray.In a large bowl, whisk together melted butter and brown sugar until combined.'),(608138,2,'Whisk in egg and vanilla extract until thoroughly combined.Stir in flour, baking powder, salt, and malted milk powder until just combined. Fold in white chocolate chips and sprinkles. The mixture will be very thick.'),(608138,3,'Transfer the mixture to your prepared pan. Evenly spread the mixture into the pan, starting in the center and pushing the thick dough out to the edges.'),(608138,4,'Bake for 23-25 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out mostly clean (a few wet crumbs are recommended).Allow the blondies to cool in the pan completely.'),(608138,5,'Transfer to a cutting board and cut into slices.'),(608196,1,'Preheat oven to 350ºF and spray standard sized muffin tins (18 muffins).Cream together butter and sugar in a mixer fitted with paddle attachment, then mix egg in.'),(608196,2,'Add mashed bananas and mix until well blended.'),(608196,3,'Combine dry ingredients in one bowl and in a separate bowl (or measuring cup), mix together milk and vanilla. Alternate adding the dry ingredients and milk into the butter sugar mixture and beat until combined.Fold in chocolate chips.Scoop into prepared muffin tins, filling about 2/3 full (a large cookie dough scoop makes easy work of this!).'),(608196,4,'Bake at 350º F for 18-22 minutes (until toothpick inserted comes out clean without any raw dough).Allow to cool in pan for 10-15 minutes before turning out onto a cooling rack.'),(608410,1,'Add the flour, sugar and salt to a food processor and pulse just until combined. In a small bowl, whisk mix together the egg, vinegar and water.'),(608410,2,'Add the cold butter pieces into the food processor and pulse until small coarse crumbs remain.'),(608410,3,'Sprinkle the water/egg mixture over the flour and pulse again until the dough comes together.'),(608410,4,'Remove the dough with your hands and wrap it in plastic wrap. Refrigerate the dough for 30 minutes.After 30 minutes, preheat the oven to 400 degrees F.'),(608410,5,'Roll the dough out until it fits your tart pan (mine was a 10-inch springform pan) and press it into the pan. Poke holes in the crust with a fork.'),(608410,6,'Bake the crust until golden and set, about 20 to 25 minutes. Allow the crust to cool to room temperature.To make the feta, add crumbled feta to a food processor and pulse until small crumbs remain.'),(608410,7,'Add in cream cheese and puree for 4-5 minutes, scraping down the sides when necessary, until feta is super creamy.'),(608410,8,'Spread the feta inside of the crust. Top the feta with the sliced tomatoes, lots of salt and pepper and few fresh basil leaves.'),(608410,9,'Cut into slices and serve immediately. You can refrigerate this overnight, but it\'s definitely best served fresh. If you want to make it ahead, I suggest making the crust ahead, keeping the whipped feta in a bowl, and assembling right before serving.'),(608469,1,'Get the full list of directions here.'),(608581,1,'Heat salted water for pasta: Put a large pot of salted water (1 Tbsp of salt for every 2 quarts of water) on to boil. While the pasta water is heating, start cooking the eggplant.'),(608926,1,'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a medium saucepan and cook the barley over medium-high heat for a few minutes until fragrant.'),(608926,2,'Add the stock or water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to a simmer then cover and cook for 30 to 40 minutes or until the barley is tender.'),(608926,3,'Place the cooked barley in a large bowl and let cool.In a large skillet, heat the remaining tablespoon of oil over medium-high heat. Sauté the onion until it becomes tender, about 5 minutes.'),(608926,4,'Add the jalepeno pepper and cook 1 minute.'),(608926,5,'Add the corn and bean and cook until the corn becomes golden, about 5 minutes.'),(608926,6,'Add this to the barley. Toss and let cool.'),(608926,7,'Place the oil, lime juice, cumin, coriander, honey, 