e back of a rubber spatula to press out all of the liquid. At the end you should be left with the ginger chunks and berry seeds.Refrigerate the strained berry-honey-ginger mixture so that it is completely cold, a minimum of 8 hours or overnight. This is a good time to place your ice cream maker insert in the freezer if you haven\'t already.The next day, whisk together the cold berry mixture and the whole milk yogurt along with lemon zest and a pinch of salt. Stir until fully incorporated.'),(609885,4,'Pour mixture into ice cream maker and freeze according to manufacturer\'s instructions.'),(609969,1,'Add the olive oil to a large skillet over medium heat.'),(609969,2,'Add the bell peppers & onion.'),(609969,3,'Saute 5-7 minutes.'),(609969,4,'Add the garlic and sauté an additional 1-2 minutes.'),(609969,5,'Add the chicken and cook through.While the chicken is cooking.'),(609969,6,'Combine the lime juice, salt, cumin, chipotle pepper & cilantro in a small bowl.Once the chicken is cooked through, pour the sauce over the chicken & veggies.Reduce the heat to low and simmer 5-10 minutes.'),(609969,7,'Remove from the heat and set aside.'),(609969,8,'Pour 1 cup of salsa in the bottom of the crock pot.Tear the tortillas into strips and layer 2 tortillas on top of the salsa.'),(609969,9,'Pour half of the chicken fajita mixture on top of the tortillas.Top with 1 cup of salsa.'),(609969,10,'Layer 2 more tortillas on top of the salsa, then top with the remaining chicken fajita mixture. Top with another cup of salsa.Top with the remaining 2 tortillas, then cover with the remaining salsa.Cook on low for 3-6 hours.'),(610657,1,'Combine ingredients for bowl. In a small jar with lid, shake dressing together.'),(610657,2,'Pour over bowl and toss everything together.'),(611205,1,'In 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of the oil over medium heat.'),(611205,2,'Add potatoes; cover and cook 12 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until thoroughly heated (potatoes will not brown).'),(611205,3,'Transfer to bowl; keep warm.'),(611205,4,'In same skillet, heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil.'),(611205,5,'Add chicken; cook 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally, until no longer pink. Stir in potatoes and tomatoes; cook 2 to 3 minutes longer or until thoroughly heated.'),(611205,6,'Sprinkle evenly with bacon pieces, 3 tablespoon of the onions and the cheese. Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 5 to 6 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.'),(611205,7,'Meanwhile, in small bowl, stir sour cream and taco seasoning mix until well blended.'),(611205,8,'Serve skillet dinner with sour cream mixture and remaining 1 tablespoon onions.'),(611626,1,'Place butter and brown sugar in a medium saucepan or small skillet. Cook over medium heat until butter has melted and sugar has dissolved.'),(611626,2,'Add pears and cinnamon and stir to combine. While you prepare the pancakes, continue cooking the pears over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes or until thickened.'),(611626,3,'Remove from heat.Lightly grease a griddle or skillet.'),(611626,4,'Heat over medium heat.'),(611626,5,'Whisk together pancake mix, water, and vanilla until combined. Stir in ricotta, mixing just until combined. Stir in almonds.'),(611626,6,'Pour 1/4 cup of batter** onto griddle or skillet. Cook pancakes for 1 & 1/2 to 2 minutes. Then, flip and cook about 1 & 1/2 minutes. Stack pancakes and serve with warm pear topping.'),(611854,1,'In a large bowl, beat together the peanut butter, butter, brown sugar and agave or honey vigorously with a fork, or with a handheld electric mixer on low-speed, until just combined. Stir in the vanilla, oats, and flour until a soft dough forms.'),(611854,2,'Roll the dough into teaspoon-sized balls in the palm of your hand. Gently roll the balls into the finely chopped sundae peanuts to cover.'),(611854,3,'Place the garnished cookie dough balls onto a foil-lined plate or small baking sheet.Briefly freeze the dough balls for about 20 minutes or until firm. Eat up! Store leftover dough balls (which there wont be any) covered in the fridge or freezer. They also taste great at room temperature!'),(613222,1,'Add all ingredients into a blender or food processor and process for about 30 seconds. This will breakdown the pumpkin so you can squeeze out as much flavor as possible.'),(613222,2,'Pour into a small saucepan and bring to a simmer on medium heat, stirring occasionally. Turn the heat up until a rolling boil occurs and remove from heat.'),(613222,3,'Pour through a fine mesh strainer pressing syrup through with a spatula. Store in fridge for up to 3 weeks. Some separation will occur. Shake well before using.'),(613949,1,'Preheat oven to 375F. Coat an8x8-inch baking dish with nonstickspray and set aside.Meanwhile, bring a pot ofwater to a boil and prepare pastaas directed on package.In a large non-stick skillet,brown ground beef over Medium-High heat. Stir in ketchup andmustard.'),(613949,2,'Remove from heat.When pasta is cooked to desiredtenderness, drain and add to beefmixture, tossing to combine.'),(613949,3,'Transfer to prepared baking panand top with shredded cheese.'),(613949,4,'Bake 3 to 5 minutes,until cheese is melted.'),(614419,1,'Heat a small amount of olive oil in a large sauce pot, add in diced onions to the fat and cook until lightly browned, for about 3 minutes.  Next stir in flour and rub. Cook for an additional 3 minutes.'),(614419,2,'Add all liquids, starting with the beer and bring to a light simmer. Gently stir in grated cheese and allow to melt.'),(614419,3,'Garnish with green onion.'),(615266,1,'Place cubed chicken and cauliflower florets in the bottom of your slow cooker.In a medium bowl, whisk together next 12 ingredients (coconut milk through cayenne.)Lastly, using a mortar and pestle or a spice grinder, crush together the cumin seeds, fenugreek and cardamom pods.'),(615266,2,'Add to the yogurt mixture and whisk to combine.'),(615266,3,'Pour spiced yogurt mixture into the slow cooker and stir until chicken and cauliflower is evenly coated.'),(615266,4,'Heat on Low for 8 hours or High for 4 hours.Five minutes before you\'re ready to serve, stir in green peas.'),(615266,5,'Serve over brown rice with cucumber raita and fresh cilantro if you wish.'),(616344,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease an 8-inch square pan.In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, oats, flour and butter.'),(616344,2,'Mix until crumbly.'),(616344,3,'Place half of crumb mixture in pan.'),(616344,4,'Spread the apples evenly over crumb mixture.'),(616344,5,'Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and top with remaining crumb mixture.'),(617261,1,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with foil.'),(617261,2,'Cut acorn squash in half lengthwise and scrape out seeds.'),(617261,3,'Place halves facing up on foil-lined baking sheet. In a small bowl, mix together coconut oil and cinnamon. Use your fingers to rub each half of the flesh of the acorn squash with the coconut oil and cinnamon mixture.'),(617261,4,'Place 1 teaspoon of brown sugar in the middle of each half and rub into the squash.'),(617261,5,'Bake for 45 min-1 hour or until squash is fork tender.Once squash is done, allow to cool for 5-10 minutes then place on plates or put in tubberwear if you are planning to enjoy this later. When ready to serve, make sure squash is warm then scoop 1/2 cup yogurt into each squash half.'),(617261,6,'Drizzle each with a teaspoon of honey and pecans.'),(617261,7,'Serves'),(617261,8,'Enjoy!'),(617801,1,'In the bowl of a stand mixer with the flat attachment, beat together the butter, sugars, vanilla extract and cream cheese on medium high speed for about 5 minutes or until fluffy.'),(617801,2,'Whisk together the flour, baking soda, cornstarch, salt and pumpkin pie spice.'),(617801,3,'Add to the wet ingredients and mix on low until combined.'),(617801,4,'Mix in the cinnamon chips with a spoon. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes to one hour. Do not skip this part or your cookies will flatten while baking.While the cookie dough is chilling, preheat your oven to 35'),(617801,5,'Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. When the cookie dough is chilled, roll the dough into 1 tbsp balls. I used a cookie scoop to measure out the dough. Cookie scoops make life easier.'),(617801,6,'Place the dough balls onto the baking sheet, about 2 inches apart.'),(617801,7,'Bake for 8 - 10 minutes. If your cookies are a little too puffy after baking, gently press down a little with the back of a wooden spoon. I did this and you can see that my cookies are still nice and thick.Allow the cookies to cool for 5 minutes and then transfer to a wire rack to cool.'),(618267,1,'Make sure your oven rack is in the middle position. Preheat oven to 375 degrees.'),(618267,2,'Heat the olive oil in a medium Dutch oven over medium heat until shimmering.'),(618267,3,'Add onion and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, for ten minutes, then add the minced garlic. Cook for another 2 to 4 minutes, until the onions are well browned.'),(618267,4,'Add 4 cups broth (or 3 cups broth and 1 cup water), cover, and bring to a boil over medium-high heat.'),(618267,5,'Remove from heat and stir in the rice. Cover the pot and bake until rice is tender and cooked through, about 60 to 65 minutes.During the last 20 minutes of baking time, prepare the mushrooms. Warm 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large skillet until shimmering.'),(618267,6,'Add the cleaned, sliced mushrooms to the pot with a dash of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the mushrooms are darker in color, fragrant and have soaked up most of their own juices, about 13 minutes.'),(618267,7,'Remove the pot from the oven.'),(618267,8,'Pour in the remaining cup of broth, the Parmesan, wine, butter, tamari, salt, and a generous amount of pepper. Stir vigorously for 2 to 3 minutes, until the rice is thick and creamy. Stir in the mushroom mixture and any remaining juices. Season to taste with salt and pepper, divide into bowls and top with a generous sprinkling of torn, fresh oregano leaves.'),(618682,1,'Preheat oven to 375 degrees.Brown ground beef over medium-high heat using a spoon to break it up into small chunks as it cooks. Season with salt and pepper.'),(618682,2,'Add onion and continue to cook until translucent, stirring frequently.'),(618682,3,'Drain off excess grease after cooking.Cool the ground beef mixture for 5 minutes and then stir in blue cheese and Worcestershire sauce.Mist 12 regular-size muffin cups with cooking spray.In a medium bowl, stir together Bisquick, milk and eggs until thoroughly combined. Spoon one heaping tablespoon of Bisquick mixture into each muffin cup. Top with 1/4 cup burger mixture. Finally, spoon another tablespoon of Bisquick mixture over the burger mixture.'),(618682,4,'Bake at 375 degrees for 25-30 minutes. With about 5 minutes left to cook, sprinkle the top of each muffin with French-fried onions.Cool and serve.'),(618682,5,'Drizzle with homemade buffalo sauce (optional).'),(618983,1,'For the filling, toss together all ingredients in a large bowl until the apples are coated. Cover the bowl and let the mixture sit for 1 hour, stirring a couple times. For the crust, whisk together the flour, pulverized walnuts (if using), and salt in a large bowl and then cut in the butter with a pastry cutter or a fork until it looks like coarse meal.'),(618983,2,'Add water 1 tablespoon at a time, working the dough together with your fingertips just until it comes together, and only adding enough water so the dough comes together when you squeeze it. Gather the dough together into a ball and then flatten it into a rectangle; wrap it in plastic wrap and refrigerate until chilled, about 30 minutes.For the crumble topping, use a fork to mix the flour and brown sugar together in a large bowl.'),(618983,3,'Cut in the butter, and then stir in the oats and walnuts.Preheat the oven to 375F; get out a 15 by 10 by 1-inch baking sheet. (I dont bother lining the baking sheet because theres enough butter in the crust to prevent it from sticking, but you can line the bottom with parchment paper if you want).'),(618983,4,'Roll out the dough to an 18 by 13-inch rectangle on a lightly floured surface. Drape it over the rolling pin to help you transfer the dough to the prepared baking sheet. If necessary, trim the dough to within 3/4-inch of the edge of the pan, and then fold it over and flute it as desired. Use the tines of a fork to poke a few holes in the bottom of the crust.Give the apple filling a good stir and spread it (along with any juices that have collected) into the prepared crust.'),(618983,5,'Sprinkle on the crumble topping.'),(618983,6,'Bake the pie until the apples are tender and the crust is golden, about 40 to 45 minutes; cool on top of a wire rack.Once the pie is cooled, whisk together all ingredients for the glaze and drizzle on top.'),(618983,7,'Let the glaze set before cutting and serving.'),(619035,1,'Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F.Slice the squash in half lengthwise, then scoop out and discard the seeds.'),(619035,2,'Brush the inside of each squash half with olive oil and sprinkle with salt.'),(619035,3,'Place cut-side down on a rimmed baking sheet and cook for 20 minutes.'),(619035,4,'Remove from the oven and cool the squash for about 10 minutes.Meanwhile heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a large saut pan, over medium heat.'),(619035,5,'Add the kale, season with a pinch of salt and pepper, and stir to coat with the oil. Cook until the kale becomes soft, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.'),(619035,6,'Add the garlic, chili flakes and chickpeas and cook for another 5 minutes.'),(619035,7,'Transfer the kale mixture to a plate and set aside.Use a fork to scoop out the cooked squash.'),(619035,8,'Heat the remaining oil in the saut pan.'),(619035,9,'Add the squash to the pan, along with the kale mixture. Stir to combine and cook until  heat through, 3-4 minutes.'),(619035,10,'Remove the pan from the heat and stir in the parmesan cheese. Taste, and season with additional salt and pepper, if necessary.'),(619035,11,'Serve immediately.'),(619272,1,'Wash masoor dal and soak for 30-45 minutes.Discard the soaking water and boil it with fresh 1  cups of water in pressure cooker for 5-6 whistles on medium heat.'),(619272,2,'Let the pressure go down by itself and then open the lid.'),(619272,3,'Heat the oil in a pan on medium heat. Once hot add cumin seeds.As cumin seeds sizzle, saute in ginger, garlic paste and green chili.Then add chopped onions and sprinkle salt. Cook till they are soft.'),(619272,4,'Add tomatoes and cook till soft.'),(619272,5,'Add spice powders and cook for 1 minute.'),(619272,6,'Mix in boiled masoor with extra water to make gravy.Simmer for 5-7 minutes.Lastly add lemon juice and cilantro. Stir well and serve.'),(619443,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. and line two cupcakes trays with paper liners.'),(619443,2,'In a medium bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, and kosher salt and set aside. In a stand mixer or with a hand mixer, cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Then beat in eggs one at a time followed by vanilla.'),(619443,3,'On low, stir in half of the milk, followed by half of the dry ingredients, then the rest of the milk and dry ingredients. Stir until just mixed together.'),(619443,4,'Divide batter between the cupcake tins, filling about 3/4 full.'),(619443,5,'Bake until the cupcakes are set and a tester comes out clean, 18-20 minutes.'),(619448,1,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Butter a 9x13-inch casserole dish; set aside.'),(619448,2,'In a large skillet, melt the butter over medium-high heat.'),(619448,3,'Add the celery and onion and saut until softened, stirring occasionally, about 8 to 10 minutes. Stir in the parsley, sage, thyme and marjoram, and cook until fragrant, about 1 additional minute.'),(619448,4,'Transfer to a very large mixing bowl.'),(619448,5,'Add the bread cubes, chicken stock, eggs, salt and pepper, an