 the right consistency. If it\'s too thick, add water,  tsp at a time.)Dip the donuts into the glaze, one at a time, then return to the wire rack for 15 minutes or so to allow the glaze to set.'),(622865,1,'Prepare 8x8 inch square pan by lining with foil (see picture in post), parchment paper, or spraying with oil/butter mixture such as'),(622865,2,'Baker\'s Joy.'),(622865,3,'Combine flour, brown sugar, and salt in a small bowl.'),(622865,4,'Add melted butter and lightly mix with a fork. Press evenly into prepared pan.'),(622865,5,'Bake at 350 degrees for 12 minutes or until lightly browned around the edges.In medium bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Gradually add brown sugar to eggs and beat until thick.Stir in remaining ingredients.'),(622865,6,'Spread over baked shortbread layer.'),(622865,7,'Bake for 15 minutes at 350 degrees F.When cool, turn the entire baked cookie out onto a flat surface and peel off paper or foil if using. Flip over and sprinkle with powdered sugar or ice with Browned Butter Glaze.'),(622865,8,'Cut in squares or diamonds as you prefer.Microwave butter in pyrex dish for 3 minutes (or heat on low in a skillet on the stove) until it just starts to turn brown.'),(622865,9,'Add cream or milk and combine.'),(622865,10,'Add sugar and mix until smooth.'),(622865,11,'Add vanilla if using. If icing is too thick, add more milk. If too thin, add more sugar.'),(623037,1,'In a large bowl with a hand or stand mixer, cream together butter, cream cheese, and sour cream until light and fluffy.'),(623037,2,'Add in vanilla and sugar, and mix until combined. Then add in flour and vanilla.'),(623037,3,'Mix just until all ingredients are combined.Divide dough into four equal balls and flatten into disks. Dough may be slightly sticky. Wrap each one with saran wrap and chill for two hours or overnight. Dough can also be frozen for up to 3 months.When ready to bake, combine chocolate, cocoa powder, sugar and cayenne pepper for filling in a small bowl.'),(623037,4,'Roll ou