espoons oil over medium-low heat.'),(625821,4,'Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, for 6-7 minutes, until translucent.'),(625821,5,'Add garlic and cook for 30 seconds. Raise heat to medium.'),(625821,6,'Add kale,  cup water, and  teaspoon vinegar. Cover pot and wait 2-3 minutes for the kale to wilt.'),(625821,7,'Remove cover and cook, stirring occasionally, for 3-4 minutes longer or until the kale is tender.'),(625821,8,'Sprinkle with a pinch of salt and a few grinds of black pepper.'),(625821,9,'Add kale mixture to potatoes and mash until thoroughly combined.In the same heavy skillet used for the kale, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook the sausages for 4-5 minutes, until nicely browned on both sides and heated through.Divide the kale-potato mash between 4 or 5 bowls. Arrange sausages on top.'),(625821,10,'Drizzle on a teaspoon of olive oil per bowl and sprinkle with chopped scallions, if you like. Enjoy!Time Saving Tip: Before you do any other prepping, peel and slice the potatoes and get them into the pot and onto the stove. It will take a while for that pot to get boiling so you should have plenty of time to get everything else sliced and diced while the potatoes cook.'),(625897,1,'Prepare the ingredients for the salad. Cook eggs and rinse all the veggies. Dice all the vegetable into small pieces.'),(625897,2,'Combine all ingredients into a bowl, you don\'t need to separate them like I did for the photos.'),(625897,3,'Add ranch dressing and stir to combine it all together.'),(625897,4,'Serve while the salad is still fresh.'),(626288,1,'A Perfect Fall Leek Soup In truth, this is one of those \"no measurement recipes\", but Ill try'),(626288,2,'Printable Recipe'),(626288,3,'Prep time: 15 minutes'),(626288,4,'Cooking time: 20 minutes or so'),(626288,5,'Serves 2-4Ingredients:1 tbsp olive oil1-2 tbsp butter3 large leeks, white &amp; pale green parts only, well rinsed*, and thinly sliced2 cups cremini mushrooms, thinly sliced'),(626288,6,'Swiss Chard, I used  bunch, separate stalks from leaves4 cups roasted vegetable broth you have to scroll down the post for the recipe, or buy some really good vegetable broth.1 sprig fresh thyme'),(626288,7,'Salt &amp; pepper to taste -1 cup orecchiette or other small pasta'),(626288,8,'Shaving of Parmesan or Pecorino Romano cheese'),(626288,9,'Prepare the vegetables. Small dice the Swiss chard stalks, coarsely chop the leaves and keep them in separate piles as youll be cooking the stalks with the mushrooms and the leaves only when you add the broth.*To prepare the leeks, I like Jamie Olivers method: slice lengthwise down the leek, but leave attached at the root. Rinse with the root side at the top so that all the sand drains out and doesnt get caught. Then cut off the roots and pat dry. Thinly slice the two halves stopping where the leeks start to get dark and coarse.'),(626288,10,'In a medium sized pot over medium high heat, pour the oil into the cold pot and once the pan is warm, add the butter. This is a great trick to keep the butter from burning. Saut the leeks until they are softened but not browned (about 3-4 minutes), stirring to coat with the butter/oil. Once the leeks are softened, add the chopped Swiss chard stalks and sliced mushrooms. Continue to saut until the mushrooms are golden (another 2-3 minutes).'),(626288,11,'Add the vegetable broth and allow to come to a boil.'),(626288,12,'Add the orecchiette and reduce to a simmer and add the Swiss chard leaves, thyme sprig and some salt &amp; pepper to taste. The soup is done once the pasta is al dente ( 5 minutes or so  you are using little pasta, so it doesnt take long)'),(626288,13,'Ladle into bowls and shave some cheese over top.'),(626288,14,'Serve with crusty bread and youll be in heaven.'),(626343,1,'Preheat the oven to 350F. Line two cookie sheets with parchment paper, silicone baking mats or leave ungreased.In the bowl of your mixer, using the whisk attachment, beat the butter on medium speed until creamy.'),(626343,2,'Add the molasses, stevia and agave powder and beat until thoroughly combined.In a separate bowl, whisk together the flour, flax seed meal, baking powder, baking soda, gum, and cinnamon, if using.'),(626343,3,'Add this mixture to the butter mixture; and beat until combined.Switch to the paddle attachment or use a rubber or silicone spatula.'),(626343,4,'Add the oatmeal packets, raisins, and if using, walnuts; and fold them into the dough.Scoop 2 tablespoons full of dough onto a cookie sheet, 2 inches apart. (A spring-actioned scooper comes in very hand for this step.)'),(626343,5,'Bake for 7 to 10 minutes (7 for warm dough and 10 for chilled) or until bottoms are golden brown around the edges.Allow the cookies to cool about 4 minutes in the baking sheet and then transfer them to a wire to cool completely. Store in an airtight container for up to two days. Freeze cookies immediately that will not be consumed within two days.'),(626352,1,'Preheat oven to 360F - 180C. Line a square baking pan with parchment paper (I used a 9-inch - 22cm pan similar to this one)In a large bowl, combine oats, shredded coconut, dates, goji berries, chia seeds, pepitas and cinnamon.In a small pot, combine coconut oil, honey and maple syrup in a small pot.'),(626352,2,'Heat on low until melted and pour over dry ingredient. Stir until dry ingredients are well coated.'),(626352,3,'Transfer to lined pan and press mixture very firmly. Make sure it\'s as compact as possible. Smooth surface using the bottom of a cup so it\'s nice and even.'),(626352,4,'Bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown.'),(626352,5,'Remove from the oven and cool. Set aside in the fridge for at least two hours before removing from the pan and cutting into bars. Store in the fridge to make sure they hold their shape.'),(626402,1,'Line an 8\" x 8\" baking pan with parchment paper, so the paper comes up the sides of the pan.'),(626402,2,'Place the biscuits (whole) in a single layer on the bottom of the pan. Since the cookies are slightly rounded, I broke up smaller pieces of another biscuit to fill any gaps. Finely chop the cherries in your food processor or blender then place in a bowl.'),(626402,3,'Add the sweetened condensed milk, melted coconut oil and coconut to the bowl. Stir to combine.'),(626402,4,'Pour the mixture over the cookies and smooth into an even layer. Melt the dark chocolate candy melts according to package instructions and pour over the top of the coconut layer.'),(626402,5,'Place the bars in the fridge or freezer until firm (about 2 hours).'),(626402,6,'Cut into small squares to serve.'),(626948,1,'Heat the oil in a medium skillet.'),(626948,2,'Add the mushrooms, carrots, red bell peppers, and red onions. Toss in the soy sauce and cook the vegetables over medium high heat until they soften slightly -- only 4-5 minutes.'),(626948,3,'Remove from the heat and gently stir in the tuna.In the center of each flour tortilla add  cup rice and  cup black beans. Top with the veggie tuna mixture and then sprinkle each with cheese, green onions, and diced tomatoes.To roll the burritos, pull the left and right sides toward the center. Then fold the bottom towards the center. Fold up while sort of stuffing the filling back in while you roll.'),(626948,4,'Heat a small skillet over medium heat. Placing them in the pan SEAM SIDE DOWN, toast each burrito for about 30 seconds, flip, and then toast on the second side. You just want a light toasty brown on the outside of the tortilla.To make the honey wasabi sauce, mix together the wasabi paste, honey, and Greek yogurt until smooth.'),(626948,5,'Drizzle over each burrito when serving or serve it for dipping on the side.'),(627028,1,'Cook the soba noodles according to the package directions.'),(627028,2,'Drain, rinse with cold water, and set aside.'),(627028,3,'Heat the oil in a small pot over medium heat.'),(627028,4,'Add the garlic and ginger and cook for 1 minute.'),(627028,5,'Add the broccoli florets, salt and coconut milk, bring to a boil, reduce to medium and cook for 5 minutes'),(627028,6,'Add the noodles to the coconut milk mixture and toss to thoroughly coat.'),(627028,7,'Sprinkle with the lime juice and cilantro and serve. optional ingredients: cooked shrimp or chicken'),(627267,1,'Preheat oven to 275 degrees.'),(627267,2,'Combine oatmeal, almonds, walnuts,pistachio nuts,sunflower seeds,flax seed meal, andsalt andstir to combine.In a separate bowl, combine oil, maple syrup, agave syrup and liquid stevia.'),(627267,3,'Add the liquid mixture to the dry mixture and stir to moisten all of the dry ingredients.'),(627267,4,'Transfer to a rimmed baking sheet and bake for 30 minutes, stirring once midway through baking.'),(627267,5,'Add dried fruit and stir to combine.'),(627267,6,'Transfer to a cooled baking sheet or heat-proof bowl and allow to cool, uncovered.'),(627267,7,'Serve as a snack or cereal. I enjoy it with homemade raw almond milk. Cover and store at room temperature for up to 1 week.'),(627508,1,'Season chicken legs with salt and pepper and let them sit for a while, 15 minutes to an hour, or overnight in the refrigerator.'),(627508,2,'Heat oven to 450 degrees. Put a cup or two of flour in a large bowl, add half the chicken and tumble the legs around to coat.'),(627508,3,'Set a large oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat. Swirl in 2 tablespoons oil or butter and allow to melt and foam. Shake excess flour off the chicken legs and slide them into the hot pan in one layer; adjust the heat so the legs are sizzling nicely. When the legs begin to brown, after about 5 minutes, turn them over to brown the other side, an additional 4 to 5 minutes.'),(627508,4,'Remove the chicken to a platter and repeat with remaining legs, adding more oil or butter if the pan seems dry.'),(627508,5,'Pour off the grease in the pan and add the wine or other liquid to the skillet, scraping at the sticky bits.'),(627508,6,'Let simmer over medium heat until pan is completely deglazed.'),(627508,7,'Pour that liquid into a small bowl and set aside.'),(627508,8,'Add remaining oil or butter to the pan and allow it to heat.'),(627508,9,'Add onion, carrot, celery and a pinch of salt and cook, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables have softened nicely, approximately 10 minutes.'),(627508,10,'Add garlic, thyme and bay leaf and cook for a minute or so, then return all the chicken to the pan, skin side up, along with the reserved glazing liquid and 3 cups stock or water. Bring to a simmer and then put the skillet in the oven.'),(627508,11,'After 5 minutes or so, reduce the oven heat to 325 degrees and cook until chicken is very tender, 30 to 40 minutes. (Test for doneness by inserting a slender-bladed knife into the meat. It should pull out easily.)'),(627508,12,'Remove the skillet from the oven, lift the legs from the skillet and put them aside again.'),(627508,13,'Pour the liquid contents of the skillet into a small bowl and allow it to sit for 5 minutes or so, letting the fat rise to the surface. Use a small ladle to skim off and discard the fat, then return liquid to the pan, along with the chicken. Bring back to a simmer on the stovetop, then return to the oven for 5 minutes or so before serving, sprinkled with the chopped parsley, or save to reheat later.'),(627722,1,'Blend Spinach and the Almond milk first'),(627722,2,'Then'),(627722,3,'Add other fruits'),(627722,4,'Serve chilled.'),(627729,1,'Blend leafy greens and liquid base together first.'),(627729,2,'Add remaining ingredients and blend again.'),(627851,1,'Preheat oven to 400°F.  Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil.'),(627851,2,'Place corn on baking sheet.  Reserve about 1/2 of the butter.'),(627851,3,'Spread remaining butter on the whole ear of corn.'),(627851,4,'Sprinkle liberally with salt and pepper (I use about 1 teaspoon of each).'),(627851,5,'Bake for 30-45 minutes, until starting to brown. Turn corn occasionally.'),(627851,6,'Remove from oven and spread remaining butter over the top of the corn.'),(627851,7,'Sprinkle with more pepper as desired.'),(627851,8,'Serve and enjoy!COOK\'S NOTE:  We also love to add a dash of cayenne pepper.  The best way to do that is to place 4 tablespoons butter in a small dish.'),(627851,9,'Add desired amount of cayenne pepper and mix together. Smear butter on corn and then continue with recipe.'),(628690,1,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil, then coat with non-stick cooking spray.In a small skillet, heat the olive oil over medium.'),(628690,2,'Add the garlic and cook until fragrant and beginning to brown, about 2 minutes, watching carefully so that it does not burn.'),(628690,3,'Add the balsamic vinegar, honey, mustard, salt and pepper.'),(628690,4,'Whisk and simmer until the mixture thickens, about 4 minutes.'),(628690,5,'Place salmon skin-side down on the prepared baking sheet.'),(628690,6,'Brush liberally with the glaze.'),(628690,7,'Bake for 5 minutes, brush again with the glaze, then bake 5 to 10 additional minutes, until the fish flakes easily with a fork and is cooked through.'),(628690,8,'Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve. Bask in applause from your Valentine.'),(629158,1,'Place all the ingredients for the Charmoula in the bowl of your food processor. Pulse to create a smooth paste.'),(629158,2,'Place the skinned salmon chunks in a dish. Spoon the Charmoula over the fish and mix to coat. Set aside to marinade.*In a large cast iron skillet with a lid or Dutch oven (or Tajine), heat oil.'),(629158,3,'Add the diced onions and saut over medium high heat for 1-2 minutes, until they begin to soften.'),(629158,4,'Add peppers and saut 1-2 minutes.'),(629158,5,'Add carrot slices and continue to saut 3-4 minutes, stirring occasionally.Reduce the heat to medium low and mix in the diced tomatoes with any of their juices and  c water.'),(629158,6,'Add the marinated fish and all of the marinade.Cover the dish and cook for 10-15 minutes.As your fish is finishing up, heat 1  c of water to a boil in a small, covered saucepan.'),(629158,7,'Remove the boiling water from the heat and stir in the couscous. Cover and let the pot stand, off of the heat for 5 minutes.'),(629158,8,'Remove the lid and fluff the couscous with a fork.'),(630044,1,'Heat the oven to 400 F. Salt the chicken pieces and cook them in the butter over medium heat until nearly done and lightly colored on all sides -- about 20 minutes, adding the breasts only after the first 10 minutes.'),(630044,2,'Transfer them to a gratin dish of a size to just hold them, arranged side by side.'),(630044,3,'Cook the crumbs in the chicken\'s cooking butter until slightly crisp and only slightly colored -- still blond, stirring.'),(630044,4,'Put them aside (don\'t worry if a few remain in the pan) and deglaze the pan with the white wine, reducing it by about half.'),(630044,5,'Whisk together the cream, egg yolks, seasonings, and cheese, then incorporate the lemon and the deglazing liquid. Spoon or pour this mixture evenly over the chicken pieces, sprinkle the surface with the breadcrumbs, and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until the surface is nicely colored and the custard is firm.'),(631191,1,'Preheat oven to 350Line a 9x9 pan with foil and spray with cooking spraypress 1 of the cookie dough into the bottom of the prepared pan.Top the cookie dough completely with the Hershey Bars'),(631191,2,'Spread the peanut butter on top of the chocolate using an off-set spatula or knife.'),(631191,3,'Sprinkle the graham cracker crumbs on top of peanut butter.'),(631191,4,'Spread the Fluff on top of the graham cracker layer. The Fluff is hard to spread, so do your best when spreading over the graham crumbs.Finally roll the remaining cookie dough out on a flour-dusted counter top.'),(631191,5,'Place rolled dough on top of Fluff. My dough ripped, so I just pieced it on, which was totally fine!'),(631191,6,'Bake for 20-22 minutes until top is golden.Allow to cool for 2 hours on a wire rack. Then transfer to refrigerator to cool for at least another 2 hours. If bars aren\'t completely cooled they will be far too oozy to eat.'),(631191,7,'Cut into squares while chilled.'),(631966,1,'Pierce squash and microwave on HIGH for five minutes or until tender (turn after three minutes). While it is cooking, mix apple slices with brown sugar; let stand.'),(631966,2,'Cut cooked squash in half and remove seeds. Fill hollowed squash with apple mixture. Return it to microwave and cook another two minutes or until apples are softened. Top each with one tablespoon of diet margarine.This recipe yields 2 servings.'),(633005,1,'Take the aubergine, prick it several times with a fork (this is very important!), place in a shallow baking pan and bake at 350 F. for an hour or so till it is cook through.'),(633005,2,'Remove from oven and allow to cool. Peel and mash.'),(633005,3,'Add the remainder of the ingredients.Refrigerate mix for an hour or two before eating because it allows the flavors to blend and smooth out better. After the dip sits for a while some of the water from the tomatoes separates out and I just pour that off.One advantage aubergine has over avacados (aside from the FF aspect) is that aubergine keeps longer. Aubergine guacamole can be made ahead of time and it will keep for a couple of days in the refrigerator.'),(634187,1,'MOLTEN CAKEPre-heat oven to 350 degrees.Sift flour and salt together.Butter muffin tins, or spray with non-stick spray.In a double boiler, gently melt chocolate chips and butter together.In a separate bowl, whisk eggs and sugar together.Allow the chocolate and butter mixture to cool.'),(634187,2,'Add the egg and sugar mixture to it, then whisk in flour.Fill buttered muffin tins with mixture and place into oven.When sides of cake settle (7-10 minutes), remove from oven and leave to cool before removing from tins.BANANA WHIP TOPPING'),(634187,3,'Add cream, sugar and vanilla extract into mixer and whip on second speed until fluffy.Fold Tropical Foods Banana Split into the whipped cream.Top cakes with banana whip topping once they are completely cooled.'),(634951,1,'Prepare the Tamarind Date chutney'),(634951,2,'Soak  the dates in hot boiling water for 5 to 10 minutes. Deseed and blend with the tamarind paste and a pinch of red chilli powder.'),(634951,3,'Add water to get a pancake batter consistency'),(634951,4,'Bring to a boil on a medium low flame in  heavy bottom saucepan and simmer for 5 minutes.'),(634951,5,'Add salt to taste.Prepare the Coriander chutney'),(634951,6,'Place the cilantro leaves, mint leaves and the green chilli in a blender and blend into a crepe batter consistency by adding little water at a time.'),(634951,7,'Add salt to taste.Prepare the Garlic chutney'),(634951,8,'Soak the red chillies in hot water for 10 minutes.'),(634951,9,'Peel the garlic clove and blend with the drained red chillies to a crepe batter consistency by adding little water at a time.'),(634951,10,'Add salt to taste.Finley chop fresh tomotoes, onion and the boiled potato'),(634951,11,'Place 2 cups of puffed rice in a large mixing bowl.'),(634951,12,'Add a handful each of tomatoes, onion and potatoes. Spoon in about 6 TBSP of the tamarind chutney, 2 TBSP of the cilantro chuntney and 1-2 tsps (depending on how much heat you prefer) into the mixture.'),(634951,13,'Add a pinch of salt, juice of 1/2 a lemon and stir with a spatula to combine the mixture.'),(634951,14,'Garnish with some cilantro leaves and serve immediately before the puffed rice loses its crunch and bite.'),(636096,1,'Preheat the oven to 180 C.'),(636096,2,'In a large frying pan, heat a little olive oil and fry the chopped onion and garlic.'),(636096,3,'Add the mince, stirring, until browned all over.'),(636096,4,'While the meat is frying, break up any lumps with the back of the spoon.'),(636096,5,'Add the flour (this helps to thicken the juices) and stir.'),(636096,6,'Mix well and add the thyme and the rosemary and stir.'),(636096,7,'Add the chopped tomatoes and pour the stock mixture.'),(636096,8,'Add a pinch of salt and freshly ground black pepper and let it simmer for about 5 minutes.'),(636096,9,'For the mash, boil the potatoes, then drain them in a sieve and place into a clean bowl.'),(636096,10,'Add the milk, butter and egg yolk, and mash together.'),(636096,11,'Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper.'),(636096,12,'Pour the meat into an ovenproof dish and spread the mash on top, smooth over and mark with a spatula.'),(636096,13,'Put the dish into the oven and cook until the surface is bubbling and golden-brown.'),(636124,1,'For the Brine: To make the brining solution, dissolve the salt and sugar in 2 gallons of cold water in a non-reactive container (such as a clean bucket or large stockpot, or a clean, heavy-duty, plastic garbage bag.)'),(636124,2,'Add the oranges, lemons, thyme, and rosemary. (Note: If you have a big turkey and need more brine than this, use 1/2 cup salt and 1/2 cup brown sugar for every gallon of water.)'),(636124,3,'Remove the neck, giblets, and liver from the cavity of the turkey and reserve for the gravy. Rinse the turkey inside and out under cold running water.Soak the turkey in the brine, covered and refrigerated, for at least 4 hours and up to 24 hours.Preheat the oven to 325 degrees.'),(636124,4,'Remove the turkey from the brine and rinse well under cold running water. Pat dry with paper towels, inside and out.'),(636800,1,'Cook rice as per directions and allow to cool.'),(636800,2,'Add the rice vinegar and stir well.'),(636800,3,'Place cucumber across the length of the sushi paper.'),(636800,4,'Cut crab meat in half lengthwise.Peel avocado and slice into 1/2 thick slices, dip into lime juice so it wont brown.Using a generous strip of plastic wrap, place one sushi paper on the wrap.Rub a small amount of Wasabi along one edge of the Nori.'),(636800,5,'Roll in Sesame Seeds, cut into 8 pieces.'),(636896,1,'Heat olive oil in a medium sauce pan over medium high heat.'),(636896,2,'Add onions and saute for about a minute or two until onions start to soften.'),(636896,3,'Add garlic and saute another 30 seconds or so.'),(636896,4,'Add smoked turkey pieces and saute for another minute.'),(636896,5,'Add diced tomatoes, broth, salt and red pepper. Bring to a boil, and then reduce heat to medium low and  simmer for about 15 minutes.'),(636896,6,'Add beans and let everything cook for another 15 min.'),(636896,7,'Add more broth or water if it\'s starting to get too thick.'),(636896,8,'Add spinach and simmer another 5 min.Taste and adjust seasoning to your taste. Stir in parsley at the end.'),(636896,9,'Garnish with a drizzle of good olive oil, a little chopped parley, freshly ground pepper and some good bread.  Grate a little pecorino or parmigiano reggiano to serve if you like.'),(637178,1,'In a large bowl combine brown and white sugar and softened butter.  Beat until light and fluffy.'),(637178,2,'Add the egg and vanilla and beat on medium speed until well combined.'),(637178,3,'In another large bowl, combined flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger and fluff with a fork until well combined.  Gradually add the flour mixture to the butter mixture and mix well.'),(637178,4,'Add the oats and carrots...stir until combined and then chill for an hour.'),(637178,5,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees and line a cookie sheet with foil and spray with cooking spray.  Using a teaspoon, place little collops of dough 2 inches apart and back for about 12 minutes.  Cool the cookies completely on a wire rack.'),(637178,6,'Once the cookies are completely cool, gently spread 1 teaspoon of peanut butter on one cookie and then make a sandwich with a second cookie.'),(637178,7,'Store in a well sealed tupperware.  Makes 12 sandwiches.'),(637852,1,'Place all the chicken on a baking sheet or cutting board, season both sides evenly with kosher salt, black pepper.In a shallow bowl scramble the eggs add a small pinch of salt, set aside.In another shallow bowl add the biscuit flour, paprika, and garlic powder.  Set next to the eggs bowl.'),(637852,2,'Place a large skillet set over medium high heat, when skillet is hot add oil.Meanwhile begin dredging only a few pieces of chicken (once the first batch is cooking then continue to dredge and flour, set aside).First dip the chicken into the egg then into the flour, gently pressing the chicken to have the flour stick to it.Note: I use one hand for egg dipping and the other for flour dipping to prevent clumps of egg white forming in the flour mix and on my hands.Test oil by dropping a little bit of flour, when it quickly sizzles, its ready for frying.Gently add each piece of chicken slowly, do not overcrowd the pan, otherwise, it will not get crispy.Cook on each side 4-5 minutes.'),(637852,3,'Transfer to a cooling rack over a baking sheet or onto a plate.At this point I turn on my waffle maker (I have my waffle batter prepared and set aside before making my chicken) and wait a few minutes for it to get hot while I begin to dredge and cook my second batch of chicken.Gently and slowly put the remaining floured chicken into the pan.Again, cook for 4-5 minutes on each side.Note: When your oil is very hot before frying (350 degrees F) it will not have any oil drippings on your plate or baking sheet so a paper towel on the plate is not necessary.For the Waffles:Follow instructions on the back of the cornbread mix, adding any additional ingredients required.Once the ingredients on the cornbread mix have been blended (I use a hand held mixer for this recipe), add almond milk, and oil, mix to combine.'),(638470,1,'Melt 1/4 cup butter in a large skillet over medium heat; add chicken, and saute until done.'),(638470,2,'Remove chicken from skillet, and set aside.Cook broccoli in a steamer basket over boiling water 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.'),(638470,3,'Remove from heat; drain well, and set aside.Melt remaining 1/4 cup butter in skillet over medium heat.'),(638470,4,'Whisk in flour, and cook, whisking constantly, 1 minute. Gradually add milk, and cook, whisking constantly, until thickened and bubbly.'),(638470,5,'Remove from heat, and stir in Swiss cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, lemon juice, and salt.'),(638470,6,'Layer half of chicken, broccoli, and cheese sauce in a lightly greased 11- by 7-inch baking dish. Repeat layer once. Cover and chill casserole up to 8 hours, if desired; remove from refrigerator, and let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before baking.'),(638470,7,'Bake, covered, at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, if desired, and bake 5 more minutes.This recipe yields 4 servings.'),(639325,1,'Pour the sugar and water into a medium skillet with high sides (taller than the chorizo is thick).  A non-stick skillet makes for easier cleanup.  Do not stir the sugar and water together, just make sure all the sugar is wet.'),(639325,2,'Over medium-high heat, bring the sugar water mixture to a boil.  Continue boiling until the mixture reaches 235F.  If you dont have a candy thermometer, spoon a small amount of the hot sugar into a glass of cold water.  The hardened caramel should be pliable and soft when cooled.  Youll notice the sugar turn amber colored just before this stage.  Dont worry if you overcook the sugar we have some leeway with the temperature.  But if you smell burning, start over.'),(639325,3,'Stir in the butter until melted.  Then reduce the heat to a low simmer and add the whole chorizo.  Cover and simmer, turning ever 30 minutes, for 3 hours.  The longer you cook it, the more flavor the caramel will pick up from the chorizo.'),(639325,4,'Youll notice the oil from the chorizo leaking out into the caramel.  Thats a good thing.'),(639325,5,'Whisk the oil and caramel together with a fork every now and then.'),(639325,6,'To serve, remove the chorizo and slice it into 1/2 pieces.  Butter one side of thin baguette slices and toast in the oven or on a skillet.'),(639325,7,'Place each piece of chorizo on a piece of toasted bread and drizzle with the caramel sauce in the pan.'),(640449,1,'Coarsely chop cranberries.'),(640449,2,'Mix dry ingredients, stir in cranberries.'),(640449,3,'Mix liquids together, then add to dry, beat for about a half minute (batter will be lumpy). Greased loaf pan. 350 degrees for 60 - 65 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.'),(640663,1,'Heat a large saucepot with a drizzle of olive oil.'),(640663,2,'Place the garlic, long hot pepper, onion and mushrooms in the pot to saut until the onion is clear.Prepare the bacon on a heated griddle and let the bacon get nice and crispy. When the bacon is done set it aside.'),(640663,3,'Add the tablespoon of bouillon and the cups of water to the pot and simmer.'),(640663,4,'Add the cup of potato buds, stir and continue to simmer on low.'),(640663,5,'Add the cups of milk and simmer on low for a few more minutes.When the soup is ready to be served add the lime juice and stir. Top the soup with the bacon bits, cilantro and cheddar cheese.'),(641652,1,'Prepare (A), combine sugar syrup, peanut oil and alkaline water together and blend well with a rubber spatula.'),(641652,2,'Pour sugar syrup mixture into sifted flour and mix well to a soft dough. Cover dough and rest for 30 minutes.Prepare (B) ingredients first and mix them together in a bowl.'),(641652,3,'Add ingredient (C) to (B) -'),(641652,4,'Add sugar, kao fen and salt to (B), mix well. Then add in apricot jam, canola oil and water into it. Put on a plastic hand glove and mix the mixture well and shape it into 12 pieces ball shape OR put the dried fruits mixture in a small plastic bag, squeeze and turn it to a ball shape and set aside. (please refer to tutorial) Not too tight as you\'ll find it very hard to shape the nutty filling in the mooncake mould later on. (about 70 each for my mooncake mould)Lightly dust some plain flour on table and knead dough (A) again till smooth. Measure dough to 55g each.Wrap the filling with the soft dough then dust some plain flour on it and place inside the mooncake mold, flatten dough to conform to shape of mould.To dislodge the mooncake, gently push out the unbaked mooncake and place on the lined baking tray, about 10 pieces on one tray, not too close for even baking.'),(641652,5,'Baked in preheated oven 190C for 10 mins at the center rack of the oven and rest to cool down (about 5 mins) before egg wash mooncake with a soft brush and bake for another 10 mins at the lower rack of oven.'),(641652,6,'Remove mooncakes from oven and brush some glaze on mooncake.'),(642294,1,'Preheat the oven to 425 degrees.Wash the eggplants, trim the stems, and slice crosswise into l/4-inch-thick slices. Line a baking sheet or two, as needed with foil. Oil lightly and sprinkle with water. Arrange the eggplant slices on the sheets so that they\'re slightly overlapping, and cover with foil.'),(642294,2,'Bake until easily pierced with a fork but not mushy, 10 to 15 minutes.'),(642294,3,'Remove from the oven and uncover.Turn the oven down to 350 degrees.'),(642294,4,'Heat the oil in a heavy saucepan.'),(642294,5,'Add the onion and saute over moderate heat until golden.'),(642294,6,'Remove from the heat. Stir in the tomato puree and herbs, and season with a bit of salt and pepper.'),(642294,7,'Combine the tofu and Parmesan cheese in the container of a food processor. Process until completely smooth.Oil a wide, round or square 2-quart casserole dish.'),(642294,8,'Layer the casserole as follows: first, half of the bread crumbs, then half of the tomato mixture, then the eggplant slices in one or two overlapping layers, then the remaining tomato mixture, then the remaining crumbs. Finally, spread the \"custard\" over the top, evenly and gently, using a cake spatula, and finish with the grated cheese.'),(642294,9,'Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until the top is touched with light-brown spots.'),(642294,10,'Let stand 10 minutes, then cut into wedges or squares to serve.This recipe yields 6 to 8 servings.Description: \"Moussaka, a hearty, layered Greek casserole, is often quite rich and complicated. This version is neither. The usual eggy custard topping is replaced with a deceivingly rich-tasting topping of silken tofu.\"'),(643306,1,'Preheat oven to 350F, grease and flour a 10\" springform pan.'),(643306,2,'In a medium bowl, toss together sugar and rhubarb. Allow to stand for 15 minutes, then drain liquid and set rhubarb aside.'),(643306,3,'In another bowl, whisk together flours, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Set aside.'),(643306,4,'In a large bowl, cream 1/2 cup butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar until fluffy.'),(643306,5,'Add banana and vanilla, beating well.'),(643306,6,'Beat in alternating additions of the dry ingredients with the buttermilk, blending well, then fold in the rhubarb.'),(643306,7,'Scrape into the pan and set aside while preparing topping.'),(643306,8,'With a fork or your fingers, work the butter into the cinnamon, spelt flour and brown sugar until crumbly.'),(643306,9,'Scatter over the top of the cake batter and lightly press on.'),(643306,10,'Bake 30 minutes on the middle rack of the oven, then cover with a piece of aluminum foil, move to the bottom rack and bake another 30 minutes.'),(643823,1,'Heat up oil, saut chopped garlic and dried shrimp until fragrant and shrimp started to dance.'),(643823,2,'Add in chopped preserved radish, ground black pepper and minced meat and stir fry until aromatic.'),(643823,3,'Add in Udon, seasoning and stir fry until well mixed. Dish up and serve.'),(643823,4,'Garnish with coriander/parsley/chili as you like.'),(644244,1,'Mix all the ingredients into the jar of mayo with a spoon.'),(644244,2,'Place jar in the refrigerator overnight to let things blend. The dry roasted garlic will dry your mayo out as it absorbs most  of the moisture, so I found if I soak it in some olive oil first I dont have that problem.'),(644376,1,'In a small bowl, mix together water, yogurt, 1/4 c. o