d.'),(657302,1,'Melt the butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Stir in the brown sugar until it dissolves with the butter. Stir in the pumpkin and the spices. Continue to stir over medium heat for about 10 minutes. Make sure the filling is not too watery; otherwise let it cook for a couple more minutes.'),(657302,2,'Remove the saucepan from the heat and let it cool down. After its cooled off for about 15 minutes, put the filling in the refrigerator to help it set for 30 minutes or overnight.'),(657302,3,'You can make the Empanada Dough while the filling is cooling off.'),(657302,4,'Mix the first 3 dry ingredients.'),(657302,5,'Cut in the shortening with the dry ingredients. Works better if you use your hands.'),(657302,6,'Add the eggs, milk and sugar. Continue to work in with your hands. Split the dough in half, wrap in plastic wrap and put into the refrigerator for about 20-30 minutes. Take out one half of the dough and split it into 12-18 balls of dough. Depending on how small you want your empanadas. I prefer one dozen per half of the dough. They also fit nicely on one large cookie sheet.'),(657302,7,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. You can fill your empanadas with any preserves made ahead of time.'),(657302,8,'Roll out the dough into small round circles.'),(657302,9,'Add a small dollop of filling on one half of the rolled out dough. Wet the bottom edge of the dough with water to help seal the two halves. Fold over the dough to seal. Seal off the edges with a fork by pressing down along the two edges. This also makes for a pretty pattern when baked.'),(657302,10,'Brush each empanada with egg whites, sprinkle with sugar and puncture each empanada with a fork to allow steam to escape while baking. Spray a large cookie sheet with cooking spray, place the empanadas on the cookie sheet and bake for 15-20 minutes on medium rack in the oven. If after 15 minutes you notice the bottoms of the empanadas starting to brown, move the cookie sheet to the top rack and continue to bake for the last 5 minutes.'),(658210,1,'Place rhubarb, onion and vinegar into large saucepan.Bring to a boil over medium heat. Cook uncovered for 20 minutes, stirring often.'),(658210,2,'Add remaining ingredients and stir.Continue to cook until thick, stirring often, about 30 minutes.'),(658210,3,'Pour into hot sterilized half pint jars to within 1/2 inch of the top.'),(658210,4,'Place sterilized metal lids on jars and screw metal bands on securely.Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.'),(658211,1,'First, I set the oven to a healthy 400 degrees.'),(658211,2,'Then, I dig into my potatoes.  These are actually leftover from another meal; I had a perfect amount of these little guys left for one more party.'),(658211,3,'Then I cut their little outfits into middrifts and low-waisters.  Read: I skinned their middles out.'),(658211,4,'Next, I wash, pat dry, salt, pepper, and chugalug EVOO over my lovely thighs.  My lovely chicken thighs, that is.'),(658211,5,'I stud my thighs with little spud balls and shove some rosemary sprigs in all the gaps and crannies.  Then I glugachug another douse of EVOO over the whole dish for good measure, before setting it into my hot oven for 30 minutes to roast.'),(658211,6,'While my chicken and potatoes roast,  I dress my trimmed rhubarb with my honey and sugar, then I set this mess aside to soak bask and absorb in its cross-cultural deliciousness.'),(658211,7,'Then, I cut the stems and hard spines off my kale, before washing and spinning it thoroughly and drying it even more thoroughly with paper towels.  Kale is so sturdy, you can squeeze it in between sheets of papers to absorb all the water sticking to the leaves.  Make sure its good and dry, and make sure you break out only the finest of your EVOOs to douse it with.  I thank the Doctor again for his gracious donation to Lolitas kitchen.'),(658211,8,'I dress my kale carefully with my EVOO, not just tossing the leaves in oil, but using my fingers to rub each curly surface completely until the entire surface, on both sides, is glossy.  I spread these leaves out single layer on two cookie sheets.'),(658211,9,'After 30 minutes, my chicken has begun to brown, my potatoes are almost tender to the forkpierce, and the EVOO and chickenfatO are sizzling on the porcelain surface. Its time to add the sweet to this succulence.'),(658211,10,'Using tongs, I pick up and move my chicken thighs and potaotes out of the way only in order to layer my honeysweetened rhubarb underneath them.  I set this platter  rhubarb topped with chicken studded with spuds and rosemary and sizzling in fats  back into the oven, alongside my sheet pans of oiled kale, for final 15 minutes.'),(658211,11,'My simply spiced salt and pepper chicken has crisp skin and its own amazing flavor.  My spuds are silky tender in the center, with crisp blistered skin on the edges.  The rhubarb has softened and sweetened, but is also tart and structured, toothsome and tender. The kale is so surprisingly crispy and ethereal; at the last moment, I sprinkled it with sea salt, and it crackles like paper, thin like the finest spun sugar, charred on the ruffles like the lace edges of a fine doily caught too close to the flame.  This is a meal of incredible complexity, all accomplished with only several ingredients and a most moderate amount of effort.  For my students flying the coop in the next few weeks, among my wishes for your fame, your riches, your accomplishments, and your true deep happinesses and joys, I hope you learn how to cook a'),(659277,1,'Using a 4cm pastry cutter cut out a cylinder from the centre of each potato.'),(659277,2,'Cut each cylinder into 3 discs about 1cm thick.Then coarsely mash the remaining potato and set side.Melt the duck fat.Prepare 4 x 8.5 cm diameter galette mould by pouring a litde of the fat into the base of each one.'),(659277,3,'Place in the refirigerator to set.Cook the bacon in the remaining duck fat until lightly coloured then drain.'),(659277,4,'Combine the bacon thyme salt and pepper with the mashed potato and mix.Moisten widh a litde duck fat.'),(659277,5,'Remove the galette moulds from the refrigerator and place 3 of the potato discs at the bottom of each.Fill all the moulds to the top with the mashed potato mixture prmsing down to fill all the gaps.Using a spatula even out the mixture so that it is flush with the top of the mould.'),(659277,6,'Place the moulds on a hot griddle to make the base golden then finish off in the oven preheated to 200C/400F/gas mark 6 for about 8 minutes.Unmould on to kitchen paper to remove excess fat.'),(659277,7,'Serves 4'),(660245,1,'Slice the pork and combine all of the ingredients in a a large bowl and let sit for  hour to an hour in the refrigerator.'),(660245,2,'Combine all of the ingredients for the salsa in a bowl and let sit while grilling the pork.'),(660245,3,'Heat a griddle.'),(660245,4,'Place the pork on the hot griddle and let the pork become a beautiful golden color on both sides. Set in a platter.'),(660245,5,'Heat a frying pan with a drizzle of olive oil.'),(660245,6,'Place the salsa in the pan and toss until the onion is almost clear.'),(660245,7,'Remove from the heat and place in a serving bowl.'),(660360,1,'Serve in small portions to begin a dinner or for a light brunch. Prepare the dough and preheat the oven as directed in the basic recipe.Shape the pizza dough as directed in the basic recipe. Divide the dough and roll into small pies, about 3 to 4 inches in diameter. Prick dough all over with the tines of a fork, then brush with olive oil.'),(660360,2,'Transfer the pie to the preheated baking surface and bake until the crust just begins to brown, about 6 minutes.'),(660360,3,'Remove from the oven and cover with the cheese, leaving a 1/2 inch border around the edges. Arrange the salmon and onion on top and drizzle evenly with olive oil. Return to the oven and bake until the crust is golden brown and puffy, the cheese begins to melt and the salmon is heated through, about 4 minutes.'),(660360,4,'Remove from the oven to a cutting tray or board and lightly brush the crust with olive oil.'),(660360,5,'Garnish with the dill. Slice and'),(661530,1,'In a small bowl place the tomatoes, lemon juice, parsley, basil, green onions, olive oil salt and pepper.'),(661530,2,'Mix well and let it rest.Slightly cover the bottom of a large skillet with salt, and place over high heat. When hot add the steaks and sear them to your desire doneness. 5 minutes per each side for medium rare.'),(661530,3,'Place the steak on a plate and serve with the tomatoes salad on the side and pour the juice over the steak'),(661850,1,'Sprinkle oat mixture evenly over strawberry batter.'),(661850,2,'Bake for 15 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.'),(661850,3,'Let cool in pans for 10 minutes.'),(661850,4,'Remove from pans, and cool completely on wire racks.'),(661850,5,'Serve with Strawberry Butter.'),(662343,1,'Place 1 graham cracker on a plate; place XoBiotic Squares on top.'),(662343,2,'Place marshmallow on top of the two XoBiotic Squares, then put int he microwave for about 8 seconds or long enough that you see the bottom start to bulge outwards.'),(662343,3,'Remove and quickly place the other graham cracker on top of the marshmallow, gently compressing it until the marshmallow spaces out.'),(662343,4,'Serves 1'),(662586,1,'Making the pesto'),(662586,2,'Preheat the oven to 400F / 200C'),(662586,3,'Cut a cross in the flat side of the chestnut and put them in water for 20 minutes.'),(662586,4,'Put the chestnuts cross side up on a baking tray and slide in the oven until the edges of the cross curl up.'),(662586,5,'Let them cool only slightly and peel them. If they are cold they are hard to peel so just warm them a bit up when they cooled down to make the work easier.'),(662586,6,'Put them in a kitchen machine with the parmesan, walnuts, parsley and olive oil.Grind into a coarse pesto, it should not be a smooth paste.Season with pepper, salt and a squeeze of lemon juice.Gnocchi'),(662586,7,'Cook the potatoes in their skin in boiling water until soft; peel of the skin and mash them slightly.'),(662586,8,'Spread them out on a baking tray and put them in the oven for 5 minutes to dry them out a bit, make sure they dont brown.You just want them to lose some water.Prepare a clean worktop to knead on and baking paper to put the gnocchi on when formed.Press the potato through a sift and make a pile on your worktop. Make a well in the middle and incorporate the egg, nutmeg and salt. Now we have to work a bit fast; we dont want to over knead the dough because then it becomes sticky again.Start adding flour in batches and knead until the mixture is not sticky anymore.Divide it in three and roll them out into long snakes.'),(662586,9,'Cut the snake into gnocchi the size you like and place them on the baking sheet.You can now form them into little egg shapes, make edges with a fork or twist them around their axe to make a nice curl if you like.Boil water in a big pan and cook the gnocchi until they start floating on the surface.'),(662586,10,'Mix them with the pesto and serve with some grated parmesan on top.'),(662952,1,'Combine boiling water and tea in a bowl; cover and steep for 3 minutes.  Strain the tea into another bowl (or remove tea bags).'),(662952,2,'Add remaining ingredients, stir and then cover and chill for about 30 minutes.'),(662952,3,'Brush sauce on steak, chops or shrimp before grilling and/or use as a dipping sauce.'),(662959,1,'Teff is a very tasty grain used for thousands of years in Ethiopia. It is easily the tiniest grain I have ever seen and adds a delicious character to bread.'),(662959,2,'*NOTE (if both are available, try using some flour and some whole grain.'),(662959,3,'The total amount should still be 3/4 cup.)'),(662959,4,'When set on a 13-hour cycle, the center collapses and makes a very dense loaf.'),(662959,5,'Variation:2-1/4 cup flour1/4 cup poppy seed ) excellent loft1/4 cup bran1/4 cup millet'),(665421,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees farenheit. Coat a 9-by-13- inch baking pan with cooking spray. Line with a 9-by-21-inch sheet of parchment paper, leaving a 2-inch overhang on each short side.'),(665421,2,'Put the caramels and cream in a small saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until the caramels are well melted, about 5 minutes.'),(665421,3,'Let cool.'),(665421,4,'Stir together the oats, flour, brown sugar, baking soda, and salt in a large bowl. Blend in the butter with a fork or until the mixture is coarse; press half of the mixture onto the lined pan.'),(665421,5,'Bake until just set and starting to color around edges, about 20 minutes.'),(665421,6,'Let cool in pan on a wire rack for about 5 minutes.'),(665421,7,'Sprinkle the crust with the chocolate chips and drizzle it with the caramel mixture. Top with the remaining crumb mixture and bake until golden, about 20 to 25 minutes.'),(665421,8,'Let cool in the pan. Then cut into squares and serve.'),(665927,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F, grease a 9-inch springform pan and set aside.Finely crush the cookies in a food processor, add melted butter and blend until its all moistened.Press crumb mixture onto the bottom of the prepared pan and bake for 8 minutes.'),(665927,2,'Remove from the oven and set on a wire rack to cool while making the filling.Melt 10 ounces bittersweet chocolate and set aside to cool.'),(665927,3,'Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth, mix in cocoa powder'),(665927,4,'Add the eggs one at a time, mixing on low speed and do not overbeat it.'),(665927,5,'Add melted chocolate and mix on low speed to combine.'),(665927,6,'Pour the filling over the crust and smooth the top.'),(665927,7,'Bake the cheesecake until the center is set and the top looks dry (about 1 hour to 1 hour 10 minutes).Cool on a wire rack for 5 minutes, then run a thin knife around the sides of the pan and set the cake in the refrigerator (uncovered), for at least 8 hours, or better overnight.In a medium saucepan stir together cream, chocolate and sugar on low heat until the chocolate is completely melted and the mixture is smooth.Cool and pour over the cheesecake.When the topping is set and cooled again run a thin knife around the sides and remove the springform pan sides.This cheesecake can be prepared up to 2-3 days in advance just store covered in the refrigerator.'),(665927,8,'Garnish with chocolate curls (optional).'),(665996,1,'Wash and soak almonds for at least 6 hours. Peel the skin.crush saffron with the help of your fingers. Refrigerated saffron easily gets crushed and blends well with the milk.Bring 2 cups of water or milk to a boil, add saffron, sugar and cardamom powder.While the milk boils, blend the almonds with little water to a smooth paste. you can as well blend sugar saffron cardamom and almonds to a smooth paste.'),(665996,2,'Add this to the boiling milk.Simmer for 2 minutes. off the heat.'),(665996,3,'Let the temperature come down to warm before you serve. If you are serving it to a little kid, you may need to filter to remove the coarse granules. This is optional and depends on your blender.'),(666193,1,'Wash and cut brussels sprouts in half or quarter.In a large skillet heat oil over medium heat.Once sizzling add brussels sprouts and cook until crispy, stirring to crisp all sides.'),(666193,2,'Add apple cider vinegar, honey, Sriracha, lemon juice, tamari sauce, minced garlic, and ground ginger in food processor or blender.Once mixed slowly add in olive oil while continuing to mix.'),(666193,3,'Remove brussels sprouts and coat in vinaigrette.Top with slivered almonds and chopped cilantro.Enjoy!'),(666405,1,'To cook the quinoa: First, rinse the quinoa in a fine mesh colander under running water for a minute or two. In a medium-sized pot, combine the rinsed quinoa and 2 cups water. Bring the mixture to a gentle boil, then cover the pot, reduce heat to a simmer and cook for 15 minutes.'),(666405,2,'Remove the quinoa from heat and let it rest, still covered, for 5 minutes. Uncover the pot, drain off any excess water and fluff the quinoa with a fork. Set it aside to cool.To cook the sweet potatoes: In a large skillet, warm the olive oil over medium heat.'),(666771,1,'Heat oven to 450 degrees F.'),(666771,2,'Combine cauliflower and garlic in a large bowl.'),(666771,3,'Drizzle with olive oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper.'),(666771,4,'Transfer, in a single layer, to a large rimmed baking sheet. Roast at 450 degrees F for about 25 minutes, stirring once.'),(666771,5,'Sprinkle with cheese.'),(666771,6,'Serve immediately'),(666969,1,'In a standing electric mixer fitted with the paddle, beat the butter with the sugar and salt at medium speed until creamy.'),(666969,2,'Add the vanilla and egg yolk and beat until smooth.'),(666969,3,'Add the flour and pistachios and beat just until incorporated. Scrape the pastry onto a sheet of plastic wrap. Flatten the pastry into a disk, wrap in the plastic and refrigerate until firm, about 30 minutes.'),(666969,4,'Preheat the oven to 35'),(666969,5,'Roll out the pastry between 2 sheets of plastic wrap to a 13-inch round.'),(666969,6,'Remove the plastic and ease the pastry into a 10-inch fluted tart pan with a removable bottom; trim the overhang and patch any tears. Refrigerate the pastry until firm, about 10 minutes.'),(666969,7,'Line the tart shell with parchment paper and fill with pie weights or dried beans.'),(666969,8,'Bake in the center of the oven for 30 minutes.'),(666969,9,'Remove the parchment and weights and bake for 15 minutes longer or until golden and cooked through.'),(666969,10,'Let cool completely.'),(666969,11,'In a medium saucepan, combine the milk with the vanilla bean, seeds and salt and bring to a boil. In a large bowl, whisk the sugar with the cornstarch and eggs. Gradually whisk in 1/2 cup of the hot milk. Scrape the mixture into the saucepan and cook over moderate heat, whisking constantly, until very thick, about 4 minutes.'),(666969,12,'Remove from the heat and whisk in the butter. Strain the pastry cream into a bowl, press a piece of plastic wrap directly onto the surface and refrigerate until chilled, about 1 hour.'),(666969,13,'Spread the pastry cream in the tart shell and arrange the raspberries on top; sprinkle with the pistachios to garnish. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.'),(667069,1,'Preheat oven to 325F. Grease a 9x13 pan.Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat. Stir in sugars and heat while stirring until hot to touch, but not bubbling.'),(667069,2,'Remove pan from heat and whisk in cocoa powder, vanilla, saltand baking powder.'),(667069,3,'Whisk in eggs, one at a time, until incorporated. Stir in flour.'),(667069,4,'Spread evenly in prepared pan and bake for 25 minutes.Meanwhile, make caramel. Over medium-low heat, melt caramel bits and evaporated milk together, stirring frequently.After 25 minutes, remove brownies from oven and top with the cookies, pressing down slightly. Some brownie will still remain visible.'),(667069,5,'Pour caramel sauce evenly over cookies. Return to oven and bake for 5 more minutes.'),(667082,1,'Preheat oven to 350F.Line a 17.25 x 11.5 cookie sheet with foil and place crackers flat side to side with salt side up.Melt unsalted butter on medium heat (slowly as it will burn easily) about 5 minutes.'),(667082,2,'Add sugar and stir constantly until mixture comes to a quick boil.'),(667082,3,'Remove butter mixture from heat. Immediately pour butter mixture over crackers. Make sure all crackers are covered with butter mixture. Then, sprinkle pecans all over.'),(667082,4,'Bake for 15 minutes. Once removed from oven, sprinkle chocolate chips all over top.'),(667082,5,'Let sit for a minute to allow chocolate chips to melt. Use a fork and gently spread chocolate all over top.'),(667082,6,'Place in refrigerator until completely cooled (about 4 hours). Peel off foil and break into pieces.'),(667149,1,'In a large pot of boiling water, cook the potatoes for about 10 minutes until tender and can easily be pierced with a knife.'),(667149,2,'Drain and add to a large mixing bowl while still warm.In the same large mixing bowl with the warm potatoes, add in the sour cream, mayonnaise, sliced scallions, salt and pepper. Gently toss to combine.Can be served warm, or covered with saran wrap and refrigerated for 1-2 hours and served cold. Will keep in an airtight container for 4 days.'),(667311,1,'Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.'),(667311,2,'Add potatoes and cook until tender but still firm, about 15 minutes.'),(667311,3,'Drain, cool, peel and chop.'),(667311,4,'Place eggs in a saucepan and cover with cold water. Bring water to a boil; cover, remove from heat, and let eggs stand in hot water for 10 to 12 minutes.'),(667311,5,'Remove from hot water, cool, peel and chop.In a large bowl, combine the potatoes, eggs, celery, onion, relish, garlic salt, celery salt, mustard, pepper and mayonnaise.'),(667422,1,'Whisk together flour, baking powder, and 1 teaspoon salt in a bowl.'),(667422,2,'Cut in butter with a pastry cutter or rub in with your fingers until small clumps form. Stir in cheese, then add cream, stirring with a fork to combine until dough forms. (Dough will be slightly sticky.)'),(667515,1,'Spray a 9\" x 13\" pan with cooking spray.  In a large stock pot, melt the butter and salt over medium heat.  Once it is melted, add 4 cups of the mini marshmallows and stir until they are completely melted.'),(667681,1,'Preheat broiler to high.'),(667681,2,'Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),(667681,3,'Add oil to pan; swirl to coat.'),(667681,4,'Add onion; saut 5 minutes or until tender.'),(667681,5,'Add garlic; saut 30 seconds.'),(667681,6,'Add zucchini and next 5 ingredients (through salt); cook 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.'),(667681,7,'Add beans; cook for 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.'),(667681,8,'Arrange tortilla wedges in a single layer on a large jelly-roll pan coated with cooking spray. Lightly coat tortilla wedges with cooking spray. Broil 2 minutes on each side or until lightly browned and crisp.'),(667681,9,'Sprinkle shredded Mexican cheese evenly over tortillas. Broil 1 minute or until cheese melts.'),(667681,10,'Top chips evenly with bean mixture, avocado, queso fresco, cilantro, and tomato.'),(667681,11,'Serve with lime wedges.'),(667994,1,'Combine the mango, fish sauce, lime juice, brown sugar, jalapeno, red onion, garlic, and cilantro in a bowl.'),(667994,2,'Mix well and set aside.'),(667994,3,'Sprinkle the shrimp with the kosher salt.'),(667994,4,'Combine the coconut and flour in a shallow bowl and mix well.'),(667994,5,'Place the beaten egg white in another shallow bowl.  Dip each shrimp first in the beaten egg, letting any excess dripping off. Next dip the shrimp in the coconut mixture, coating them completely.  Set the shrimp on waxed paper.'),(667994,6,'Heat about 1-inch of oil in a deep skillet over medium-high heat (to about 360 degrees F).'),(667994,7,'Add the shrimp, in batches, and cook until golden brown, turning as needed.'),(667994,8,'Remove the shrimp with a slotted spoon and let drain on paper toweling.'),(667994,9,'Serve the shrimp with the dipping sauce.'),(668332,1,'Lightly saute all'),(668471,1,'Over medium heat, mix together the cream, half-and-half and salt in a medium saucepan until hot and steamy, but not simmering (about 5 minutes).'),(668471,2,'Place the egg yolks in a medium mixing bowl and whisk until combined.'),(668471,3,'Pour half of the warm milk mixture into the yolks in a slow and steady stream, whisking constantly.'),(668471,4,'Pour the mixture back into the saucepan and heat over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture is thick enough to coat the back of a spoon. If using a candy thermometer, the mixture should reach 170F (77C).'),(668471,5,'Remove from the heat and stir in the vanilla and maple syrup.If the mixture has any bits of egg yolk clumps (which mine didn\'t), strain the mixture through a fine-mesh sieve or a food mill set over a storage container.'),(668471,6,'Let the ice cream cool completely, about 1 hour, and then refrigerate for at least 2 hours (preferably overnight) before churning according to your ice cream makers instructions.'),(668471,7,'Serve immediately for soft serve ice cream. For firmer ice cream, place the ice cream in a freezer-safe airtight container. Press a piece of plastic wrap against the ice cream (to prevent ice crystals from forming). Freeze for 2 to 3 hours or until firm. After 4 to 5 hours, it will become quite hard and not very easy to scoop.'),(668471,8,'Let sit at room temperature for 10 to 15 minutes or until easier to scoop. Freeze for up to 2 weeks.'),(668876,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees and grease a 10 inch skillet or baking dish with butter.'),(668876,2,'Whisk the butter and sugar until smooth in a medium bowl.'),(668876,3,'Add the egg and vanilla and whisk again.'),(668876,4,'Add the milk and whisk once more until smooth. Set aside.'),(668876,5,'Combine the flour, baking powder and spices in a separate bowl.'),(668876,6,'Add the flour mixture to the wet ingredients slowly whisking together to incorporate as you go.'),(668876,7,'Spread the batter onto the bottom of the skillet in an even layer.'),(668876,8,'Combine the peaches, blueberries and lemon juice in a small bowl. Toss together then pile on top of the cake batter in the skillet.Make the streusel by combining all the ingredients in a small bowl and working the mixture with your fingers or a fork until crumbly.'),(668876,9,'Sprinkle the streusel on top of the fruit.'),(668876,10,'Bake for about 40 minutes until cake layer is cooked through.'),(668876,11,'Remove from oven, let cool for 10 minutes before slicing.'),(668876,12,'Serve with vanilla ice cream.'),(668911,1,'Preheat oven to 350F and line two 12-cup muffin pans with paper liners (I can get up to 14 out of this batch).'),(668911,2,'Whisk together dry ingredients in a large bowl: flours, cocoa powder, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Set aside.In a blender, place oil, milk, maple syrup or agave, banana, vanilla and spinach. Blend on high for about 30 seconds or until completely pured.'),(668911,3,'Pour pured mixture into dry mixture and fold together with a rubber spatula until completely combined. Stir in chocolate chips.Fill muffin cups about  full and bake 20-22 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.'),(670350,1,'In a large sauce pan or pot, add crushed tomatoes, chicken broth, Italian seasoning and onion powder. Bring to a simmer, stirring occasionally, until it thickens. Turn up heat and add in zucchini noodles. Don\'t be afraid it if seems that there isn\'t enough liquid for the noodles because the zucchini will release water and shrink once it starts to heat up. Cook for 3-5 minutes, stirring occasionally so that all zucchini cooks evenly, until your zoodles are cooked. Zoodles should be tender but still somewhat firm. If your sauce becomes too watery, you can drain some liquid out. If it isn\'t liquid enough, you can add another 1-2 tbsp of broth during the cooking.'),(670350,2,'Toss in cherry tomatoes and cook for about 1 minute. Top with grated parmesan cheese and serve.'),(670572,1,'Add beef stock, star of anise, cinnamon to a large stock pot and bring to a low simmer'),(670572,2,'Cook rice noodles according to package directions'),(670572,3,'Sprinkle salt and pepper over thinly sliced beef.'),(670572,4,'Remove star of anise an cinnamon from stock. Spoon stock into bowls and add thinly sliced beef and a serving of noodles.Top each bowl with desired vegetables and a squeeze of lime.Divide the broth between four to six large bowls, then add thinly sliced beef and desired amount of noodles.Top with bean sprouts, sliced jalapeos, fresh cilantro, avocado and serve with lime wedges.'),(670572,5,'Add a drizzle of Tsangs stir fry sauces to your desired taste.'),(670572,6,'Serve and Enjoy.'),(671170,1,'In a blender or food processor, blend the pineapple and coconut milk until smooth.'),(671170,2,'Let the pineapple chunks soften for about 5 minutes, if necessary, to help blend smoothly. This works best in a high powered blender or mini food processor. If you only have a large food processor, you may wish to double the recipe so there is enough stuff to get blended.'),(671170,3,'Add the creamed coconut and continue blending. It will appear to harden in chunks, but continue blending. There will be only small flecks of the creamed coconut. Enjoy immediately or freeze for later.'),(671354,1,'Melt the coconut sugar in a large skillet set over medium heat, stirring gently from time to time. This may take anywhere from 5 to 10 minutes depending on the heat of your stove and thickness of your pan.   Once the coconut sugar is completely melted, add the toasted hazelnuts and raw almonds. Stir to coat, and transfer to a rimmed baking sheet lined with parchment paper.'),(671354,2,'Spread in a single layer and let cool completely.'),(671354,3,'Put the cooled nuts, along with the ghee, coconut oil, and salt into the bowl of a food processor and process for a total of 8 to 10 minutes or until smooth and creamy, stopping to scrape the sides as needed.'),(671354,4,'Add the cacao powder and resume processing until its completely incorporated.'),(671354,5,'Add the vanilla extract and give your nut butter a final spin just to mix it in.'),(671354,6,'Transfer to airtight containers and store in a cool, dry place. This nut butter will keep for several weeks in the pantry and up to a few months in the refrigerator.'),(671537,1,'Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),(671537,2,'Add onion and saute 3 minutes then push far to the side.'),(671537,3,'Add chicken, season with salt and pepper and cook until golden, about 2 1/2 minutes per side.'),(671537,4,'Remove chicken from skillet and transfer to a plate, while leaving oil and onions in skillet (if you don\'t have much oil left you can add another 1/2 Tbsp).'),(671537,5,'Add garlic to skillet and saute 20 seconds (you can push onions back to center if you haven\'t already).'),(671537,6,'Add balsamic vinegar and cook and stir until reduced by half, about 1 minute. Stir in honey then add in peaches and tomatoes and toss, season lightly with salt and pepper. Return chicken to skillet, nestling between peaches and tomatoes (you can lift some of the peaches and tomatoes over the chicken to create more room), cover skillet with lid, reduce heat to medium-low and allow to simmer until chicken has cooked through (it should register 165 degrees on an instant read thermometer), about 6 - 9 minutes. Top with fresh basil and serve warm.Recipe source: adapted from allrecipes'),(672130,1,'In top of a double boiler over hot water, melt chocolate.');
INSERT INTO `recipe_instructions` VALUES (672130,2,'Remove from heat and set aside to cool. Or, place the chocolate in a microwave-safe bowl, use 50% power and stir frequently just until the chocolate is melted; do not overheat as chocolate will burn easily. Set aside to cool slightly. Tip: Create a double boiler by filling a saucepan with 2 inches of water and bringing it to a simmer. Turn the heat off and place a stainless steel, ceramic, or glass bowl on top of the simmering water, the upper pan should not touch the water.In a medium mixing bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt; sift or whisk together to mix. Set aside.In a small mixing bowl, stir the milk, crme de menthe, and vanilla extract together. Set aside.In a large bowl of an electric mixer, cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Tip: To cream, start by placing the butter in the bowl, with an electric mixer on medium speed begin by beating the butter about 1 minute until it is smooth and light in color. With the mixer still on medium speed, slowly add the sugar to the butter, either one tablespoon at a time, or in a very slow steady stream, taking from 4 to 8 minutes to add all of the sugar, and beating until the butter and sugar are fully incorporated and the mixture is a light, or pale yellow color, with a fluffy texture. While adding the sugar, stop the mixer occasionally to scrape the mixture off the paddle and scrape down the sides and bottom of the bowl with a rubber spatula so the mixture blends evenly.'),(672130,3,'Add eggs one at a time, beating until thoroughly mixed. Tip: For each egg, crack the egg into a small bowl and whisk with a fork to thoroughly break up the egg before adding to the creamed mixture. Start with the mixer on low speed so the liquid from the egg doesnt splatter, once the egg is partially mixed increase the speed to medium. Each egg should be fully incorporated into the mixture before adding the next egg, taking about one minute to blend in each egg.With the mixer on low speed, add about one third of the flour mixture, mix just until the flour is almost completely blended. Scrape the bowl down, and add about one half of the milk mixture, blending just until mixed. Scrape the bowl down again and continue alternating with the flour mixture and milk mixture, ending with the last portion of the flour, and stirring just until blended.'),(672130,4,'Remove the bowl from the mixer. Using a large rubber spatula, gently fold the melted and cooled chocolate into the batter.Spoon the batter into the cupcake liners. Fill about  full, using about  cup of batter per cup. Tip: Avoid over-filling the liners which may cause the batter to run-over the sides when baking. It is better to bake any remaining batter separately after the first pan of cupcakes has finished baking.'),(672363,1,'Mix the dry ingredients for the bars together.'),(672363,2,'Add the hazelnut (or almond) milk, mandarin juice, and zest.'),(672363,3,'Mix well until it comes together as a homogeneous mass.  Do not be tempted to add more liquid.  Keep working the mixture.  Once all ingredients are fully incorporated, divide the mixture into 4 equal pieces and form into bars.Refrigerate.'),(672363,4,'Place the mandarin juice in a small bowl.  Gradually whisk in the Natvia Icing'),(672363,5,'Mix (or icing sugar) until smooth.'),(672363,6,'Spread the glaze over each bar.  Decorate with some cacao nibs.'),(672363,7,'Let the glaze set and serve, or store airtight in the refrigerator.'),(672505,1,'Preheat oven to 400.Bring eggs, milk and yogurt to room temperature.(take out 30 minutes prior to cooking)Line a mini muffin tin with paper mini muffin liners'),(672505,2,'In a large bowl, thoroughly whisk together, flour,coconut sugar,oats,flax seeds,baking powder,baking soda and kosher salt.In a separate medium bowl, whisk together coconut oil, yogurt, milk, eggs and vanilla extract.'),(672505,3,'Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and mix with a rubber spatula. (do not over mix)Carefully fold in blueberries.Batter will be thick.With 2 spoons, spoon batter into cups. Fill  full.'),(672505,4,'Bake 15 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean.Allow to cool prior eating or blueberries may stick to wrapper.Store at room temperature in a covered container.'),(672740,1,'Preheat your grill to high.In a large bowl, combine the potatoes and olive oil. Toss to coat.'),(672740,2,'Place potatoes on top of a large sheet of heavy-duty foil.'),(672740,3,'Sprinkle the potatoes with all of the seasonings. Pull the two shorter ends of the rectangle together in the center. Hold them together and roll down. Fold in the remaining openings. Grill the potatoes on the upper rack of your grill for 20-30 minutes, flipping part way through, or until potatoes are tender and browned.'),(673147,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray a 9x13 casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.'),(673147,2,'Combine the sour cream, cream of celery soup, cheese, garlic powder, hash browns, and salt and pepper in a large bowl. Stir together until well blended.'),(673147,3,'Transfer the potato mixture into prepared casserole dish. Top evenly with cornflakes and bake for 45 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.'),(673357,1,'Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Grease three 6x2-inch round cake pans. Line bottoms of pans with parchment paper; grease the paper. Set pans aside.For the remainder of the cake recipe, click here.'),(675219,1,'On a slice of bread, spread one tablespoon of pesto then top layer the mozzarella, tomato and mozzarella again. You can divide one big slice of mozzarella to make two layers or just leave is as one slice.'),(675219,2,'Spread some pesto again on another slice of bread then close the sandwich.On a griddle or regular pan, cook both sides until the mozzarella melts.'),(675219,3,'Serve immediately.'),(675893,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.Spray 9x13\" baking dish with cooking spray.In large bowl combine flour, oats, flax, brewers yeast, brown sugar, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, and pumpkin pie spice.Stir well to combine.In medium bowl, whisk together pumpkin puree, eggs, coconut oil, milk, and vanilla.'),(675893,2,'Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients and stir until just combined.Fold in chocolate chips.'),(675893,3,'Pour into prepared baking dish and bake in preheated oven for 38-42 minutes, until slightly golden and toothpick comes out clean from the middle.'),(675893,4,'Let cool completely.'),(675893,5,'Cut into bars and enjoy!'),(676429,1,'Place a medium pot over medium-high heat and add in the sesame oil. Once oil heats, add in the pork, breaking it up in the pan. Once broken, add in the garlic, ginger, the whites of the scallions and red pepper flakes. Season with salt and cook until browned. When the pork is just about browned.'),(676429,2,'Add in the chicken broth, bok choy, soy sauce, fish sauce and bring to a boil. Then, add in the zucchini noodles and let cook for 3-5 minutes or until the noodles are cooked to your preference.Meanwhile, place the corn in a small pot and cover with water and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil. Once boiling, cook until fork-tender, about 2-3 minutes.'),(676429,3,'Drain into a colander and shave the kernels off with a knife and set aside.Divide soup into two bowls and top with corn and remaining scallions.'),(676437,1,'Preheat oven to 35'),(676437,2,'Place the lemon cake mix, egg and cool-whip in a bowl and mix with a fork or spoon until well blended. Be careful not to over mix. Freeze the cookies for about 2-3 minutes before you roll them in the powdered sugar.'),(676437,3,'Roll them in the powdered sugar and place them onto a baking sheet lined with parchment paper or a Silpat.'),(676437,4,'Bake in a 350 oven for 8-10 minutes.'),(676679,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees'),(676679,2,'Spray a loaf pan or 3 mini loaf pans with cooking spray; set a side'),(676679,3,'In a bowl, add flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and lemon zest; mix until combined.In a large bowl, add eggs, vanilla extract, yogurt, canola oil, milk, lemon juice and lemon zest; mix until well combined.Slowly mix in flour mixture, just until combined. Stir in raspberries.'),(676679,4,'Pour mixture into prepared baking pan or pans (if using mini-loaf pans, fill  way in each pan).'),(676679,5,'Bake for 50 - 60 minutes for single loaf pan or 30-35 minutes for mini loaf pans, until center of bread comes out clean with a toothpick.Cool for about 10 minutes. Take bread out of pan and place on cooling rack to cool completely.Once bread is cooled. In a bowl, add powdered sugar and lemon juice.'),(676679,6,'Whisk together until smooth.'),(676679,7,'Drizzle over the top of the bread.'),(677156,1,'For the Homemade Pickling Spice'),(677156,2,'Add all of the ingredients to a small bowl and stir to mix.'),(677156,3,'For the Spicy Killer Garlic Dill Pickles'),(677156,4,'Prepare your jars and lids for canning. I run my jars through the dishwasher to sterilize and remove them while still warm.'),(677156,5,'Add the lids to a small pot of simmering boiled water to pull from for the canning process.'),(677156,6,'In a large stock pot to avoid contaminationbring the vinegars, water and salt to a simmer.'),(677156,7,'To each sterilized jar add: 2-3 tablespoons of pickling spice, 2-3 fronds and stalks of dried dill weed, 2-3 Thai red peppers depending on your preference and 4-5 whole garlic cloves to each jar. Pack the whole or sliced cucumbers into the jars so they are tight but aren\'t damaged in the process. The cucumbers should sit below the neck of the jar. Trim the cucumbers if they\'re poking up too high.'),(677156,8,'Pour the brine into the jars leaving 1/2 inch headspace, just covering the cucumbers.'),(677156,9,'Wipe the rims of the jars and use tongs to place the lids and rings (that have been sterilized in simmering water) on top of the jars. To avoid contamination, do not touch the lids where they sit on the jars with your fingers.'),(677156,10,'Process in a canner water bath of boiling water for 10 minutes.'),(677156,11,'Remove the jars from the pot and allow them to cool on a dishtowel on the counter. As the jars cool you will hear them pop as they seal. Sealed jars should feel solid when tapped and be concave in shape.'),(677156,12,'Store in a dry cool place. Pickles will be ready to try in about 7-10 days but get even better over time. They can be stored for up to 1 year.'),(677819,1,'This cheesy, delicious vegetarian lasagna shows that the slow cooker is not just for soups and stews. We make lasagna healthier by using whole- wheat noodles and lots of vegetables for extra fiber and nutrients. In a bowl, combine 1 egg and one 16- ounce container of part- skim ricotta cheese, which helps cut saturated fat. Then add a 5- ounce package of coarsely chopped baby spinach, 3 largehalved and sliced portobello mushroom caps and 1 thinly quartered and sliced zucchini. Stireverything together and set aside. Next, in a medium bowl, with a 28- ounce can of crushed tomatoes, add a 28- ounce can of diced tomatoes, 3 cloves of minced garlic and, if you like a bit of heat, a pinch of crushed red pepper. Stir it well. Now that the filling and the sauce are ready, let\'s build the lasagna. Spray a 6- quart slow cooker with nonstick cooking spray.'),(677819,2,'Spread 1- 1 / 2 cups of the sauce in the bottom, then arrange 5 uncooked lasagna noodles on top of the sauce, overlapping them slightly and breaking them into pieces to cover as much of the sauce as possible. Choose whole- wheat noodles because they have heart- healthy fiber.'),(677819,3,'Spread half of the filling over thenoodles and firmly pat it down. Evenly spoon another 1- 1 / 2 cups of sauce, then sprinkle 1 cup of shredded part- skim mozzarella cheese.'),(677819,4,'Add 5 more lasagna noodles on top of the cheese, thenspread the rest of the filling over the noodles and pat it down. Spoon on another 1- 1 / 2 cups of sauce and sprinkle another 1 cup of mozzarella. Arrange 5 more lasagna noodles on top, then top it with the remaining sauce. Cover the slow cooker and cook on High for 2 hours or on Low for 4 hours. Once the cooking time is up, turn off the slow cooker.'),(677819,5,'Sprinkle 1 more cup of mozzarella on top of the lasagna. Replace the cover and allow the lasagna to stand for 10 minutes to melt the cheese. And there it is: healthy Slow- Cooker Vegetarian Lasagna with 250 fewer calories and 9 grams less saturated fat than traditional lasagna.'),(677819,6,'Add a green salad and a loaf of crusty bread and your dinner is complete. Find this recipe and more healthy recipes on Eating'),(677819,7,'Well. com.'),(677876,1,'Add all ingredients to a food processor and process for about 5 - 7 minutes, scraping the sides and stirring every minute or so until it\'s smooth and creamy.Store in an air-tight glass container in the refrigerator.Enjoy!'),(678264,1,'In a small bowl soak spilt chana dal for 30 minutes.'),(678264,2,'Heat a thick bottomed pan and add 1 tsp of coconut oil to it.'),(678264,3,'Add 2 cup of water and salt and bring it to boil.When water is boiled adds the rice flour andmixes every well. When the dough leaves the sides of the pan in a ball, remove from the stove.Keep covered for 10 minutes. When cool, smear a little oil in your palms and knead the dough well. Make small marble sized balls with 1 teaspoon of dough and steam in a steamer or idli cooker for 20 minutes. Allow to cool.'),(678264,4,'Heat the remaining oil in a pan and when the oil starts smoking, add mustard seeds, urad dal,  soaked chana dal and broken red chillies.When the dals starts turning pink add the curry leaves.'),(678264,5,'Add the steamed kozhukkattais andgrated coconut and stir fry for 5 minutes.If the kozhukkattais are steamed properly, they will not break while stir frying.'),(678264,6,'Remove from stove  and serve warm ammini kozhukkattais'),(678504,1,'To a Blendtec Twister Jar add 3 Tbsp reserved liquid from chick pea can, lime juice, olive oil, tahini, adobo sauce (I added this later but I think it would be best added with the other liquids), and garlic. Then add chick peas, chipotle chilies, cumin, coriander, paprika and salt. Cover with Twister lid (lid with paddles), then process (using Dips Cycle or on medium speed), while rotating lid counter clockwise, and adding an additional 1 Tbsp liquid as needed, until hummus is smooth. Plate and top with more olive oil, adobo sauce and chipotle chilies if desired, then sprinkle with cilantro.'),(678504,2,'Serve with pita chips, tortilla chips or veggies. Store in refrigerator in an airtight container. Recipe source: Cooking Classy'),(678513,1,'Preheat the oven to 350F.  Grease a 9x9\" square baking dish (or a similar size pan - I used a very deep dish pie plate!);  Set aside.In a medium bowl, stir together the streusel ingredients until combined;  Set aside.In another medium bowl, stir together the flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder, cinnamon and salt for the cake;  Set aside.In a large mixing bowl, mix together the 1/2 cup coconut oil and 1/2 cup brown sugar until well blended.  Stir in the pumpkin, and then beat in the eggs, one at a time, until just well combined.Stir in the flour mixture until just combined (don\'t over-mix!) and then spread half of the pumpkin batter into the greased baking dish and then top with half of the streusel mixture.  Carefully spread the rest of the batter on top of that, and then sprinkle evenly with the remaining streusel.'),(678513,2,'Bake for 45-55 minutes, until the top is golden and a toothpick inserted in the center comes out almost clean, with just a few crumbs on it - no wet batter.'),(678513,3,'Let cool a bit before cutting and serving, if you can stand it!'),(679079,1,'Cream butter and sugar until soft and creamy.'),(679079,2,'Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.'),(679079,3,'Combine flour and baking powder, then blend into the butter mixture.Break off small, walnut sized pieces of dough and shape into bows, braids, knots,\"s\" shapes, or any shape you desire.'),(679079,4,'Bake in a preheated oven at 375 F until lightly browned, about 15-20 minutes.Cool on wire racks,then ice as desired.Icing: Blend sugar and your choice of flavoring, adding milk slowly to form a soft, smooth icing (some ice the cookies while they are still warm, others wait until they are cooled).'),(679079,5,'Sprinkle with colored sugar or confettini (tiny multi-colored sprinkles) before icing sets.'),(679240,1,'Rinse the chickpeas and soak in several inches of water for 8 hours or overnight. Separately, rinse the quinoa and soak in 1 cup of water in a medium saucepan for 8 hours or overnight.Soak the cashews in hot water for 2 hours.'),(679240,2,'Drain and rinse the chickpeas and transfer to medium saucepan. Cover with fresh water and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until buttery soft.'),(679240,3,'Drain and transfer to a medium bowl and let cool to room temperature.Meanwhile, bring the quinoa and soaking water to a boil. Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes or until the water is absorbed.'),(679240,4,'Remove from heat, fluff with a fork, and set aside to cool.While the chickpeas and quinoa are cooking, soak the sun-dried tomatoes in hot water for 20 minutes.'),(679240,5,'Drain, chop finely, and set aside.'),(679240,6,'Drain the cashews and transfer to a food processor.'),(679240,7,'Combine with the remaining ingredients for the cashew sauce and process until smooth. The sauce should be fairly thick.To make the wrap filling, heat the oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium heat. When hot, add the red onion to the pan and saut for 5 to 7 minutes until the onion begins to soften. Now add the spices and jalapeo and stir for 1 minute until the spices are fragrant.'),(679240,8,'Add the sun-dried tomato and plum tomato to the pan and cook, stirring occasionally, for another few minutes to thicken. Stir in the carrot and red pepper and simmer for another few minutes  don\'t overcook.Stir in the chickpeas, quinoa, cashew paste, cilantro, lemon juice and salt. Cook for another few minutes to warm and then remove from the heat.To assemble, spoon some of the mixture onto a tortilla and add chopped lettuce and sprouts. Wrap it up, cut in half, and serve with slices of avocado, additional lettuce or sprouts, and salsa if you like, or enjoy just as is.'),(679333,1,'Butter an 8 inch cast iron skillet, and set aside.In a large bowl, whisk the eggs, cream, milk, sugar and extracts together.Butter one side of each slice of bread and arrange them in the pan, overlapping the slices.'),(679333,2,'Sprinkle the chocolate over the bread, being sure to tuck some of the pieces in between the slices of bread.'),(679333,3,'Pour the cream mixture over the top of the bread. Cover with a piece of plastic wrap, and set a heavy pan on top to push the bread down into the cream. Allow the bread to soak up the cream for 30 minutes.Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.'),(679333,4,'Bake the bread pudding for 30 minutes, sprinkling the sliced almonds on top for the last 10 minutes. Cover with a piece of tin foil if the top begins to brown.'),(679333,5,'Remove from the oven.Allow the bread pudding to cool. There will be a thin layer of butter on top of the pudding, and this will soak in as it cools.'),(679333,6,'Serve warm.'),(679646,1,'Heat oven to 350F. Grease a 12 cup Bundt pan.In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, spices, and salt.In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, beat together the butter and sugar on medium speed, scraping down the bowl as necessary. Beat for 3 minutes, or until smooth and thick.'),(679646,2,'Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Reduce the mixer to low and beat in the apple butter. Still on low speed, add in the grated apples and mix until blended.'),(679646,3,'Add the dry ingredients, mixing until just combined. Fold in the nuts. Spoon the batter into the Bundt pan and smooth with the spatula.'),(679646,4,'Bake for 50-55 minutes, or until a knife inserted comes out clean.'),(679646,5,'Transfer the pan to a rack to cool for 5 minutes, then unmold the cake, allowing to cool completely.In a small bowl, whisk together the sugar and the lemon juice.'),(679646,6,'Drizzle over the top of the cake and let stand until the icing dries, just a few minutes.'),(680002,1,'For Butterscotch Sauce: In a medium sized saucepan melt 1/4 cup Melted Butter, 1 cup Brown Sugar and 1/4 teaspoon Salt. Slowly stir in 1/3 cup Heavy Whipping Cream and bring to a boil cook for 5 minutes.'),(680002,2,'Remove from heat. Stir in remaining 1/3 cup Heavy Whipping Cream and 1 teaspoon Vanilla Extract. Allow to cool. Store in refrigerator until ready to use and place over low heat to thin sauce.'),(680002,3,'For Pumpkin Cheesecake:Preheat oven to 350 degrees.'),(680162,1,'Preheat oven to 35'),(680162,2,'Place the chickpeas in a large bowl. In a small bowl, mix together the pumpkin, maple syrup, spices and salt. Stir well.'),(680162,3,'Pour the pumpkin mixture over the chickpeas and mix until everything is well coated.'),(680162,4,'Spread the chickpeas onto a lined baking sheet.'),(680162,5,'Bake for about 60 minutes, stopping every 15 minutes to shake the chickpeas around.'),(680226,1,'Pat the chicken thighs dry with a paper towel, then season both sides with salt and pepper.'),(680226,2,'Heat a large deep skillet over medium heat.'),(680226,3,'Add the oil, then tilt the skillet to spread the oil over the surface.'),(680226,4,'Place the chicken thighs in the skillet, skin side down, and allow to brown before flipping (about five minutes). Flip the thighs and let brown on the second side (another five minutes).'),(680226,5,'Remove the browned thighs to a clean plate.If there is excess oil in the skillet, pour it off into a bowl to cool, leaving about 1 tablespoon of oil and fat in the skillet.'),(680226,6,'Add the minced garlic, turmeric, cumin, and cinnamon to the skillet. Saut for about one minute, or until the garlic is soft and fragrant.'),(680226,7,'Pour the chicken broth into the skillet and use a wooden spoon to dissolve any browned bits off the bottom of the skillet. Once the browned bits are dissolved, add the frozen peas and rice, and give it a quick stir to distribute the broth and spices. Nestle the browned chicken thighs into the rice and peas.'),(680226,8,'Place a lid on the skillet and turn the heat up to medium-high. allow it to come to a boil. Once it reaches a boil, turn the heat down to low (or just above low) and let the skillet simmer for 25 minutes. After 25 minutes, turn the heat off and let it sit undisturbed for an additional 10 minutes. Finally, remove the lid and fluff the rice with a fork, mixing the peas in as you go. Top with fresh cilantro, if desired.'),(680279,1,'Wash your celery and cut the stalks in half.'),(680279,2,'Spread peanut butter or make it nut free with Sunbutter on the celery sticks.'),(680279,3,'Add two candy eyes.Decorate with your choice of mustaches, lips or teeth.'),(680650,1,'Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F.Spray a 9 x13 baking dish with cooking spray.'),(680650,2,'Place the quinoa, red onion and green onion in a single layer at the bottom..In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the Swanson Chicken Broth, hummus, cheese, and broccoli.'),(680650,3,'Pour the chicken broth mixture over the quinoa followed by the spinach, butternut squash, parmesan and 15 minutes of the mozzarella cheese.'),(680650,4,'Bake for 20-25 minutes.'),(680650,5,'Remove quinoa casserole out of the oven and mix in the broccoli.'),(680650,6,'Sprinkle the rest of the cheese over the quinoa and broccoli and place back in the oven for 5 minutes or until the cheese has melted. If you like, you can add more parmesan cheese over the top as well.'),(680650,7,'Remove from oven and serve while still warm.'),(681115,1,'Mix together oats, coconut, walnuts, cranberries, and salt.In a separate bowl, cream peanut butter, butter and sugar.Fold in the oat mixture.'),(681115,2,'Spread the mix in an 8 x 8 greased glass dish'),(681115,3,'Bake 25 minutes at 375'),(681301,1,'Preheat oven to 450FSpray a 9\" round baking pan with nonstick spray. Line the bottom of the pan with a parchment paper round. Spray again and set aside.In a medium bowl combine the melted butter, brown sugar and cinnamon and stir until smooth. Set this aside while you make your dough.In a large bowl combine the cold butter and the self rising flour with a pastry cutter or fork until it resembles coarse sand. Make a well in the center of the mixture and pour in your buttermilk. Stir this until the dough just comes together.'),(681301,2,'Place the dough onto a heavily dusted work surface. Knead the dough about 10 times until it is less sticky. Flour a nonstick silicone liner, parchment paper or wax paper.'),(681301,3,'Place the dough onto this surface and roll it out into a rectangle shape that is approximately  inch thick. (about 12\"x15\"). This doesn\'t have to be exact.The filling mixture will have thickened up at this point making it easy to spread.'),(681301,4,'Spread it all over your dough leaving a small border at the edge.'),(681301,5,'Roll the dough up starting at the long side.Once it\'s rolled up slice it into 12 -14 1\" slices.'),(681301,6,'Place the slices into the prepared pan and bake for 13-15 minutes until golden brown.When the rolls are done allow them to cool for 10 minutes before glazing.'),(681301,7,'Whisk together all the ingredients and pour onto warm rolls.'),(681301,8,'Serve warm or room temperature'),(681572,1,'Shape the raisins into the witchs hat, starting at the top of the baking sheet or tray. The hat should take up about 1/3 of the tray.Shape the pistachios into the witchs face.'),(681572,2,'Add 2 large marshmallows with a raisin on top of each for her eyes.'),(681572,3,'Add a pickle nose (be sure to dry the pickle with paper towels)'),(681572,4,'Add 2 apple slices for her mouth.Arrange the red grapes to look like hair. Slice 1 grape into 4 pieces and use those pieces as eyebrows.'),(681572,5,'Add a snaggletooth or a whole mouth full of teeth, using mini marshmallows.'),(681572,6,'Add halloween sprinkles around the witch for festive flare!'),(683689,1,'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees. Spray a 9x13-inch baking dish with cooking oil spray. Set aside.'),(683689,2,'Heat the olive oil in a skillet set over medium heat.'),(683689,3,'Add the onions and zucchini. Cook, stirring frequently, until softened -- about 5-7 minutes.'),(683689,4,'Add the ground beef to the pan and cook, stirring occasionally and breaking apart, until browned all over.'),(683689,5,'Drain, if necessary.In a small bowl, stir together the chili powder, cumin, salt and pepper.'),(683689,6,'Pour over the meat mixture and add the water to the pan. Stir well. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the water is mostly evaporated. Stir in  cup cheddar cheese.'),(683689,7,'Place the bell pepper halves in the prepared pan. Divide the meat mixture evenly among them, pressing lightly to get it inside the cavities.'),(683689,8,'Sprinkle with additional cheese, as desired.'),(683689,9,'Bake for 15-20 minutes, until the cheese is melted and the peppers are warm and slightly softened.'),(684271,1,'Preheat the oven to 400 F. Line a rimmed baking sheet with foil, and place a cooling rack on top of the foil.'),(684271,2,'Lay the bacon strips on the rack, and bake for 10-15 minutes, until desired crispness.Prepare an ice bath by filling a large mixing bowl with ice cubes and water; set aside.Bring a large pot of water to a boil. When the water comes to a boil, carefully drop the green beans in the water and boil for about 2-3 minutes. You want the beans to have a slight crunch and still be bright green. If working in batches, remove the beans with a slotted spoon directly into the prepared ice bath. If not, simply drain the hot water and transfer the beans to the ice bath quickly.'),(684271,3,'Drain the green beans from the ice bath once they are cooled, and set aside in a colander to dry off.'),(684271,4,'Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat and add 1 teaspoon of oil and the onions. Cook for 4-6 minutes, until the onions begin to become translucent.'),(684271,5,'Add the minced garlic and drained green beans, and cook for 2-3 minutes moving the beans around frequently.In the last minute of cooking, add the vinegar, salt, black pepper and bacon crumbles. Toss gently to combine.'),(685177,1,'Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).'),(685177,2,'In a medium skillet, melt butter over medium heat.'),(685177,3,'Saute garlic and onion in butter until lightly browned, about 7 minutes. Stir in spinach, mushrooms, feta and 1/2  cup Cheddar cheese. Season with salt and pepper. Spoon mixture into pie crust.'),(685177,4,'In a medium bowl, whisk together eggs and milk. Season with salt and pepper.'),(685177,5,'Pour into the pastry shell, allowing egg mixture to thoroughly combine with spinach mixture.'),(685177,6,'Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes.'),(685177,7,'Sprinkle top with remaining Cheddar cheese, and bake an additional 35 to 40 minutes, until set in center. Allow to stand 10 minutes before serving.'),(685759,1,'Combine cream cheese, milk, sun-dried tomatoes, and salt in food processor and blend until pureed. Set aside.In large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil over medium-high heat.Cook chicken until cooked through.'),(685759,2,'Remove from skillet and set aside.Meanwhile, start a pot of water to cook your pasta. You will want you pasta cooking while you are making the sauce.'),(685759,3,'Add additional tablespoon of olive oil over medium-high heat.'),(685759,4,'Add shallots and cook until softened, about 3-5 minutes.'),(685759,5,'Add garlic and cook another minute.'),(685759,6,'Add diced tomatoes and salt, and cook another 2-3 minutes.Return chicken to the skillet.'),(685759,7,'Add cream sauce, and stir quickly so it incorporates well in the sauce.'),(685759,8,'Let cook over medium heat for a few minutes.'),(685759,9,'Drain pasta and reserve about  cup of pasta water.'),(685759,10,'Add pasta to skillet with the sauce, and stir well to combine.'),(685759,11,'Add spinach, stirring well until wilted.'),(685759,12,'Add additional water if you feel the sauce needs thinned out. I added just a couple of tablespoons.'),(685759,13,'Serve immediately and enjoy!'),(687872,1,'Follow directions on how to make perfect butter pie crust and be sure to make two crusts - one for top and one for bottom. You can always use premade store bought as well.Bring cider to a boil in a large, heavy saucepan over high heat. Cook until reduced to 1/2 cup (about 20 minutes). Cool completely.Preheat oven to 45'),(687872,2,'Combine cooled cider, 1/3 cup sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice, vanilla, and pumpkin pie spice in a large bowl. Stir apple slices into cider mixture.'),(687872,3,'Roll dough out into a large circle large enough to fill the pie dish and slightly hang over.'),(687872,4,'Add apples and all of that wonderful liquid to the crust.'),(687872,5,'Roll out top crust to the same size and place on top of the apples. Work your fingers around the outside to tuck the top crust under the bottom crust.'),(687872,6,'Cut about 6 (1-inch) slits into the top crust using a sharp knife to vent.'),(687872,7,'Combine egg and 1 tablespoon cream.'),(687872,8,'Brush top and edges of pie with egg mixture, and then sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.'),(687872,9,'Place pie on a baking sheet, and bake in center of oven at 450 for 15 minutes. This will make the top of the crust very golden brown. Reduce oven temperature to 350 (do not remove pie from oven), and bake an additional 60 minutes or until done. Cool on a wire rack.'),(687936,1,'In large bowl, combine 1 cup flour, sugar, onion, dill seed, 1 teaspoon salt, baking soda and yeast; mix well.In small saucepan, heat water, 1 tablespoon margarine and cottage cheese until very warm (120 to 130F.).'),(687936,2,'Add warm liquid and egg to flour mixture; blend at low speed until moistened.Beat 3 minutes at medium speed. By hand, stir in remaining 1 to 1 cups flour to form a stiff batter.Cover loosely with greased plastic wrap and cloth towel.'),(687936,3,'Let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size, 45 to 60 minutes.Grease 1 or 2-quart casserole. Stir down batter to remove all air bubbles. Turn into greased casserole. Cover; let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size, 30 to 45 minutes.Preheat oven to 350F.'),(687936,4,'Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until loaf is deep golden brown and sounds hollow when lightly tapped.If necessary, cover with foil to prevent overbrowning.'),(687936,5,'Remove from casserole; place on wire rack.'),(687936,6,'Brush loaf with melted margarine; sprinkle with coarse salt. Cool 15 minutes.'),(688199,1,'Line a cookie sheet with parchment paper or a silicone mat.In a medium bowl, beat the butter and eggs until pale, about 2-3 minutes on medium speed.'),(688199,2,'Add the cookie mix and mix until combined and dough forms. Fold in the butterscotch chips into dough.Using a 2 tablespoon cookie scoop, ball out dough and place on prepared sheet. Chill cookie dough balls for at least 30 mins - 1hr.'),(688199,3,'Heat oven to 350 degrees F.'),(688199,4,'Bake cookies for 10-12 minutes until the edges are lightly browned.'),(688199,5,'Remove from oven and let cool on sheet for 2 mins.'),(688199,6,'Transfer to a cooling rack and let cool completely.Meanwhile make the filling. In a medium bowl, combine all the frosting ingredients and beat until combined.When cookies are cooled, fill with frosting to make cookie sandwiches'),(688457,1,'In a 8x8 cake pan add the eggs, heavy cream, honey, salt and whisk together well.'),(688457,2,'Place a skillet on your stove over medium-low heat, add 1 tbsp of the butter and melt.While butter is melting soak 2 of the banana bread slices in the egg mixture, turn over after 30 seconds and soak on the other side for another 30 seconds.Once the butter is melted and skillet is hot, add the 2 slices to the skillet and cook for about 3 or 4 minutes. After 3 or 4 minutes take a peek and see if the French toast is golden brown, if it has flip each slice carefully and continue cooking until this side is golden brown, another 3 or so minutes, making sure to watch it closely so it doesn\'t burn.'),(688457,3,'Remove from skillet.Soak the remaining 2 slices of bread and repeat the process to cook these last 2 slices.In the same skillet, prepare the caramelized bananas.'),(688457,4,'Add the 2 tbsp of butter and wait until it melts then sprinkle the tbsp of brown sugar over the surface of the skillet.'),(688457,5,'Add the banana slices over the brown sugar, and cook for a couple minutes until the bottom of the banana get golden brown. Flip each slice over and cook for another 2 or 3 minutes.'),(688457,6,'Remove from heat.Dust the banana bread French toast with some icing sugar then spoon the caramelized bananas over the slices and serve.'),(688490,1,'Preheat oven to 300 degrees. Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper and a 12 by 17-inch jelly roll pan with a silicone baking mat or lightly grease with butter.'),(688490,2,'Spread the chopped pecans evenly onto parchment lined baking sheet and toast in preheated for 7 - 8 minutes, or until very lightly browned. Set aside.Melt butter in a 3-quart heavy bottomed saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally with a wooden spoon (about every 2 minutes). Once butter has fully melted, add the water, 1 cup (200g) of the sugar, salt and corn syrup. Stir constantly until the sugar dissolves, then brush down the sides of the pan with a wet pastry brush. Attach a candy thermometer to pan, without letting it touch the bottom of pan.Once the sugar has dissolved, bring mixture to a boil. Rapid bubbles, a thicker consistency, and a slightly darker color form around 235F (113C). Stir lightly once every minute until candy reaches 290F (143C).'),(688490,3,'Remove pan from heat, stir in pumpkin pie spice and 1 cup of the pecans.'),(688490,4,'Pour toffee onto baking sheet lined with silicone liner. Smooth into an even layer with a wooden spoon (toffee should be thick and won\'t spread to edges of pan). Allow toffee to cool for 5 minutes. Meanwhile in a small bowl whisk together cinnamon and remaining 2 Tbsp (25g) sugar.'),(688490,5,'Sprinkle white chocolate evenly over slightly cooled toffee and allow white chocolate to rest until it has melted then spread into an even layer.'),(688490,6,'Sprinkle the top evenly with remaining pecans and cinnamon sugar mixture. Refrigerate for 20 minutes, or until white chocolate has set.Once set, remove from refrigerator and cut or break into pieces. Store in an airtight container at room temperature up to 2 weeks or freeze up to 3 minutes.Recipe source: recipe from Sally\'s Candy'),(688490,7,'Addiction, pg. 108.'),(688635,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.Set up a steamer basket (or a colander or sieve) over a few inches of water in a pot so that the water is not touching the basket.'),(688635,2,'Add all of the vegetables to the basket (or colander). Cover and steam over high heat for about 10-15 minutes until vegetables are fork-tender, yet still bright.Meanwhile, add 2 tablespoons olive oil to a saut pan over medium-low heat.'),(688635,3,'Whisk in the flour.Continue whisking constantly for about 2 minutes, until the paste formed smells nutty, but not burnt.'),(688635,4,'Add in about 1/4 cup of the milk, half of the pepper, and the herbs, whisking all the while.Once thickened, add an additional 1/4 cup of milk and whisk until thickened.Repeat with the last 1/4 cup of milk. Once thickened, add the cheddar cheese and half of the parmesan, whisking to incorporate.'),(688635,5,'Remove from the heat.'),(688635,6,'Place all vegetables in an 8 x 8-inch pan or a round pie dish.'),(688635,7,'Pour the creamy cheese sauce over the vegetables to cover.'),(688635,8,'Sprinkle the panko breadcrumbs over the top.'),(688635,9,'Sprinkle on the remaining parmesan cheese.'),(688635,10,'Drizzle the olive oil and sprinkle on the salt and the other half of the pepper.'),(688635,11,'Bake for about 20 minutes, until crisp and golden brown on the top and bubbly.'),(688635,12,'Serve hot.Enjoy!'),(689116,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with a paddle attachment (or using a hand mixer), cream butter.'),(689116,2,'Add brown sugar and granulated sugar.'),(689116,3,'Mix until smooth.'),(689116,4,'Add egg, molasses, and apple sauce.In a bowl, whisk together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and sea salt.'),(689116,5,'Add to mixing bowl. Fold in rolled oats and walnuts.Use a 1 1/2 inch scoop to portion out cookies. Arrange on parchment lined baking sheet at least 2 inches apart.'),(689566,1,'Melt the butter over medium heat in a large saucepan.'),(689566,2,'Remove from the heat, add both sugars and stir until smooth. Chill the mixture for about 10 minutes in the refrigerator.Stir in egg, egg yolk and vanilla.'),(689566,3,'Add flour, rolled oats, baking soda, salt and cinnamon and mix together.Stir in both white and dark chocolate chips.Use a scoop to make 24 equal size portions, then roll the dough by hand into balls.'),(689566,4,'Place on a cookie sheet and chill for at least 30 minutes.'),(689566,5,'Bake the cookies in preheated 325 F (160 C) oven for 12 to 14 minutes.'),(689927,1,'Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),(689927,2,'Add the breadcrumbs and saut until golden and crispy, about 4 to 5 minutes.'),(689927,3,'Add the rosemary, immediately remove from heat and allow to cool.'),(689927,4,'Mix in lemon zest and set aside.'),(689927,5,'Bring a large pot of well-salted water to a boil and cook pasta to al dente according to directions on box.  (I usually undercook the pasta by about a minute.)'),(689927,6,'Wipe out the skillet from the pangritata, add 1 T olive oil and 1 T butter and melt together over medium heat.'),(689927,7,'Add the garlic and immediately break the eggs into the skillet.'),(689927,8,'If need be, lower the heat a bit.  You want the garlic to cook without burning and the egg whites to set, but the yolks to remain runny.'),(689927,9,'Drain the pasta well, reserving  c of the cooking liquid.'),(689927,10,'Add pasta back to the pot, pour over the eggs and all the fat from the skillet, add the parsley and capers and toss well, breaking up the eggs as you do.  If you prefer a wetter dish, you can add in some of the reserved cooking liquid.'),(689927,11,'Plate the pasta and eggs, season well with freshly ground black pepper, sprinkle with the grated cheese and then top with the pangritata.'),(689927,12,'Pour yourself a glass of wine and enjoy!'),(690096,1,'Preheat oven to 450.Toss together cauliflower, olive oil, italian seasoning, salt and pepper in a bowl. Then spread out onto a rimmed baking sheet into a single layer.Roast until cauliflower starts to brown on edges, 20 minutes.'),(690096,2,'Remove from oven and set aside to cool.Tos together all ingredients in a large bowl and set aside. When cauliflower has cooled slightly toss together with kale mix.'),(690096,3,'Add all ingreinets in a small bowl, whisk to combine.'),(690096,4,'Pour on top of salad and toss well.'),(690096,5,'Serve and enjoy.'),(690202,1,'In a pot over medium heat, heat about 2 tablespoons oil.'),(690202,2,'Add bananas and cook, turning on sides as needed, until lightly browned.'),(690202,3,'Remove from pot and set aside.'),(690202,4,'Add about 1 tablespoon oil as needed.'),(690202,5,'Add beef shank and cook on both sides until lightly seared.'),(690202,6,'Remove from pot and set aside.'),(690202,7,'Add about 1 tablespoon oil as needed.'),(690202,8,'Add chorizo de bilbao and ham pieces. Cook, stirring regularly, for about 1 to 2 minutes or until chorizo de bilbao releases color.'),(690202,9,'Add water and bring to a boil.'),(690202,10,'Add beef shank and continue to boil, skimming scum that floats on top. When broth has cleared, add onions, garlic, pepper corns and salt. Lower heat, cover, and simmer for about 2 to 2/12 hours or until meat is almost done.Increase heat to high.'),(690202,11,'Add chicken and bring to a boil, skimming scum that floats on top. Lower heat, cover and continue to simmer for another 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and beef is fork-tender.'),(690202,12,'Add garbanzo beans and saba bananas and cook for about 3 to 5 minutes or until heated through.'),(690202,13,'Add green beans and cabbage and cook until tender yet crisp.'),(690202,14,'Add pechay and cook for another 1 to 2 minutes. Season with additional salt as needed.To serve, arrange meat and vegetables on a serving platter.'),(690202,15,'Transfer broth into a serving tureen.'),(690202,16,'Serve hot with berenjana sauce.Over open stove flames, roast eggplant until skins are charred. Under cold running water, peel and discard skins.In a bowl, mash eggplant.'),(690202,17,'Add garlic, vinegar, oil and salt to taste.'),(690240,1,'In a small bowl, combine chicken, lime juice, cumin and salt; toss well to combine.'),(690240,2,'Place 4 tortillas on a flat surface and spread each one with 2 tablespoons of bean dip. Top each with about 1/3 cup of chicken and then sprinkle each with 1 1/2 tablespoons of cheese; divide scallions over top. Cover with remaining tortillas and gently press down on each one.Coat a very large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat. Cook quesadillas in a single layer until golden brown on bottom, about 2 minutes. Flip quesadillas and press down on them with a spatula; cook until golden brown on second side, about 2 to 3 minutes more.'),(690240,3,'Remove to a serving plate and cover to keep warm (or place in a warm oven); repeat with remaining quesadillas.Slice each quesadilla into 4 pieces; serve with salsa and sour cream. Yields 1 quesadilla, 2 tablespoons of salsa and 1 teaspoon of sour cream per serving.'),(690479,1,'Remove the crusts from the freezer to thaw. When ready, roll one smooth and use in the base of a 9\" tart pan.'),(690479,2,'Place into the fridge while making the filling.Toss the frozen cherries with  cup of sugar and place them into a colander over a large bowl.'),(690479,3,'Let the cherries thaw and drain into the bowl for 45 minutes to an hour. There should be anywhere from  to  cups of cherry juice from collected.'),(690479,4,'Place the drained cherries into a large pan with the lemon juice.'),(690479,5,'Mix up to  cup of the cherry juice with the cornstarch and the remaining half cup of sugar until no lumps are visible.'),(690479,6,'Add the mixture to the cherries and cook over medium heat stirring gently until the mixture bubbles and thickens.'),(690479,7,'Pour the pie filling into the prepared chilled pie crust and place it into the fridge to cool.Take the second pie crust and roll out on a lightly floured surface.'),(690479,8,'Cut parallel strips of the pie crust. Make your lattice top.'),(690479,9,'Whisk the egg and milk together and brush on the pie crust.'),(690479,10,'Sprinkle on the turbinado sugar and return the pie to the fridge.'),(690479,11,'Heat the oven to 400F and place the pie on a cookie sheet to catch anything that might over flow.'),(690479,12,'Bake for 35 - 40 minutes, but check the pie half way though to check if the crust is browning too much. Tent if necessary.'),(690479,13,'Remove and cool completely. Leave it to cool for at least 3 to 4 hours. The pan should no longer be warm to the touch. It\'s best if you can refrigerate to get a clean slice with minimal oozyness.Top with vanilla ice cream and enjoy!'),(691136,1,'Drizzle the olive oil in the bottom of a skillet over medium-high heat.Brown the stew beef in the skillet for about 1-2 minutes per side.'),(691136,2,'Remove from heat and place in the slow cooker.'),(691136,3,'Add ALL remaining ingredients to your slow cooker and mix.Set the slow cooker to cook for 4-6 hours.'),(691136,4,'Serve hot with crusty bread or in bread bowls!'),(691385,1,'In a pitcher, combine all ingredients except the sparkling apple cranberry juice (or club soda). Put in the fridge and let marinate for at least 4 hours or up to 3 days. At serving time, pour into glasses, putting some of the fruit in each glass.'),(691385,2,'Add a bit of sparkle by pouring a little sparkling juice or club soda onto each serving. Enjoy!'),(692167,1,'Line an 8 inch square pan with nonstick foil.'),(692167,2,'Put the chocolate chips and butter in large microwave-safe mixing bowl and heat on high for 30 seconds. Stir well, then stir in half a can (7 oz) of condensed milk.'),(692167,3,'Heat for another 30 seconds, then stir until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.'),(692167,4,'Add the marshmallows and peanuts and stir until coated, then turn into the lined pan and press down with another sheet of nonstick foil. Chill for an hour or until mixture is firm, then cut into squares. For a cleaner cut, freeze the candy before slicing.'),(693079,1,'Place flour, yeast, cocoa powder, sugar, vanilla, Kahlua, Lebkuchen spice, Skyr or quark, ground almonds, chopped pistachios, soft butter and eggs in a bowl of a standmixer fixed with a dough hook and knead until the dough comes together. Stop in between to scrape the sides down if required. Cover and allow to rise for 60 minutes Knead the cranberries and papaya into the dough,then flatten the dough with your fingers slightly and scatter the gianduia. Fold the dough over and slowly knead it into the dough. Do not over-knead. Divide the dough into two equal parts. Shape the dough in a roughly oval form, 3-4 cm thick, fold dough in half lengthwise and put it on baking tray.'),(693079,2,'Brush with the melted butter then allow the dough to rise for 30 minutes.'),(693079,3,'Heat oven to 180C degrees'),(693079,4,'Place both loaves on a baking tray lined with baking paper and bake for 45-55 minutes. Once out of the oven brush again with the remaining butter then sprinkle generously with the icing sugar and/or some cocoa powder.'),(693079,5,'Serve sliced and spread with your favorite jam and extra melted nougat, sprinkled with some pistachios.'),(693860,1,'Butter or coat with cooking spray a 2-quart baking dish.Preheat oven to 350-degrees F.'),(693860,2,'Combine all ingredients and spread evenly into prepared baking dish.'),(693860,3,'Bake uncovered at 350-degrees F until hash browns are tender, about 45 minutes.**'),(694486,1,'In a bowl, combine the flour and baking powder. Set aside.'),(694486,2,'Place the sugar and butter in a mixing bowl and using an electric mixer beat until creamy, about 2 minutes.'),(694486,3,'Add in the egg, vanilla extract, and almond extract, beat.Spoon the flour mixture into the wet ingredients, and mix gently until incorporated and dough forms with a spatula.Dye 1/3 of the dough brown with food coloring. Knead the dough until the color is incorporated.'),(694486,4,'Roll the brown dough to about 1/2 inch thick.Use a lightly floured 1 inch cookie cutter to cut out your shapes. Re-roll the scraps to make as many gingerbread men as you can.Line up the gingerbread men together on a piece of plastic wrap, then wrap the gingerbread men in plastic and stick them in the fridge for 1 hour.10 minutes before the gingerbread men come out of the fridge, begin to roll the outside dough into long narrow ropes. The ropes need to be long enough to cover all of the center cut outs length wise.Begin to place the ropes around the gingerbread men, gently pressing the ropes to fit around the gingerbread men.Continue until the gingerbread men are completely covered.'),(694486,5,'Place some nonpareil sprinkles in a baking dish, and gently roll the cookie dough in the sprinkles, covering all of the sides.Wrap the cookie dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or over night.After the dough has been refrigerated, slice it into about 1/2 inch thick cookies.'),(694486,6,'Place them on a baking sheet, at least 1 inch apart, and bake at 350 F for 8-10 minutes.Allow the cookies to cool for 3-5 minutes of the baking sheet then transfer them to a cooling rack to cool completely.Store in an air tight container.'),(694867,1,'Preheat oven to 350 F degrees. Line baking sheet with parchment paper or silicone mat.'),(694867,2,'Place pretzels on a single even layer. Top with unwrapped caramel candies.'),(694867,3,'Place the pan into the oven and bake for 3-4 minutes or until the caramels become soft. Watch the caramels carefully so they do not melt completely into puddles. Different brands of caramel will melt at different times.'),(694867,4,'Remove pan from oven and immediately press a chocolate candy melt (or Hershey\'s Kisses) over caramel. Return pan back into the oven for just 1 minute.'),(694867,5,'Remove pan from oven and take a pecan, nut or topping of your choice and gently press it right into the center of the chocolate candy.Allow the chocolate to set completely before storing in an airtight container.'),(695806,1,'Put a large pot of water on to boil. Preheat oven to 450F. Coat an 8-inch-square (2-quart) baking dish with cooking spray.'),(695806,2,'Mix breadcrumbs, oil and paprika in a small bowl.'),(695806,3,'Place spinach in a fine-mesh strainer and press out excess moisture.'),(695806,4,'Heat 1 1/2 cups milk in a large heavy saucepan over medium-high heat until steaming.'),(695806,5,'Whisk remaining 1/4 cup milk and flour in a small bowl until smooth; add to the hot milk and cook, whisking constantly, until the sauce simmers and thickens, 2 to 3 minutes.'),(695806,6,'Remove from heat and stir in Cheddar until melted. Stir in cottage cheese, nutmeg, salt and pepper.Cook pasta for 4 minutes, or until not quite tender. (It will continue to cook during baking.)'),(695806,7,'Drain and add to the cheese sauce; mix well.'),(695806,8,'Spread half the pasta mixture in the prepared baking dish. Spoon the spinach on top. Top with the remaining pasta; sprinkle with the breadcrumb mixture.'),(695806,9,'Bake the casserole until bubbly and golden, 25 to 30 minutes.'),(696757,1,'Heat 2 teaspoons oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),(696757,2,'Add polenta and cook in a single layer, stirring occasionally, until beginning to brown, 8 to 10 minutes.'),(696757,3,'Transfer to a plate.Reduce the heat to medium, add the remaining 2 teaspoons oil and garlic to the pan, and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 30 seconds.'),(696757,4,'Add onion and bell pepper; cook, stirring, until just tender, 3 to 5 minutes.'),(696757,5,'Sprinkle with paprika; cook, stirring, for 30 seconds. Stir in beans, spinach and broth; cook, stirring, until the beans are heated through and the spinach is wilted, 2 to 3 minutes.'),(696757,6,'Remove from the heat; stir in cheese and vinegar.'),(696757,7,'Serve vegetables over polenta.'),(696757,8,'Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.'),(696847,1,'Place rack in lower third of oven; preheat to 350&amp;ordm;F.Melt butter over medium-high heat in a large ovenproof Dutch oven; add rice and cook, stirring, until lightly toasted, about 1 1/2 minutes. (If using curry powder, add it now and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 15 seconds.)'),(696847,2,'Add water. Stir in lentils, garlic cloves, cinnamon stick, ginger, curry paste, if using, and salt; bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve the curry paste.Cover the pot tightly with a lid or foil.'),(696847,3,'Transfer to the oven and bake until the rice and lentils are tender and all the water is absorbed, 50 to 55 minutes. Fluff with a fork, removing the cinnamon stick and ginger slices.'),(696847,4,'Serve garnished with scallions.'),(697211,1,'Place chicken in a large bowl.'),(697211,2,'Add lemon juice and toss to coat.'),(697211,3,'Whisk yogurt, garlic, ginger, paprika, mint and salt in a separate bowl.'),(697211,4,'Pour the yogurt mixture over the chicken and stir to coat. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour or up to 24 hours.Position rack in upper third of oven; preheat broiler.'),(697211,5,'Remove the chicken from the marinade (discard marinade).'),(697211,6,'Place the chicken on a broiler rack and broil until browned on top, about 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 400F and bake until the chicken is juicy and just cooked through, about 15 minutes longer. (Thigh meat will appear dark pink, even when cooked through.)'),(697211,7,'Serve immediately.'),(697956,1,'Preheat oven to 350 F. Coat a 9-by-13-inch glass baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.Cook noodles in a large pot of boiling water until tender but firm, 5 to 7 minutes.'),(697956,2,'Drain and refresh with cold water. Set aside.Melt butter in a small skillet over low heat. Skim off froth and cook until it begins to turn light, nutty brown, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. (Be careful not to burn the butter.)'),(697956,3,'Pour into a small bowl and let cool.'),(697956,4,'Whisk together eggs, egg whites and cornstarch in a large bowl.'),(697956,5,'Mix in cottage cheese, yogurt, milk, sugar, raisins, vanilla, salt and the browned butter. Stir in the cooked noodles and turn into the prepared baking dish. Stir together cornflakes, brown sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl.'),(697956,6,'Sprinkle evenly over the noodle mixture.'),(697956,7,'Bake until browned and set, about 1 hour. (If topping starts to burn, cover with aluminum foil.)'),(697956,8,'Let cool for at least 20 minutes.'),(697956,9,'Cut into squares and serve warm or cold.'),(697998,1,'Cut leeks in half lengthwise; rinse thoroughly under water.'),(697998,2,'Cut crosswise into thin slices, place in a colander and rinse again.'),(697998,3,'Heat 2 teaspoons butter in a 12-inch cast-iron skillet over low heat, add pancetta (or bacon) and cook, stirring, until almost crisp.'),(697998,4,'Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate with a slotted spoon.'),(697998,5,'Add the remaining 1 teaspoon butter and the leeks to the pan. Season with 1/8 teaspoon each salt and pepper and add 1/4 cup broth (or water); simmer, covered, until tender, about 5 minutes.'),(697998,6,'Add cabbage and the remaining 1/4 cup broth (or water); season with the remaining 1/8 teaspoon each salt and pepper. Cover and simmer until tender, about 15 minutes. (Check the cabbage after 5 minutes; if necessary, add more broth or water, a tablespoon at a time, to prevent scorching.) Stir in mushrooms; cover and continue simmering until the vegetables are tender, 5 to 7 minutes more.'),(697998,7,'Serve sprinkled with the reserved pancetta (or bacon).'),(698951,1,'Season pork with salt and pepper.'),(698951,2,'Heat 1 teaspoon oil in a Dutch oven or heavy soup pot over high heat.'),(698951,3,'Add pork and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned on all sides, about 6 minutes.'),(698951,4,'Transfer to a plate lined with paper towels and set aside.Reduce heat to medium and add remaining 1 teaspoon oil to pot.'),(698951,5,'Add onion and bell pepper and cook, stirring, until vegetables are soft, about 5 minutes.'),(698951,6,'Add garlic, curry powder, thyme, allspice and cinnamon; cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 1 minute more.'),(698951,7,'Add broth, sweet potatoes, tomatoes, chiles and bay leaf. Bring to a simmer, reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until sweet potatoes are very tender and the sauce has thickened, 15 to 20 minutes.'),(698951,8,'Add reserved pork and cook until heated through, about 3 minutes.'),(698951,9,'Remove chiles and bay leaf. Adjust seasonings and serve.'),(699903,1,'1 Cook the potatoes.'),(699903,2,'Place peeled cut potatoes in a large saucepan, cover with an inch of cold water.'),(699903,3,'Add 2 teaspoons of salt to the water.'),(699903,4,'Add the garlic cloves and rosemary sprig.'),(699903,5,'Heat on high to bring to a boil, then reduce to low, cover to maintain a simmer until the potatoes are just cooked through, about 10 to 12 minutes.Once potatoes are done, drain the potatoes. Discard the rosemary sprig, save the garlic cloves with the potatoes.2 Mash the potatoes and garlic cloves.While the potatoes are still hot, use either a potato masher or a potato ricer to roughly mash the potatoes in a large bowl. A ricer will yield fluffier, less gluey, mashed potatoes.3'),(699903,6,'Mix in cream cheese and yogurt. In a large upright mixer (or if you have strong arms, you can do this by hand), add the riced or roughly mashed potatoes into the mixer bowl, along with 2 Tbsp of butter, the softened cream cheese, and the yogurt.'),(699903,7,'Mix on low to start, then increase the speed to medium and mix just until everything is well incorporated. (Don\'t overmix!) Stirin the minced rosemary, the salt and pepper. Taste and add more salt and pepper if needed.4'),(699903,8,'Place in casserole dish. Butter generously the inside of a 2-quart casseroledish.'),(699903,9,'Add the mashed potatoes, and spread out in an even layer. Dot with the remaining 1 Tbsp butter.At this point, you\'ve done the make-ahead part of the recipe. You can cover with plastic wrap and chill until ready to bake. You can make up to 2 days ahead. (Or you can freeze for up to 2 weeks ahead.)5'),(699903,10,'Bake. When ready to make, remove from refrigerator and let sit for an hour to come to room temperature.'),(699903,11,'Bake at 350F for 30 to 45 minutes, until the top is lightly browned.'),(700120,1,'Bring a large pot of water to a boil.'),(700120,2,'Add the tortellini and cook according to the package directions.'),(700120,3,'Drain and reserve.Meanwhile, in a large skillet over medium heat, heat the olive oil.'),(700120,4,'Add the sausage and cook, breaking it up as it cooks, until browned and cooked through, about 7-8 minutes.'),(700120,5,'Add the Brussels sprouts, salt, and pepper. Cook for 5-8 minutes or until beginning to brown.'),(700120,6,'Add the chicken broth, bring to a simmer, and cook an additional 2-3 minutes or until sprouts are al dente.'),(700120,7,'Add the reserved tortellini and stir to combine.'),(700120,8,'Serve hot, topped with the Parmesan cheese.'),(700250,1,'Place almond bark in a 6 quart slow cooker and melt it on HIGH stirring occasionally. This should take less than 1 hour.'),(700250,2,'Add in 6 cups of dry Cheerios stirring well coating all cheerios with the melted almond bark.Next, add in dry cake mix slowly while stirring the cheerios until coated.  Cool on a cookie sheet lined with waxed paper or parchment paper.Store in a cool place in an airtight container or bag for up to 2 weeks.'),(700593,1,'Preheat oven to 325.Cream together softened butter and powdered sugar until light and fluffy.'),(700593,2,'Mix in cocoa powder and peppermint extract, just until combined.'),(700593,3,'Add half the flour, mix until combined, then add remaining flour to mix well.Lightly flour your work surface, roll dough out to about \".'),(700593,4,'Cut with a shaped cookie cutter or use a knife to cut into rectangles.'),(700593,5,'Bake for 14-17 minutes until edges just begin to brown.Cool completely.Melt chocolate chips in a microwave safe dish, 30 seconds at a time, stirring between each until completely melted and smooth.Use a fork to drizzle melted chocolate over cooled cookies.Immediately sprinkle with crushed peppermint.Allow to set completely.Store in an airtight container.'),(700633,1,'Start by combining the dry ingredients (spelt flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, ginger, cinnamon and cloves) in a medium-size bowl and sift together.In a separate large bowl, stir together the wet ingredients (molasses, maple syrup, coconut sugar, applesauce, and melted coconut oil) until well combined.'),(700633,2,'Add the dry ingredients to the bowl with the wet and stir together with a spatula until a dough forms. It might look like the dough is dry but dont worry, just keep stirring. After moist dough has formed, divide it in two separate halves and wrap each one with plastic. Refrigerate until cold and firm, for about one hour or up to 2 days.When you are ready to bake the cookies, take the dough out and preheat the oven to 350F. Line a hard surface with parchment paper and lightly sprinkle it and a rolling pin with flour. Gently roll the dough out on the floured surface to roughly 1/4 thick. If it is too hard to roll, try giving it a minute to warm up some. Using cookie cutters, press shapes into the dough and use your hands to pull away any excess pieces. Form the excess pieces into a large ball and continue to roll out and cut shapes until all of the dough is gone.'),(700633,3,'Transfer the cookies to two baking sheets lined with parchment paper and bake for 10 minutes. Set aside to cool completely before icing.Meanwhile, make the icing by combining all of the ingredients in a small bowl and whisking together until smooth. Spoon it into a plastic bag and cut one corner off or use a pastry bag. Slowly pipe the icing on as desired.Store cookies in an airtight container between layers of parchment paper for up to one week.'),(700790,1,'Slice tofu in -inch thick slabs and spread in a single layer in between two, doubled-over kitchen towels.'),(700790,2,'Place a large cutting board overtop and stack a few books on top to press out the liquid for 20-30 minutes.De-stem the kale, stack the leaves and chop into thin ribbons.  Measure 3-4 cups and place in a mixing bowl with the cooked and chilled quinoa.After pressing the tofu, preheat a 10-inch cast iron skillet over med-high heat with about 2 teaspoons of oil.Cube the tofu into -inch pieces and place in the skillet once hot.  Season lightly with salt + pepper.'),(700790,3,'Let brown for about 2-3 minutes and then toss a few times until browned on all sides.  About 7-10 minutes total or longer if desired.Once the tofu is done, let fully cool then place in the bowl of quinoa and kale.'),(700790,4,'Add desired amount of dressing and toss together until well-coated.'),(700790,5,'Add salt + pepper as desired and chill in the fridge until ready to serve.'),(700790,6,'Add the avocado and sun-dried tomatoes and toss with more dressing as it will have absorbed some in the fridge.'),(700790,7,'Place in a lettuce or tortilla and serve with extra dressing on the side.notes/substitutions:  If wanting to serve this warm/hot, add the quinoa and kale mixture to the skillet over med-low heat after browning the tofu.  Toss with the caesar dressing, avocado, and sun-dried tomatoes until hot.'),(700790,8,'Add more dressing as needed.  I used about  of the dressing recipe when making this.  Feel free to sub chickpeas or cubed tempeh instead of tofu if desired.  Fresh tomatoes are also a great addition in the wrap.  Romaine lettuce can be subbed the kale if desired.Rinse + drain your chickpeas and soaked cashews and place in a high-speed blender with 5 tablespoons lemon juice,  cup water, tahini, 2 teaspoons tamari, garlic, agave or honey,  teaspoon mustard, and  teaspoon black pepper.Blend until fully smooth, scraping the sides as needed.'),(700790,9,'Add more water as needed to thin to desired consistency.Crumble  of an 8x8 sheet of sushi nori and blend into the dressing.Taste and adjust flavors as necessary adding more lemon, tamari, pepper, and/or the last  sheet of nori if desired.Refrigerate for about 5 days.  Dressing thickens as it sits.  Thin out with water/lemon juice/olive oil as needed.'),(701119,1,'Preheat oven to 35'),(701317,1,'Preheat oven to 450 degrees F. Line a heavy duty baking sheet with parchment paper or a Silpat.'),(701317,2,'Mix the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt very thoroughly in a large mixing bowl.'),(701317,3,'Cut butter into flour mixture with a pastry cutter until crumbly and coarse.'),(701317,4,'Add 3/4 cup of cream along with the vanilla and stir to make a thick dough. Stir in the butterscotch morsels or whatever add-ins you like.On a piece of parchment paper, shape the dough into a 7 inch round.'),(701317,5,'Transfer to the freezer and freeze round for 10 minutes.With a sharp knife, cut the round into 8 wedges.'),(701317,6,'Place wedges 2 inches apart on baking sheet.'),(701317,7,'Brush tops of wedges with remaining cream and sprinkle with a little extra sugar if desired.'),(701317,8,'Bake at 450 for 13 to 15 minutes or until golden.'),(701317,9,'Let sit for about a half hour or so before serving..'),(702334,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).'),(702334,2,'In a medium saucepan, bring the water to a boil.'),(702334,3,'Mix in the instant rice, cover, and remove from heat.'),(702334,4,'Let stand 5 minutes.'),(702334,5,'In a 9x13 inch baking dish, mix the prepared rice, chicken, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, butter, milk, broccoli, onion, and processed cheese.'),(702334,6,'Bake in the preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until cheese is melted. Stir halfway through cooking to help cheese melt evenly.'),(702550,1,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (204 C). Poke a few holes in the sweet potatoes with a sharp knife to allow steam to escape.Once oven is hot, bake sweet potatoes directly on oven rack (with a baking rack below to catch any drippings) for 45 minutes - 1 hour, or until tender to the touch. Time will vary depending on size of potato.In the meantime, heat a small saucepan over medium-high heat. Once hot, add rinsed quinoa and toast for 3-5 minutes, or until all water is evaporated and quinoa is fragrant and slightly toasted.'),(702550,2,'Add water, a pinch of sea salt, lime juice and bring to a simmer. Then reduce heat to low and cover. Cook for 15-20 minutes, or until all liquid is absorbed and the quinoa is fluffy. (For more tips, see this helpful article from Food52.)'),(702550,3,'Remove quinoa from heat and season with another healthy pinch sea salt and 1/4 tsp ground cumin. Stir, adjust seasonings as desired, and set aside, slightly covered.To prepare dressing, add all ingredients besides water to a blender or food processor and blend.'),(702550,4,'Add only enough water to encourage blending. Scrape down sides as needed.Taste and adjust seasonings as needed, adding more lime, salt, cumin or sweetener as desired. Set aside.Prepare any remaining toppings, such as chopped onion, cilantro or crushed tortilla chips (optional).To serve split open baked potatoes and gently press in on both ends to allow room for toppings. Fill each potato with 1 Tbsp salsa, and 1/4 - 1/2 cup cooked quinoa.Top with a healthy drizzle of avocado-cilantro sauce, and any other desired toppings (hot sauce, extra cilantro, and tortilla chips being my favorite). Best when fresh, though leftovers store separately in the refrigerator up to 2 days.'),(703656,1,'In each jar, add 1/2 cup oats and a pinch of salt.Top each with 1 tsp. of brown sugar.'),(703656,2,'Add 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk to each jar'),(703656,3,'Add 1/2 tsp. vanilla extract and 1/4 tsp. to 1/8 tsp. almond extract to each jar.Stir everything.Top each jar with 2 TBS. sliced almonds and sprinkle of cinnamon. Close jars and refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.Stir before serving.'),(703910,1,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.In a small bowl, whisk together dijon mustard, lemon juice, and maple syrup. Give it a taste and add salt and pepper if it\'s needed (but I rarely feel like it needs the extra seasoning).Lightly oil a sheet pan (or cover it in a piece of parchment paper) and place salmon fillet on the pan.'),(703910,2,'Pour mustard mixture over salmon and use a spoon or a spatula to smooth it out so the mustard covers the entire fillet.'),(703910,3,'Bake salmon for 12-15 minutes or until it\'s reached your desired level of doneness.'),(703910,4,'Serve immediately.'),(705232,1,'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. Line a standard muffin tin with paper liners (or spray with non-stick cooking spray).'),(705232,2,'Melt the butter and chocolate together in a bowl over a saucepan of simmering water (or do so in a microwave on 50% power in 30-second increments), until completely melted and smooth.'),(705232,3,'Remove from the heat.'),(705232,4,'In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda and salt. In a large glass measuring cup or a small bowl, whisk together the buttermilk, egg and vanilla until well combined.'),(705232,5,'Pour the liquid ingredients and the melted butter and chocolate over the dry ingredients, add the chocolate chips, and with a rubber spatula, gently fold until all ingredients are incorporated. Do not overmix the batter. Divide the batter evenly among the muffin cups.'),(705232,6,'Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until a thin knife inserted into the center of the muffins comes out clean.'),(705232,7,'Transfer the pan to a rack and cool for 5 minutes before carefully removing each muffin from its mold.'),(705232,8,'Serve warm or at room temperature. Muffins can be stored at room temperature in an airtight container for up to 4 days (or frozen for up to 2 months).'),(706208,1,'Combine olive oil, vinegar, salt, and black pepper in a bowl, stirring with a whisk.'),(706208,2,'Add greens, peas, and orange sections to bowl; toss to coat.'),(706461,1,'Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.'),(706461,2,'Combine mayonnaise, rind, and juice in a small bowl, stirring with a whisk.'),(706461,3,'Add mayonnaise mixture to crab mixture; toss gently to coat. Arrange tomatoes on a serving platter; drizzle with oil.'),(706461,4,'Sprinkle tomatoes with salt and pepper. Mound crab mixture over tomatoes.'),(706461,5,'Sprinkle with basil leaves.'),(706542,1,'Place first 6 ingredients on 1 tortilla; top with second tortilla.'),(706542,2,'Heat a skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),(706542,3,'Add quesadilla to pan; cook 1 minute on each side or until golden.'),(706813,1,'Combine first 4 ingredients in a small saucepan over medium-high heat. Bring to a boil; cook 15 minutes or until reduced to 1/2 cup. Discard thyme sprig.'),(706813,2,'Preheat grill to high heat.'),(706813,3,'Thread 3 chicken pieces, 2 shallot quarters, and 2 sage leaves alternately onto each of 8 (8-inch) skewers. Coat with cooking spray.'),(706813,4,'Sprinkle evenly with 3/4 teaspoon pepper and salt. Thread 6 fig halves onto each of 4 (8-inch) skewers, cut sides facing the same direction. Coat with cooking spray; sprinkle with remaining 1/4 teaspoon pepper.'),(706813,5,'Arrange chicken skewers on grill rack coated with cooking spray; grill 12 minutes, turning to brown all sides.'),(706813,6,'Brush chicken skewers with half of wine mixture during final minute of cooking. Arrange fig skewers, cut side down, on grill rack; grill 3 minutes. Turn fig skewers over; grill 1 minute. Arrange skewers on a serving plate.'),(706813,7,'Drizzle with remaining wine mixture; sprinkle with thyme leaves.'),(706869,1,'Preheat oven to 35'),(706869,2,'Place potatoes in a medium saucepan filled with water. Bring to a boil; cook 15 minutes or until tender.'),(706869,3,'Drain. Return potatoes to pan.'),(706869,4,'Add buttermilk, salt, and cheese; mash with a potato masher to desired consistency. Keep warm.'),(706869,5,'Coat 8 muffin cups with cooking spray.'),(706869,6,'Combine sausage, sirloin, carrot, green onions, panko, black pepper, and egg in a large bowl, stirring just until combined. Divide sausage mixture evenly among prepared cups. Make a (1/2-inch-deep) indentation in the center of each meat loaf. Top each meat loaf with about 2 teaspoons barbecue sauce.'),(706869,7,'Bake at 350 for 15 to 20 minutes or until a thermometer inserted in the center registers 160.'),(707057,1,'Hull and slice strawberries, if using; place in a medium bowl.'),(707057,2,'Slicing bigger berries speeds up maceration--liquids will release faster.'),(707057,3,'Add remaining ingredients, stirring gently to combine.'),(707057,4,'Let stand for 20 minutes or until mixture is syrupy, gently stirring occasionally. Sugar, lime, and gin soften and preserve the berries while extracting their natural juices to become a syrupy sauce.'),(707057,5,'If desired, refrigerate and continue to macerate for up to 4 hours. Delicate raspberries and strawberries can oversoften, so macerate them only a few hours. Thick-skinned berries like blueberries can go overnight.'),(707142,1,'Start with Van\'s Multigrain Belgian waffle.'),(707142,2,'Add avocado, poached egg, prosciutto, cilantro, and chopped tomato.'),(707893,1,'Spread half of hazelnut butter on one side of each bread slice.'),(707893,2,'Layer one slice with avocado, sprouts, spinach, onion, and chutney. Top with remaining bread slice, hazelnut butter side down.'),(708163,1,'Combine all ingredients in a 5-quart electric slow cooker. Cover and cook on low 10 hours or until apples are very tender.'),(708163,2,'Place a large fine-mesh sieve over a bowl; spoon one-third of apple mixture into sieve. Press mixture through sieve using the back of a spoon or ladle. Discard pulp. Repeat procedure with remaining apple mixture. Return apple mixture to slow cooker. Cook, uncovered, on high 1 1/2 hours or until mixture is thick, stirring occasionally. Spoon into a bowl; cover and chill up to a week.'),(708176,1,'Preheat oven to 35'),(708176,2,'Place potatoes in a large stockpot; cover with stock. Bring mixture to a boil; cook 4 minutes.'),(708176,3,'Remove from heat. Carefully remove potatoes from pot using a slotted spoon, reserving cooking liquid. Arrange potato slices in a single layer on a jelly-roll pan; set aside. Strain cooking liquid through a fine-mesh sieve over a bowl; reserve 1 cup cooking liquid. Discard solids and remaining cooking liquid.'),(708176,4,'Heat a medium saucepan over medium heat.'),(708176,5,'Add oil to pan.'),(708176,6,'Sprinkle flour over oil; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly with a whisk.'),(708176,7,'Add garlic; cook 2 minutes, stirring frequently.'),(708176,8,'Combine milk and reserved 1 cup cooking liquid. Gradually pour milk mixture into flour mixture in pan, stirring constantly with a whisk.'),(708176,9,'Add thyme sprigs to pan. Bring mixture to a boil; cook 4 minutes or until slightly thick, stirring frequently.'),(708176,10,'Remove from heat. Strain mixture through a fine-mesh sieve over a bowl, reserving sauce; discard solids. Stir 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper, and Gruyre cheese into sauce.'),(708176,11,'Spread 1/2 cup sauce in bottom of a broiler-safe 2-quart ceramic baking dish coated with cooking spray. Arrange a single, flat layer of sweet potato and then baking potato slices over sauce. Over flat layer, alternate baking potato and sweet potato slices, in shingle-like fashion.'),(708176,12,'Sprinkle evenly with remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1 tablespoon chives, and chopped thyme; pour remaining sauce over potato mixture.'),(708176,13,'Sprinkle with Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese.'),(708176,14,'Bake at 350 for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender when pierced with a knife.'),(708176,15,'Remove gratin from oven. Preheat broiler to high.'),(708176,16,'Place gratin in oven. Broil gratin 3 minutes or until browned.'),(708176,17,'Sprinkle with remaining 1 tablespoon chives.'),(708781,1,'Put the potatoes in a large saucepan. Cover them with water to about a inch above the potatoes. Bring to a boil over high heat. Once it begins to boil turn the heat down to medium and cook until the potatoes are easily pierced by a fork, about 10 minutes. They should be almost ready to eat, but not mushy.'),(708781,2,'Drain in a strainer and set aside.'),(708781,3,'Mix all the glaze ingredients into a large mixing bowl and toss the tempeh in it until each piece is coated. Set aside for later.Now you\'ll prepare the vegetable mixture. First heat the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Once it\'s hot add in the onions and saute until they\'re translucent.'),(708781,4,'Add the garlic and bell peppers and cook until the peppers begin to get soft.Stir in the kale, carrots, broth, soy sauce, maple syrup, marjoram, glazed tempeh and potatoes. Cook another 10 minutes until everything is heated thoroughly.'),(708781,5,'Add salt and pepper, to taste and serve.'),(709271,1,'Youre going to need a pot thats at least 12 quarts large. Over medium-high heat, get that olive oil to a shimmer and start browning. Work in batches, so as not to crowd the pot. Even the neck bones will get a little sear.Once youve seared and transferred to a plate, reduce heat to medium and add your onions.After about 8 minutes, or until they are soft, add the garlic and lightly brown for another 5 minutes.'),(709271,2,'Add in the tomato paste and combine with onions and garlic until its mixed thoroughly, about 2 minutes.Now its time for the wine.'),(709271,3,'Add the cup and reduce by half, making sure to scrape up all those bits on the bottom of the pot from the searing.Once youve reduced your liquid by half, you can add back in your bones and add the tomatoes and remaining spices. You can crush them a bit by hand as you add them or notbother. The long cooking time will reduce them to pulp.Increase the heat to bring everything to a nice bubble and give a good stir. Once its bubbling, reduce the heat and cook for at least 2 hours while everything thickens.After that you can add in your country-style ribs and any beef cuts you purchased. Theyll take the longest, as theyll need time to break down the connective tissue. After another three hours, you can add your sausage. If you decided to go the meatball route, toss them in at the end  they wont need long to cook, maybe an hour. You want them to stay formed, not break apart like in a Bolognese.'),(709745,1,'Toast the waffle and cut it into quarters.In a small bowl, combine the cream cheese alternative or coconut cream and cinnamon.'),(709745,2,'Spread it over the waffle bites.Top each bite with the diced peaches and sprinkle with walnuts.'),(709900,1,'Wash the fennel before cutting into slivers about  inch wide. (You can sliver it more thinly if desired, but reduce the cooking time.) Theres no need to remove the core. If the outer skin looks scarred or banged up, remove the damage with a vegetable peeler. Set the fronds aside.'),(709900,2,'Heat the oil a large, non-stick skillet over medium-high heat.'),(709900,3,'Add the fennel and cook until it begins to soften but still has a bit of crunch, about 5 minutes.Stir in the honey and vinegar. Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until the liquid has evaporated, about 3 minutes.'),(709900,4,'Transfer to serving bowl.'),(709900,5,'Sprinkles with pistachios and fennel fronds. Season with salt and pepper.'),(709900,6,'Serve warm, or allow to cool.'),(710854,1,'Unwrap tofu. Lightly blot with paper towels to remove excess moisture. Slice block into 1-inch thick strips. Reassemble block, wrap tightly in plastic wrap and freeze for 3 hours our up to 2 months.When ready to cook, remove tofu from freezer and unwrap. Bring a pot of water large enough to completely submerge the tofu to a boil. Gently slip frozen tofu block into the water (no need to break apart the strips.) Reduce heat to a gentle simmer. Continue simmering for 10-15 minutes, until tofu floats.'),(710854,2,'Remove immediately and set aside on a paper towel-lined plate to cool. Once tofu is cool enough to touch, carefully separate any strips that have not yet come apart.'),(710854,3,'Cut strips into 1/2 to 3/4 inch-wide pieces.In a large wok or skillet, heat the oil over medium-high heat until very hot but not smoking.'),(710854,4,'Add tofu pieces in a single layer.'),(710854,5,'Let cook for a few minutes on one side, then with a heat-proof spatula, turn the tofu pieces so that all sides brown, cooking for a few minutes on each side. Once tofu is lightly browned and crispy (about 10 minutes), remove from pan. Use in your favorite stir fry, dip in peanut sauce, or add to soups or stews.'),(712195,1,'Combine all dressing ingredients in a small mixing bowl and whisk well to combine.  Note: It\'s best to let this sit (sealed, refrigerated) for 24 hours before using. This gives the herbs time to infuse. Shake well before dressing the salad.Gently combine zucchini noodles with dressing.Gently combine remaining ingredients.Taste test, adjust seasoning if needed.Enjoy immediately.'),(712677,1,'Preheat oven to 350F degrees.Spray a bundt pan with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.Brown the butter by placing a saut pan on the stove set to medium heat. Melt butter, stirring occasionally until it starts to brown about 3-6 minutes. It will start to smell to bubble, smell nutty and then turn a golden color. Take butter off the heat immediately so that it doesn\'t burn; set aside while you prepare the other ingredients. Stove tops vary so the time could be more or less. In a medium bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and salt.In a large bowl, beat slightly cooled butter, sugar, and eggs until light and fluffy. Stir in mashed bananas, vanilla and creme fraiche.To make the cinnamon swirl, melt 4 tablespoons butter in a small bowl and add brown sugar, granulated sugar, cinnamon and a tiny pinch of salt; stir to combine.'),(712677,2,'Spread 1/3 of the batter evenly into the bottom of the prepared bundt pan. Dollop 1/2 of the cinnamon sugar mixture over the batter in the pan and then make a nice thick swirl through the batter with a table knife or bottom of a wooden spoon.'),(712677,3,'Place 1/3 of the remaining batter evenly over the first layer and top with the other half of the cinnamon sugar mixture; swirl.'),(712677,4,'Spread the remaining batter evenly over the top.'),(712677,5,'Bake cake in preheated oven about 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into center of bread comes out clean.'),(712677,6,'Remove from oven, let cake cool 10 minutes on a cooling rack before removing  from pan.'),(712677,7,'Let cool another 20-30 minutes before diving in head first!'),(713636,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.'),(713636,2,'Remove shells from package and arrange on a baking sheet; set aside.In a bowl, combine cheese, pimentos, mayo, chopped bacon and salt.  Stir until combined.Fill each shell with a spoonful of cheese.'),(713636,3,'Bake for 8-10 minutes or until cheese is bubbly; serve'),(714105,1,'Place butter, herbes de Provence, and salt in small bowl; mash with fork until blended to thick granular paste. Starting at neck end of each chicken, carefully run fingers under skin of breasts to loosen. Starting at each side of main cavity, carefully run fingers under skin of thighs to loosen. Rub herb-seasoned butter on chicken under loosened skin and on outside of each chicken. Truss chickens by tying legs together and tying wings flush to sides. Enclose chickens in extralarge resealable plastic bags. Chill at least 6 hours. DO AHEAD Chickens can be prepared 1 day ahead. Keep refrigerated.'),(714105,2,'Let chickens stand at room temperature about 30 minutes before cooking.'),(714105,3,'Remove spit from rotisserie attachment and prepare barbecue (medium-high heat). Thread chickens on spit, pushing close to center. Reattach spit to motor.'),(714105,4,'Place shallow disposable foil pan(s) under chickens for drips. Close grill, inserting stem of instant-read thermometer through hole in hood of grill to monitor temperature. Maintain temperature at around 400F by opening vents to increase heat and closing vents to reduce heat. Cook chickens until thermometer inserted into thickest part of thigh registers 170F, about 50 minutes. Turn off grill, but do not open.'),(714105,5,'Let chickens rest in covered grill 10 minutes.Slide chickens off spit and onto platter.'),(714105,6,'Cut each chicken into 6 or 8 pieces and arrange on platter.TO GRILL A WHOLE CHICKEN WITHOUT A ROTISSERIE: If using a charcoal grill,arrange coals on either side of a disposable aluminum baking pan, dividing coals equally. If using a three-burner gas grill, light burners on left and right, leaving center burner off. If using a two-burner gas grill, light burner on side opposite disposable pan. Insert an instant-read thermometer into top vent of grill or place oven thermometer inside grill on grate over pan. Bring temperature to 350F to 375F.'),(714105,7,'Place chicken on grate above pan. Close grill. Adjust grill vents or heat setting as needed to maintain temperature.'),(714182,1,'See Domedtic Man'),(714959,1,'Just mix and serve.'),(715171,1,'Combine spinach leaves, snow peas, strawberries, almonds in a bowl.'),(715171,2,'Add in salt and lemon juice.'),(715171,3,'Combine well and serve.'),(716282,1,'Peel, wash and chop the plantain and place in the pot.Wash, and season the goat meat with the above listed spices.'),(716282,2,'Pour in some water and Boil. You may need to take out the plantain half way as the goat meat will need longer to cook. Keep adding water to the pot till the meat is soft. When the meat is ready, add the plantain again and simmer for 2 minutes and serve hot. '),(716456,1,'Heat a large saucepan and fry the chorizo for 3-4 minutes, or until crisp.'),(716456,2,'Add the onion, garlic and chilli and fry for 2-3 minutes, or until softened.'),(716456,3,'Add the paprika and stir until well combined.'),(716456,4,'Place the tomatoes, chickpeas and chicken stock into the pan and bring to the boil.'),(716456,5,'Reduce the heat and simmer for 4-5 minutes.'),(716456,6,'Add the spinach and fold it through the stew.'),(716456,7,'Return the mixture to the heat and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Cook for another minute to wilt the spinach, then season with lemon juice.'),(716456,8,'For the chorizo-stuffed chicken, heat a deep fat fryer to 170C/340F. (CAUTION: Do not leave hot fat unattended.)'),(716456,9,'Place the chorizo and butter into a food processor and blend to a pure.'),(716456,10,'Add a little touch of lemon juice and black pepper, then spoon into a piping bag. Make an incision in the side of the chicken breast and pipe some of the chorizo butter into the chicken.'),(716456,11,'Press the incision shut then dust with the flour. Prepare a plate of egg and a plate of breadcrumbs. Dip the chicken first in the egg, then the breadcrumbs.'),(716456,12,'Place into the fat