ll.Begin to warm up the oil to medium-high heat.'),(720858,4,'Place the okra in the eggs, and then dip in the cornmeal mixture. Be sure the okra is fully coated.'),(720858,5,'Place the okra immediately into the oil.'),(720858,6,'Let it fry on each side for about 5-10 minutes or until browned.Continue for all okra, adding more oil if needed.'),(720858,7,'Place the fried okra on a paper towel lined plate to drain the excess oil and grease.'),(720858,8,'Add additional salt to taste before serving.'),(720861,1,'Add all of the ingredients into a high-speed blender (I used my Vitamix). Puree on high speed, using a tamper if needed, until completely smooth.Enjoy!'),(721498,1,'In blender (my personal favorite is Blendtec) combine all ingredients and blend on smoothie for about 1 minute.TIPS: I like to wash and prepare fruit as soon as I get home from grocery store. If fruit- like pineapple- then wait till ripe to prepare it.Use ripe, or almost over  ripe fruit for added sweetness in smoothie. If you use fruit too soon it can add a bitter taste to your smoothies.'),(723246,1,'Place roast, pepperocini and half the pepperocini juice in crockpot.'),(723246,2,'Mix water, au jus, oregano, basil and garlic in measuring cup and pour over roast.Cook on low heat for 7 to 8 hours.When roast is tender, pull apart with forks and let simmer in juice another 1/2 hour or so.'),(723246,3,'Serve on toasted Hoagie rolls with cheese, pepperocini and juice from pan for dipping.'),(723525,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees and line pans with cupcake liners, I used green liners because I wanted them to look even more minty!'),(723525,2,'In a medium bowl, combine cocoa flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Set aside.'),(723525,3,'In a large bowl, combine eggs, sugar, brown sugar, oil, buttermilk and vanilla extract.'),(723525,4,'Pour half the dry ingredients into the wet and stir. Then add the rest of the dry ingredients and stir again. Don\'t over mix.'),(723525,5,'Fill cupcake liners 2/3 full and bake for 18-22 minutes or until an inserted knife comes out clean.'),(723525,6,'Let cool.'),(723525,7,'FROSTING:  Beat butter until smooth.'),(723525,8,'Add vanilla, 1 Tbsp. milk, cocoa and malt powder.  Beat until smooth.  Slowly add in a little powdered sugar at a time until you reach your desired consistency.'),(723525,9,'Add more milk if it gets too thick!'),(723525,10,'Frost cooled cupcakes and top with Whopper Eggs, I put mine in like a little \"nest\" but you can crush them up and sprinkle them on top too!'),(724403,1,'Slice potatoes in half and toss with olive oil, salt and pepper.'),(724403,2,'Lay potatoes out onto a baking sheet in an even layer.'),(724403,3,'Bake potatoes at 425 degrees for 35-40 minutes, turning every 10 minutes or so.'),(724403,4,'Meanwhile, add all pesto ingredients except olive oil and lemon juice to a food processor. Pulse a few times to combine.'),(724403,5,'Drizzle in olive oil and continue to pulse until it\'s a coarse paste.'),(724403,6,'Stir in lemon juice and set aside.'),(724403,7,'When potatoes come out of the oven, add to a bowl and toss with a few tablespoons of pesto.'),(724403,8,'Serve with extra pesto on the side!'),(724440,1,'Heat grill to medium high heat.Season chicken with salt & pepper on both sides.'),(724440,2,'Add chicken to the grill and grill each side for 5-6 minutes, until there is no more pink. For the last minute, add 1 slice of mozzarella to the top of each chicken. Close the grill and let the cheese slightly melt.'),(724440,3,'Remove from grill and let sit.Next add ciabatta bread to the grill, place the inside part of the bun on the grill and toast for 1-2 minutes until slightly charred.'),(724440,4,'Remove.Assemble the sandwich: spread 1 tablespoons of pesto on the bottom bun, place the grilled chicken and melted cheese on top of the bottom bun, then a slice of tomato, and a few slices of fresh avocado, add the top bun.'),(724440,5,'Serve!'),(724568,1,'In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter, stir in flour and cook for a few minutes until golden.'),(724568,2,'Add milk and cream, bring to a gentle simmer and continue to stir until thickened.'),(724568,3,'Add pesto, parsley, garlic, parmesan, salt, pepper, worcestershire and tabasco, and stir until blended.Reduce heat and keep warm, stirring occasionally.Cook pasta quickly in a large pot of boiling water (3 to 4 minutes, or until al dente).At the same time, poach the pepper and snowpeas in another pot of boiling water ( 2 or 3 minutes, or until just heated through).'),(724568,4,'Drain the pasta, mix it with the sauce and portion it into heated individual serving bowls.'),(724568,5,'Garnish each portion with shrimp and vegetables, and serve immediately.Note: You can also poach the veggies ahead of time and add them directly to the sauce just before serving as a step saver.'),(725996,1,'In a skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink. Meanwhile, quarter the biscuits; place in a greased shallow 3-qt. baking dish. Top with pizza sauce.'),(725996,2,'Drain beef; sprinkle over biscuits and sauce.'),(725996,3,'Layer with green pepper, onion, mushrooms, pepperoni and cheeses.'),(725996,4,'Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees F for 25-30 minutes or until cheese is melted.'),(725996,5,'Let stand for 5-10 minutes before serving.'),(727389,1,'Have ready a 5 quart pot, a rack or steamer basket to set in pot and an 8\" square baking dish.'),(727389,2,'Cut tops off peppers just below stem and remove seeds. Fill pot with 1\" water and insert a rack or steamer basket. Bring to a boil.'),(727389,3,'Place peppers, cut side down on rack, cover pot and cook 4 minutes.'),(727389,4,'Remove peppers and place cut side up in baking dish.'),(727389,5,'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over med heat.'),(727389,6,'Add onion and garlic and saute until onion softens, about 3 minutes. Stir in zucchini, tomatoes, Italian seasoning and 1/2 tsp. salt. Break up tomatoes with a spoon. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes. Stir in corn.'),(727389,7,'Remove 1 cup and reserve.'),(727389,8,'Heat oven to 375 degrees F.   Stir rice and 1/4 cup cheese into remaining vegetable mixture. Spoon into peppers. Loosely cover baking dish with foil.'),(727389,9,'Bake 20 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle peppers with remaining cheese.'),(727389,10,'Bake 10 minutes, longer or until hot and cheese is melted.   Meanwhile puree reserved vegetable mixture in a food processor or blender until smooth.'),(727389,11,'Pour into skillet.'),(727389,12,'Add water, remaining 1/4 tsp. salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.'),(727389,13,'Serve sauce with peppers.'),(727785,1,'Drain the tofu and press it for at least 15 minutes.'),(727785,2,'Cut the tofu into small cubes (about 1/2 inch).'),(727785,3,'Sautee the tofu cubes in the peanut oil until it has browned a little on each side, or until it\'s as crispy as you like it. Personally, I like it pretty crispy.'),(727785,4,'Add the minced onions, garlic & ginger, and saute until the onions are translucent.'),(727785,5,'Add the spaghetti sauce and tomato paste, and mix well. Stir in the chickpeas, and let the mixture simmer for about 10 minutes.Now stir in the peanut butter. It will melt and be easy to mix in with sauce.'),(727785,6,'Serve over rice with optional chopped scallions &/or cilantro as a garnish.'),(728220,1,'Put ground sausage in a skillet over medium high.When almost cooked through, add diced onions.Continue to cook, untill completly cooked.Turn off burner.'),(728220,2,'Place 3 paper towels on a plate.'),(728220,3,'Transfer sausage from the skillet to the paper towels.Put 3 more paper towels on top of meat.Pat down to remove grease.Take a paper towel to the skillet and wipe down.Turn the burner to medium heat and spray with enough cooking spray to coat the pan nicely (you could also use butter or oil instead).'),(728220,4,'Add the 4 eggs and break the yolks.Flip them over when the whites become opaque.'),(728220,5,