 the wok and cook on a high heat for 6-7 minutes, turning two or three times during cooking, until well browned. You may need to cook in two batches (I find I can do it in one batch so long as there are no more than 3 chicken breasts).Once golden brown, add the plum slices, peppers and garlic. Cook, with the chicken for 2 minutes, stirring often, until the plum starts to soften.Now add all of the sauce ingredients to the wok, stir and bubble on a high heat until the sauce reduces by about a third (should take 2-3 minutes).Turn off the heat and divide between four bowls.'),(843468,5,'Serve with boiled rice and top with spring onions and chilli flakes.'),(844237,1,'Start by making a basic polenta.'),(844237,2,'Pour the water into a large pot.'),(844237,3,'Heat the water but don\'t let it come to a boil (it helps against the formation of lumps).'),(844237,4,'Add the salt. Slowly add the cornmeal while stirring or whisking (with an egg beater not a mixer) all the time. A word of caution - be careful when the polenta starts to bubble, if the bubbles are too big you might get burned  so turn the heat down if that happens. When all the cornmeal is incorporated, continue stirring or whisking shortly to make sure there are no lumps. Turn the heat down, place a lid on top but leave a crack open. Stir every 4-5 minutes or so but there is definitely no need to stir all the time.Read the cooking instructions on the polenta packet just to know for sure how long the cornmeal needs to be cooked. I cook the polenta made with coarse cornmeal for 40 to 50 minutes and the polenta made with medium cornmeal for about 15 minutes.Preheat the oven to 220 degrees Celsius/ 400 degrees Fahrenheit.To make the balls: mix the polenta with the finely chopped sausages and the crumbled feta cheese.'),(844237,5,'Add the lightly beaten egg, dill, salt and pepper. Make about 30 balls about the size of a golf ball. Wet your hands after every 3 or 4 balls, it makes things easier.'),(844237,6,'Place the balls in a buttered casserole dish and sprinkle each ball with a little bit of the grated cheese.'),(844237,7,'Place a tiny amount of butter on each ball.'),(844237,8,'Bake for about 20 minutes in the hot oven or until golden.'),(844237,9,'Serve immediately with crme fraiche/ sour cream/ Greek yogurt and a green salad.'),(844350,1,'Chop the cauliflower and keep in warm water for 15-20 minutes to remove any insects in the cauliflower.'),(844350,2,'Drain and set aside.Prepare the carrots and turnip by peeling and chopping to 1.5 to 2 inches sticks.In a large pan, boil some water for blanching the vegetables.Once the water comes to a rolling boil, add the cauliflower florets, carrots and turnips and blanch for 2-3 minutes.'),(844350,3,'Drain the water out.Dry the vegetables out on a cloth evenly. You can dry them in the sun for a day or in the shade for a day or two. Make sure there is no moisture left and the vegetables are completely dry.When dry, prepare the masala. Puree the onions, ginger and garlic in a blender, without adding any water.'),(844350,4,'Mix the jaggery with vinegar in a saucepan on low flame. You can adjust the quantity of jaggery used as per your tastes. Stir till the jaggery dissolves and the cook till mixture reaches 1 string consistency. Switch flame off and keep aside.In another large pan, heat the mustard oil till its smoking point.'),(844350,5,'Add the ground paste and cook it, stirring continuously.'),(844350,6,'Saute till the onions become light brown, about 15-18 minutes on low flame.'),(844350,7,'Add the salt, garam masala. red chilli powder and split mustard seeds. Stir well.'),(844350,8,'Add the chopped veggies and stir till combined and remove from flame.'),(844350,9,'Add the jaggery and vinegar solution and stir well. Allow the pickle to cool down, without covering it with any lid.In clean, sterilized and absolutely dry jars, add the cool pickle making sure the oil covers the top of the veggies in the jar. Cover tightly and let sit at room temperature or in the sun for 2-3 days. Enjoy'),(844700,1,'Start off by mixing the baking soda and the lemon juice in a small bowl. In a separate bowl mix the vinegar and hydrogen peroxide and add this mixture in the baking soda and lemon mixture, one drop at a time. Once done, add a fragrant oil of your choice to give it a refreshing smell.Take a spoon and make a few half-ball shapes and place them on some parchment paper to dry. They will take a minimum of 4 hours to dry, but feel free to leave them to dry overnight. Once theyre dry completely, store them in air-tight glass jar near your toilet.Every time you notice that your toilet bowl is in a need of cleaning, drop a tab. Do this 2-3 times a week.Source: healthyfoodhouse.com'),(844842,1,'Toast pine nuts (I bought mine raw, and used the skillet method)Wash basil and pat dry, lightly press into a measuring cup.'),(844842,2,'Add to a food processor or blender.'),(844842,3,'Add; Garlic,  cup avocado oil, nutritional yeast, toasted pine nuts, and salt.Puree until it forma a loose paste.I put Mine into freezer safe containers in  cup portions, leaving enough space to top with the remaining  cup avocado oil.optional'),(844842,4,'Stir in the cheese at the end if you are NOT freezing the pesto.Preheat oven 350 F.'),(844842,5,'Place chicken thighs, cherries and pesto in a bowl.Massage pesto/cherries into the chicken, let sit for 10 min.'),(844842,6,'Sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),(844842,7,'Place on a lined baking sheet spooning excess pesto and cherries overtop of the thighs.'),(844842,8,'Bake for 30 min, until the chicken is done.(If using bone in chicken, cooking time will have to be longer)'),(844954,1,'Cut each thawed roll into 4 pieces.'),(844954,2,'Cut a slit on the curved side of each roll piece to make a heart shape. Allow the roll bites to rise for 20-30 minutes.Preheat oven to 375 degrees F and bring a large pot of water to boil on the stove.Once the roll bites are nice and puffy, carefully transfer 8-10 of them to the boiling water. Boil for 30 seconds and then flip each heart and boil on the other side for 30 seconds.'),(844954,3,'Remove them from the water and allow to dry on a paper towel while you boil the rest of the heart bites 8-10 at a time.'),(844954,4,'Place the boiled bites on a parchment lined baking sheet and bake in the 375 degree oven for 18-20 minutes or until golden brown. While the bites are cooking, melt the butter and mix the sugar and cinnamon together in a large bowl.'),(845522,1,'Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Toss potatoes with olive oil, garlic and oregano in a large bowl. Season with salt and black pepper.'),(845522,2,'Spread potatoes evenly on 2 large baking sheets and roast for 35 minutes, flipping halfway, until golden and tender.While potatoes are baking, mix all garlic-scallion sauce ingredients together. Season with salt to taste. Set aside until ready to use.When potatoes are cooked, transfer to large serving dish. Top with tomatoes, cucumber, feta, olives and parsley.'),(845522,3,'Serve with garlic-scallion sauce.'),(846245,1,'Blanch the pea pods in boiling water for 20 seconds before removing and running under cold water to stop cooking. Slice in to thin diagonal slices.'),(846245,2,'Combine the dressing ingredients in a bowl and whisk to combine.Lightly toast the bread'),(846245,3,'First, smear a good dollop of mayonnaise on to each slice of toast.'),(846245,4,'Add a few slices of avocado and season lightly with salt.'),(846245,5,'Sprinkle with the pea slivers and a little mint.Finally, dress lightly with the wasabi miso drizzle and sprinkle with black sesame seeds to serve.'),(846430,1,'teaspoon of olive oil, butter or butter substitutescallions choppedsweet potatoes, peeled and cut into  inch cubes/2 cup of brown/black raw quinoa, rinsed/4 teaspoon fo salat/2 teaspoon of black pepperteaspoon of oreganotablespoon of water/3 cup of white navy beans (drained and rinsed from a can or home cooked)cups of chopped fresh kale/4 teaspoon of salt/4 teaspoon of pepper/4 teaspoon of oregano/2 cup of slivered almondscallions, chopped'),(846430,2,'Dressing:small clove of garlic, minced/4 cup of Balsamic vinegarpinch of saltpinch of pepperteaspoon of mustardteaspoon of olive oil ( up to 2 Tablespoons for extra flavor)Preheat a wide pot with a lid over medium high heat, and add in the olive oil or butter.'),(846430,3,'Sautee the scallions for one minutes over medium hight heat and then add in the sweet potatoes, quinoa, seasoning and saut for 1-2 minutes over medium hight heat.'),(846430,4,'Add the water and cover the pot firmly. Lower the heat to low and allow the sweet potatoes too cook for about 15-18 minutes. Check the sweet potatoes with a fork, when its fork tender, its ready.'),(846430,5,'Add the white navy beans, toss them with the sweet potatoes and let them cook for two more minutes then turn off the heat.'),(846430,6,'Add the kale, seasoning and toss the kale with the sweet potato mixture. Then cover the pot and let the kale wilt form the heat in the pan for 2-5 minutes.Plate the salad, sprinkle extra almonds and scallions (optional).For the dressing, mix all the ingredients in a bowl and pour over the salad. Enjoy warm'),(846824,1,'In the food processor, process the drained canned artichokes, about 1 minute.'),(846824,2,'Add the basil and lemon juice and process until smooth. You may need to scrape down the bowl once.'),(846824,3,'Add the garlic powder, olive oil, hemp hearts and 2 tbs. water. Process until smooth.'),(846824,4,'Add another tbs. or two of water as needed.Store in airtight container up to 1 week in the fridge'),(847002,1,'To make the sponge cakes, preheat the oven to 325F (160C). Lightly spraytwo 7-inch (18cm) round cake pans and line with parchment paper.Sift the cake flour with salt.Separate the eggs.In a mixing bowl with paddleattachment, beat egg yolks 2 tablespoons cold water until it\'s doubled in size, abouta minute.'),(847002,2,'Addsugar,vanilla extract and almond extract. Continue to beat until the mixture is thick and pale yellow on medium high speed.Reduce the speed to low and slowly pourinhot water.'),(847002,3,'Add theflour and mix until combined.In a separate bowl, whisk egg whites until foamy. Then add cream of tartar and continue to beat until hard peaks form.Gently fold in half of egg whites into the egg yolk mixture.'),(847002,4,'Add the remaining egg whites and fold in until well combined.Divide the batterinto the prepared cake pans.'),(847002,5,'Bake for 30 minutes, or until the inserted toothpick comes out clean.Cool the cakes in the pan for 5 minutes.Carefully run a knife around the edges to release the cake from the pan. Then invert the cakes onto a cooling rack. Cool completely.To make the syrup, dissolve espresso powder in 1/3 cup of water, and stir in disaronno.To make the tiramisu cream, in a mixing bowl with whisk attachment, beat mascarpone cheese, sweetened condensed milkand vanilla extract until combined.In a separate bowl, whip the heavy cream until hard peaks form.Gently fold in half of whipped cream into mascarpone cheese mixture. Then add remaining whipped cream and mix until well combined. Refrigerate until ready to use.To assemble the cake, once the cake is completely cooled, cut each cake horizontally.'),(847002,6,'Place the first layer on a serving platter lined with parchment paper.Generously brush on coffeesyrup. Dont be shy; soak the cake with the syrup pretty good.Then spread about 1 cup oftiramisu cream.'),(847002,7,'Place the next layer and repeatuntil all the layers are stacked.Cover the cake with remaining cream. If desired, decorate the cake using a piping bag fitted with star tip. (I used Wilton 1M tip.) Dust with cocoa powder. Refrigerate until ready to serve.'),(847186,1,'Wash the potato well and cut them into small bite size pieces.'),(847186,2,'Slice the sausages about 1cm thick and cut the bacon into small pieces too.'),(847186,3,'Place the potato in water (just cover the potato) and bring to boil over medium heat. Cook the potato for about 10 minutes or until the potato becomes soft.'),(847186,4,'Drain the water.'),(847186,5,'Heat olive oil in a large frying pan over high heat and crush the garlic into the frying pan.'),(847186,6,'When the garlic becomes fragrant, add the bacon and sausages into the frying pan. Cook the bacon and sausages till brown.'),(847186,7,'Add the cooked potato and mustard to the frying pan. Stir and fry them all together and add salt and pepper to taste.'),(847186,8,'Serve and garnish with Parsley or Thyme *1'),(847243,1,'Heat oven to 350F. Grease and flour two 4 inch ramekins or baking pans.'),(847243,2,'Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.'),(847243,3,'Add eggs, milk, vegetable oil and vanilla; beat on medium speed for two minutes. Stir in the hot coffee.'),(847243,4,'Pour into pans.'),(847243,5,'Bake 30 -35 minutes or until a tooth pick when inserted comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes. Cool completely before frosting. Frosting'),(847243,6,'In a medium bowl, sift together powdered sugar and cocoa. Set aside.In a large bowl, cream butter until smooth, then gradually beat in sugar mixture alternately with milk. Stir in vanilla extract. Beat until light and fluffy. If necessary, adjust consistency with more milk or sugar.'),(847527,1,'Heat oven to 400F.'),(847527,2,'Cut brussel sprouts in 1/2 if they are big. If brussel sprouts are small, you can use them whole. Chop kimchi and set aside.'),(847527,3,'Heat 1 Tbs vegetable oil in an ovenproof pan on medium high heat on stove.'),(847527,4,'Saute pancetta in oil for short time about 1 minute.'),(847527,5,'Add brussel sprouts to pan with pancetta -with the cut side down. Season lightly with salt and pepper.Put pan with brussel sprouts and pancetta in oven and roast for 5 minutes.In the mean time, in a small frying pan add 1 tsp vegetable oil and saut kimchi and gochujang for 2-3 minutes.After roasting brussel sprouts for 5 minutes (from step 4), take out pan from oven and add sauteed kimchi from 5 and toss everything together, coating brussel sprouts with oil.'),(847527,6,'Sprinkle 1 tsp sugar and mix again.Put everything back in the oven and roast for another 15 minutes. This will produce soft brussel sprouts. For crunchier sprouts, reduce roasting time. Check doneness after 10 minutes.'),(847527,7,'Sprinkle sesame seeds and serve!!'),(847588,1,'For the Slow Cooker Italian Beef:In a small bowl, stir together Italian seasoning, garlic, onion powder, salt, pepper & olive oil.Rub the mixture all over the beef and place beef in crock pot.'),(847588,2,'Add stock, red wine, pepperocinis and juice, cover, and cook on low for 8-10 hrs.'),(847588,3,'Remove beef from juice, shred with two forks, remove and discard any fat or grissle, and place the shredded beef back in the juice in the slow cooker.'),(847588,4,'Serve Italian beef warm on Amoroso or slider rolls (or mashed cauliflower) and top w/ Homemade Giardiniera and freshly grated Parmesan cheese.For the Homemade Giardiniera :In a large bowl, stir together vinegar, pepperocini juice, Italian seasoning, garlic, sugar, salt & pepper then slowly whisk in the olive oil until well blended.'),(847588,5,'Add chopped veggies, jalapenos, pepperocinis, and parsley to the dressing and toss to coat.Allow veggies to marinate until ready to serve.'),(847588,6,'Serve cold on top of warm Italian Beef.'),(848699,1,'Preheat oven to 375 degrees'),(848699,2,'Preheat grill'),(848699,3,'If you dont have pepper jelly, take regular jelly and add pepper flakes to it.'),(848699,4,'Let sit for about 10 minutes'),(848699,5,'Wrap beets in foil and place on baking tray.'),(848699,6,'Placed wrapped beets into the oven and let cook for 45minutes to 1 hour. About 25 minutes in, turn over the beets in the baking tray'),(848699,7,'Remove the beets from the oven and remove from foil.'),(848699,8,'Let cool for about 10 minutes and then peel the skin. It will peel away easily'),(848699,9,'Brush the watermelon slices with the pepper jelly and place on grill.Grill both sides of the watermelon. On a Grill or Bar-b-Que, grill for 1min on both sides. On a Panini Press, grill it for about 5min on high'),(848699,10,'Remove the watermelon and place aside'),(848699,11,'Cut the beets into bite size shapes and place on the grill. If you want, you can brush some of the pepper jelly on the beets before grilling.Grill the tomatoes just long enough to see the skin tighten. Cooking these tomatoes for longer than that will make them explode or burn.In the salad plate, place the greens first'),(848699,12,'Place 2 grilled watermelons per plate'),(848699,13,'Add the tomatoes and beets to the salad plate'),(848699,14,'Divide the goat cheese for each plate and place it on top of the salad'),(848699,15,'Drizzle Pomegranate Balsamic vinegar on the salad and serve immediately'),(848707,1,'Cut the tomatoes into small cubes'),(848707,2,'Wash the raspberries thoroughly'),(848707,3,'Place the tomatoes, raspberries, salt and sugar in a medium pan. Do NOT add water to this mixture because it produces its own water when heated. If you add water, you will have to leave on medium heat for a very long time trying to burn of all the water.'),(848707,4,'Heat at medium heat and stir constantly. Don\'t let the jam stick at the bottom'),(848707,5,'Add the lime juice, pepper flakes and the cinnamon powder just as the mixture is about to boil'),(848707,6,'Continue stirring on medium heat until the consistency is thick.Do a taste test and add any ingredients accordingly'),(848707,7,'Allow to cool at room temperature'),(849272,1,'Combine the cream, powdered sugar, and vanilla extract in the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with a whisk attachment. Whip until medium peaks form and the cream is the texture of shaving cream.'),(849272,2,'Spread a thin layer of whipped cream on the bottom of your serving platter, in about an 8-inch circle. Arrange a layer of chocolate wafer cookies on top of the cream in a circle, overlapping them slightly to get them to fit (some blank spaces are okay too!). I used about 15 cookies per layer: 10 cookies in the outer circle, 4 cookies in the inner circle, and a cookie in the middle, but your exact numbers will depend on the size of your serving platter.  '),(849272,3,'Spread a thin layer of cream on top of the cookies, around ¼-inch thick. You can go all the way to the edge, or leave about ½-inch uncovered at the edge if you want the cookies to poke out. Press fresh berries into the whipped cream—if they’re large, cut them in half lengthwise so they don’t poke up too much.'),(849272,4,'Spread another thin layer of whipped cream on top of the berries, just to make the surface smooth for the next layer of cookies. '),(849272,5,'Repeat with a second layer of cookies, and top with more cream and berries. Continue until you’ve used up all the cookies—I got 6 layers of cookies for my 8-inch cake. Top with the remaining whipped cream. Cover the cake loosely with plastic wrap, and refrigerate for at least 8 hours, to let the cookies absorb the moisture and soften—longer refrigeration is okay, too. '),(849272,6,'When the cookies are soft, top the cake with fresh raspberries, chocolate curls, and a light dusting of powdered sugar, if desired. Slice and serve!'),(849527,1,'In a small bowl mix together sea salt, cinnamon, and cayenne, if using. Set aside.'),(849527,2,'Heat a large skillet over medium heat.Cook the bacon in the skillet for 4-5 minutes, until they are crispy.'),(849527,3,'Add the cashew and cook while stirring for 2-3 minutes, until toasted evenly.'),(849527,4,'Add the mixed spices and stir together for 1 minute until evenly coated.'),(849527,5,'Remove from heat and let cool.'),(849527,6,'Serve immediately, or store in the fridge until ready to eat.'),(850208,1,'Brown ground beef, onion, and garlic until no pink remains.'),(850208,2,'Drain any fat.'),(850208,3,'Place beef in a 4 qt slow cooker.'),(850208,4,'Add remaining ingredients (except rolls) and stir to combine.Cook on low 6-7 hours or high 3-4 hours.'),(850208,5,'Serve over rolls or slider buns.'),(850362,1,'Pre heat oven to 150c / 300f / Gas 2 and line a baking tray with baking paper.'),(850362,2,'Add all the dry ingredients to a large mixing bowl and combine.'),(850362,3,'Add the coconut oil and stir through, coating the mixture.'),(850362,4,'Add the beaten egg whites and gently stir to coat the mixture.'),(850362,5,'Spread the mixture onto the baking tray and bake for approx. 30 mins (until golden)'),(852419,1,'Combine the apples, onion, ginger, pomegranate juice, vinegar, brown sugar, mustard seeds, pepper flakes, star anise and salt and in a large saucepan. Bring the mixture to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally. Reduce the heat to simmer and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, for 45-50 minutes, until most of the liquid has evaporated.'),(852419,2,'Remove the star anise and allow to cool.For the Pork:-3 days ahead, Rub the flesh with 1 tablespoon of the kosher salt, including where the bones pull away. Dry the skin as much as possible with a paper towel.'),(852419,3,'Place on a sheet tray on a wire rack, skin-side up and place in the refrigerator, uncovered, to let the skin dry.Preheat the oven to 475 degrees F.If the butcher has not done it for you, score the rind with a very sharp knife, using long, parallel slits -inch to -inch apart across the width of the loin; be careful not to cut into the flesh. Rub the rind with the last  tablespoon coarse salt, ensuring that the salt is rubbed well into the slits. Coat the rind with  of the oil.Flip the loin over and rub the flesh side with the remaining oil.'),(852419,4,'Place the garlic, thyme, and rosemary up against the flesh. Using butcher\'s twine, tie the herbs and garlic to the loin. If you have ribs, tie ribs to loin as well.'),(852419,5,'Place the loin, skin-side up, on a rack in a roasting pan and roast for 30 minutes. Reduce the heat to 425 degrees F and cook until an instant-read thermometer poked into the center of the loin reaches 135 degrees F, about 1 hour. Skin should be puffy and crisp, if its not puffy enough, set the roast under the broiler for a minute or two until it puffs.'),(852419,6,'Remove from the oven and let the loin rest on a carving board for 30 minutes; the internal temperature will continue to rise about 10 degrees F, and the juices redistribute to make it moister).'),(852419,7,'Remove the ribs by cutting the remaining flap, discard the garlic and herbs. Carve the loin into slices following the scores so that each slice has a segment of crackling (approx -inch strips).'),(852419,8,'Serve the warm pork loin with cracklings, Yorkshire Puddings and a bitter green salad.'),(852487,1,'About 2-3 hours before, or the night before, pour coffee into an ice cube tray and place in the freezer.Day of, add bananas into the blender. Blend until the bananas become crumbly.'),(852487,2,'Add almond milk. Blend until smooth and creamy, scraping down the sides of the blender as needed.'),(852487,3,'Add coffee ice cubes. Blend until well incorporated and smooth, again scraping down the sides of the blender as needed.'),(852487,4,'Add cocoa powder, blending until well incorporated.'),(852487,5,'Pour into two cups. Top with coconut whip or any of your favorite toppings. Enjoy!'),(853183,1,'In a large pan, saute the shallots 2 tablespoons of butter until they are cooked and soft but not browned.'),(853183,2,'Add the garlic and cook for another minute.'),(853183,3,'Add all the rice and stir it around with the other ingredients to toast the grains thoroughly without browning.Raise the heat to high, add the wine and reduce it until nearly all of the liquid is absorbed into the rice.Stir in the stock, lemon zest, and lemon juice. reduce the heat, stir and leave to cook covered 15-18 until the rice is just under cooked (Checking after about 15 minutes to make sure no additional stock is needed. If the risotto looks dry, add some of the remaining stock).'),(853183,4,'Add the Shrimp, broccoli and peas. Cook 5 minutes.'),(853183,5,'Add the chopped parsley, the remaining butter, and grated cheese.'),(853183,6,'Mix together and season to taste before serving.'),(853271,1,'Add the flour, eggs, and panko bread crumbs into three separate bowls. Be sure to whisk the eggs. Season the chicken cutlets with salt and pepper on both sides. Using a medium to large saute pan, heat the canola oil on medium high heat. Dredge the chicken cutlets through the flour and shake off excess, then the egg mixture, and finally the panko bread crumbs.'),(853271,2,'Place in the hot saute pan and cook on each side for 5-7 minutes until golden brown and crisp. Once the cutlets are cooked, turn to a baking sheet and sprinkle with a little more salt and pepper.'),(853271,3,'Place in oven on warm.Using a medium shallow saute pan, heat the olive oil for the sauce on medium heat.'),(853271,4,'Add the shallot and cook until translucent, about 3-5 minutes.'),(853271,5,'Add the garlic and cook for an additional 2 minutes. Next, add the white wine and allow to cook for about 5 minutes.'),(853271,6,'Add the juice of a lemon, capers, and rosemary. Reduce the heat to low. Next, add the butter allow to melt and simmer.'),(853271,7,'Whisk in the heavy cream until sauce is well combined. Strain the sauce into a serving dish ( I didnt want to strain my sauce but that is up to you).'),(853271,8,'Add salt and pepper as desired and serve on top of the chicken cutlets.'),(853694,1,'If your chicken is frozen thaw it out in the microwave oven. While it\'s thawing slice up or grate the mozzarella or use some of the pre shredded stuff.Salt and pepper both sides of the chicken and fry in the skillet just enough to sear the outside. They are going to cook some more in the oven.In a shallow bowl or baking sheet spread a little of the marinara sauce. Then lay the chicken out in the bowl - or pan - and top it with marinara sauce. A thicker layer than you have on the bottom.Chicken Parmesan-4-poppopcooks.com-chicken parmesan recipe-easy chicken parmesan-easy chicken parmesan recipe chicken recipes-quick and easy recipes-parmesan-chicken'),(853694,2,'Put on a layer of the mozzarellaI and just barely get it coated with a tiny bit of marinara just to keep it from getting any burnt crusty patches.Then a generous layer of grated parmesan cheese,'),(853694,3,'Sprinkle the dried basil, and lightly drizzle with some good extra virgin olive oil.Chicken Parmesan-5-poppopcooks.com-chicken parmesan recipe-easy chicken parmesan-easy chicken parmesan recipe chicken recipes-quick and easy recipes-parmesan-chicken'),(853694,4,'Then, into the oven it goes until the liquid on the bottom of the dish is bubbling and the cheese has melted. About 8 - 10 minutes. Then serve up and enjoy your Chicken Parmesan! Buon Appetito!Put on a layer of the mozzarella and just barely get it coated with a tiny bit of marinara just to keep it from getting any burnt crusty patches.Then a generous layer of grated parmesan cheese,'),(853694,5,'Sprinkle the dried basil, and lightly drizzle with some good extra virgin olive oil.Then, into the oven it goes until the liquid on the bottom of the dish is bubbling and the cheese has melted. About 8 - 10 minutes. Then serve up and enjoy your Chicken Parmesan! Buon Appetito!'),(853754,1,'Drizzle in olive oil and water and stir together until the mixture forms a dough. If its sticky, add more flour by the tablespoon. If the dough is cracking and dry, add an extra drizzle of water. Knead the dough in the bowl a few times to smooth it out. No need to knead it more than a few minutes. Then let the dough rest for 5-10 minutes.'),(853754,2,'Roll dough out on a clean surface into a large rectangle about the size of a baking sheet. The dough should be very thin, but not quite translucent.'),(853754,3,'Transfer dough to a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.'),(853754,4,'Brush dough with olive oil and sprinkle it with any toppings you want. Extra nutritional yeast is a must, but I also recommend sesame seeds and even a pinch of salt and/or pepper. Poke a bunch of holes in the dough with a fork and cut the dough into cracker sized pieces using either a knife or a roller.'),(853754,5,'Bake the crackers at 450 degrees F. for 13-15 minutes, rotating them once halfway through.'),(853754,6,'Let cool before breaking apart and serving.  Store extras (yea right) in an airtight bag at room temp for a few days.'),(854164,1,'Peel your sweet potatoes and chop them into the shape of wedges.Preheat your air fryer for 5 minutes at 180c.In a mixing bowl add all your seasonings and mix well.'),(854164,2,'Add your potato wedges, toss in the seasonings until they are well covered.'),(854164,3,'Place the potato wedges into the air fryer, toss in olive oil and cook for 20 minutes. Shake them every 5 minutes until they are cooked.Once they are cooked serve with a thousand island dip and sprinkle with a little extra chilli powder.'),(854565,1,'To begin making Methi, Mooli Makkai Paratha Recipe, we first prepare the ingredients one by one.Wash, peel and grate the radish and keep aside.Similarly, seperate out only the methi leaves from its stem, wash and roughly chop it and keep aside.Now, take a big bowl, squeeze out the water from the grated radish and add it into the bowl.'),(854565,2,'Add the chopped methi leaves, green chillies, makkai aata, gently crushed ajwain seeds between the palms, red chilli and coriander powder.Season with salt and mix the ingredients well.Now, slowly add the water or butter milk to make it into a tight dough. The maize will keep absorbing water into it.Divide the dough into 12 equal balls and keep aside.Now, line a butter or parchment paper on the kitchen slab, greese it with few drops of oil.Take one small dough ball, knead it till it becomes soft, and gently press it over the parchment paper.Pat it with your fingers and flat it out to the size of small poori\'s.'),(854565,3,'Heat skillet on medium flame, place the patted makkai roti over the skillet, add a few drops of oil / ghee on the sides and let it cook on the surface for 2-3 minutes.Flip over and cook the other side for another 3 minutes brushing it with little oil. Similarly, make the rest of the roti\'s.'),(854565,4,'Serve the Methi, Mooli Makkai Paratha Recipe along with Gur/jaggery, dollop of white butter and traditional'),(854565,5,'Sarson Ka Saagfor a weekend Punjabi cuisine inspired lunch.'),(854569,1,'Cut a large piece of wax paper and place it on top of a baking sheet.Unwrap and chop the butterfingers in small pieces. Put aside.In a microwave-safe bowl mix 1 cup chocolate chips and 1-tablespoon shortening. Melt in the microwave in intervals of 10 seconds, stirring in between to avoid overcooking.Use a knife to spread chocolate on top of wax paper. You want this layer to be  inch thick.For the second layer line saltine crackers on top of the melted chocolate.Melt the remaining chocolate and shortening.'),(854569,2,'Spread on top of the saltine crackers, the same way you did the first layer.Top with chopped butterfingers or your favorite candy bar.Put in the fridge for 30 minutes or until chocolate has hardened.'),(854569,3,'Cut in pieces and enjoy!'),(855213,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees and spray a bread pan with non-stick cooking spray'),(855213,2,'In a large bowl, sift together dry ingredients; flour, sugar, baking soda and salt'),(855213,3,'Add oil and eggs, one at a time. Beat after each addition'),(855213,4,'Add mashed banana and vanilla, beat well'),(855213,5,'Fold in nuts'),(855213,6,'Pour into pan ( recipe makes 1 regular loaf (9x'),(855213,7,'or 3-4 mini loaves)'),(855213,8,'Bake at 350 degrees - regular loaf 50-60 minutes or mini loaves 30-40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean'),(855218,1,'In a large skillet, cook beef and onions over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in uncooked spaghetti and the next eight ingredients; bring to a boil.  Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until the spaghetti is tender.'),(855218,2,'Sprinkle with cheese; cover and heat until melted.'),(855507,1,'Rub your frying pan with a little oil and heat on a medium to high heat until the pan is really hot.'),(855507,2,'Sift your flour into a bowl and add the salt.'),(855507,3,'In a jug, whisk your milk, agave nectar, oil and vanilla extract until well combined. Make a well in the middle of your flour and pour in most of the wet mixture. You want it to be like thick pouring cream, you may not need all the liquid.'),(855507,4,'Try a teaspoon full of your batter in your frying pan, to test if it is hot enough. It should bubble up quickly, flip, then cook on the other side for just a few seconds. You should have a wee golden pancake.'),(855507,5,'Cook the rest of your pancakes. Each pancake is made from a generous tablespoon of batter. They will take about 3 minutes each. Turn them when they start to bubble. You can have a sneak peek underneath using a palette knife to check it they are golden underneath and ready to flip.'),(855507,6,'Serve the pancakes warm with maple syrup.'),(855507,7,'Enjoy!'),(855630,1,'Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.'),(855630,2,'Add leeks, fennel, garlic,  tsp. salt and pepper flakes.Saut until vegetables are soft, about 5 minutes.'),(855630,3,'Add farro and toast for one to two minutes.'),(855630,4,'Add tomatoes in juice, chicken stock, rosemary, Parmesan rind and water.Bring to a boil and reduce to a simmer.Cook, stirring occasionally, until farro is tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.'),(855630,5,'Add carrots, beans, kielbasa and kale.Cook until carrots are just tender, about 30 minutes.'),(855630,6,'Remove rosemary sprig and Parmesan rind.Stir in lemon juice and serve.'),(856187,1,'Preheat oven to 375 degrees'),(856187,2,'Cut the tops of the mini sweet peppers and remove the seeds inside them'),(856187,3,'Wash them thoroughly and dry them'),(856187,4,'Baste the peppers with olive oil and place them in a baking pan'),(856187,5,'Bake them for about 20 minutes or until the outside skin starts to wrinkle'),(856187,6,'Remove from the oven and allow to cool'),(856187,7,'While the peppers are baking, assemble the stuffing'),(856187,8,'Cook the rice and strain itIn a small pan, heat the sunflower oil'),(856187,9,'Add the cumin seeds and let them brown slightly'),(856187,10,'Add the red onions and roast them until golden brown'),(856187,11,'Add the cooked rice and the beans'),(856187,12,'Add remaining ingredients'),(856187,13,'Stir well'),(856187,14,'Once the mini sweet peppers have cooled to the touch, stuff them with rice mixture'),(856187,15,'Be generous in your stuffing (about 2-3 tsp per pepper) but be gentle so as to not break them'),(856187,16,'Place the peppers in a baking pan again and top with your favorite Enchilada Sauce'),(856187,17,'Heat in the oven for 10 more minutes at 350 degrees'),(856187,18,'While the peppers are being heated, prepare the plate for serving'),(856187,19,'On the plate, add half a ladle of the creamy enchilada sauce'),(856187,20,'Place peppers on the sauce and top with more sauce if desired'),(856187,21,'Garnish with coriander'),(856777,1,'Preheat the oven to 450 and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.Peel the sweet potatoes, and cut both ends off.'),(856777,2,'Cut the sweet potatoes into 3-4\" slices and spiralize them. I used the 6mm blade on the Paderno spiralizer.'),(856777,3,'Place the spiralized sweet potatoes on the cookie sheet.'),(856777,4,'Cut both ends off the onion and peel away the tough outer layer, then spiralize it using the same blade.'),(856777,5,'Add the onion to the baking sheet with the sweet potato noodles.Toss the sweet potato and onion noodles with 1 tablespoon of the olive oil, balsamic vinegar, and Italian seasoning. Season with salt and pepper and roast the noodles until tender and beginning to caramelize, about 20 minutes.While the noodles cook, preheat a 9\" cast iron skillet over medium-high heat. When the pan is hot but not smoking, add the remaining tablespoon of olive oil along with the sliced sausage.Saut for 3-4 minutes until the sausage has browned on the edges. Then lower the heat to medium and add the baby spinach. Cook stirring until the spinach has just wilted.When the noodles are tender, toss them together with the sausage/spinach mixture, and season to taste with salt and pepper.'),(856777,6,'Serve immediately with parmesan if desired.'),(856796,1,'In your slow cooker, add all of your ingredients. Cook on low for 3-4 hours. Top with sour cream, avocado, tortilla strips and fresh cilantro. Easy, right?!'),(856890,1,'Place ingredients into a small ziplock bag or a small plastic bag closed tight with a twistee tie.To prepare soup, place contents of the bag into a 9 oz. or larger cup.'),(856890,2,'Add 6-8 oz boiling water. Stir and let sit for at least 5 minutes before eating.'),(856936,1,'Simply combine all the above ingredients (minus the whole wheat flour) into a small saucepan and allow to simmer for about 5-7 minutes. Then, youll want to blend the sauce into a more smooth puree. Its easy to do this with a stick blender if you have one, or you can transfer to a blender for a few seconds. Also add about a tablespoon of flour (to thicken) while blending. Finally, return to the saucepan and simmer for another 5 minutes until slightly thicker and adjust any spices/seasonings to taste. Done! This will save in a mason jar for up to a week.Part Two  The Jackfruit Filling'),(856936,2,'If using canned jackfruit (Ive never seen it fresh before) drain and rinse thoroughly, then pull the junks apart until it looks like pulled pork.'),(856936,3,'Add to a saucepan with the garlic, soy sauce, black pepper, and chili powder. Then, simply let it marinate over medium heat for about 10 minutes, stirring regularly to coat the jackfruit evenly. After 10 minutes, it will be darker and more tender. Basically, what would take 10 hours with meat takes 10 minutes with jackfruit. Amazing.Also at this point, grab some fresh or frozen corn, some cooked or canned black beans, and a few sprigs of fresh cilantro. Then, preheat the oven to 350 F.Part Three  The Enchilada'),(856936,4,'The first step of making the enchiladas is softening the tortillas. If the corn tortillas are hard and brittle, theyll be a nightmare to roll. My favorite way to do this is to moisten two paper towels, sandwich two tortillas between them, and microwave for 10 seconds. Then, while rolling those enchiladas, repeat the process with two more.To make the enchiladas, grab a deep 913 baking dish (or something similar) and lay out a thin layer of the enchilada sauce. Then take one of the warm tortillas and line with the jackfruit, the corn, the beans, and the cilantro.'),(856936,5,'Roll lengthwise around the filling, then place seam-side down in the pan. Repeat about 7 more times until the pan is full, then pour most of the remaining sauce over top (but reserve a few tablespoons for after cooking). Cover with foil and pop in the oven for about 25 minutes until the edges just start to turn golden. Note: You may have enough extra ingredients to make another smaller pan as well; just repeat the same process.At this point, you can use your blender to pulverize some raw cashews into powder, which can be sprinkled on top for a cheesy garnish. Or, you can skip that and just add a few more tablespoons of the green sauce. Then return to the oven, uncovered, for just a few minutes to further crispify the tortillas. Finally, use a spatula to plate the enchiladas and garnish with a sprig of cilantro.'),(857904,1,'(*optional)'),(857904,2,'Cut the crust off your bread one piece at a time'),(857904,3,'Spread peanut butter and jelly on one piece of bread.Now, cut out a shamrock from the center of another piece of bread.'),(857904,4,'Place that piece of bread (with the shamrock cut out) on top of your peanut butter and jelly bread.Now fill in the shamrock space with the sprinkles'),(857904,5,'Enjoy!'),(857990,1,'To prepare the dressing: In a high-speed blender, combine the seed butter, vinegar, olive oil, lemon juice, tamari, honey or maple syrup, garlic, ginger, salt, red pepper flakes, and water and blend until completely smooth. Set aside.In a large bowl, combine the lettuce, cabbage, carrots, bell pepper, and sunflower seeds.'),(857990,2,'Pour the dressing over the top and toss well to coat.'),(857990,3,'Serve immediately. This salad will wilt rather quickly after its dressed, so if you want to save a portion for later, store the salas and dressing separately in airtight containers in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.'),(858852,1,'Add all ingredients to large bowl and combine with your hands but do not over mix.Form meatballs between the palms of your hands.Flatten meatball and place a  inch cube of cream cheese into the center of the meatball.Wrap meat back around cream cheese and roll between your palms again to form into a meatball.'),(858852,2,'Place stuffed meatballs onto a Bradley rack or other pan for easy transport to the smoker.Set up smoker for cooking indirect at about 225-240F using pecan or other smoking wood.'),(858852,3,'Place meatballs into smoker and cook until they reach an internal temperature of 160F.'),(858852,4,'Serve meatballs immediately while they are still hot.'),(859332,1,'Heat your oil over medium high heat.'),(859332,2,'Add the shrimp, orange juice, and ginger. Cook for 3 minutes (or until shrimp turns pink) and remove from pan.'),(859332,3,'Add onions, carrots, peppers, scallions, mushrooms, and garlic. Cook for 5 minutes until soften but still \"al dente\".'),(859332,4,'Drizzle soy sauce and add shrimp.Toss quickly and serve over rice noodles or jasmine rice. Top with sesame seeds.'),(859967,1,'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.In a large bowl, mix the oats, flour, baking soda, sugar, salt, and spices.To the same bowl, stir in the remaining ingredients, including your add-ins.Dollop the batter onto a parchment paper-lined baking sheet (this makes eight cookies).'),(859967,2,'Bake 13-15 minutes until golden.Cool and enjoy!'),(860115,1,'Place the eggs in a pot with cold water, just enough cover the eggs. Bring to a boil without a lid.'),(860115,2,'Let the eggs simmer for about 8 minutes. Cool down quickly in cold water.Peel and chop the eggs finely. Stir in the butter, salt and pepper.'),(860115,3,'Add optional flavoring, suggestions below.'),(860115,4,'Serve as is or as a topping on seed crackers or as a dip for veggies like cucumber or celery stalks.'),(860849,1,'Preheat your oven to 350 {F}Mash your bananas in a mixing bowl and add in the eggs, mix together.'),(860849,2,'Add in your almond flour + coconut flour and mix well again.'),(860849,3,'Add in the rest of your ingredients and mix it all up! And absolutely feel free to add more chocolate chips Fill lined muffin tin with batter and bake muffins for 20-30 minutes until cooked all the way through and slightly golden on top.'),(861293,1,'Season chicken pieces with salt and pepper. Set aside.In a Ziploc bag, combine together the balsamic vinegar, olive oil, pepper flakes and oregano.'),(861293,2,'Add chicken pieces, seal and toss to coat the chicken pieces completely. Marinate chicken in the fridge for at least an hour.Preheat the oven to 425 degree F. Line a rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil.'),(861293,3,'Drain the chicken from the marinade and then place on the prepared baking sheet.'),(861293,4,'Bake for 20 minutes or until cooked through.'),(861293,5,'Serve with steamed rice and salad.'),(861332,1,'Add the almonds, oats, dates, pumpkin puree, protein powder, and spices to the food processor. Turn on until a choppy dough forms, several minutes.'),(861332,2,'Add 2 tablespoons of the raw pumpkin seeds, and pulse until combined so the pumpkin seeds remain a little coarse. The dough will be slightly sticky.In a small food processor or Nutri'),(861332,3,'Bullet, quickly chop the remaining 2 tablespoons of pumpkins seeds with the chocolate chips — this only takes 1 second; you want it chopped, not powdery.'),(861332,4,'Pour mixture into a small bowl.'),(861332,5,'Roll dough into 20 balls, roll each in the pumpkin seed and chocolate chip topping, and place on a clean cookie sheet. Refrigerate for at least 20 minutes to set. Store uneaten balls in an airtight container in the fridge.'),(861538,1,'Preheat oven to 400F. Arrange rack in the middle of the oven.In a medium skillet over medium heat, cook the sausage, about 3 minutes.'),(861538,2,'Add the peppers and scallions and cook until soft, about 3 minutes.Divide sausage mixture in 4 individual souffle dishes; top with cheese.'),(861538,3,'Add 1 beaten egg to each dish.'),(861538,4,'Bake for 15 17 minutes until eggs are firm.'),(861701,1,'In a large stainless steel mixing bowl, whisk together eggs, yolks and granulated sugar.'),(861701,2,'Whisk in the blood orange juice, lemon juice and blood orange zest.Bring a pot of water to a simmer.'),(861701,3,'Place bowl over simmering water and cook curd, while stirring with a whisk. Continue to cook until curd begins to thicken, about 10-12 minutes.'),(861701,4,'Remove from the heat.'),(861701,5,'Whisk in butter until melted and well combined.Strain the curd through a fine mesh sieve. Chill for at least 2 hours before enjoying. You can make the curd three days in advance.'),(861870,1,'1 Prepare pasta according to package directions.'),(861870,2,'Place in large bowl.2 For pesto, place spinach, basil, Parmesan cheese, lemon juice, olive oil, water and red pepper flakes in food processor. Pulse until combined. Season with salt and pepper, as desired.3'),(861870,3,'Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.'),(861870,4,'Add garlic, shallot, carrots and bell pepper. Cook 4 to 5 minutes or until carrots are crisp-tender.'),(861870,5,'Add zucchini, summer squash, mushrooms and cherry tomatoes. Cook 4 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are just tender. Season with salt and pepper, as desired.4'),(861870,6,'Add vegetables and pesto to pasta. Toss to combine.'),(862633,1,'Add chipotle, molasses, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard, hot sauce, tomato sauce, and salt. Stir to combine and bring mixture to a simmer, reduce heat to medium low and let flavors combine simmering for 10 minutes.'),(862633,2,'Remove sauce from heat and blend until smooth in a standing blender.Meanwhile, heat a large saute pan over medium high heat with remaining vegetable oil. Season pork chops on both sides with salt and pepper.'),(862633,3,'Add to oil in saute pan and cook for about 2-3 minutes per side depending on the thickness until cooked through.'),(862633,4,'Remove pork chops from heat.To serve, assemble a sort of open faced sandwich with pork chops on top of cornbread smothered in barbecue sauce.'),(862644,1,'Preheat the oven to 350F. Lightly spray a 12-cup muffin tin with non-stick spray and set aside.In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, and brown sugar until combined. In another bowl, whisk together the buttermilk, melted butter, egg and vanilla.'),(862644,2,'Add this mixture to the dry ingredients and whisk together until well combined.Divide the pancake batter between the prepared muffin cups.'),(862644,3,'Sprinkle the berries on top of the muffins and drizzle them with maple syrup (about 1/4 teaspoon per muffin).'),(862644,4,'Bake for 18-20 minutes, or until puffed and lightly browned on the edges.Pancake muffins freeze well in an airtight container for up to 3 months. You can enjoy them either warm or cold, served with jam or maple syrup.'),(862977,1,'In a small bowl, whisk together the psyllium and yeast. In a stand mixer bowl fitted with a beater attachment, add the almond milk, applesauce, egg whites, and butter flavor. Turn on medium speed. While mixing, sprinkle in the psyllium/yeast mixture.'),(862977,2,'Mix until smooth. Scrape down the sides of the bowl, then mix until smooth again.'),(862977,3,'Mixture should look like thick gravy. In a medium-sized bowl, whisk together the soy flour, coconut flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.'),(862977,4,'Add to the stand mixer and mix on low speed. Scrape down the sides of the bowl and mix on last time. Dough should be very thick, dense, and slightly sticky. Shape the dough into a ball and cover the bowl with plastic wrap.'),(862977,5,'Place the bowl in a warm area for 1 hour. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit and line two cookie sheets with Silpats or parchment paper. Divide the dough into 8 equal portions. Carefully roll the dough into long logs (if the log breaks, just stick it back and it\'ll be fine... these are gluten free, so that\'s kinda expected right?) and carefully shape into pretzels. Carefully transfer the pretzels onto the prepared pans. In a small bowl, whisk together the egg yolk and water.'),(862977,6,'Brush the pretzels with the egg wash and sprinkle with the salt.'),(862977,7,'Bake for ~23-25 minutes, or until golden brown.'),(862977,8,'Let cool slightly and serve warm!'),(864405,1,'Cook sausage.'),(864405,2,'Add carrots, onions, 2 tbsp water, and thyme.'),(864405,3,'Cook 15 minutes.'),(864405,4,'Preheat broiler.'),(864405,5,'Combine panko with olive oil, thyme. Return sausage to pan with beans, tomatoes, and 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Simmer for 5 minutes.'),(864449,1,'Pour milk into Instant Pot cooking pot and cover with Glass Lid or Black IP Lid.Push the Yogurt button and then the Adjust button. The display should read \"Boil.\" During the Boil cycle, remove the lid and whisk the milk a couple of times during the cycle.When Beep sounds, remove lid and take temperature.. Anywhere from 170-180 degrees is fine. Slowly pour in the vinegar and gently move around the milk. It will begin to look curdled. Cover the milk with the Glass Lid and let sit for at least 30 minutes.'),(864449,2,'Add Salt to the Cream and'),(864449,3,'Whisk together. Set aside.'),(864449,4,'Pour the'),(864449,5,'Cottage Cheeseinto a Strainer Basket, sitting inside of a Cooking Pot or other device to catch the Whey.'),(864449,6,'Remove Strainer Basket to sink and run a slow stream of cool water over the Strainer Basket to remove excess Vinegar.'),(864449,7,'Place Cottage Cheese into bowl.'),(864449,8,'Pour Salt/Cream into bowl and gently incorporate.Refrigerate and enjoy.'),(864835,1,'Puree frozen pineapple, banana, coconut milk, collagen, lime juice, vanilla and sea salt in a high-powered blender until smooth.'),(864835,2,'Pour into an individual serving bowl or glass.'),(864835,3,'Garnish with additional pineapple chunks, shredded coconut and lime zest.'),(864835,4,'Serve cold.'),(864937,1,'Make the salsa verde: Whiz parsley leaves and 1/2 cup oil in a food processor or blender to a pesto-like consistency, then transfer to a small bowl. (Alternatively, chop parsley by hand and combine with oil.)'),(864937,2,'Add garlic, chopped olives, anchovies, capers, lemon zest and red pepper to parsley mixture and stir well. Season with salt if necessary and freshly ground black pepper to taste. Thin with more oil as desired.'),(864937,3,'Cut baguette crosswise into 4 equal pieces, then split each lengthwise with a serrated knife. (If using rolls, split each lengthwise.) For each sandwich, lay bread flat, crust side down.'),(864937,4,'Spread cut sides with 2 tablespoons salsa verde. Put a few lettuce leaves on 1 piece of bread and arrange 2 ounces of tuna over lettuce. Top tuna with 1 egg, quartered. Season egg lightly with salt and pepper.'),(864937,5,'Add sliced serrano chile, if using.'),(864937,6,'Drizzle with a little more salsa verde, then press sandwich closed.'),(865258,1,'Place sweet potatoes in a large saucepan and cover with cold water.'),(865258,2,'Heat water to 160°F (70°C) as registered on an instant-read thermometer. Cover and set aside for 1 hour.'),(865258,3,'Adjust oven racks to upper-middle and lower-middle positions and preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).'),(865258,4,'Drain sweet potatoes and transfer to a large bowl. Toss with oil and season to taste with salt and pepper.'),(865258,5,'Spread sweet potatoes on 2 rimmed baking sheets and roast until bottom sides are browned, about 30 minutes. Carefully flip potatoes with a thin spatula and roast until second side is browned and potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes longer.'),(865258,6,'Meanwhile, in a small container, sprinkle gelatin over chicken stock and let bloom for 5 minutes. Microwave until gelatin is dissolved, stopping and stirring as needed to help it dissolve, about 2 minutes.'),(865258,7,'In a small saucepan, melt butter over medium-high heat until foamy. Continue to cook, swirling pan, until milk solids in butter turn a deep hazelnut brown, 1 to 2 minutes.'),(865258,8,'Remove from heat and add rosemary (don\'t be alarmed; butter will foam and fizzle when rosemary is added), swirling to coat.'),(865258,9,'Add chicken stock to butter, return to medium heat, and bring to a simmer. Cook, swirling, until stock reduces slightly and sauce becomes rich and silky, about 3 minutes.'),(865258,10,'Remove from heat, discard rosemary, and add lemon juice. Season with salt.'),(865258,11,'In a mixing bowl, toss potatoes with butter sauce and serve. Potatoes can be made in advance, tossed with sauce, and set aside until ready to serve; rewarm in the oven before serving.'),(865341,1,'Follow the video tutorial for assembly'),(865468,1,'To begin making the'),(865468,2,'Baked Fish In Coconut Milk recipe, in a mixing bowl, add lemon juice and oil and mix it with the fish fillets.'),(865468,3,'Let the fish marinade for 1 hour in refrigerator.Pre heat the oven to 350 degree C. In a fry pan heat 1/4 cup of oil and fry onion till golden.'),(865468,4,'Add minced garlic, ginger and green chilies and stir for 2 mins.Now add tomatoes, spices, crushed fennel seeds and salt to taste. Fry for 3 to 4 minutes till tomatoes are tender.'),(865468,5,'Add coconut milk and simmer for 5 minutes until thick.Take the fish out from the fridge and arrange them on a greased baking tray or a cast iron pan.'),(865468,6,'Bake the fish for 10 mins.'),(865468,7,'Pour the coconut milk sauce all over the fish. cover the baking tray/pan tightly with aluminium foil and return to the oven to bake for another 15 minutes.Carefully remove the pan and the foil and garnish with chopped coriander and serve hot.'),(865468,8,'Serve'),(865468,9,'Baked Fish In Coconut Milk along with'),(865468,10,'Steamed ricefor a weeknight dinner.'),(865700,1,'Preheat the oven to 35'),(865700,2,'Lightly mist 12 cups in a muffin tin with cooking spray.'),(865700,3,'Combine the oats, brown sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl and stir until thoroughly mixed.In a separate bowl, whisk together the egg white, egg, milk, yogurt and vanilla.'),(865700,4,'Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and stir until blended together. Stir in the raspberries and peaches.Spoon the oatmeal mixture evenly between the prepared muffin cups.'),(865700,5,'Bake uncovered for 22-25 minutes or until oatmeal is lightly browned and a toothpick inserted into the middle comes out clean.'),(865719,1,'Make the Crust: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.'),(865719,2,'Combine the Oreo cookie crumbs and the melted butter in a medium bowl and toss with a fork until the crumbs are evenly moistened.'),(865719,3,'Transfer the crumbs to a 9-inch pie plate. Press the crumbs evenly into the bottom and up the sides of the pan, forming a crust. Refrigerate the lined pie plate for 20 minutes.'),(865719,4,'Bake for 10 minutes, until the crust is fragrant and set. Cool on a wire rack while the filling is prepared.Make the Chocolate Cream Filling: Bring the half-and-half, salt and 3 tablespoons of the sugar to a simmer in a medium saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally with a wooden spoon to dissolve the sugar. Stir together the remaining sugar and cornstarch in a small bowl.'),(865719,5,'Whisk the yolks thoroughly in a medium bowl for about 30 seconds, until slightly thickened.'),(865719,6,'Add the cornstarch mixture and whisk until the mixture is glossy and the sugar has begun to dissolve, about 1 minute. When the half-and-half reaches a full simmer, drizzle about  cup hot half-and-half over the yolks, whisking constantly to temper; then whisk the egg yolk mixture into the simmering half-and-half. Return to a simmer, whisking constantly, until 3 or 4 bubbles burst on the surface and mixture is thickened and glossy, about 15 seconds longer.Off the heat, whisk in the butter, one piece at a time, until incorporated; add the chopped chocolate and whisk until melted, scraping the bottom of the pan with a rubber spatula to fully incorporate. Stir in the vanilla, then immediately pour the filling through a fine-mesh sieve set over a bowl. Using a spatula, scrape the strained filling into the baked and cooled crust and spread into an even layer. Press plastic wrap directly on the surface of the filling and refrigerate the pie until the filling is cold and firm, about 3 hours.Make the Whipped Cream Topping: When ready to serve, beat the cream, sugar, and vanilla on low speed until small bubbles form, about 30 seconds.Increase the speed to medium and beat untilthe beaters leave a trail, about 30 seconds more. Increase speed to high and beat until the whipped cream is smooth and thick, forming soft peaks, about 20 more seconds.'),(865719,7,'Spread or pipe the whipped cream over the chilled filling and serve. Leftovers should be stored, covered, in the refrigerator for up to 2 days.'),(866046,1,'Preheat the oven to 325ºF(160ºC). Grease a 9- or 10-inch (23-25 cm) cake or spring form pan with butter,dust it with flour and tap out any excess. Line the bottom of the pan with around of parchment paper. (See Note, below.)'),(866046,2,'In the bowl of a foodprocessor, grind the sugar, almond paste, and 1/4 cup (35g) of flour until thealmond paste is finely ground and the mixture resembles sand.'),(866046,3,'In a small bowl, whisktogether the remaining 3/4 cup (105g) of flour, baking powder, and salt.'),(866046,4,'Once the almond paste iscompletely broken up, add the cubes of butter and the vanilla and almondextracts, then process until the batter is very smooth and fluffy.'),(866046,5,'Add the eggs one at a time,processing a bit before the next addition. (You may wish to open the machineand scrape the sides down to make sure the eggs are getting fullyincorporated.) After you add all the eggs, the mixture may look curdled. Don’tworry; it’ll come back together after the next step.'),(866046,6,'Add half the flour mixtureand pulse the machine a few times, then add the rest, pulsing the machine untilthe dry ingredients are just incorporated, but do not overmix. (You can alsotransfer the batter to a bowl and mix the dry ingredients in, which ensures thedry ingredients get incorporated evenly and you don’t overbeat it.)'),(866046,7,'Scrape the batter into theprepared cake pan and bake the cake for 45-60 minutes, or until the top is deepbrown and feels set when you press in the center.'),(866046,8,'Remove the cake from theoven and run a sharp or serrated knife around the perimeter, loosing the cakefrom the sides of the pan.'),(866046,9,'Let the cake cool completely in the pan.'),(866689,1,'Make the orange syrup:In a medium saucepan, whisk together the orange juice, sugar and cornstarch. Bring the mixture to a boil and cook it, stirring occasionally, until it thickens enough to coat the back of a spoon, about 5 minutes.'),(866689,2,'Remove it from the heat and immediately stir in the orange zest, vanilla extract and butter until the butter is melted.'),(866689,3,'Serve the orange syrup warm atop the French toast roll-ups (recipe follows) or store it in an airtight container in the fridge for up to 1 week.Make the French toast roll-ups:Using a rolling pin, roll each slice of bread until it is flattened. Set the bread aside.In a medium bowl, combine the cream cheese, orange zest and vanilla extract. Using a handheld mixer or a spatula, beat the mixture until combined.'),(866689,4,'Spread a portion of the mixture atop each slice of bread and tightly roll up the bread slices lengthwise.In a shallow dish, whisk together the eggs and milk. In a separate shallow dish, whisk together the cinnamon and sugar.'),(866689,5,'Heat a large nonstick saut pan over medium heat.'),(866689,6,'Add the butter and once it has melted, dip each French toast roll-up in the egg-milk mixture then place it in the saut pan. Repeat the dipping and cooking process with the remaining roll-ups, turning them in the pan until all sides are golden brown.Once the roll-ups are cooked, immediately transfer them to the cinnamon-sugar mixture, coating them on all sides.'),(866689,7,'Serve the French toast roll-ups topped with the orange syrup for dipping.'),(866819,1,'Make the Toffee: Take a 8x8 pan, line with parchment paper and set aside. In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, butter, and water together. Stir on medium heat until sugar is dissolved and butter has melted. Once the mixture is brought to a boil, place a candy thermometer inside and do not stir. You want the temperature to reach somewhere between soft and hard crack status (this will take around 10 minutes). At around 300 degrees, place the peanut butter into the saucepan and stir.'),(866819,2,'Remove from heat and add the vanilla and baking soda.'),(866819,3,'Pour into 8x8 pan. Allow the toffee to set for a couple of minutes. You will notice that the longer it sits, the harder it will become. You want to \"score\" (see post for definition) the candy before it completely sets so don\'t waste too much time letting it cool.'),(867355,1,'Add olive oil to a large skillet and heat until oil is very hot.'),(867355,2,'Add ground chicken and cook until no longer pink and starts to brown, break it up with a wooden spoon as necessary. Should take about 3 minutes.'),(867355,3,'Add red curry paste, ginger, garlic, peppers, coleslaw mix, and stir-fry for another 3 minutes.'),(867355,4,'Add hoisin sauce and green onions, and toss.'),(867355,5,'Remove from heat then add basil and toss.'),(867355,6,'Transfer cooked chicken to a bowl.'),(867355,7,'Serve by placing spoonfuls of chicken into pieces of lettuce, fold lettuce over like small tacos, and eat.'),(868064,1,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Lightly grease a 12 muffin pan. Divide the onion, green pepper, and ham evenly over the 12 muffin tins.'),(868064,2,'Add the cheddar cheese evenly on the top.In a medium sized bowl whisk the eggs, half and half, salt and pepper.'),(868064,3,'Pour over the top of the cheese and fill the liner until almost full.'),(868064,4,'Bake for 20-22 minutes or until set.'),(868064,5,'Remove and serve warm or let cool and store in the refrigerator or freezer. Reheat from fridge for about 30 seconds or frozen for about 1 minute or until heated through.'),(868075,1,'Heat the butter in a small skillet over medium high heat.'),(868075,2,'Add the garlic and shrimp; sprinkle with the chili powder and cayenne directly in the pan.'),(868075,3,'Saute for a few minutes on each side until the shrimp are no longer clear and have a nice golden color on the outside.'),(868075,4,'Cut the avocados in half; cut lines through the avocado vertically and horizontally and scoop the flesh out with a spoon (like this). Peel and dice the cucumber. Chop the spinach or baby kale into small bite sized pieces. Arrange in a bowl with the shrimp.Puree all the dressing ingredients together in a food processor until smooth. Taste and adjust to your preferences.'),(868075,5,'Pour the dressing over the salad and serve immediately (or store the individual parts separately in the refrigerator until ready to serve). Top with fresh cilantro and peanuts for crunch.'),(868488,1,'Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Season both sides of chicken with salt and pepper.'),(868488,2,'Add chicken to skillet and cook through, about 6 to 8 minutes on each side.'),(868488,3,'Transfer to a plate.Reduce heat to medium and add garlic cloves to pan. (If the skillet is looking dry, add a bit more olive oil.) Cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Then add chicken stock, scraping up the bottom of the skillet with a wooden spoon. Bring to simmer, then stir in heavy cream, lime juice, and cilantro. Return chicken to skillet and spoon sauce over each breast.'),(868488,4,'Serve chicken over white rice, spooning more sauce over each breast.'),(868488,5,'Garnish with more cilantro and serve with lime wedges.'),(868578,1,'Preheat oven to 40'),(868578,2,'Set a wire rack inside a large rimmed baking sheet. Season steak with kosher salt and 2 tablespoons spice rub, pressing onto all sides of meat and adding more spice rub by the teaspoonful if needed to coat entire surface.'),(868578,3,'Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a large cast-iron or other ovenproof skillet over high heat. When oil begins to shimmer, place steak in skillet (be sure to have fan on high; the rub creates some smoke). Sear steak for 1 minute (any longer and the rub will start to burn).'),(868578,4,'Transfer steak to a plate and carefully drain fat from skillet.Wipe skillet clean with a paper towel.'),(868578,5,'Heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil in skillet and sear other side of steak for 1 minute.'),(868578,6,'Add butter, garlic, and herbs to skillet; cook until butter is foamy. Carefully tip skillet and, using a large spoon, baste steak repeatedly with butter for 1 minute. Turn steak and baste other side for 1 minute.Pile herbs on top of steak, transfer skillet to oven, and roast until an instant-read thermometer inserted horizontally into center of meat registers 125 for medium, 15-17 minutes.'),(868578,7,'Transfer steak to prepared rack; let rest for 20 minutes.'),(868578,8,'Cut steak from bone, slice, and sprinkle with sea salt.'),(868674,1,'Prepare dressing my adding everything except salt and pepper to a glass jar.'),(868674,2,'Mix os shake until well incorporated.'),(868674,3,'Add salt and pepper to taste. Set aside.To assemble salad, add salad greens to bowl. Arrange vegetables in rainbow color order OR just throw them in and mix.'),(868674,4,'Serve with orange vinaigrette dressing. Enjoy!'),(868907,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 F. Line a 13x9 pan with heavy-duty aluminum foil or parchment paper. Lightly grease the foil or the parchment paper.'),(868907,2,'Place the flour, powdered sugar, cold butter and vanilla extract in the bowl of a food processor. Pulse until the mixture just comes together but is still crumbly. Press the mixture onto the bottom of the prepared pan.'),(868907,3,'Bake for 20-25 minutes or just until golden brown and baked through.Meanwhile, in a large bowl, whisk together the eggs, granulated sugar, lemon zest and juice until blended.'),(868907,4,'Combine the -cup of flour, baking powder and salt in a small bowl.'),(868907,5,'Whisk it into the egg mixture until blended.'),(868907,6,'Pour the lemon mixture over the prepared crust.'),(868907,7,'Bake on the middle oven rack for 30 to 35 minutes, or until the filling is set and firm.'),(868907,8,'Let cool in a pan on a wire rack for 30 minutes. Lift from the pan onto a wire rack, using the foil or parchment paper sides as handles.'),(868907,9,'Let cool for 30 minutes or until completely cool.'),(868907,10,'Cut into 24 (2-inch) squares.Just before serving, dust with powdered sugar and place on a serving platter.'),(869153,1,'Preheat a large stock pot over medium high heat.  Once hot, add the oil.'),(869153,2,'Add the brisket, fat, jalapeno and poblano peppers, and 1 onion.  Cook for 3 minutes.'),(869153,3,'Add the cumin, coriander, turmeric, pepper, and pepper flakes.  Flip meat and cook for about 3 minutes more until browned.'),(869153,4,'Add stock and water, bring to a boil, and reduce to a simmer.'),(869153,5,'Place a lid on the pot and cook for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally, adding more water if needed.'),(869153,6,'Add the remaining onion, fennel, potatoes, and carrots and cook for an additional hour with the lid on, stirring occasionally.'),(869153,7,'Remove the lid and taste for seasoning.'),(869153,8,'Add more spice, pepper, or some salt as suits your taste.'),(869153,9,'Add the kale.  Cook for an additional 20 minutes with the lid off to allow the liquid to reduce.'),(869153,10,'Serve immediately.  Chili may also be stored in the refrigerator in an airtight container for 3 days or frozen in an airtight container for up to 3 months.  Reheat in the microwave or on the stovetop until piping hot.'),(869329,1,'Place in the oven and bake uncovered for 1 hour.  This will soften the ribs to prepare for the second baking with the sauce.For the sauce:In a saucepan, over medium high heat, add oil and saut onions until transluscent, about 3 minutes.'),(869329,2,'Add the chopped garlic and saut for another minute.'),(869329,3,'Add ketchup and water. Stir to combine.'),(869329,4,'Add sugar, Worcestershire sauce, dijon and lemon juice. Simmer over low heat. Season with salt and pepper to your liking. I simmered this for about 5-7 minutes.This is what the ribs will look like after 1 hour ok baking.'),(869329,5,'Add the simmered sauce over the ribs and bake again for another 1 hour and 30 minutes or until ribs are falling off the bone and the sauce has thickened.'),(869329,6,'Serve and Enjoy!Source: Purpose Driven Chef'),(869805,1,'In a large skillet, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp.'),(869805,2,'Remove from skillet using a slotted spoon, and let drain on paper towels, reserving drippings in skillet.'),(869805,3,'Sprinkle shrimp with  teaspoon each salt and pepper.'),(869805,4,'Add shrimp to skillet, and cook over medium-high heat until pink and firm, about 4 minutes.'),(869805,5,'Add peas; cook over medium-low heat for 1 minute. Stir in alfredo sauce, half-and-half, and parsley, and bring to a low boil.'),(869805,6,'Add fettuccine and remaining  teaspoon each salt and teaspoon pepper, tossing to combine. Top with cheese and bacon.'),(869805,7,'Serve immediately.'),(869898,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees (F)'),(869898,2,'Combine the crust ingredients in a medium bowl and mix well with a fork until a dough forms.Press into an 8 inch springform pan or pie plate.'),(869898,3,'Bake the crust for 15 minutes, or until light golden brown.Cool until firm - about 15 minutes.'),(869898,4,'Combine the strawberries, cream cheese, xanthan gum, erythritol, and vanilla extract in a blender and puree until smooth.Whip the 1 cup heavy whipping cream and 1 Tbsp erythritol until stiff peaks form.Gently fold the strawberry puree mixture into the cream until combined.Spoon into the cooled pie crust and chill for at least 1 hour, or freeze for at least 2 hours.'),(869898,5,'Combine the cream, sweetener and vanilla in a large bowl and whip with a mixer or by hand until fluffy peaks form.Carefully spoon over the center of the pie, leaving a 2 inch border of pink showing all the way around.'),(869898,6,'Garnish with fresh strawberries if desired and serve cold.'),(871108,1,'Transfer to side dish and sprinkle with, salt and pepper.Return skillet to medium high heat, add 3-4 tablespoons butter and dash of oil.'),(871108,2,'Add liver and cook about 5 minutes until brown.'),(871108,3,'Remove liver and onions from pan and plate.Use stock to deglaze pan and reduce liquid til you have a thickened sauce.'),(871108,4,'Sprinkle with parsley if desired and serve.'),(871118,1,'Heat oven to 275 degrees.Wrap ham completely in heavy duty aluminum foil and place in a roasting pan.If ham is not sliced, use a knife to cut a crosshatch pattern, only going about 1/4-inch deep. This will help keep the glaze on the ham.'),(871118,2,'Bake for about 2 1/2 hours. The ham is already fully cooked, but you want it to reach an internal temperature of 120 degrees.'),(871118,3,'Combine all ingredients for glaze in a medium bowl and mix well.'),(871118,4,'Remove ham from oven and raise oven temp to 400 degrees.'),(871118,5,'Brush glaze all over ham, being sure to get a little between the slices.'),(871118,6,'Place ham back in oven for 10 minutes. You can keep it loosely wrapped in foil or pull the foil down and away from the ham.'),(871118,7,'Remove ham from oven, baste again and place ham under broiler for a few minutes to get glaze golden brown.'),(871599,1,'Label gallon freezer bag with contents, directions, and date.Chop chicken into small bite sized pieces.*Tip- slightly frozen chicken slices easily'),(871599,2,'Place diced chicken in gallon freezer bag.'),(871599,3,'Pour honey, soy sauce, ginger,water, crushed garlic, and black pepper on top of chicken.Seal bag, pressing flat and pushing all air out.Generously coat slow cooker with nonstick cooking spray.'),(871599,4,'Pour contents of thawed bag into slow cooker.Cook on low for 5-6 hours.'),(871599,5,'Serve over rice or noodles and sprinkle with sesame seeds to serve.'),(872098,1,'For the Meatballs'),(872098,2,'Combine the beef, pork, egg yolks, parsley, salt, pepper, cinnamon, nutmeg, and cloves in a bowl.'),(872098,3,'Heat a skillet to medium and add ½ Tablespoon of lard/cooking fat.'),(872098,4,'Add the minced onion and garlic and stir-fry for a minute.'),(872098,5,'Add to the meat bowl.'),(872098,6,'Mix the contents of the bowl until well blended.Form about 2 Tablespoons worth into a ball.'),(872098,7,'Heat a cast iron skillet to medium and add the rest of the lard/cooking fat.'),(872098,8,'Add about ten balls to the skillet and cook for about 8-10 minutes, continuously rotating each ball, until they are nice and browned.'),(872098,9,'Remove the balls and place in a strainer to drain. Repeat cooking the balls in a few more batches.For the Gravy'),(872098,10,'Add the onion and garlic to the skillet and cook for about a minute.'),(872098,11,'Add the coconut milk, broth, butter, and pepper.'),(872098,12,'Whisk and continue to cook for about 5 minutes.'),(872098,13,'Add the tapioca flour one tablespoon at a time and whisk until dissolved. If the gravy clumps then transfer the contents to a blender and blend. Taste and add salt if desired.'),(872098,14,'Remove from heat and return the meatballs to the sauce.'),(872098,15,'Serve with mashed potatoes and lingonberry jam.'),(872259,1,'first soak cashews in hot water for 20 to 30 minutes.meanwhilerinse 4 cups tightly packed spinach very well and then drain the excess water.heat 3.5 cups water till it starts boiling. switch off the flame and then add the spinach leaves. let the spinach leaves blanch in the hot water for 2 minutes.then with the help of tongs remove the leaves and place them in a grinder jar. you can even strain the blanched leaves in a colander/strainer and then add them to the blender jar.next add chopped green chilies, roughly chopped ginger and the soakedcashews in the grinder jar.grind to a smooth puree. there should be no bits of cashews in the puree. keep aside.heat 2 tablespoons ghee or oil in a pan.keep the flame to a low when adding spices, so that they do not get burnt.add teaspoon cumin seeds and let them crackle.then add1 tej patta,1 inch cinnamon,4 cloves,2 green cardamoms,1 or 2 single strands of mace,1 dry red chili anda generous pinch of asafoetida.stir well.then add teaspoon dry methi leaves or kasuri methi (crushed) and teaspoon finely chopped ginger. mix very well and saute till raw aroma of ginger goes away.next add teaspoon turmeric powder and teaspoon red chili powder.mix well.now add the spinach puree andmix very well.season with salt as per taste.then add to  teaspoon sugar.add to  cup water or add as required. mix very well.on a low to medium flame simmer the gravy for 6 to 7 minutes. stir at intervals.then add to teaspoon lemon juice.  teaspoon lemon juice makes palak paneer slightly sour and the tang is felt. so you can add accordingly. mix well.then add paneer cubes and  teaspoon garam masala powder.if you want you can add 1 to 2 tablespoons cream at this step.stir very well and cook for a minute.serve palak paneer hot or warm with steamed rice, peas pulao, jeera rice or with chapatis, phulkas or naan.'),(872604,1,'firstly, in a small blender take peas, ginger and chilli.blend to coarse paste without. keep aside.further, in a large kadai heat oil.add in cumin seeds and saute till they turn aromatic.also add in spices and saute.further add blended peas and saute.also add salt and coriander leaves. mix and keep aside.firstly, in a large mixing bowl add maida, rava and oil and salt.crumble the flour well with oil.in addition, add water and knead to form a dough. rest for 15 mins.now pinch a ball sized ball and flatten it.scoop prepared matar stuffing.get the edges together and form a bundle.deep fry kachoris to golden brown.finally, serve matar kachori.'),(872803,1,'Begin by preparing the tart crusts. Soak the dates if they are not already very soft to the touch.Once dates are soft, add to a food processor with the rest of the crust ingredients and process for 2 minutes on high, stopping the processor periodically to scrape the sides with a spatula.The mixture will become sticky, clumped together, and slightly oily with only small chunks of almonds and walnuts remaining.Using a regular sized muffin tin, take a golf-ball sized portion of the crust mixture, roll into a ball with your palms, then press evenly into a muffin tin cup to create a crust that\'s about 1 cm thick on all sides.Repeat this process to create 8 crusts in total.'),(872803,2,'Place the muffin tin in the freezer for 15-20 minutes so the crusts can harden.Once the crusts are firm to the touch, carefully remove each crust from the muffin tin and place on a large plate or platter.Next, mix the coconut yogurt with the sweetener of choice, if using, and divide between the chocolaty crusts until they are each filled with yogurt, then place back in the freezer.'),(872803,3,'Heat a small non-stick pan over low heat or a double boiler and melt the chocolate.Once the chocolate is melted, remove the tarts from the freezer and drizzle the chocolate over each tart.Finish by topping each tart with additional superfood toppings as desired.Enjoy!'),(873343,1,'Preheat oven to 450 F. Lightly Spray 9x11 baking pan.In mixing bowl combine flour and your choice of liquid (cream, buttermilk, or whole milk).Stir just until blended. do not over mix.'),(873343,2,'Transfer dough to a lightly floured surfaced and knead dough 10 times.Using rolling pin, roll dough to 1/2 inch thick.'),(873343,3,'Cut with a 2 inch cutter or drinking glass,'),(873343,4,'Place biscuits close together on baking sheet.'),(873343,5,'Bake 10 minutes. till lightly browned.'),(874494,1,'Soak dried chickpeas overnight, they should swell and look the same as canned ones but still quite hard.In a food processor combine all falafel ingredients and process until you have a paste.'),(874494,2,'Roll falafel into small balls, approximately 2 inches in diameter, then flatten them slightly with your hand.'),(874494,3,'Heat 2-3 tablespoons of olive oil and fry falafel until crispy all around for approximately 3 minutes on each side. Set aside.Cook bulgar according to package instructions and set aside to cool.Once bulgar is cooled combine with all vegetables, herbs and dress with lemon juice, olive oil and salt to taste.Set your oven to a broil/grill mode on a highest temperature and set an oven rack approximately 6\" away from the top element.'),(874494,4,'Place two eggplants on an aluminium lined shallow baking tray and cook for 15 minutes until the outside is charred and smoky and the inside collapses and turns into a mush.Cool until safe to handle and remove the burned skin.In a food processor or a blender combine eggplant flesh, sliced garlic, tahini, lemon juice, smoked paprika and run until smooth and creamy, then open the shoot and add olive oil with the motor still running until baba ganoush is desired consistency.'),(874494,5,'Add salt to taste.'),(874494,6,'Add all ingredients to the food processor and process until smooth'),(874494,7,'In a jam jar combine all ingredients except for water, put a lid on and shake very hard until you have a homogenised dressing, add water 1 tbsp at a time until you have a desired consistency.'),(874742,1,'Preheat oven to 400F (200C). To make the Parmesan Wafers, place the quinoa, Parmesan and pepper in a bowl and toss to combine.'),(874742,2,'Place tablespoons of the mixture on a baking tray lined with non-stick baking paper and bake for 57 minutes or until golden. Allow to cool on the tray and set aside.'),(874742,3,'Place the tomatoes, basil and garlic on a baking tray lined with non-stick baking paper and drizzle with oil. Roast for 45 minutes or until the tomatoes are soft and the basil is crisp.'),(874742,4,'Spread the quinoa on a separate baking tray lined with non-stick baking paper, drizzle with oil and toss to coat. Roast for the last 15 minutes of the tomato cooking time. Reserve and set aside the crispy basil leaves. Squeeze the roasted garlic from its skin into a large saucepan.'),(874742,5,'Add the tomatoes and stock and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat to medium and simmer for 10 minutes or until thickened. Using a hand-held stick blender, blend until smooth.'),(874742,6,'Add the roasted quinoa, salt and pepper and stir to combine. Divide the soup between serving bowls and top with the reserved basil.'),(874742,7,'Serve with the Parmesan Wafers.'),(874742,8,'From Life in Balance: A Fresher Approach to Eating  2016 by Donna Hay. Reprinted with permission by Harper'),(874742,9,'Collins Publishers.Buy the full book from Harper'),(874742,10,'Collins or from Amazon.'),(875323,1,'In a small mixing bowl,combine goat cheese,parsley and rosemary.'),(875323,2,'Mix well and set aside.Lightly brash baguette halves with olive oil.Grill,turning once,until light golden.'),(875323,3,'Remove grilled baguette from the grill.'),(875323,4,'Spread evenly cheese mixture onto baguette halves.'),(875323,5,'Cut into slices about 3/4 inch (2 cm) wide.'),(875323,6,'Serve warm.'),(875486,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Spray a 95 loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray and set aside.In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda, and salt. Set aside.In a medium bowl, whisk together the brown sugar, granulated sugar, and egg.'),(875486,2,'Whisk until smooth and there are no brown sugar clumps.'),(875486,3,'Whisk in the Greek yogurt, buttermilk, oil,and vanilla extract.Slowly pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and gently whisk until there are no more lumps. Dont overmix. Gently toss the strawberries in the tablespoon of flour and add them to the batter. Gently fold in the strawberries.'),(875486,4,'Pour batter in prepared pan and sprinkle the top with turbinando sugar.'),(875486,5,'Bake for 60 minutes, loosely covering the bread with aluminum foil after 45 minutes to prevent the top from getting too dark. A toothpick inserted in the center of the loaf will come out clean when the bread is done.'),(875486,6,'Remove from the oven and allow the bread to coolfor 15 minutes on a wire cooling rack. Use a knife to loosen the bread around the edges in the pan. Carefully remove the bread from the pan and cool completely.Note-the bread will keep covered on the counter for up to 3 days.'),(875655,1,'Simmer pomegranate juice, lemon juice, and syrup in a medium saucepan over medium heat for 60-75 minutes.Stir every 10-15 minutes.Liquid should reduce down to about -1/4 original volume (about a cup), and should be of thicker than syrup but not quite as thick as molasses (will coat the back of the spoon). *This should produce enough to coat two 1 lb salmon fillets.'),(875655,2,'Remove from heat (it will continue to thicken).'),(875655,3,'Place filet into baking dish, top with half of sauce, and let marinate in the refrigerator for 15-60 minutes.Pre-heat oven to 400F.Spoon sauce that has dripped to the sides of the dish back on top of the salmon (ahhhh yeeeaahh, look at that!).'),(875655,4,'Place in oven for 17-30 minutes (depending on thickness of filet). Fish will be cooked when meat flakes apart easily with a fork.'),(875655,5,'Brush on another coat of the glaze and serve with extra sauce as desired.'),(875807,1,'Place the butter, Sukrin :1 (or Swerve), vanilla, and stevia glycerite in a medium bowl and cream together until light and fluffy - about 1 1/2 minutes.'),(875807,2,'Add 2 large eggs and beat until completely incorporated, making sure to keep that nice light texture. (The mixture may break or separate a little - it\'s okay.)'),(875807,3,'Add 1/3 of the dry ingredients and beat until fully incorporated and the batter is fluffy.'),(875807,4,'Add 1 egg and 1/4 cup of buttermilk, beating until incorporated and until the batter is light and fluffy.'),(875807,5,'Add 1/2 of the dry ingredients and beat as before, followed by 1 egg and 1/4 cup of buttermilk. The goal is to keep everything light and fluffy.'),(875807,6,'Add the last of the dry ingredients, beating well, followed by the last of the wet ingredients, making sure to scrape down the sides and bottom of the bowl.Divide the cake batter evenly between the two pans. The batter will be very thick - like a cookie dough, and will need to be spread into the pan with a small offset spatula or knife. Lift a pan a few inches off of the counter and let it fall onto the counter. Do this twice for each pan to help knock out any larger air bubbles.'),(875807,7,'Place the pans in the oven and turn the oven up to 400 for 8 minutes, then back down to 350 for 30 minutes or until the tops of the cakes are firm, but still springy to the touch.'),(875807,8,'Remove the pans from the oven and let the cakes cool in the pans until cool enough to handle. Loosen the cakes by running a slender knife along the edge of the pan and turn out onto a cooling rack to cool completely. Wrap in cling film and refrigerate until needed.Assembly: Whip the French buttercream frosting and refrigerate. Whip the heavy cream with sweetener and lemon zest until soft peaks form.'),(875807,9,'Add the xanthan gum and beat until very stiff. Carefully slice off the tops of the cakes to level the tops. Slice the cakes in half, horizontally and place one on the serving plate.Snip the corner off of a quart ziploc bag ( 1/2-inch up from the corner ) and insert a large round tip, if you don\'t have one, just use the bag. Starting on the inside edge of the sliced cake, squeeze concentric circles (one inside the other) to cover the cake. Top with a cake half and press gently to level it. Squeeze another circle of whipped cream along the outside edge of the new cake layer to form a dam.'),(876544,1,'In a small bowl, season the shallots with a pinch each of salt and sugar. Cover with vinegar and let sit for 10 minutes.Meanwhile, bring a large pot of water to a boil over high heat. Shell the fava beans, then drop them in the water and cook for 1 minute.'),(876544,2,'Drain and plunge them into an ice bath. Peel the favas and set aside. If youre using edamame, boil for 1 minute, then plunge into the ice bath.In a large bowl combine the endive, scallions, radishes, and favas.'),(876544,3,'Whisk  cup oil into the vinegar mixture, pour it over the vegetables, and toss to coat. Taste and adjust the seasoning with salt, as needed. If you have small, tender basil leaves, add them to the bowl whole; otherwise, roughly chop the leaves, add them to the bowl, and toss to coat.In a small bowl, stir together the ricotta, mixed herbs, and lemon zest. Season with salt and pepper to taste.Preheat the broiler to high. Arrange the bread on a sheet pan and drizzle with oil. Turn the slices over and drizzle with more oil.'),(876544,4,'Transfer to the oven and broil for about 2 minutes, until golden, keeping an eye on them to prevent burning. Flip and broil the other side until golden, 1 to 2 minutes more.'),(876544,5,'Transfer the bread to a serving board or platter.'),(876544,6,'Spread each slice of bread with ricotta and mound the endive salad on top.'),(876544,7,'Serve immediately.Set a large fine-mesh sieve over a deep bowl. Line itwith2 layers of cheesecloth.'),(876544,8,'Pour the milk and cream into a mediumpot. Stir in the salt. Bring to a full boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally, watching closely. Turn off the heat and stir in the vinegar. Allow the mixture to stand for 1 minute until it curdles. It will separate into thick parts (the curds) and milky parts (the whey).'),(876544,9,'Pour the mixture into a cheesecloth-lined sieve and allow it to drain into the bowl at room temperature for 20 to 25 minutes. The longer you let the mixture drain, the thicker the ricotta will be.'),(876544,10,'Transfer the ricotta to a bowl, discarding the cheesecloth. Save the whey  you can make bread with it. Use the ricotta immediately or cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate. The ricotta will keep refrigerated for 4 to 5 days.'),(877621,1,'Preheat oven to 400F. Line a rimmed baking pan with parchment.Fruit Filling: In a large bowl, toss the berries to combine evenly.'),(877621,2,'Sprinkle the vanilla and citrus zest over the fruit and toss again.'),(877621,3,'Combine the sugar and cornstarch.'),(877621,4,'Sprinkle it over the fruit and toss to coat the fruit well.Assembly:Unfold the phyllo and cut the sheet in half crosswise. Stack the halves, then quickly cover with a sheet of plastic wrap and a lightly dampened clean kitchen towel to prevent it from drying out. (See Working with Phyllo for more details).'),(877621,5,'Place one sheet of phyllo lengthwise on the prepared baking sheet.'),(877621,6,'Brush with oil or butter.'),(877621,7,'Place a second sheet of phyllo on top crosswise, then brush lightly with oil or butter. Repeat until 8 sheets are used.Spoon half the fruit filling in the centre forming a 6- to 7-inch circle. Dot with half of the butter. Turn the corners of the phyllo over to form an octagon. Press flat. Fold the pastry edge over the filling to form a rim, pleating the dough as necessary.'),(877621,8,'Brush the top of the pastry rim.'),(877621,9,'Sprinkle the crust and filling with sugar. Repeat with second galette.'),(877621,10,'Bake about 30 minutes or until the crust is golden and the filling is bubbling.Allow the galette to cool on the parchment before eating. Like most pies, galettes are best eaten the day theyre made, but leftovers if there are any can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.Makes 2 small galettes.'),(877621,11,'Serves 8.'),(877774,1,'Tap For Ingredients'),(877774,2,'Ingredients out  Kettle boiled  Griddle pan, high heat  Medium lidded pan, medium heat  Large casserole pan, low heat  Food processor (bowl blade)START COOKING'),(877774,3,'Remove the outer leaves from the cauliflower, then slice it 1cm thick and put it on the griddle pan, turning when lightly charred.Put 1 mug of rice and 2 mugs of boiling water into the medium pan with the cloves, lemon half and a pinch of sea salt, and put the lid on.'),(877774,4,'Pour 2 tablespoons of oil into the casserole pan, then quickly stir in the mustard and fenugreek seeds, turmeric and curry leaves.Peel the ginger and garlic cloves, and trim the spring onions. Pulse these, together with the chilli and coriander stalks in the processor until fine, then stir into the casserole pan.Roughly chop and add the tomatoes.'),(877774,5,'Pour in the coconut milk, drain and add the chickpeas, then tip in the pineapple chunks and their juices.'),(877774,6,'Add the griddled cauliflower, cover, turn the heat up to high and bring to the boil.'),(877774,7,'Put the uncooked poppadoms into the microwave (800W) for a minute or two to puff up.Tear off the top leafy half of the mint and bash to a paste in a pestle and mortar. Stir in the yoghurt, add a good squeeze of lemon juice and season with salt and black pepper. Squeeze the juice of the remaining lemon into the curry and season to taste.'),(877774,8,'Sprinkle over the coriander leaves and serve with the rice and poppadoms.'),(877774,9,'Lets build a healthier, happier world through the joy of food! Join the Food Revolution for the latest on sustainable food, farming and cooking projects across the globe. Join our Food Revolution!'),(877774,10,'Tips'),(877774,11,'To make this recipe vegan, simply leave out the yoghurt dip for the poppadoms. You could replace it with a quality mango chutney, if you want.'),(877774,12,'Tip'),(877993,1,'Heat oven to 200C/180C fan/gas'),(877993,2,'Tip the potatoes, onion, garlic, oregano and olive oil into a roasting tin, season, then mix together with your hands to coat everything in the oil. Roast for 15 mins, turn everything over and bake for 15 mins more.'),(877993,3,'Add the lemon and tomatoes, and roast for 10 mins, then top with the fish fillets and cook for 10 mins more.'),(877993,4,'Serve with parsley scattered over.'),(878360,1,'Line an 8x8 (20x20cm) baking pan with parchment paper, set aside. In a large mixing bowl, add the warmed milk and sprinkle yeast over the top.'),(878360,2,'Whisk and set aside for 15 minutes to proof. It will be bubbly and frothy when ready. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, pour the rum over the currants/raisins, cover and warm for 30 seconds in the microwave. This will plump them up.'),(878360,3,'Drain, pressing the currants/raisins through a fine strainer just before using in the recipe.To the frothy milk/yeast mixture add 2 eggs, melted butter, vanilla extract and maple syrup.'),(878360,4,'Whisk throughly. To the wet ingredients, add the flour, cardamom, cinnamon and sea salt. Use a wooden spoon to mix first, then as the ingredients come together mix by hand until there are no dry patches.'),(878360,5,'Add the lemon and orange zest and the drained currants/raisins. Using one hand, gently lift and press the dough over and onto itself while rotating the bowl in quarter turns with each fold with the other hand. Do this for about one minute to throughly fold in the zest and currants/raisins.Turn the dough out onto a floured work surface. Knead the dough for about 9 minutes until the dough has a tacky, not sticky, feel to it. If it\'s sticking to your hands, dust the dough with flour and continue kneading.'),(878360,6,'Roll into a ball by tucking the edges in underneath the ball.'),(878360,7,'Place in a lightly greased clean bowl, cover with plastic wrap and place in a warm location to rise (see tip in notes) to double in size.Turn dough out onto a lightly floured work surface. Gently roll the dough into a log and divide into 12 equal pieces (about 74g ea).'),(879448,1,'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a medium skillet over medium and cook panko, stirring, until golden, about 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper; transfer to paper towels to drain and toss with dill and lemon zest.'),(879448,2,'Cook pasta in a large pot of boiling salted water, stirring occasionally, until al dente.'),(879448,3,'Drain, reserving 1/2 cup pasta cooking liquid.'),(879448,4,'Meanwhile, mash anchovies and garlic to a paste on a cutting board with the side of a chef\'s knife.'),(879448,5,'Combine with parsley, basil, and half of olives and capers in a large bowl. Chop remaining olives and capers and add to bowl, along with remaining 1/2 cup oil.'),(879448,6,'Mix well; season sauce with salt and pepper.'),(879448,7,'Add pasta and 1/4 cup reserved pasta cooking liquid to sauce. Toss, adding Parmesan a bit at a time, along with more pasta cooking liquid as needed, until sauce coats pasta.'),(879448,8,'Add lemon juice; season with salt and pepper.'),(879448,9,'Serve pasta topped with panko and more Parmesan.'),(879448,10,'Do Ahead'),(879448,11,'Sauce can be made 1 day ahead. Cover with plastic wrap, pressing directly against surface, and chill.'),(880425,1,'Preheat oven to 350F. Line a sheet pan with foil or parchment paper for easy clean up. Slice the top off of each roll (about a quarter of the roll) and set the tops aside.With a small, sharp knife, cut around the edge of the roll, leaving a 1/4-inch rim. Extend your knife almost to the bottom of the roll but dont cut through the bottom. Once youve cut all the way around, use your knife to gently wedge out the center**. If it doesnt all come out, use your fingers to pull out the rest. You can also compress the inner walls of the rolls with your finger a bit to make the opening a bit larger, to accommodate your eggs. This will depend on the size of your rolls and eggs. Test an egg with one of the rolls to see what works best.Check each roll when you finish by holding it up to the light. If you notice a small hole, take a small piece of bread (from one of the cutout centers), place it over the hole and push it down with your finger to form a little plug for the hole. (See pictures in the post for this.)'),(880425,2,'Brush the rims and outsides of each roll with melted butter (about 1 teaspoon per roll) and place on prepared pan. The butterwill makethe rolls super crisp and delicious after baking. (If youre watching your calories, this only adds 34 calories per serving but adds tons of flavor). If prepping ahead, place all rolls on a baking sheet at this point and cover with plastic wrap or foil till just before baking time.Break an egg into a small bowl (check for any tiny bits of shell) and carefully pour it into the bread basket. Repeat for all the rolls and eggs.****.'),(880425,3,'Bake for 18-22 minutes.'),(880425,4,'Remove from oven and let sit for 2-3 minutes.'),(880425,5,'Sprinkle with your choice of fresh herbs (I used dill and thyme).'),(880425,6,'Serve and enjoy!The last 5 minutes of baking, pop the topsin the oven and serve these fun little toasts on a pretty plate with a jar of jam. All you need is fresh fruit for a fabulous breakfast or brunch!'),(880531,1,'Preheat the oven to 300 degrees F. Position the oven racks so one is just above the middle position and the other is in the bottom third of the oven. Lightly grease a 9-inch springform pan.In a medium bowl, stir together the graham cracker crumbs and sugar.'),(880531,2,'Add the melted butter and mix until the graham cracker crumbs are evenly coated in sandy in texture. Press the mixture into the bottom and 1/2-inch or so up the sides of the prepared pan.'),(880531,3,'Bake the crust for 15 minutes.'),(880531,4,'Remove from the oven and let cool while you prepare the filling.In a large bowl with an electric mixer (or in the bowl of an electric stand mixer), whip the cream cheese, sugar, cornstarch and lime zest together until smooth and creamy, 1-2 minutes, scraping down the sides of the bowl as needed.'),(880531,5,'Add the lime juice (or lemon + lime juice) and mix until combined.'),(880531,6,'Add the eggs and mix until just combined (over mixing can cause the cheesecake to crack while baking thanks to all the extra air beat into the filling).'),(880531,7,'Pour the cheesecake filling over the crust and spread evenly.'),(880531,8,'Place a metal 9X13-inch or similar-sized pan on the bottom rack of the oven and pour in 2-3 cups of boiling water. Immediately place the cheesecake on the upper rack and bake for 50-65 minutes until the cheesecake is set around the edges. A slight jiggle in the center of the cheesecake is fine.Turn the oven off and prop the oven door open about 4 inches. Keep the cheesecake in the oven for 30 minutes.'),(880531,9,'Remove and let cool completely.Refrigerate the cheesecake overnight.When ready to serve, whip together the cream, powdered sugar and vanilla until thick and creamy. Either spread the whipped cream evenly over the cheesecake or pipe it around the edges with a large star piping tip or just dollop a spoonful on each individual piece.'),(880531,10,'Garnish with lime slices or lime zest, if desired.'),(881010,1,'Boil lasagna noodles per package directions for al dente. Set aside (I laid mine out on wax paper the keep them from sticking to each other).Brown the beef and onions over medium-high.'),(881010,2,'Add taco seasoning and mix. Then add corn, beans, tomatoes, enchilada sauce and tomato sauce.Bring the pan to a boil and then reduce heat to medium. Simmer for around 8 minutes, stirring often.'),(881010,3,'Remove from heat and stir in 1 cup cheese.Give it a couple minutes to cool slightly and then place a small amount of the beef mixture on the bottom of a 9x13 pan (just to wet it).'),(881010,4,'Lay out one noodle at a time. Spoon a thin line of the beef mixture down the middle ending about an inch from the top.'),(881010,5,'Roll it up slowly, holding the sides closed as you go. Once it\'s rolled, place it into the pan, with the end of the noodle on the bottom.Once they\'re all rolled, top them with remaining sauce and cover with foil.'),(881010,6,'Bake at 350 for 30-40 min and then uncover and top with 2 cups cheese.'),(881010,7,'Bake 10 min more or until cheese is melted.Enjoy!'),(882095,1,'Add everything to the slow cooker except the Parmesan cheese. Stir together.'),(882095,2,'Cook on low for 4-5 hours (or high 2-3 hours) until quinoa is cooked through.'),(882095,3,'Sprinkle the cheese over top and close. Cook for 15 more minutes until cheese melts.'),(882835,1,'Combine lemon juice, olive oil, garlic, and tahini in food processor. Pulse until whipped and smooth.'),(882835,2,'Add cooked chickpeas and spices to food processor. Pulse until smooth and creamy.'),(882835,3,'Add equal parts oil and water to thin out the mixture. Enjoy with vegetables, pita bread, or pita chips!'),(883170,1,'Stir 1 bottle barbeque sauce and dry onion soup mix together in the bottom of a large slow cooker crock.'),(883170,2,'Place pork loin and ribs into the slow cooker.'),(883170,3,'Cook on High until the meat begins to fall apart, 6 to 8 hours.'),(883170,4,'Remove meat and set aside. Allow crock to cool enough to handle; pour liquid into a bowl. Clean the crock and return it to the slow cooker.'),(883170,5,'Debone ribs; discard bones and any fat. Shred meat from the ribs. Shred pork loin meat using two forks pulling them in opposite directions. Return all the shredded meat to the slow cooker.'),(883170,6,'Pour 1 bottle barbeque sauce over the pork.'),(883170,7,'Add a small amount of water to the sauce bottle, shake vigorously to get as much sauce from the bottle as possible, and pour into the slow cooker.'),(883170,8,'Cook on Low for 1 hour.'),(884564,1,'Mix the melted butter, brown sugar, and coconut extract.'),(884564,2,'Place the Rice Chex, Corn Chex, and macadamia nuts in a large bowl.'),(884564,3,'Pour the butter mixture over the cereal mixture and stir until everything is evenly distributed.'),(884564,4,'Spread on a parchment-lined cookie sheet.'),(884564,5,'Bake at 275 degrees for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.If using shredded coconut, add it to the mix for the last 15 minutes of baking.Cool and store in an airtight container.'),(884825,1,'Watch how to make this recipe.'),(884825,2,'Heat the olive oil in a pot over medium heat.'),(884825,3,'Add the garlic and onions and saute until starting to soften, 3 to 4 minutes.'),(884825,4,'Add the ground beef and sausage and cook until browned.'),(884825,5,'Drain off almost all of the fat, leaving a bit behind for flavor and moisture.'),(884825,6,'Add the tomato sauce, tomatoes, Italian seasoning, red pepper flakes and some salt and pepper. Stir, bring to a simmer and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.'),(884825,7,'Remove 3 to 4 cups of the cooked sauce to a bowl to cool down.'),(884825,8,'Bring a large pot of water to a boil and add some salt. Cook the ziti until not quite al dente.'),(884825,9,'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.'),(884825,10,'In a bowl, mix 2 cups of the grated mozzarella, the ricotta, Parmesan, parsley, eggs and some salt and pepper. Stir together just a couple of times (do not mix completely).'),(884825,11,'Drain the pasta and rinse under cool water to stop the cooking and cool it down.'),(884825,12,'Pour it into the bowl with the cheese mixture and toss to slightly combine (there should still be large lumps).'),(884825,13,'Add the cooled reserved meat sauce and toss to combine.'),(884825,14,'Add half the coated pasta to a large casserole dish or lasagna dish. Spoon half of the remaining sauce over the top, then top with half the remaining mozzarella. Repeat with another layer of the coated pasta and the remaining sauce and mozzarella.'),(884825,15,'Bake until bubbling, about 20 minutes.'),(884825,16,'Let stand 5 minutes before sprinkling with chopped parsley to serve.'),(885208,1,'Preheat oven to 400, and line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper. In a large bowl, toss the brussel sprouts and potatoes with the olive oil, garlic, cumin, and salt and pepper.'),(885208,2,'Pour the vegetables onto the baking sheet and roast for about 40-45 minutes, or until browned.'),(885208,3,'Place the hot vegetables in a large bowl, and toss with the red wine vinegar.'),(885208,4,'Serve hot.'),(885922,1,'Whisk together BBQ sauce, Sriracha, honey, mustard and pineapple juice.'),(885922,2,'Place chicken in a gallon ziplock bag and pour marinade over chicken.Refrigerate a few hours to overnight.'),(885922,3,'Remove chicken from marinade and grill for approximately 15 minutes, until done.'),(886174,1,'Combine in a medium bowl the strawberries, blueberries and jicama'),(886174,2,'In a small food processor combine the vinegar, honey, mustard, poppy seeds, salt, pepper and oil - mix until combined'),(886174,3,'Pour about 2 tablespoons dressing (or more to liking) over other ingredients and lightly toss until combine'),(886174,4,'Serve immediately or store in refrigerator until ready to eat (keeps about 1 day in refrigerator)'),(886365,1,'Preheat the oven to 350F and lightly oil a six cavity doughnut pan.In a medium mixing bowl stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt. In a separate bowl or liquid measuring cup, stir together the milk, coconut oil, and vanilla.'),(886365,2,'Add the milk mixture to the flour mixture and stir just until mixed.Divide the batter among doughnut cavities.'),(886365,3,'Bake for 10 minutes, or until the tops spring back when lightly touched.'),(886365,4,'Transfer to a cooling rack to cool.While the doughnuts bake, combine the coconut sugar, coconut milk, coconut oil, and salt in a small saucepan, then place it over medium heat. Bring everything to a simmer while whisking and lower heat. Allow to simmer for about 5 minutes, whisking constantly, until the mixture darkens a bit and smells like caramel. Watch the pot closely while simmering to avoid burning.'),(886365,5,'Remove from heat and allow to cool completely. The caramel will thicken as it cools.When the doughnuts and caramel are cool, dip the top of each doughnut into the caramel to coat it.'),(886365,6,'Place the doughnut on a sheet of parchment paper, and repeat for all of the doughnuts. If you\'d like to glaze the bottoms, place the doughnuts into the refrigerator for about an hour to chill, so they\'re easier to grip without making (as much of) a mess.'),(886365,7,'Sprinkle the tops lightly with coarse ground sea salt and serve.'),(887089,1,'To make the spaghetti squash, preheat oven to 350 degrees F and cut squash right down the middle. Scoop out all the seeds and place cut side down on a baking sheet lightly sprayed with oil. DO NOT PIERCE WITH A FORK!! Many recipes say to do this, but we are using these cuts of squash later as bowls so you want them to remain intact.'),(887089,2,'Bake squash in the oven for 45 minutes until tender.Meanwhile, drizzle oil into a large skillet and saute onion and garlic until fragrant, about 2 minutes.'),(887089,3,'Add turkey sausage and cook until crumbled and lightly brown, draining if necessary, then add chicken broth, tomatoes, half and half, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper. Bring everything to a boil then cover and allow flavors to simmer on low to medium heat until spaghetti squash is ready.'),(887089,4,'Remove squash from the oven and scrape out all the strands of spaghetti using a fork.'),(887089,5,'Add all the spaghetti squash to your skillet along with a  cup of cheese. Toss well until cheese is melted and squash is fully coated with sauce.'),(887089,6,'Transfer squash mixture into your now scraped out squash bowls and top with the rest of your cheese.'),(887089,7,'Place them back in the oven for about 3 to 4 minutes until cheese is melted and squash is heated through.Top with basil, serve and enjoy!'),(887425,1,'edible flower ice cubes (such as peonies and marigolds)Begin by adding edible flowers to an ice cube tray and filling with water and freezing.'),(887425,2,'Mix all ingredients except for club soda and flower ice cubes in shaker filled with ice.'),(887425,3,'Add flower ice cubes into glasses.'),(887425,4,'Pour cocktail over ice and top with club soda.Lemon Syrup'),(887425,5,'Zest lemon. Juice lemons to make 1/2 cup juice.'),(887425,6,'Add to pot with water and sugar. Bring to a boil and then turn off the heat.'),(887425,7,'Let syrup cool before using.'),(887524,1,'Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.'),(887524,2,'Add pasta and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until al dente; drain.'),(887524,3,'In a medium saucepan, melt butter over medium low heat; add wine, cheese, garlic, parsley and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer over low heat for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently.'),(887524,4,'Increase heat to medium high and add shrimp to saucepan; cook for about 3 to 4 minutes or until shrimp begins to turn pink. Do not overcook.'),(887524,5,'Divide pasta into portions and spoon sauce on top; garnish with Parmesan cheese and fresh parsley, if desired.'),(888291,1,'Combine 1 1/2 cups water and 2 pounds beef chuck roast in the slow cooker and cook on LOW for 6-8 hours or HIGH for 3-4 hours.When it\'s done cooking, remove roast and shred the beef with 2 forks.'),(888291,2,'Remove and discard any pieces of fat. Discard the water (it has the melted fat in it.)'),(888291,3,'Put the shredded beef back into the slow cooker and add 2 tablespoons of unsalted butter.'),(888291,4,'Mix in.'),(888291,5,'Add half the container of BBQ sauce and reserve some for people who wish to add more to their sandwich. Alternately, you can just add the whole bottle, if you prefer. Turn the setting to WARM and serve on buns with shaved Iceberg lettuce, shaved red cabbage, sliced red onion, and sliced cheese, and any other condiments, if you wish. Salt and pepper to taste. Enjoy!'),(889591,1,'Combine the water, hemp seeds, spinach, broccoli sprouts, banana, strawberries, pineapple chunks, cocoa powder, vanilla, and dates into the base of a high-speed blender.Process on the smoothie mode or for at least 45 seconds on high until completely blended.The texture should be smooth and creamy.'),(890315,1,'In a large bowl, combine olive oil, lemon juice, zest, garlic, oregano, and salt. Season with black pepper, to taste.'),(890315,2,'Add chicken to the bowl tossing to coat evenly and let marinate for 30 minutes at room temperature. (note: while the chicken marinates prepare the salad and tzatziki sauce).Thread the chicken onto skewers. Lightly grease the grilling surface and grill the skewers in a hot grill for about 3 minutes per each of the 4 sides or until fully cooked through.'),(890315,3,'Remove chicken from the skewers and serve in warmed pita or naan bread with salad and tzatziki sauce.In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients. If not serving immediately, cover and refrigerate.In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients. If not serving immediately, cover and refrigerate.'),(890723,1,'Place the mozzarella ball in a bowl. In a smaller bowl, whisk together the olive oil, lemon and lime juice, basil, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper.'),(890723,2,'Pour it over the mozzarella and stick it in the fridge while you use a melon baller to scoop out the watermelon and cucumber.'),(890723,3,'Place the watermelon and cucumber in a large bowl.'),(890723,4,'Pour the mozzarella and all the dressing contents in the bowl with the melon and toss well. You can keep this is the fridge for about an hour before serving. Top with extra fresh basil and herbs before serving and toss well!'),(891403,1,'In a large skillet, heat  teaspoon of olive oil over medium heat.'),(891403,2,'Add the onion and cook until soft, about 2 minutes.'),(891403,3,'Add the mushrooms, pinches of salt and pepper, and cook until browned and soft, 5 to 8 minutes.'),(891403,4,'Add  cup of the black beans, the balsamic vinegar and tamari sauce, and cook for 2 minutes or until everything is well browned and soft.'),(891403,5,'Remove the mixture from the heat and let cool slightly.In a food processor, pulse the walnuts.'),(891403,6,'Add the mushroom mixture and pulse 2 to 3 times until just combined. Do not puree or the mixture will be too mushy.'),(891403,7,'Add the remaining  cup of black beans and pulse briefly.'),(891403,8,'Transfer the mixture to a large bowl and stir in the brown rice, chili powder, onion powder, salt and pepper.'),(891403,9,'Mix until combined. Taste and adjust seasonings.Preheat the oven to 400F and line a large baking sheet with parchment paper.'),(891403,10,'Spread the panko breadcrumbs onto a plate. Form the mixture into 18-1 inch balls and gently roll in the crumbs, using the breadcrumbs to pat the mixture into cohesive balls.'),(891403,11,'Place on the baking sheet and refrigerate for 20 minutes or overnight.'),(891403,12,'Drizzle generously with olive oil and bake for 35 to 40 minutes, carefully flipping halfway through.'),(891403,13,'Heat the marinara sauce in a skillet and add the meatballs.'),(891403,14,'Heat until just warmed through and serve immediately on the buns with arugula, basil, and parmesan cheese, if desired. (Tip: dont let the meatballs sit in the sauce for too long or they will start to fall apart).'),(891418,1,'In a microwave-safe bowl add peanut butter, chocolate, sweetener and coconut oil.'),(891418,2,'Heat it at 50% power for 1 minute'),(891418,3,'Remove from the microwave and stir.Return it to the microwave and repeat, stopping to stir every 15-seconds until the mixture is totally melted.'),(891418,4,'Add the remaining ingredients and stir until the ingredients are well combined.'),(891418,5,'Pour into an 88 removable bottom pan. Refrigerate until the chocolate hardens. It is about 4 hours.Slice into square pieces and store in the refrigerator.'),(891660,1,'In a medium bowl, whisk the coconut oil and cacao together.'),(891660,2,'Add in the sweetener, salt and vanilla.'),(891660,3,'Pour into mini lined tins.Chill in the fridge for 30 minutes.'),(891660,4,'Serve.'),(892498,1,'Preheat oven to 350'),(892498,2,'Cut 6 Brussels sprouts into long strips'),(892498,3,'Baked vegan spring rolls made with Brussels sprouts and sweet potatoes. Quick and easy lunch recipe is a twist on the traditional Chinese recipe staple.Peel the skin from one medium sized potato.  Using a cheese grater, grate 1/2 of a sweet potato'),(892498,4,'Baked vegan spring rolls made with Brussels sprouts and sweet potatoes. Quick and easy lunch recipe is a twist on the traditional Chinese recipe staple.Grate ginger to make 1 Tbsp and grate 2 cloves of garlic'),(892498,5,'Report this ad'),(892498,6,'Cut a 1/4 of red onions into thin, long strips'),(892498,7,'In a bowl, add 2 Tbsp of tamarind paste (or tamarind sauce) and 1 Tbsp of soy sauce.'),(892498,8,'Add 1/8 tsp of salt and 1 tsp of water.'),(892498,9,'Mix well and set aside.  You can find tamarind paste in Indian grocery stores or from Walmart.In a stir fry pan, add 1 Tbsp of sesame oil and heat at medium heat'),(892498,10,'Add the onions, ginger and garlic.'),(892498,11,'Mix until the onions are translucent'),(892498,12,'Add the Brussels sprouts and sweet potatoes'),(892498,13,'Stir fry for a few minutes.  When the Brussels sprouts are soft, add the tamarind sauce mixture and mix well'),(892498,14,'Cook for about 2 more minutes.  Continue stirring this time.In a small bowl, add 1 cup of water and in a separate bowl add 1 cup of oil'),(892498,15,'Take one egg-free wrapper (found in many Asian grocery stores, sometimes in the freezer section).  Set one tip of the square wrapper to be on the top.  This will make a diamond shape.  See video below for full instructions.'),(892498,16,'Add the Brussels sprouts mixture diagonally'),(892498,17,'Start with the bottom of the diamond.  Fold it over the stuffing'),(892498,18,'Wet the sides of the wrapper.  Then fold the left and right sides.  Finally fold the top of the wrapper to close it.  Make about 8-10 more spring rolls in the same way'),(892498,19,'On a baking tray, place the spring rolls.  Using a basting brush, lightly brush spring rolls with oil'),(892498,20,'Bake in the oven for about 7-10 minutes.  When the top of the spring rolls has browned, remove from the oven and let it cool.'),(892853,1,'Preheat oven to 350.Grease or spray a 913 baking dish with cooking spray.In a mixing bowl, combine all the cake ingredients except for the chopped pecans.'),(892853,2,'Mix well.'),(892853,3,'Add chopped pecans and stir to combine.'),(892853,4,'Pour batter into prepared baking dish.'),(892853,5,'Bake for about 40-50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.'),(893916,1,'Melt butter in a large pot over medium heat.'),(893916,2,'Add the onion and bacon and cook, stirring frequently, until onion has softened and just starting to brown around edges, about 8 - 10 minutes.'),(893916,3,'Add in the flour and garlic and cook 1 1/2 minutes. While whisking, slowly pour in 5 cups water.'),(893916,4,'Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly, then stir in corn kernels and potatoes.'),(893916,5,'Add in thyme and bay leaf and season with salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a light boil, then reduce heat to medium-low and allow to simmer, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.'),(893916,6,'Remove bay leave then transfer 2 1/2 cups of the chowder to a blender and blend until smooth. Stir the mixture back into the pot then stir in half and half and honey.'),(893916,7,'Sprinkle each serving with chives and optional cheddar.'),(894386,1,'Mix the flour, rolled oats, baking powder, baking soda and salt.'),(894386,2,'Mix the milk, egg, butter, banana and honey.'),(894386,3,'Mix the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients followed by the blueberries and chia seeds.'),(894386,4,'Heat a pan over medium heat, melt a touch of butter in it, pour 1/4 cup of the batter into the pan and cook until the surface starts to bubble and the bottom is golden brown, about 2-3 minutes, before flip the pancake to cook the other side until the bottom is golden brown, about 1-2 minutes and repeating with the remaining batter.Enjoy topped with the mixture of yogurt, honey and lemon or maple syrup, etc.'),(894993,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Line a 18x12-inch rimmed baking sheet (half-sheet size) with parchment, and spray with nonstick cooking spray.'),(894993,2,'Sift or whisk together the cake flour and salt in a small bowl.'),(894993,3,'Combine the butter, cream cheese, and sugar in the bowl of a large stand mixer. Beat them together on medium-high speed until very light and fluffy, 3-4 minutes. Reduce the speed to medium and add the eggs one at a time, beating for 1 minute after each addition.'),(894993,4,'Add the vanilla and almond extracts. Finally, turn the speed to low and add the cake flour, mixing until just a few streaks of flour remain.'),(894993,5,'Stop the mixer and finish mixing by hand, scraping the bottom and sides of the bowl and stirring well. Scrape the batter into the prepared pan and smooth it into an even layer.'),(894993,6,'Bake the cake for about 20 minutes, until its golden brown and it springs back when touched lightly with the fingertips.'),(894993,7,'Let it cool completely at room temperature. The cake can be made several days ahead of time; wrap it well in cling-wrap if youre making it in advance.'),(895046,1,'Preheat oven to 350F.'),(895046,2,'Place a piece of parchment paper in a 9X13 ba