ng apart except the buttermilk, lemon juice and one tablespoon tarragon into your slow cooker. Cook on Low 6 hours so the chicken is really tender and falls easily off the bone.Once cooked, remove the chicken, bacon and vegetables using a slotted spoon and put to one side.'),(900256,3,'Add the buttermilk to the remaining liquid and, using an immersion blender, blitz until smooth.'),(900256,4,'Add the lemon juice and remaining tarragon. Season to taste and then put the chicken, bacon and vegetables back into the crockpot to keep everything warm until you are ready to serve.Nutrition per serving284 calories29 grams protein12 grams carbohydrates2 grams fiber13 grams fat'),(900256,5,'More Slow Cooking Recipes'),(900256,6,'Find more recipe to inspire your moments. Invite your friends and family, prepare healthy delicious meals and impress them with easy recipes. All my slow cooking recipes here.More recipes here'),(900256,7,'PinShare+1Email'),(900256,8,'Whats'),(900256,9,'AppShares 0'),(900293,1,'Spray a 9x13 glass baking dish with cooking spray and set aside'),(900293,2,'In a medium sized sauce pan combine the granulated sugar and light karo syrup. Bring mixture to a boil over medium high heat.Allow mixture to boil for exactly one minute.'),(900293,3,'Remove from heat and add peanut butter, mix well.'),(900293,4,'Add rice krispies and mix until all are coated.'),(900293,5,'Pour rice krispie mixture out into the prepared 9x13 pan and press down with buttered hands or put your hand inside a small plastic bag to keep mixture from sticking to your hands.'),(900293,6,'Put the milk chocolate chips and the butterscotch chocolate chips in a microwave safe bowl and microwave for 30 seconds at a time (stirring in between each one) until chips are melted.'),(900293,7,'Drizzle melted chips over krispie bars and then spread it out evenly with the back of a spoon.Allow to cool until chocolate mixture is set up. To speed this up you can put it in the fridge or freezer, but remember do