hing!Freeze the sandwiches until ready to eat.Make ahead tip:For longer storage or for making ahead, I like to wrap the cookie sandwiches individually in plastic wrap and store for up to 1 month.'),(902124,1,'Beat 3 cups of heavy cream until stiff peaks form, about 5 minutes.'),(902124,2,'Add marshmallow crme and keep beating for 3 minutes. Fold in 1 cup of the miniature marshmallows and set aside.'),(902124,3,'Heat remaining heavy cream until simmering.'),(902124,4,'Remove from heat and pour over chocolate chips in a heat-proof bowl.'),(902124,5,'Let sit 5 minutes, then stir until combined and creamy. Set aside to cool until mixture is lukewarm. If the mixture is too runny place it in the fridge briefly to set before assembling the cake.'),(902124,6,'Spread a thin layer of marshmallow mixture in a 9x13 pan just to coat the bottom.'),(902124,7,'Layer 5 graham crackers across the center of the pan, then 2 more, breaking them as needed to fit around the top and bottom edges.'),(902124,8,'Spread a layer of marshmallow mixture over grahams and top with a layer of chocolate ganache.Repeat the graham-marshmallow-chocolate layers 1 more time.'),(902124,9,'Place graham crackers on top of chocolate ganache layer, then remaining marshmallow mixture, and you should reach the top of the pan.Refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight until the graham crackers have softened completely.When ready to serve, heat broiler.'),(902124,10,'Garnish cake with remaining mini marshmallows, graham cracker crumbs and chopped chocolate.Broil 1 minute to toast marshmallows.'),(902268,1,'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.'),(902268,2,'Mix the hoisin sauce, soy sauce, sherry wine, red wine vinegar, sriracha sauce, sugar and garlic in a small bowl.'),(902268,3,'Cut diagonal lines into the chicken to give the sauce more to cling to.Toss the broccoli and carrots with the canola oil and 1 tablespoon of the sauce.'),(902268,4,'Add the chicken to the sheet pan, then scatter the vegetables around it.')