t cook for 5 minutes or until very crispy.'),(905593,5,'Transfer to a paper towel lined plate. Crumble the bacon into bacon bits.In a medium bowl, combine the Greek yogurt, oil, lemon juice, parsley, dill weed, garlic powder, onion powder, dried onion, black pepper, chives and salt.'),(905593,6,'Mix together well.'),(905593,7,'Place a watermelon wedge on a plate. Top with a dollop of the yogurt ranch. Top with bacon bits, tomatoes, and pickled onions.'),(905772,1,'Heat oil in a large pot over medium heat.'),(905772,2,'Add garlic and onion, cook for 30 seconds or so.'),(905772,3,'Add oregano and fennel seeds, cook for 2 minutes (lets flavour bloom).Turn heat down to medium low.'),(905772,4,'Add carrots and celery, cook, stirring regularly, for 8 minutes until onion is sweet (not browned). This step is key to the flavour base of this soup.'),(905772,5,'Add capsicum, turn heat up to high and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.'),(905772,6,'Add remaining Soup ingredients, bring to simmer then place lid on. Turn heat down to medium low, simmer for 25 minutes.'),(905772,7,'Remove lid, adjust salt and pepper to taste.Ladle soup into bowls. Grate over lemon zest, squeeze of lemon juice and sprinkle with parsley.'),(905772,8,'Serve!'),(906623,1,'It\'s been quite a while since I posted a traditional Mangalorean recipe. Today as I sifted through my draft posts I found this recipe for a lovely Mangalorean pudding which in Konkani is called as \'MaNi\' (the pronunciation of the \'N\' is made with a little twist in the tongue). The main ingredient of this pudding, \'Indachepeet\' as it is popularly called in the Konkani dialect spoken by Catholics is derived from the trunk of the Caryota Urens tree. Caryota Urens is the botanical name for the fishtail palm. In the olden days, everyone used to have at least one or two trees in their backyard and the flour was a must-have ingredient in every Mangalorean pantry. Some people still follow the tradition and stock it all year round to be quickly cooked into a thin gruel and drunk by anyone having an upset tummy. I have had this concoction for as long as I can remember, especially during my childhood when my mother used to make it and mix some milk, a pinch of salt and a little sugar to taste. The drink was satisfying and delicious. I will post the recipe soon.During my childhood I only knew about the rice mani which is prepared by soaking and grinding raw rice before it is slow cooked along with coconut milk and jaggery for anything between 45 minutes to 1-1/2 hours depending on the quantity. Blogging got me acquainted with the ragi (finger millet) mani which is made by soaking and grinding finger millet and then placing thepastemixed with water in a bowl, untouched until the water turns clear and the sediment settles at the bottom of the bowl. The paste is then slow cooked till the right, glutinous consistency and texture are achieved after which the mixture is poured into greased plates, cooled and cut into slices before serving. The laborious procedure is a deterrent to making it which is why many people don\'t make it at home these days and prefer to buy it from home cooks that take up small catering orders.However, the effort is really worth it because the taste is unmatchable and slow cooked food wins over fast food any day, isn\'t it? The reason why most of our Mangalorean cooking is laborious is because most of the dishes call for coconut - freshly grated, ground to paste or in the form of its milk that is extracted and added to sweets or savouries. Today\'s recipe uses it too, making this sweet dish a dairy-free (and vegan if you grease the plate with oil instead of ghee) and gluten-free delicacy that can be enjoyed by all. This dish is almostexinctin Mangalore especially because procuring the main ingredient - \'indachepeet\' is not very easy in the sense that it is not available at every grocery store. You need to buy it from traditional folks who harvest the starch (sago), clean, dry and sell it or from select stores in Mangalore. Also, the sago flour is costly as the process of extracting flour is tedious and today the trees are fewer as compared to their number in the past.Fishtail Palm / Caryota Urens - Picture clicked near Bangalore Central Mall, M.G Road Bengaluru'),(906623,2,'Caryota Urens, commonly known as the fishtail palm has bipinnate leaves, which means that the leaves are divided into leaflets that are again divided the second time. Since the leaves that are shaped like the tail of fish the name stuck around as \'fishtail\'. The term \'urens\' means \'stinging\' in Latin, referring to the fruit of the palm which is a skin irritant. The fruit, shaped like little green pearls growing in clusters look like necklaces strung across the length of the tree. While the fruits are not suitable for eating, the palm has many other uses. While the tree looks nice and pretty and is used for ornamental purposes, the trunk yields starch (sago) that used to be eaten during famine. The starch is believed to have anti-oxidant and anti-diabetic properties. The sap from the inflorescence is fermented into an alcoholic drink (toddy/palm wine) and is also boiled and reduced to a thick consistency to make a syrup (treacle) or sugar (jaggery). The jaggery thus derived is pretty famous in Sri Lanka and is known askithuljaggery. If you live outside India and need to source the flour or jaggery, Sri Lankan grocery stores are your best bet. From what I have read, the extraction ofkithulsap was a closely guarded secret and the treacle thus prepared has a lot of medicinal value. Most Sri Lankans love eatingkithuljaggery withyogurt. How yum is that?Anyway, let\'s head back to the dish of today which is made from the sago/flour. While a lot of people mistake it for arrowroot, the easiest way to differentiate between the two would be to check the colour and texture of each. Arrowroot is starch obtained from rhizomes of several tropical plants while the palm sago flour is derived from the trunk of the fishtail palm. Arrowroot flour is smooth in texture like fine talc and bright white incolourunlike the fishtail palm sago flour that is dusky in colour and has a texture that is more dense and crumbly. The best substitute for this dish is to use arrowroot but that would make it an arrowroot pudding! Ha!In other news, my blog turned 8 in April! Yoo hoo! Sometimes it feels like I started blogging just yesterday, sometimes it feels like forever. Nevertheless, it is mine to nurture and yours to enjoy. As always I need to make that customary speech too but I\'ll keep it short this time. As I step into the 9th year of blogging, I hope to share more recipes to delight your palate and appetite. The abundant love and encouragement I have been receiving from my readers over the years has been a huge, huge morale booster so keep it flowing :-) I love to hear from you and try my best to respond to most emails. Since I am a one (wo) man army it is sometimes difficult to keep up with every email and comment. Sometimes I wish I had an assistant but then my blog has and will always remain to be my passion instead of a business, so you can rest assured that the recipes I post are handpicked from my personal collection and not posted just to keep the ball rolling. Should you have a query, want to give feedback or just like to say hello, do drop me an email at ruchikrandhap@gmail.com. For those inclined to reach out to me on social media, you can find me on Instagram, Facebook, Pinterest,Google'),(906623,3,'Plus and Twitter (although I am more active on the former two and respond faster there!)Indhacha Peetachi Mani | Fishtail Palm Sago Pudding'),(906623,4,'Prep time: 30-45 mins | Cooking time: 45-50 mins |'),(908481,1,'Mix all the ingredients for the hamburgers and form eight oblong patties.Fry over medium-high heat in both butter and olive oil for at least 10 minutes or until the patties have turned a nice color.'),(908481,2,'Pour the tomato paste and the whipping cream into the pan when the patties are almost done. Stir and let the cream boil together.'),(908481,3,'Sprinkle chopped parsley on top before serving.'),(910807,1,'Mince the garlic scapes.In a small bowl, combine room temperature butter with the minced garlic scapes, lemon juice, sea salt and fresh pepper.'),(910807,2,'Serve soft on fresh baguette bread.To store leftovers, scrape the butter into a small container and refrigerate. Use the butter for sauting, or bring it back to room temperature for future appetizers.In a food processor or high speed blender, combine garlic scapes, basil, and pine nuts. Blend until a paste has formed.'),(910807,3,'Add the olive oil, lemon juice and salt and pepper. Blend until smooth and add additional olive oil if desired for a thinner pesto.Store pesto in the fridge and use on fresh baguette bread, tossed with pasta, on roasted vegetables or grain bowls.'),(910874,1,'Bake for 35 to 40 minutes and serve warm with fresh whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.Bonne Apptit!Easy, peasy and sweet! Its good to make a nice and delicious delight from time to another! Give this recipe a shot and let me know how it turns out!Facebook'),(910874,2,'Pinterest'),(910874,3,'Print'),(910874,4,'Messenger'),(911293,1,'Serves 1-multiply as needed'),(911293,2,'Ingredients1 large egg, beaten until smooth with a tablespoon water1 Tsbp Creme fraiche or sour cream1 tsp chopped fresh fines herbes- (Equal parts: Tarragon, Parsley, Chives, Chervil-slice the chives individually, chop the other herbs together, then mix all when finished)1.5 ounces fresh chanterelles (about a small handful if you don’t have a digital scale)Salt and pepper to taste1 tbsp grapeseed oil, or other searing oil like vegetable, or canola1 tbsp unsalted butter'),(911293,3,'Clean the chanterelles by holding them individually by their stems, swhish them lightly in cold water, then allow them to drain until thoroughly dry on towels. Very clean chanterelles may simply be brushed without washing.'),(911293,4,'Whisk together the eggs, chopped herbs, and sour cream or creme fraiche.'),(911293,5,'Heat the oil in a small cast iron skillet or a small teflon pan. (I used a small six inch cast iron with 2 inch sides). When the oil is hot and just begins to smoke, add the drained and completely dry chanterelles to the pan, cooking in the oil until they are lightly caramelized and golden, about 2-3 minutes.Season the chanterelles to taste with salt and pepper, then add the butter and melt.'),(911293,6,'Add the egg mixture to the pan,  let this cook for 30 seconds, stirring occasionally to form soft curds which should only lightly envelop the chanterelles, keeping them visible and not hidden under egg.When the egg mixture begins to coagulate, then turn the heat off of the pan and allow the eggs to set with the residual heat of the pan.Finish the omelet by seasoning with a touch of fine salt like kosher or flaked salt and serve immediately.'),(911524,1,'Place meat in a large resealable plastic bag.In a medium bowl, mix together honey and Dijon mustard'),(911524,2,'Pour marinade over tenderloin and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.Preheat grill to about 400 degrees F.Lightly oil grill grate.'),(911524,3,'Remove meat from marinade and grill over indirect heat for approximately 20-25 mins or until a meat thermometer inserted into the center reads 145 degrees F. (Discard the remaining marinade)'),(911641,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.'),(911641,2,'Whisk together the eggs, egg whites, mustard, salt, and pepper. Stir in the ham, cheese, spinach, tomatoes, and green onions.'),(911641,3,'Spray a standard muffin tin with cooking spray or line with paper liners.'),(911641,4,'Pour in the egg mixture and bake for 12-14 minutes until cooked through and puffy.'),(911781,1,'Preheat oven to 190 degrees celsius (fan-forced).Grease a casserole dish and set aside.'),(911781,2,'Place the quinoa, water and vegetable stock into a saucepan and cook for 15 minutes or until the liquid has disappeared. Fluff up with a fork and place into the prepared casserole dish.Meanwhile, place the roughly chopped vegetables into the Thermomix bowl and finely chop on Speed 8 for 5-10 seconds (using the spatula to assist).'),(911781,3,'Remove the vegetables from the Thermomix bowl and strain any excess liquid away.'),(911781,4,'Place the finely chopped vegetables into the casserole dish with the cooked quinoa.'),(911781,5,'Place the cheese in to the Thermomix bowl and grate on Speed 10, 10 seconds. Set aside.In a clean Thermomix bowl, place the butter, milk, plain flour, salt, pepper and half of the grated cheese and cook for 7 minutes, 80 degrees, Speed'),(911781,6,'Pour the cheese sauce over the vegetables and quinoa and stir to combine.'),(911781,7,'Sprinkle over the remaining grated cheese.'),(911781,8,'Bake in the oven for 25-30 minutes or until the cheese is golden on top.'),(911805,1,'In a large pot, arrange chicken in a single layer.'),(911805,2,'Add salt, peppercorns, garlic, and bay leaves.'),(911805,3,'Add wine and enough water to cover chicken to about 1-inch high (I used about 6 cups).Over medium-high heat, bring to a boil, skimming scum that floats on top. When liquid begins to boil, reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for about 10 to 15 minutes or until center of chicken reads 165 F.Immediately remove chicken from pot and allow to cool to touch.'),(911805,4,'Cut into 1-inch cubes. Strain broth and reserve about 2 cups. Discard aromatics.In a sauce pot over medium heat, heat butter until melted.'),(911805,5,'Add onions and cook until limp.'),(911805,6,'Add sweet peppers and mushrooms and cook, stirring regularly, until softened.'),(911805,7,'Add flour and cook, stirring regularly, for about 2 to 3 minutes or until lightly browned.'),(911805,8,'Add reserved broth and heavy cream, whisking regularly until smooth and well-combined.'),(911805,9,'Add chicken. Lower heat, cover and continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce is thickened.Season with salt and pepper to taste.'),(911805,10,'Serve hot over rice, noodles or toasted bread.'),(911846,1,'To begin making the Pahari Aloo Palda Recipe, we will first grind the raw rice, peeled cardamom pods into a smooth powder.'),(911846,2,'Add this to the curd and whisk well and keep it aside.'),(911846,3,'Heat a kadai with oil, add cumin seeds, black cardamom, cloves and cinnamon stick and allow the aroma to be released for 10 seconds.'),(911846,4,'Add the sliced onions and saute till it softens, add the potatoes and saute till they get cooked.You can add some water and salt and close it with the lid and cook so that the potatoes get cooked faster.'),(911846,5,'Add the spice powders into the kadai and saute them well till the raw smell goes away.'),(911846,6,'Add whisked curd mixture slowly, keeping the heat to low.'),(911846,7,'Mix well, add salt and stir until it thickens little.'),(911846,8,'Serve the'),(911846,9,'Himachali Style Pahari Aloo Palda Recipe along with'),(911846,10,'Peshawari Naan Recipeand'),(911846,11,'Kelyachi Bhaji Recipeto enjoy your mid day lunch.'),(912170,1,'Cover the shiitake mushrooms in hot water (I use off-the-boil water for fastest soaking) and let them soak till fully hydrated, about 30 minutes or longer if they are large. Once soaked, squeeze out all the water, cut off the stems and slice into thin pieces.Cover the black fungus in hot water for about 15 minutes until fully rehydrated. Slice into ribbons.Soak the dried shrimp in hot water for about 10 minutes to soften.'),(912170,2,'Drain.Soak the glass noodles in room temp water for 10 minutes and drain immediately.Using scissors, cut the noodles into 2-3 sections to shorten. If not using right away, keep the noodles covered in plastic wrap so they dont dry out.'),(912306,1,'Ingredients1 head cauliflower cut into bite sized piecessalt and pepper to taste1 Cup cheddar cheese shredded4 slices bacon cooked and crumbled2 green onions sliced thin, optional'),(912306,2,'Get full recipe >> Loaded Cauliflower Bites @ Delicious Little Bites'),(912334,1,'Place 8 (3-ounce) paper cups on a rimmed baking sheet.In the container of a blender, process watermelon, 2 tablespoons sugar, and lemon juice until pured. Strain mixture through fine-mesh sieve into a medium bowl, pressing solids to release all liquid (you should have about 2 cups liquid).'),(912334,2,'Pour liquid into cups, filling about three-fourths full.Cover cups with plastic wrap, and insert a wooden stick through wrap into each cup. Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.In the container of a blender, process honeydew and remaining 2 tablespoons sugar until pured. Strain mixture through fine-mesh sieve into a medium bowl, pressing solids to release all liquid.'),(912334,3,'Remove cups from freezer, and remove plastic wrap (leave wooden sticks in place). Working quickly, fill cups with honeydew mixture, and sprinkle with mint. Freeze until honeydew layer is firm, about 4 hours. Tear paper cups away from ice pops to serve.'),(912589,1,'If its too hot right now to turn on the oven where you are, save this recipe for later, because it is easy and delicious. Cod, potatoes, and tomatoes are all cooked together in the oven with garlic and herbs (the tomatoes with basil, the cod and potatoes with rosemary). The only difficult part to get right is the timing, because the potatoes should be golden when the fish is just cooked through. Cod is even more susceptible to overcooking than other types of fish, and will become bland and dry if you are not careful. And so the potatoes and tomatoes go in the oven 10 minutes before the fish. To take the guesswork out of getting the fish right, it is advisable to use a thermometer with a probe.If you pull the fish at a core temperature of 45C/113F (taking into account it will continue to cook a bit from the residual heat), it will be flaky but still juicy.Ingredients'),(912589,2,'For 2 servings2 pieces of cod of about 200 grams (7 oz) each500 grams (1.1 lbs) waxy potatoes400 grams (.9 lbs) tomatoes1 Tbsp finely sliced fresh basil1 Tbsp minced fresh rosemary2 cloves garlic, mincedextra virgin olive oilsalt and freshly ground black pepper'),(912589,3,'Preheat the oven to 225C/440F (fan forced).'),(912589,4,'Cut the tomatoes in half crosswise and remove the seeds (with your fingers).'),(912589,5,'Put them upside down on kitchen paper to drain while you peel the potatoes.Peel the potatoes and slice them thinly.'),(912589,6,'Mix a minced clove of garlic with a tablespoon of minced rosemary and extra virgin olive oil in a small bowl.Season each piece of cod with salt and freshly ground black pepper on all sides.'),(912589,7,'Brush with the rosemary mixture on all sides.'),(912589,8,'Mix the remaining rosemary mixture with the sliced potatoes in a large bowl.Season the tomatoes with salt and freshly ground black pepper on the cut side.'),(912589,9,'Mix a tablespoon if finely sliced basil with a minced clove of garlic and olive oil in a small bowl, and put this mixture in the tomatoes.Lightly grease an oven dish with olive oil and arrange the tomatoes (cut side up) and potatoes in a single layer.'),(912589,10,'Bake for 10 minutes at 225C/440F (fan forced).Turn the potatoes and put the cod in the same oven dish, with the probe of the thermometer inserted in the center (if using).'),(912589,11,'Bake at 225C/440F until the core temperature of the cod is 45C/113F or until the cod is just cooked through and the potatoes are golden, about 10 minutes.If not using a thermometer, you may need to adjust the cooking time according to the thickness of the cod. My piece of cod was about 4 cm (1.5 inch) thick.Plate everything on preheated plates and serve.Wine pairing'),(912589,12,'This dish calls for a medium-bodied dry white with some mature notes because of the garlic and rosemary. This 5 year old Castelli di Jesi Verdicchio Riserva was outstanding with it. It has been aged in large oak, and there is no vanilla or butter but it does have some great mature notes. The verdicchio grape is the main variety for white wines in the Marche region in Italy. It is also used in Lugana under the name Trebbiano di Lugana.Flashback'),(912589,13,'These thai shrimp cakes were really good  I should make them again!Advertisements'),(912589,14,'Rate this:Like this:Tweet'),(912589,15,'Email'),(912589,16,'Print'),(912589,17,'Like this:Like Loading...Related'),(912919,1,'Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large skillet over medium high heat.'),(912919,2,'Rub the salmon all over with olive oil and lemon juice.'),(912919,3,'Sprinkle with chili flakes, paprika, salt, and pepper.'),(912919,4,'Place flesh side down in the skillet and sear until crisp and just beginning to caramelize, about 2-3 minutes. Flip and cook 1 minute more or until your desired doneness is reached.'),(912919,5,'Remove the salmon from the skillet.'),(912919,6,'Add another drizzle of oil to the pan, add the broccoli and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.'),(912919,7,'Add the tomatoes, garlic, oregano, lemon zest, salt and pepper and cook until the tomatoes begin to burst, about 5 minutes.'),(912919,8,'Remove from the heat and add a splash of wine.'),(912919,9,'Add the olives and slide the salmon back into the skillet to warm throughout.'),(912919,10,'Serve the salmon with a side of veggies and any sauce left in the skillet.'),(912919,11,'Garnish with fresh oregano.'),(913126,1,'Bring the water with salt to a boil.'),(913126,2,'Add the macaroni; stir and simmer until tender, about 5 minutes. Do not overcook.'),(913126,3,'Drain and rinse under cold water.'),(913126,4,'In a skillet, heat the oil and add the onions, celery, green pepper and garlic. Cook, stirring, until wilted.'),(913126,5,'Add the meat, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until the meat loses its red color.'),(913126,6,'Add the oregano, basil and tomatoes. Cook, stirring, for 5 minutes.'),(913126,7,'Add the cooked macaroni. Blend well and set aside. Keep warm.'),(913126,8,'Meanwhile, melt the butter in a saucepan, and stir in the flour with a wire whisk until well-blended.'),(913126,9,'Add the milk, stirring rapidly, and bring to a simmer. Cook, stirring, for about 5 minutes.'),(913126,10,'Remove the sauce from the heat, and stir in the Cheddar cheese, cayenne, nutmeg, and more salt and pepper to taste. Stir until the cheese melts.'),(913126,11,'Preheat broiler.'),(913126,12,'Spoon the macaroni mixture into a baking dish measuring 7 by 10 by 2 1/2 inches.'),(913126,13,'Pour the cheese sauce evenly over the macaroni mixture.'),(913126,14,'Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, and place under the broiler (about 4 to 5 inches from the heat source) until it is hot, bubbling and lightly browned.'),(913950,1,'Place all of the vegetables into a mixing bowl.'),(913950,2,'Combine the ingredients for the dressing, stir well to combine the vinegar and honey, and and pour the dressing over the vegetables.Toss lightly to combine.Refrigerate for about 30 minutes and serve.'),(916999,1,'How to Make It'),(916999,2,'Step 1'),(916999,3,'Preheat oven to 42'),(916999,4,'Step 2'),(916999,5,'To prepare crema, combine the first 8 ingredients in a small bowl; set aside.'),(916999,6,'Step 3'),(916999,7,'To prepare tacos, combine cumin and next 5 ingredients (through garlic powder) in a small bowl; sprinkle spice mixture evenly over both sides of fish.'),(916999,8,'Place fish on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.'),(916999,9,'Bake at 425 for 9 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),(916999,10,'Place fish in a bowl; break into pieces with a fork.'),(916999,11,'Heat tortillas according to package directions. Divide fish evenly among tortillas; top each with 1/4 cup cabbage and 1 tablespoon crema.'),(917478,1,'Preheat oven to 450F.In a small bowl, add ingredients for the zaatar spice mix and stir until blended. Set aside.Slice the potatoes into matchsticks place them on a baking tray covered with parchment paper.'),(917478,2,'Drizzle 1 tablespoon olive oil, season with salt and toss the potatoes until they are evenly coated.'),(917478,3,'Bake for 25-35 minutes, flipping them over halfway through the cooking process.Take the fries out of the oven and transfer to a large bowl.'),(917478,4,'Drizzle the remaining 1 tablespoon olive oil, add 2 tablespoons of the zaatar spice mix and toss until the fries are evenly coated.'),(917478,5,'Add more za\'atar spice mix if needed.'),(917478,6,'Serve.'),(917612,1,'Combine  cup chicken stock and the beans in a blender.Blend until completely smooth. Set aside.'),(917612,2,'Heat olive oil in a soup pot over medium heat.'),(917612,3,'Add onion and saut until tender, about 5 minutes.'),(917612,4,'Add garlic and saut for 1 minute.Stir in cumin, cayenne and green chilies.Stir in remaining 1 cup of chicken stock and bean mixture.Increase heat to medium high and bring mixture to a boil.Stir in chicken, salt, pepper, lime juice and cilantro.Decrease heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes to allow flavors to develop.'),(917612,5,'Serve with desired toppings.'),(917770,1,'Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.In a bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and shortening. With fingertips or pastry blender, rub or combine these ingredients together until the shortening resembles small beans. Set aside.In another bowl, dissolve the baking soda in the boiling water.'),(917770,2,'Add the corn syrup and molasses. Stir to blend.'),(917770,3,'Pour filling into the shell and sprinkle the crumb mixture over the top.'),(917770,4,'Bake in the middle of the oven for 10 minutes. Reduce the heat to 350 degrees F and bake for 25 minutes more. The filling should be set, but still quiver when the pan is tapped. Do not overbake.'),(918041,1,'Preheat oven to 375 degrees.'),(918041,2,'Add oats to a food processor. Process oats until they are very finely ground, nearly to a flour, about 2 - 3 minutes.'),(918041,3,'Add to a large mixing bowl along withflour baking soda, baking powder and salt.'),(918041,4,'Whisk 20 seconds. Set aside.In the bowl of an electric stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment cream together butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar until well combined.'),(918041,5,'Mix in eggs one at a time then blend in vanilla. With mixer set on low speed slowly add in dry ingredients and mix just until nearly combined.'),(918041,6,'Add in chocolate chips chopped chocolate and walnuts if using and mix (you can set a few chocolate chips aside first if you want some to press into tops of dough for looks). Scoop dough out 2 oz. at a time (nearly 1/4 cup) and shape into rounds (at higher altitude I recommend making taller dough balls, so more of an oval shape, for less spread).'),(918041,7,'Transfer 9 dough balls to an 18 by 13-inch baking sheet lined with a silicone liner or parchment paper, spacing them about 3-inches apart (refrigerate dough that\'s not currently baking).'),(918041,8,'Bake in preheated oven until nearly set but slightly under-baked, about 10 minutes.'),(918041,9,'Let cool several minutes on baking sheet then transfer to a wire rack to cool. Repeat process with remaining dough. Store cookies in an airtight container.*Scoop into measuring cup and level top to measure flour (don\'t fluff or sift flour first either, but be careful not to pack flour into measuring cup). If you live at a fairly high altitude like I do (4,500ft), or if you generally have issues with spreading cookies you can increase this amount by 1/4 cup (35g). Original recipe calls for 2 cups but that can all vary just depending on how the original recipe creator measured the flour - so I think 1 3/4 cups is fitting for the measurement method I use.Recipe source: adapted from NYT and others'),(918293,1,'Melt the chocolate in a double boiler or use the microwave.Microwave in 20 second increments, stirring after each until completely melted. Set aside to slightly cool (so it doesn\'t melt the butter or cook the eggs!).'),(918293,2,'Whisk the flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt together. Set aside.In a large bowl using a handheld or stand mixer fitted with a paddle attachment, beat the butter, brown sugar, and granulated sugar together on medium-high speed until smooth and creamy,about 2 minutes.'),(918293,3,'Add the eggs and vanilla extract,and beat on high speed until combined, about 1 minute. Scrape downthe sides and up the bottom of the bowl and beat again as neededto combine.'),(918293,4,'Pour in the slightly cooled melted chocolate and mix on medium speed until combined.On low speed, add the dry ingredients. Turn the mixer up to medium-high speed and beat until combined. Finally, beat in the walnuts and chocolate chips.Cover and chill the dough for at least 45 minutes in the refrigerator (and up to 4 days). If chilling for longer than a few hours, allow to sit at room temperature for at least30minutes before rolling and baking because the dough will be quite hard.Preheat oven to 350F (177C). Line baking sheets with parchment paper or silicone baking mats.'),(918293,5,'Roll the dough into balls, about 1.5 Tablespoons of dough each.'),(918293,6,'Place 3 inches apart on the baking sheets and bake for 11-12 minutes or until the edges appear set. The centers will look a little soft.'),(918293,7,'Remove from the oven and allow cookies to cool on the baking sheet for 5 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely. While the cookies are still warm, I like to press a few more chocolate chips or walnut pieces into the tops-- this is only for looks!Make ahead tip:Cookies stay fresh covered at room temperature for up to 1 week. You can make the cookie dough and chill it in the refrigerator for up to 4days. Allow to come to room temperature thencontinue with step'),(918293,8,'Baked cookies freeze well for up to 3 months. Unbaked cookie dough balls freeze well for up to 3 months.'),(918293,9,'Bake frozen cookie dough balls for an extra minute, no need to thaw.Click hereformy tipsand trickson freezing cookie dough.'),(918397,1,'Add the chicken pieces to a large bowl along with a couple of tablespoons of the olive oil, plus the rest of the ingredients up to and including the chopped oregano leaves, and allow to marinate for about 20 minutes, or even overnight, if doing ahead; once marinated, thread the chicken equally onto 8 bamboo skewers (that have been soaked in water for a few minutes). -'),(918397,2,'Add the well-squeezed out grated cucumber to a bowl, along with the rest of the ingredients, and fold together until well-blended; use immediately, or, keep covered and in the fridge until ready to use. (Sauce is good for a few days.)'),(918914,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.Slice your peaches and place in the bottom of a 9x13 baking dish. If using canned peaches, make sure to drain them first.'),(918914,2,'Combine flour, brown sugar, and oats in a large mixing bowl.'),(918914,3,'Cut the butter in until the mixture is crumbly. It\'s easiest to do when the butter isn\'t right out of the refrigerator, but when it\'s had a few minutes on the counter--but not at room temperature or softened.Cover the peaches with the crumbly topping, then bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.'),(920072,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray a 95-inch metal loaf pan with baking spray (or use butter and flour), set aside.'),(920072,2,'In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the melted butter, sugar, milk and sour cream.'),(920072,3,'Add the zucchini, lemon zest, vanilla and egg, mix until combined.'),(920072,4,'In a medium mixing bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Using a rubber spatula or wooden spoon, gently fold the dry ingredients into the wet ingredients, mixing just until combined.'),(920072,5,'Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan.'),(920072,6,'Spread the top of the batter to create a smooth, even layer.'),(920072,7,'Place in the oven to bake for 45-55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the bread comes out clean.'),(920072,8,'Remove from the oven and allow to cool in the pan for 15 minutes before removing and transferring the loaf to a wire rack to cool completely.'),(920072,9,'For the optional glaze: in a small mixing bowl whisk together the powdered sugar, lemon juice and lemon zest.'),(920072,10,'Drizzle over the warm (but not hot) bread.'),(920072,11,'Let set for 15 minutes before slicing.'),(920113,1,'Preheat oven to 350 F. Spray donut pans with cooking spray.'),(920113,2,'Combine greek yogurt and water in a bowl, and set aside.Get a large bowl and combine ALL the DRY ingredients.Get a smaller bowl and combine ALL the WET ingredients.'),(920113,3,'Add the yogurt/water mixture to this bowl.'),(920113,4,'Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients, and stir to combine.'),(920113,5,'Place your large decorating tip into the piping bag.Fill the piping bag with batter.Pipe into each donut cavity.***NOTE*** If you are not piping the batter, just use a spoon to fill the cavity.'),(920113,6,'Bake for 12-15 minutes until done. You can check the doneness with a cake tester.'),(920113,7,'Remove from oven, let cool slightly and remove donuts from pan onto cooling rack.ENJOY!!'),(920121,1,'Preheat the oven to 350F. Line an 8x8-inch square pan with parchment paper (double-check your pan size, because 9x9-inch wont work for this recipeyou\'ll end up with thin, dry brownies, so please don\'t do it).In a large mixing bowl, cream together the coconut sugar, peanut butter, and vanilla on medium-high for 1 minute using a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment.Meanwhile, in a small mixing bowl, whisk together the oat flour, cacao powder, baking powder, and sea salt. Set within reach of the mixer.With the mixer off, add the oat flour mixture. Then, pour the almond milk over the oat flour mixture and begin beating on low. Increase the speed to medium and beat for 15 seconds, or until just incorporated. The dough should pull together into large, moist mounds as it moves around the mixing bowl. If the dough is dry and broken into small crumbles, add more almond milk, 1 tablespoon at a time, and beat until it pulls together.'),(920121,2,'Transfer the dough to the lined pan and press into an even layer.'),(920121,3,'Bake for 16 to 18 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out mostly clean with several moist crumbs at the tip. Dont over-bake.'),(920121,4,'Transfer the pan to a cooling rack and cool completely.Prepare the glaze while the brownie cools.'),(920121,5,'Add the cacao butter, peanut butter, maple syrup, vanilla, and sea salt to a medium saucepan.'),(920121,6,'Heat over low heat and whisk constantly until about two-thirds of the cacao butter has melted. Then, remove the pan from the heat and continue whisking until the cacao butter melts completely and the mixture is smooth and glossy. Be careful not to overheat or scorch (or splash any water into the pan) or the cacao butter will seize and become gritty.'),(920121,7,'Let cool for 10 minutes to thicken slightly.Once the peanut butter brownie is completely cool, pour the peanut butter glaze over the brownie and tilt the pan back-and-forth to evenly coat the surface.'),(920121,8,'Transfer the pan to the freezer for 20 minutes, or until the glaze has completely set. (It will lose its glossy sheen and take on a matte finish when set.)Grasp the edges of the parchment paper and gently lift the brownie from the pan. Slice into 16 squares.Store the brownies in the refrigerator to maintain a dense, chewy texture and to keep the glaze well set.'),(920640,1,'Preheat oven to 400 f.'),(920640,2,'Slice the squash lengthwise. Scoop out the seeds and discard.'),(920640,3,'Very lightly oil the insides of each squash halve. Season with sea salt and pepper.'),(920640,4,'Place the squash halves face down on a large baking sheet and bake for about 40 minutes or until fork tender.'),(920640,5,'Spray a large skillet with cooking oil and heat it on medium-high.'),(920640,6,'Add onion and garlic and saut for a couple of minutes.'),(920640,7,'Next add the turkey meat and using a wooden spoon, break up the meat until no longer pink.'),(920640,8,'Season with sea salt, pepper to your taste.'),(920640,9,'Add in the tomatoes, Italian seasoning, red pepper flakes, basil and bring to a gentle boil.'),(920640,10,'Lower the heat and simmer for 15 minutes until the sauce is reduced.'),(920640,11,'When the squash is fully cooked, flip each halve over, use a fork to loosen the spaghetti \"noodles\" a bit, then divide the turkey sauce into each halve.'),(920640,12,'Top with shredded mozzarella and broil in the oven for an additional 4-5 minutes or until the cheese has melted and it\'s all bubbly.'),(920640,13,'Garnish with fresh chopped basil and totally enjoy!'),(920743,1,'In medium bowl combine butter and onions, mix to coat.'),(920743,2,'Sprinkle steak strips with garlic pepper blend and salt.  In 3-4 quart slow cooker layer half of onions and all of steak strips and bell pepper. Top with remaining half of onions.  In measuring cup combine water and bouillon. Stir until dissolved.'),(920743,3,'Pour over mixture in slow cooker.  Cover and cook on low for 6-8 hours.  About 10 minutes before serving, place bun halves cut side up on ungreased cookie sheet. With slotted spoon, top bottom halves with beef mixture. Top each with 2 pieces of cheese.  Broil 2-3 inches from heat until cheese is melted and top halves of buns are toasted.'),(920743,4,'Place top half on bottom.'),(920814,1,'To begin making the Goan Gawar Bhaji recipe, wash and chop cluster beans.'),(920814,2,'Heat oil in a heavy bottomed pan.'),(920814,3,'Add mustard seeds, cumin seeds, and asafoetida. After 15 seconds, turmeric powder, green chillies and onions. Cook till the onions become soft and translucent.Now add tomatoes and saute till mushy.'),(920814,4,'Add cluster beans, salt and mix.'),(920814,5,'Add some water, cover and cook till cluser beans are cooked.'),(920814,6,'Mix in between. Once the cluster beans is cooked and water has dried up, switch it off.'),(920814,7,'Garnish with grated coconut and chopped coriander.'),(920814,8,'Serve Goan Gawar Bhaji along with'),(920814,9,'Keerai Sambarand'),(920814,10,'Steamed Ricefor a weekday meal.'),(921239,1,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit. Line muffin tins with paper cups.In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, and salt.In another large bowl, whisk the eggs and 1 cup of sugar until thick and pale.'),(921239,2,'Add the milk, oil, and vanilla.'),(921239,3,'Combine wet and dry ingredients until almost combined.In a small bowl crush 1/2 cup of the blueberries with a pastry blender or fork, and toss withthe remaining 1/4 cup sugar, until coated.Fold all blueberries (crushed and whole) into the muffin batter. Do not over mix. Scoop batter into the prepared muffin cups 2/3 full.'),(921239,4,'Sprinkle with coarse sugar.'),(921239,5,'Bake at 400 degrees Fahrenheit for 14 to 16 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean from the center. Store in an airtight container.'),(921247,1,'Roast the eggplant.'),(921247,2,'Meanwhile, to make the tomato sauce, heat the olive oil in a large, heavy, preferably nonstick skillet over medium heat and add the onion. Cook, stirring, until tender, about 5 to 8 minutes, and add the garlic. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, about a minute, and add the tomatoes, salt (1/2 to 1 teaspoon), pepper, sugar, and basil sprigs. Turn the heat up to medium-high and when the tomatoes are bubbling, stir well and turn the heat back to medium. Cook, stirring often, until the tomatoes have cooked down and are beginning to stick to the pan, about 25 minutes.'),(921247,3,'Remove the basil sprigs, wiping any sauce that adheres to them back into the sauce.'),(921247,4,'Put the sauce through the fine blade of a food mill if you have not peeled the tomatoes. Otherwise pulse in a food processor fitted with the steel blade until coarsely pureed. Taste and adjust seasoning.'),(921247,5,'Preheat the oven to 400F. Set aside 1/4 cup of the Parmesan and mix with the breadcrumbs. Oil a 2-quart gratin or baking dish with olive oil.'),(921247,6,'Spread 1/2 cup tomato sauce over the bottom of the dish. Slice the roasted eggplant about 1/4 inch thick and set an even layer of the slices over the tomato sauce. Season with salt and pepper. Spoon a layer of sauce over the eggplant and sprinkle with basil and Parmesan. Repeat the layers one or two more times, depending on the shape of your dish and the size of your eggplant slices, ending with a layer of sauce topped with the Parmesan/breadcrumb mixture you set aside.'),(921247,7,'Drizzle 1 tablespoon olive oil over the top.'),(921247,8,'Place in the oven and bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until bubbling and browned on the top and edges.'),(921247,9,'Remove from the heat and allow to sit for at least 10 minutes before serving.'),(921247,10,'Serve hot, warm, or room temperature.'),(921419,1,'Warm the olive oil in a large soup pot.Saut the onions, garlic and tomatoes until they are cooked al dente.Stir in the lentils, then add the water, carrots and spices. (You may need more water as this cooks.)Cook on low to medium heat for approximately 40-50 minutes or until lentils and carrots are cooked through.If needed for consistency, add more water to get a good soupy texture.Cool slightly and serve with some whole grain garlic bread.'),(922056,1,'Preheat the grill pan and preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.'),(922056,2,'Place a rack over a large baking sheet.'),(922056,3,'Cut the 2 ends off the eggplant.'),(922056,4,'Cut the eggplants lengthwise, into 1/2-inch thick slices. Arrange eggplant slices onto rack.'),(922056,5,'Sprinkle with sea salt to help remove excess moisture and any bitterness from the eggplants. Set aside for about 10 to 15 minutes. Rinse off the salt from the eggplants and pat dry with a towel. Spray hot grill pan liberally with vegetable spray and then place eggplant slices on the grill until lightly browned on each side and tender, about 4 minutes per side.'),(922056,6,'Remove slices from the grill pan and allow to cool.'),(922056,7,'In a large bowl, beat eggs until lightly scrambled.'),(922056,8,'Mix the ricotta in with the egg.'),(922056,9,'Add mozzarella, 3 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese and toasted pine nuts and gently combine. Fold in basil just to combine. Do not overmix.'),(922056,10,'Place a tablespoon of the cheese mixture on 1 end of the eggplant and roll up tightly.'),(922056,11,'Place the eggplant rollatini into a greased (with olive oil) 13 by 9-inch baking dish, seam side down. Continue with remaining eggplant. Evenly distribute the tomato sauce on top of the eggplant rollatini. Season with salt and pepper.'),(922056,12,'Sprinkle with remaining 5 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese and bake for 15 minutes. When cooked, drizzle the top with extra-virgin olive oil.'),(922056,13,'In a large casserole pot, heat oil over medium high heat.'),(922056,14,'Add onion and garlic and saute until soft and translucent, about 5 to 10 minutes.'),(922056,15,'Add celery and carrots and season with salt and pepper.'),(922056,16,'Saute until all the vegetables are soft, about 5 to 10 minutes.'),(922056,17,'Add tomatoes and bay leaves and simmer uncovered on low heat for 1 hour or until thick.'),(922056,18,'Remove bay leaves and check for seasoning. If sauce still tastes acidic, add unsalted butter, 1 tablespoon at a time to round out the flavors.'),(922056,19,'Add 1/2 the tomato sauce into the bowl of a food processor. Process until smooth. Continue with remaining tomato sauce.'),(922056,20,'If not using all the sauce, allow it to cool completely and pour 1 to 2 cup portions into freezer plastic bags. This will freeze up to 6 months.'),(922699,1,'Preheat oven to 350F.'),(922699,2,'Heat a skillet over medium high heat.'),(922699,3,'Add chicken to the pan, and cook for 5-6 minutes until browned.'),(922699,4,'Sprinkle with taco seasoning, and add water.Bring to a boil, and cook for 2-3 minutes, until liquid is absorbed.'),(922699,5,'Spread tortilla chips onto a large sheet pan, be careful not to overlap too much.'),(922699,6,'Sprinkle with about 2 cups of cheese.Evenly spread chicken over the cheese.'),(922699,7,'Sprinkle with the remaining cheese.'),(922699,8,'Bake for 10-15 minutes, until cheese is completely melted and bubbly.'),(922699,9,'Remove from the oven and top with your desired toppings.'),(922699,10,'Serve immediately'),(922717,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large skillet, cook the ground beef and onion until the beef is no longer pink and drain.'),(922717,2,'Add the taco seasoning and refried beans and heat through. In a separate bowl, blend the mushroom soup with the sour cream. Then spread half of the soup mixture in the bottom of a baking dish.'),(922717,3,'Add a layer of 3 flour tortillas to the top of the soup mixture. You will need to cut or tear the tortillas and overlap them.'),(922717,4,'Spread on a layer of the ground beef mixture and top with about a cup of cheese. Repeat all of these layers and top with the remaining cheese.'),(922717,5,'Bake for about 20 minutes until cheese is nicely melted. Enjoy!'),(923345,1,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees then line a half sheet pan with a silat or foil. Slice spaghetti squash in half using a large, sharp knife then scrape out the seeds with a spoon and place cut side down on the prepared sheet pan. Roast for 30-40 minutes, or until the squash shreds relatively easily with a fork (dont overcook or the squash will become mushy.) Set aside to cool then turn heat down to 350 degrees. Once spaghetti squash is cool enough to handle, shred squash with a fork then add to a large bowl. Can be done a day ahead of time. Meanwhile, add chopped bacon to a large, 12 skillet then place over medium heat.'),(923345,2,'Saute until bacon has browned then transfer to a plate.'),(923345,3,'Remove all but 2 Tablespoons bacon grease from skillet then turn heat up to medium-high.'),(923345,4,'Add chicken and shallots or onion, season with seasoned salt and pepper, then saute until the chicken has cooked through.'),(923345,5,'Add spinach and garlic then saute until spinach has wilted, 1 minute. Scrape mixture into the bowl with the spaghetti squash.'),(923345,6,'Add ranch, eggs, and half the cooked bacon to the bowl, plus additional seasoned salt and pepper, then mix well to combine.'),(923345,7,'Pour mixture into an 8x8 baking dish (or similar sized baking dish) then top with remaining bacon.'),(923345,8,'Bake uncovered for 45-60 minutes or until the center has completely set and sides are golden brown.'),(923345,9,'Let cool for 15 minutes before slicing and serving.'),(923412,1,'Heat a small saute pan over medium heat.'),(923412,2,'Place the walnuts in the pan and toast the walnuts, about 4 minutes.'),(923412,3,'Remove the pan from the heat.'),(923412,4,'Remove the peels from the garlic cloves.'),(923412,5,'Place the arugula, garlic, basil, Parmesan cheese, and the lemon juice into a food processor or blender. Puree the mixture until it is well-combined. Slowly add in the olive oil and continue to puree until it is fully incorporated with the other ingredients (you can add more olive oil if you feel it is necessary).'),(923412,6,'Add salt and pepper to taste.'),(923412,7,'Heat a large non-stick skillet over medium high heat.'),(923412,8,'Heat the olive oil and add the spiralized sweet potatoes.'),(923412,9,'Saute the noodles, using tongs to fluff and stir the noodles as they cook. Cook until the noodles are tender, about 7-10 minutes.'),(923412,10,'Add the pesto and toss to coat.'),(923412,11,'Serve.'),(924556,1,'In the bowl of a blender, add crepe ingredients in the order they are listed:  cup warm water, 1 cup milk, 4 eggs, 4 Tbsp melted butter, 1 cup flour, 2 Tbsp sugar and a pinch of salt. Blend until well combined, scraping down the blender with spatula if needed.'),(924556,2,'Heat a medium (9-inch) non-stick pan over medium heat.'),(924556,3,'Add a tiny dot of butter** and spread it around with spatula to lightly coat. Once butter is hot, add about 3 Tbsp of batter, or enough to lightly coat the bottom of the pan, swirling the skillet as you add the batter to evenly coat the bottom of pan. Saut about 30 seconds per side or until lightly golden then flip using thin spatula and saut another 30 seconds or until second side is golden. Flip crepe out onto a clean surface such as a cutting board and let layers cool to room temp before stacking.In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with whisk, beat butter and condensed milk on high speed 7 min. It should look whipped and lightened in color.'),(924556,4,'Add 8 oz of softened cream cheese 1 Tbsp at a time while mixing on medium high speed. Continue beating for 3 minutes or until no longer lumpy. Some tiny lumps are ok and will not be noticeable in the cake.'),(924556,5,'Place first crepe layer onto serving platter and spread about 3 Tbsp or 1 ice cream scoop of frosting between each crepe layer, totaling 15 layers of crepes and 15 layers of cream.Refrigerate cake for at least 6 hrs or until frosting has firmed up (can be made 2 days ahead) - it will be much easier to slice after refrigeration and won\'t slide apart. To serve, dust with powdered sugar if desired and top with fresh berries.'),(925235,1,'Drain your tofu well, and score into cubes with a sharp knife.'),(925235,2,'Add 1 cup veggie broth to a large skillet and set to medium-high heat.'),(925235,3,'Add tofu to heated skillet and continue to chop it up using a kitchen spatula.Keep chopping the tofu down until you reach your desired consistency. Raise heat to high.Cook tofu for 10 minutes over high heat.'),(925235,4,'Add more veggie broth as needed and stir well every 2 to 3 minutes.Reduce heat to a simmer and add the nutritional yeast, garlic powder and ground pepper to taste.Adjust seasonings to your taste, adding more nutritional yeast for a richer, cheesier taste.'),(925342,1,'1 In einem großen Topf reichlich Salzwasser zum Kochen bringen.Kelchnudeln darin 8 – 10 Min. kochen lassen, dann in ein Sieb abgießenund beiseitestellen.2 Cashewkerne grob zerkleinern. Getrocknete Tomaten in einem'),(925342,2,'Sieb abtropfen lassen, Öl in einer kleinen Schüssel auﬀangen. Tomatenklein schneiden. Knoblauch abziehen und pressen, Zwiebel abziehenund klein schneiden. Babyspinat in einem Sieb waschen und abtropfenlassen. Limette halbieren und entsafen. In einem kleinen Topf 80 mlGemüsebrühe vorbereiten.3 In einer kleinen, beschichteten Pfanne Cashewkerne ohne Fettzugabe1 – 2 Min. anrösten, bis sie fein dufen. Dann herausnehmen und beiseitestellen.4 In einem großen Topf 2 – 3 EL Tomaten-Öl erhitzen. Zwiebel und'),(925342,3,'Knoblauch 1 – 2 Min. darin anschwitzen, Tomaten zufügen und 2 Min.weiterbraten.5 Babyspinat nach und nach unterheben und bei mittlerer Hitzezusammenfallen lassen. Dann mit der Gemüsebrühe ablöschen und einmal kurz aufkochen lassen. Bei niedriger Hitze Ricotta und1 TL Limettensaf unterrühren und mit Salz und Pfeﬀer abschmecken.Kelchnudeln unterheben und alles gut miteinander vermischen.6 Pasta mit Spinat-Ricotta-Soße auf tiefen Tellern verteilen, geröstete'),(925342,4,'Cashewkerne darüberstreuen und genießen!'),(925496,1,'Place chicken thighs into the crockpot.'),(925496,2,'Combine other ingredients in a large bowl and whisk together to combine.'),(925496,3,'Pour into the crockpot.Cook on low heat for 2 hours.'),(925496,4,'Remove chicken thighs, saving the liquid from the crockpot if desired. Shred the chicken.'),(925496,5,'Serve on tortillas, in sandwiches, or over rice!'),(925822,1,'Preheat oven to 350F.Slice frozen bacon into thin strips, then cook in a skillet over medium high heat until cooked through and golden.'),(925822,2,'Drain and remove to a plate lined with a paper towel.'),(925822,3,'Place the bottom half of the sliders in a greased 9x13 inch baking dish. Top with barbecue sauce, pineapple, bacon, and cheese.'),(925822,4,'Place the tops of the buns over the pizza toppings.In a small bowl, mix together the butter, oregano, and garlic powder.'),(925822,5,'Brush the mixture over top of the buns and bake for 20-25 minutes, until the tops are golden and the cheese has melted.'),(925822,6,'Serve immediately.'),(926489,1,'In a small bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder and soda, cardamom, and salt.In a separate large bowl, beat the butter and sugar together with a handheld mixer until pale and fluffy, about 4 to 5 minutes.'),(926489,2,'Add the eggs, yogurt, honey, and vanilla and mix until combined.'),(926489,3,'Add the sourdough starter and beat until the batter is smooth.Fold the dry ingredients into the wet ones about a third at a time, being careful not to over mix.(Small lumps are okay.)'),(926489,4,'Spread the batter into a greased 9-inch cake pan and bake for 20 to 22 minutes, until it begins to pull away from the pan.'),(926489,5,'Remove from oven and let cool.As your cake is cooling, brew your rose tea. I use dried, loose rose buds in a french press so that the flowers have room to expand. Honestly, though, its not going to matter much for this application because youre mixing it with other stuff. So feel free to make tea however you usually do it.When your tea is ready, measure out your honey into a saucepan over low heat and pour the tea in.'),(926489,6,'Whisk until fully dissolved, then remove from heat and whisk in the lemon juice. Set aside to cool.Go back to your cake and use a fork or toothpick to poke lots of tiny holes in the top of the cake.'),(926489,7,'Pour the cooled syrup over the cake in 3 or 4 applications, allowing each to soak in before the next.When youre done applying the syrup, make the drizzle icing. Use hand mixer to beat together the icing sugar, egg white and lemon juice until you see soft peaks, about 5 to 7 minutes on medium/high.Using a spatula, slather icing in a thick layer across the top of your cake. You want to be quick enough that the icing doesnt set mid-way through, and quite generous in your application. Get the icing right up to the edge of your cake so that it starts dripping.Once the top is covered, assess your cake. If enough icing has drizzled down the sides of the cake on its own, great! If not, use a teaspoon and drizzle manually. Obviously, more frosting = more drizzle, so adjust as needed.Just before serving, decorate with pistachios, roses and (optional) fresh figs.'),(926783,1,'For this recipe you will roast your brussels sprouts while cooking the bacon and apples in a skillet on the stovetop.Preheat your oven to 400 degrees and line a large baking sheet with parchment paper. Make sure the brussels sprouts halves are uniform in size, if not, cut the larger pieces to ensure even cooking. Toss them with the 2 tsp olive oil + salt and spread out on a parchment lined baking sheet. Roast them in the preheated oven for about 20 minutes, until they\'re browning and fork tender.Core the apple and chop into 1/2-1 inch cubes, set aside.'),(926783,2,'Heat a medium heavy skillet over med-hi heat (I love my cast iron for this!) and cut your bacon into one inch pieces (my favorite knife does a great job with this)'),(926783,3,'Add the bacon to the skillet and cook, stirring until about 3/4 of the way done (according to your own preference). At this point, add the apples and chopped rosemary and continue to cook and stir until the apples have softened and the bacon is fully cooked, adjusting the heat to avoid excessive browning if necessary.'),(926783,4,'Remove from heat.Once brussels sprouts are done, add them to the skillet and toss to combine all the flavors.'),(926783,5,'Sprinkle with more salt and pepper, if desire, and serve hot! This can be served as a side dish or with fried eggs for breakfast. Enjoy!'),(926822,1,'Prepare the pizza dough or use your favorite store bought brand.'),(926822,2,'Roll out the dough into a 9 inch circle/square on a lightly floured surface.'),(926822,3,'Let the pizza dough rest for 20 minutes while you prepare the dip and preheat the grill.Preheat your grill to medium high.Make the Garlic Blue Cheese Dip, and set aside.'),(926822,4,'Brush one side of the pizza dough with olive oil and place that brushed side on the grill. Cover the lid and let the pizza dough cook for 2 minutes.'),(926822,5,'Brush the top side of the pizza dough and then flip the dough so the newly brushed side in now facing the flame.Cover the lid and let the pizza dough cook fully for another 2 minutes.'),(926822,6,'Remove the pizza dough from the grill and then spread a layer of the blue cheese dip, top that with the crunchy kale beet blend, some sweet sliced pears, crumbles of blue cheese and a drizzle of balsamic vinegar.Slice the pizza into wedges or roll it out like a wrap and enjoy !'),(927395,1,'Mash the potatoes with a little butter (or dairy free spread) and grated cheddar (dairy or vegan).'),(927395,2,'Season well with salt and pepper.'),(927395,3,'Mix in the sweetcorn, peas and spring onions or any other vegetables you are using up.'),(927395,4,'Roll the mixture into 8-10 balls and gently press into round cakes, not too fat.'),(927395,5,'Chill for at least half an hour.'),(927395,6,'Cook in a little hot oil or bake until golden, firm and crunchy on the outside.'),(927395,7,'Enjoy!.'),(927597,1,'SEE HOW IT\'S MADE'),(927597,2,'Preheat oven to 300 degrees.'),(927597,3,'Separate the eggs very carefully, there must be no yolk in the white.'),(927597,4,'In one bowl, mix together the egg yolks, the 3 T. of Cottage Cheese OR Cream Cheese and the one packet of Sweetener until smooth.'),(927597,5,'In the other bowl add 1/4 teaspoon of Cream of Tartar to the whites and beat the whites on high speed until they are fluffy and form nice peaks.'),(927597,6,'Very carefully fold the egg yolk mixture into the egg whites until mixed, but try and not break down the fluffiness of the egg whites too much.'),(927597,7,'Spray two cookie sheets with Pam or other fat-free cooking spray.'),(927597,8,'With a large spoon, \"scoop\" the mixture into 10 even rounds on the sheets (about the size of the top-half of the McDonalds hamburger bun; roughly 3/4 inch thick and 4 to 5 inches across).'),(927597,9,'Bake on the middle rack. Here is when you have to watch them, because the cooking time is not the same on any two batches. It is somewhere around 1/2 hour, but it could be less or more. You just need to watch them until them become nice and golden brown (again, the color of a McDonalds bun).'),(927597,10,'Remove from the pans and cool on a rack or cutting board.'),(927597,11,'While warm they are crumbly and similar to cooked meringue - but don\'t let this fool you! Once completely cool, seal them in a ziplock storage baggie or a tupperware over night. They will totally change their consistency, to something much more like bread - a softer texture that is nice and chewy. If you do not like softer chewy bread, then eat them as they are, nice and crisp.'),(927597,12,'Since the sides that were facing the pan are perfectly flat, you use these to spread things on, or make sandwiches, or even as a burger bun! The choice is up to you, and you will be quite amazed at how much like a bun these really are!'),(927597,13,'Submit a Correction'),(927597,14,'GENIUS IDEAS, SERVED DAILY'),(927597,15,'Sign up for our newsletter!'),(927597,16,'keep me posted'),(927597,17,'Oops! Please try again with a valid email address.'),(927597,18,'Privacy Policy | Terms of Use'),(927597,19,'Yasss, you\'re in!'),(927892,1,'In a largemixing bowladd the flour, salt, yeast, sun dried tomatoes and cheese. Stir to combine.'),(927892,2,'Add the water and mix though until it is well mixed. I do this step with a spatula but you can also use your hands.Cover the mixing bowl with plastic wrap and let it sit on your counter for 12 to 18 hours. I do this at night so the next morning when I wake up is risen and ready to be baked.When you are ready to bake the bread, place your3.5 qtdutch-oven(lid included) in the oven and preheat it to 450 F degrees. (You must preheat your dutch-oven to 450F)Flour your work surface.'),(927892,3,'Remove the dough from the bowl and shape it into a ball.'),(927892,4,'Add some flour to the dutch-oven prior to placing the dough to make sure it won\'t stick. Carefully place the dough into the preheated dutch-oven. Cover the pot with the lid and place it back in the oven.'),(927892,5,'Bake for 30 minutes with the lid on.'),(927892,6,'Remove the lid and bake for another 15-20 minutes or until golden brown. The bread will keep for up to 2 days.Notes: Make sure the yeast that you use is not expired. You may also like this easy crusty whole wheat bread.'),(927991,1,'On a low-medium heat fry pan, add the oil and onions and fry for 10-15 minutes until they start to brown.'),(927991,2,'Add in the vinegar and sugar and fry for a further 5-7 minutes until soft and golden.'),(927991,3,'While the onion is frying, whisk together the fish and tamari sauce and garlic powder in a bowl.'),(927991,4,'Transfer the mix into a more shallow dish and place the slices of tofu inside to marinate for about 15-20 minutes, turning over after 10 minutes.'),(927991,5,'Place the tomato sauce, mayonnaise, cashews, cayenne and smoked paprika powders, water and salt into a blender and blend until smooth. Set aside.'),(927991,6,'Once you have finished frying the onions, remove them from the frying pan and leave the oil behind to use for the tofu.'),(927991,7,'Place the slices of tofu and fry for around 3-5 minutes on either side until brown and slightly crispy.'),(927991,8,'Start to assemble the sandwich by placing the lettuce, gherkins, avocado, tofu, onions and mayo on top of a slice of bread and top it with a slice or bread. Or which ever other way makes more sense to you! It may be a little bit too big to eat like this, so cut it in half.'),(930158,1,'Preheat the oven at 400 degrees Fahrenheit (200 Celsius)'),(930158,2,'Slice the zucchini, eggplant, onion and garlic and place in a bowl. Salt lightly.'),(930158,3,'Add the 2-3 tablespoons of olive oil and oregano and mix with your hands.'),(930158,4,'In another small bowl place the tomato halves with 1 teaspoon olive oil and mix gently so that the tomatoes are coated.'),(930158,5,'Spread the zucchini mixture in a pan leaving some space for the tomatoes and place those separately on the pan.'),(930158,6,'Roast for about 20 minutes until soft.'),(930158,7,'In the meantime make the tomato sauce. In bowl mix tomato paste with 3-4 tablespoons of water, 1 teaspoon of olive oil and a bit of oregano, you should have a thickish consistency to spread on the pita.'),(930158,8,'Place the pitas on a pan and spread tomato sauce on each pita, than add the zucchini mixture and then place on top the tomatoes.'),(930158,9,'Drizzle each pita with  teaspoon of olive oil.'),(930158,10,'At this point you can add some crumbled feta.'),(930158,11,'Put in the oven and bake for about 15 minutes.'),(930158,12,'Serve as is or cut in wedges.'),(930172,1,'Thaw puff pastry. Arrange one sheet pastry on hard surface.'),(930172,2,'Spread one half of cream cheese, feta cheese, olives, artichokes, spinach, red peppers, and cheese onto pastry.'),(930172,3,'Sprinkle with 1/4 tsp each of salt, pepper, and garlic powder.'),(930172,4,'Roll tightly.'),(930172,5,'Cut roll into 1/2 \" slices.'),(930172,6,'Place slices 1\" apart on parchment lined baking sheet.'),(930172,7,'Bake at 400 for 15 min or until golden brown.'),(930220,1,'Preheat oven to 325F; line muffin wells with liners.Beat the cream cheese until smooth, then beat in the eggs and all remaining ingredients.'),(930220,2,'Pour the batter into the prepared muffin tray and bake until the cheesecakes start to puff, but are still wobbly in the center, about 15 to 20 minutes (be careful not to over-bake!).Cool to room temperature and then chill for 2 hours before serving.Store leftovers covered in the fridge for up to 1 week.'),(931307,1,'Clean and trim the cauliflower, breaking it into medium sized pieces.'),(931307,2,'Place in a microwave safe bowl with 2 Tbsp of cream and 1 Tbsp of butter.Microwave, uncovered, on high for 10 minutes.Stir to coat cauliflower with cream/butter mixture.Microwave for another six minutes on high (or until tender.)'),(931307,3,'Remove from the microwave and put into a high speed blender or food processor along with the 8 slices of pepperoni and 1/4 cup mozzarella cheese.Puree until smooth.Season with salt and pepper to taste.You can adjust the cream and butter to your preference for consistency.'),(931307,4,'Spread the cauliflower puree into an 8 x 8 oven proof casserole dish.Cover with 1/2 cup shredded mozzarella cheese, and layer with pepperoni.'),(931307,5,'Bake at 375 degrees (F) for about 20 minutes.Alternatively you could microwave this for 5 minutes.'),(931307,6,'Serve hot.'),(932426,1,'Pour your heavy cream into a large mixing bowl and whip until it becomes whipped cream, with stiff peaks (about 15 minutes).'),(932426,2,'Combine your sweetened condensed milk, canned pumpkin, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and nutmeg in another large bowl and mix well.Grind your graham crackers and pecans to make a fine crumb.'),(932426,3,'Mix your butter and sugar with your graham cracker pecan crumb. Set aside.Scoop your heavy cream in with your sweetened condensed mixture and fold together until thoroughly mixed.'),(932426,4,'Pour  of your ice cream into a 3 qt container.'),(932426,5,'Sprinkle half of your crumb mixture over the top.'),(932426,6,'Pour additional  over and spread out to even, sprinkling the last of the crumb on top, and finishing with the last third of the ice cream on top.Cover and place in freezer for at least 6 hours.'),(933171,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees.'),(933171,2,'Combine all ingredients in a medium bow and mix well.Spray a miniature muffin tin with non-stick cooking spray. (The spray with flour in it works best!) Fill each indention 3/4 of the way full.'),(933171,3,'Bake in preheated oven for approx 18 minutes.Makes 24-28 mini muffins'),(934065,1,'Preheat oven to 180 degree C. Lightly grease a 9 by 13 inch pan and dust the inside with flour, tapping off excess flour.In a bowl combine flour, baking powder, and salt.Separate the eggs and place in two bowls. (Make sure that there is no water in the bowl in which you place the egg whites)In a bowl, add sugar to the egg yolks and beat on high speed until egg yolks turn pale yellow.'),(934065,2,'Add 1/3 cup of milk and vanilla, stir to combine.Gradually add the flour mixture into the egg yolk mix. Stir gently until just combined. Do not over mix.In another clean bowl, beat egg whites on high speed and continue to beat until you get stiff peaks.Fold the egg whites into the batter gently, making sure that you do not knock off the air.'),(934065,3,'Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Smooth into an even layer.'),(934065,4,'Bake for 35-40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.'),(934065,5,'Remove cake from oven and let it cool completely.'),(934065,6,'Combine the ingredients for sauce in a bowl. Keep aside.Poke holes with a fork all over the cooled cake.'),(934065,7,'Pour the sauce all over the cake making sure to pour it near the edges too. Reserve a little sauce to pour on cake while serving.Refrigerate the cake for an hour or overnight to allow the cake to soak up all the milk.In the meantime, whip the heavy cream, sugar and rose water till you get stiff peaks.'),(934065,8,'Spread this over the cake.Refrigerate for an hour and enjoy.'),(934640,1,'Bring the coconut milk to a boil in a small saucepan.'),(934640,2,'Add the quinoa and salt and cook for 15 minutes or so, until the quinoa is cooked.'),(934640,3,'Add the Bai5, oats, cinnamon, and salt - cook for just a few more minutes to soften the oats.In a small nonstick skillet over medium high heat, add the coconut flakes and shake in the pan until lightly toasted. You can also do this in the oven, but I find it\'s a bit faster on the stovetop.'),(934640,4,'Serve up the porridge topped with toasted coconut and anything your heart desires.'),(934768,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees.Line a 9x13 baking dish with foil, leave some overhang to make removal easier.Spray foil generously with nonstick cooking spray.In the bowl of a stand mixer, beat butter, granulated sugar, and brown sugar together until fluffy.'),(934768,2,'Add in eggs and vanilla extract and continue to beat.Lower speed of mixer and add flour, baking soda and salt, and mix until combined.'),(934768,3,'Add M&M\'s and mini chocolate chips and give a final stir, reserving some M&M\'s and mini chocolate chips for topping cookie bars.'),(934768,4,'Transfer cookie dough to prepared baking dish.Press additional M&M\'S and mini chocolate chips into top of cookie dough.'),(934768,5,'Bake 30 to 35 minutes on oven rack in lower third of oven to prevent over browning.'),(934768,6,'Let cool completely and cut.'),(935559,1,'Preheat oven to 425 degrees.'),(935559,2,'Combine oats, flour, 1/3 C sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl.'),(935559,3,'In another bowl, combine milk, egg and oil.'),(935559,4,'Add liquid ingredients to the dry ingredients, mix until moist only.'),(935559,5,'DO NOT BEAT!'),(935559,6,'Fold in blueberries.'),(935559,7,'Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.'),(935559,8,'Mix topping ingredients.'),(935559,9,'Sprinkle over muffin batter.'),(935559,10,'Bake 20- 25 minutes.'),(935559,11,'Serve warm.'),(935559,12,'Submit a Correction'),(935559,13,'device-icons'),(935559,14,'get the genius kitchen app.'),(935559,15,'Watch on your iPhone, iPad, Apple TV, Roku, or Fire TV.'),(935559,16,'Learn More'),(935706,1,'Combine lager, garlic, salt and pepper in a shallow bowl.'),(935706,2,'Add in the chicken breasts, cover with plastic wrap and allow to marinade in the refrigerator for 2 hours if time allows, or over night for a deeper flavour.When ready to cook, take out of the fridge for at least 20 minutes before cooking.'),(935706,3,'Heat skillet or pan over medium - high heat.'),(935706,4,'Drain chicken from marinade and fry breasts in a small amount of oil until golden browned on both sides and completely cooked through the centre (about 6-8 minutes per side, depending on the thickness of your chicken breasts). Fry in batches of two if you need to.'),(935706,5,'Transfer chicken to a warm plate.In the same pan, cook bacon until crisp, (about 6 minutes).'),(935706,6,'Transfer the bacon to a paper towel-lined plate to let drain.To the remaining bacon fat in the pan, add the onion and celery, and cook until soft, about 6 minutes. (If there is no remaining bacon fat, melt the butter in the pan instead). Then add garlic and cook until fragrant, (about 1 minute).'),(935706,7,'Pour in the beer and allow to reduce slightly (about 3-4 minutes).'),(935706,8,'Add in the flour and cook until golden, (about 3 minutes), then slowly add the stock, whisking until flour has combined with the liquid.'),(935706,9,'Whisk in the  the milk and let simmer, while whisking occasionally, until thickened.Stir in Worcestershire sauce, stock powder, mustard and hot sauce.'),(935706,10,'Remove from heat and stir in cheese.'),(935706,11,'Mix until cheese has melted, then stir in 3/4 of the crumbled bacon. Taste test and add any extra salt, pepper, cheddar or beer.Arrange chicken back into the pan and allow to warm through.'),(935706,12,'Garnish with chives or parsley and the remaining bacon.'),(936095,1,'Add olive oil and garlic to a large skillet and bring to medium high heat. Cook garlic until lightly browned.'),(936095,2,'Add in the cauliflower rice and cook a few minutes until cauliflower is about halfway cooked.'),(936095,3,'Add chicken broth and cook cauliflower until tender (about 5 minutes). Most of the chicken broth should evaporate during the cooking but if you have a lot leftover, drain out broth until you have only about 3 tbsp of liquid left. Stir in heavy cream and cheese. Cook at a low simmer until sauce becomes uniform and cauliflower is evenly coated (about 2 minutes).'),(936095,4,'Remove from heat.'),(936095,5,'Garnish with parsley and black pepper. Top with additional freshly grated cheese before serving.'),(936649,1,'In a large pot heat olive oil over medium heat.'),(936649,2,'Add in the onion and cook for several minutes until softened.'),(936649,3,'Add in the garlic and stir and let cook about 15 seconds or until fragrant.'),(936649,4,'Add in the broth and milk. Stir to combine.'),(936649,5,'Add the cauliflower florets and seasonings. Bring to a simmer, cover and let simmer about 10 minutes until the cauliflower is softened and easily mashed with the stirring spoon.Turn the heat off, remove the bay leaf, and using an immersion blender, blend the soup until the cauliflower is all pureed and no large chunks remain. (If you dont have an immersion blender you can carefully transfer the soup to a blender or food processor to blend, then return to the pot.)Turn the heat back to medium heat, add the broccoli and bring soup back to a simmer. Cover and let cook another 10 minutes.Once the broccoli is softened and easily mashed, then again turn the heat off and using the immersion blender, blend the broccoli to desired consistency. I prefer no large chunks in my soup, and to make it nice and creamy.Once blended, turn the heat back to low, add the cheese and stir until the cheese is melted.'),(936649,6,'Serve warm and enjoy! Top with additional cheese if desired.'),(937624,1,'Mix all ingredients togetherin a medium bowl until well combined.'),(937624,2,'Serve with tortilla chips and raw vegetables for dipping and enjoy!'),(937627,1,'Ja, ich wei was nun viele denken. Das hat der CK (oder die Welt) noch gebraucht:Ein Rezept fr Pfannkuchen!! Aber glaubt mir, aus eigener Erfahrung kann ich Euch sagen: Es ist ntig!Das Mehl, die Milch, die Eier und die Prise Salz mit dem Handrhrgert zu einem glatten Teig verrhren, bis dieser leichte Blasen wirft. Dann den Teig fr ca. eine halbe Stunde im Khlschrank ruhen lassen.Dann den Teig aus dem Khlschrank nehmen, noch einen guten Schuss Mineralwasser zufgen und das Ganze nochmals kurz durchrhren.Die Herdplatte anfangs auf hchster Stufe aufheizen und etwas Butter in die Pfanne geben. Am gleichmigsten gelingen die Pfannkuchen so: Die heie Pfanne von der Kochstelle nehmen und die Butter durch geschicktes Schwenken gleichmig verteilen. Nun mit einem groen Schpflffel eine Kelle Teig in die heie Pfanne geben und diesen ebenfalls durch Schwenken gleichmig verteilen.Wichtig: Nun auf jeden Fall lange genug warten bis die Unterseite richtig schn gebrunt und der Pfannkuchen entsprechend fest geworden ist. Das merkt man ganz leicht, wenn man versucht den Pfannkuchen mit dem Pfannenwender anzuheben. Wenn das ganz einfach geht dann kann man den Pfannkuchen problemlos wenden ohne dass dieser zerreit. Nun noch die zweite Seite schn goldgelb backen.'),(938122,1,'Heat a medium stockpot over medium heat.'),(938122,2,'Add the olive oil, followed by the carrots and onions.  Saut for about five minutes, stirring frequently until beginning to brown.'),(938122,3,'Add the pepper and salt.  Stir to combine.'),(938122,4,'Add the stock and water, and bring the pot to a boil.One the mixture is boiling, add the pasta.  Cook for about 8 minutes.'),(938122,5,'Add the chicken and kale and cook for 5-7 more minutes, until the pasta is cooked.'),(938122,6,'Serve immediately.  Soup may also be stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.  Reheat in the microwave in 30 second increments, stirring in between, until piping hot.'),(938186,1,'Add flour, 2 cups warm water, oil, sugar, salt, yeast, eggs, to large bowl.'),(938186,2,'Mix until all ingredients are combined.'),(938186,3,'Add additional water if needed to achieve a nice, thick, workable dough. Cover with plastic wrap. Allow mixture to sit at room temperature for 2 hours before refrigerating for up to 3 days, but for a minimum of 2 days (the flour needs that much time to form gluten strands to give the bread strength and texture.)When you are ready to make the challah, remove dough from refrigerator and braid as desired. To make a 3-strand braid, divide dough in half. Divide each half into 3 evenly-sized pieces.'),(938186,4,'Roll each piece into a long log. Braid each piece, pinched ends to seal. Repeat with other half of dough.'),(938782,1,'Melt the butter in a heavy bottomed pan. Stir in the milk,salt and brown sugar. Bring to a hard boil and cook for 3 minutes.'),(938782,2,'Remove from heat.'),(938782,3,'Add the powdered sugar and vanilla. Beat with a mixer or a large spoon until the sugar is incorporated.'),(938782,4,'Pour into a foil lined butter 8 x 8 pan.Chill for 2 hours.'),(938939,1,'Heat oil in a heavy based large pan over a medium heat.'),(938939,2,'Add the onion, celery and pepper and saut for 2/3 mins, stirring frequently.'),(938939,3,'Add the garlic and stir for a further min.'),(938939,4,'Add the smoked paprika and cumin and stir for a further minute.'),(938939,5,'Add the tomato paste, tomatoes and stock and bring to the boil.'),(938939,6,'Add the lentils and courgette, reduce the heat to low and allow to simmer for around 10 mins. Stir occasionally and add more liquid (stock or water) if the mixture is starting to dry up.'),(938939,7,'Add the kidney beans and chickpeas, cover and allow to simmer for a further 20 mins. (Stir occasionally)'),(940208,1,'In a medium skillet brown the diced kielbasa sausages over medium-high heat stirring occasionally until all the sausage pieces are nice and toasted.'),(940208,2,'Add the cooked kielbasa and the remaining ingredients to a 4 quart or larger slow cooker and stir to combine.Cover and cook on LOW for 2 to 3 hours.'),(940208,3,'Serve with your favorite chips, crackers or slices of crusty bread.'),(940279,1,'Preheat oven to 425F.'),(940279,2,'Place tomatoes and garlic on a baking tray, drizzle with 2 tablespoons of olive oil, season with salt, pepper and red pepper flakes, roast for about 25 minutes, or until soft and charred on the tops.'),(940279,3,'Remove tray from oven and set aside.Set up the Instant Pot to the Saut function and wait until it reads HOT.'),(940279,4,'Add 2 tablespoon of olive oil, once the oil heats up, about 30 seconds, add the diced onion, red bell pepper and celery ribs, season with the garlic powder, onion powder, dried basil, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper. Cook for 2-3 minutes, stirring occasionally.'),(940279,5,'Add the tomato paste and stir to combine.'),(940279,6,'Add the garlic and roasted tomatoes with all the juices from roasting. Stir to combine.'),(940279,7,'Add the chicken or veggie broth, stir to combine. Adjust for salt and pepper and cover with the lid.Select the Soup function, adjust temperature to MORE, adjust cooking time to 10 minutes.Once the 10 minutes have passed, use a 10 Minute Natural Release (explained in the post) to release the pressure. After the 10 minute natural release, open the valve and release the remaining pressure. When valve drops carefully remove lid'),(940279,8,'Open the Instant Pot, Select the Saut function, stir the soup, and stir in the heavy cream. Taste and adjust for salt and pepper. If the soup is too thick, you can add more chicken stock,  cup at a time.Using an immersion blender or a Vitamix, puree the mixture until its very smooth. I transferred the soup in two batches into the Vitamin to puree it, but if you use an immersion blender you can puree the soup directly in the Instant Pot.'),(940279,9,'Serve garnished with grated parmesan cheese and fresh basil leaves.Store in the fridge for up to 3-4 days. Read the post for freezer instructions.Enjoy!'),(940652,1,'Place dry couscous and olive oil in a small bowl and stir with a fork to coat the grains.'),(940652,2,'Pour boiling water over the oiled couscous and gently stir.Cover and let sit for 5 minutes.Fluff up the couscous with a fork before serving.'),(940903,1,'Adjust oven rack to lower middle position and heat oven to 350 degrees. Grease bottom only of regular loaf pan, or grease and flour bottom and sides of nonstick 9-by-5-by-3-inch loaf pan; set aside.'),(940903,2,'Combine first five ingredients together in large bowl; set aside.'),(940903,3,'Mix mashed bananas, yogurt, eggs, butter, and vanilla with wooden spoon in medium bowl.Lightly fold banana mixture into dry ingredients with rubber spatula until just combined and batter looks thick and chunky. Scrape batter into prepared loaf pan. To help minimize a crack that can result in the bread, using a rubber spatula, create a line or well that runs the length of the pan.'),(940903,4,'Bake until loaf is golden brown and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 50-55 minutes. Cool in pan for 5 minutes, then transfer to wire rack.'),(940903,5,'Serve warm or at room temperature.'),(941874,1,'MAKE CORNBREAD IN ADVANCE:Preheat the oven to 37'),(941874,2,'In a medium sized bowl, combine sugar, milk, eggs, melted butter, Cornbread'),(941874,3,'Mix, and cayenne.'),(941874,4,'Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan, and bake for 24 to 28 minutes; a toothpick will come out clean, top will crack, and edges will be golden brown. Cool completely.'),(941874,5,'Remove from the pan using a small offset spatula or butter knife to release the sides, turn pan over onto cutting board, and turn out of pan.'),(941874,6,'Cut whole cornbread in quarters, each quarter in half horizontally, and finally cut -inch strips, quarter turn and cut -inch cubes. Allow cubes to dry out on half sheet pan for a day or two, or dry in 200 oven for about 1 to 2 hours, gently tossing a couple of times. Cubes should be dry on the outside, but NOT all the way through like a crouton.STUFFING: Preheat the oven to 37'),(941874,7,'Butter 8 x 8-inch pan generously.Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.'),(941874,8,'Add the onions and cook, stirring for about 15 to 20 minutes or until soft and caramelized. Season with salt and pepper, add sage and cook for one more minute.'),(941874,9,'Place the cornbread pieces in a large mixing bowl, add onions and toss until well combined. In a separate bowl, whisk together the egg, cream, and stock, and distribute over the bowl. Carefully toss all the ingredients together until thoroughly coated; some pieces will start to break apart, and others to stick together. (If it needs more liquid, add a little extra cream or stock, a TBSP or two at a time.)Spoon into buttered baking dish, cover with foil, and bake for 30 minutes.'),(941874,10,'Remove foil and bake another 15 to 20 minutes until hot, and a little crusty with some color on top. To stuff into a turkey, stuff both the neck and the body cavities, using about 1/2 to 3/4 cups of stuffing per pound of turkey. Do not pack it tight -- the stuffing needs to reach 165 degrees F. Any extra can bake alongside in a separate dish. Chefs Note: To make this dish vegetarian, use a vegetable broth instead of chicken stock, and bake in a buttered dish rather than stuffed in a turkey. Pamela\'s Products, Inc.'),(941917,1,'Roll the dough to fit a  12 fluted tart pan Prick the dough all over with a fork and refrigerate until firm'),(941917,2,'Preheat the oven to 325F convection or 350F regular'),(941917,3,'Bake the tart shell until it\'s light brown around the edges and pale in the center, about 10-15 minutes'),(941917,4,'Set the crust aside to cool while you make the filling'),(941917,5,'Cream the sugar and butter together until light and aerated'),(941917,6,'Add the eggs and mix to combine'),(941917,7,'Add the almonds, extracts and rum'),(941917,8,'Spread  the frangipane evenly into the tart crust'),(941917,9,'Arrange the apples slices in a pretty petal pattern, starting with the outside edge and working your way towards the middle'),(941917,10,'Bake until the filling is set, about 45 minutes'),(941917,11,'Turn on the broiler and run the tart under the broiler for a minute or two to brown the top of the tart.Warm the apricot preserves in the microwave for 30 seconds, stir in the rum'),(941917,12,'Brush  the warm preserves over the warm tart'),(941917,13,'Cool to room temperature'),(941917,14,'Best served at room temperature'),(942123,1,'Preheat the oven to 350F. Line two baking sheets with parchment paper.In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda, salt, and cornstarch together. Set aside.Beat the butter and both sugars together until light and fluffy. Beat in the egg and vanilla.Stir in the flour mixture and mix until just combined.Fold in the potato chips and pecans into the cookie dough.Take two tablespoons of dough and roll into balls.'),(942123,2,'Bake for 8-10 minutes, or until golden brown. Allow to cool on the baking sheet for a minute, then transfer to a wire rack. Allow to cool completely.Melt the chocolate in the microwave by heating it on 50% power for 30 seconds at a time, mixing well to help even melting.Dip the cookies in the chocolate and allow the chocolate to firm.'),(942123,3,'Serve immediately. Best within 24 hours, but will keep in an airtight container at room temperature for three days.'),(943093,1,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.'),(943093,2,'Place potatoes and carrots on large baking sheet and drizzle with 1 Tbsp olive oil, sprinkle with salt and pepper; toss to coat.'),(943093,3,'Baked for 25 minutes, stirring once.Meanwhile in a medium sized bowl mix together all of ingredients for meatloaves.In a separate small mixing bowl combine ingredients for sauce.'),(943093,4,'Remove veggies from oven, make room for 8 meatloaves. Top each meatloaf with sauce.Form meatloaf mixture into 8 meatloaves, place on sheet pan with veggies.'),(943093,5,'Bake for 25-30 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.'),(943367,1,'In a large saucepan, small stock pot, or bowl of your instant pot combine honey,  cup water, and sea ssalt and heat over medium heat until it gets to the soft ball stage (235*).As the honey-water mixture heats, attach the whisk attachment to your stand mixer.'),(943367,2,'Place gelatin and remaining  cup of water in the bottom of the mixer bowl, and use a fork (the mixer attachment usually doesn\'t get the powdered gelatin at the very bottom) to mix.'),(943367,3,'Add in 1 tablespoon more water if needed, until all the gelatin is wet. Allow to sit so the gelatin absorbs the water as the honey-water mixture comes to the correct temperature.Once the honey mixture is at the correct temperature, remove from heat and turn the mixer onto medium-low.Slowly pour the hot honey mixture into the gelatin as the stand mixer stirs, taking about a minute to pour in all the honey mixture. Do not scrape the sides of the pans, pour in only what comes out easily from the pan.Once all the honey-mixture is in the mixer bowl with the gelatin, raise speed as you can without the mixture starting to splatter, until it\'s on high speed (or medium-high if you can\'t get it to high without splatters).You now have marshmallow cream! Keep the mixer running on high for another 5-10 minutes, or until the marshmallow cream starts to form soft peaks when the mixer is lifted, you can also tell it is getting to this point because a line is left when the mixer whisk runs through the cream, rather than immediately merging back together.As you wait for the marshmallows to whip in the mixer, prepare a large (9x13 or similarly size) casserole dish by lining it with parchment paper that covers both the bottom and the edges, and then either spraying the parchment with cooking spray, or rubbing with a thin layer of coconut oil or other oil.When the marshmallow cream holds soft peaks, use a spatula to gently scoop into the middle of the prepared pan, and then smooth it evenly. Greasing the spatula with coconut oil can help prevent it from sticking.Allow marshmallows to set overnight.The next day, grease a large chef\'s knife with coconut oil. Lift marshmallows out by the parchment and place parchment directly onto a cutting board.Use the greased chef\'s knife to cut marshmallows into cubes. Allow to dry further for a couple hours, then transfer to an air-tight container, with parchment between the marshmallows.'),(943755,1,'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease a shallow baking dish.'),(943755,2,'In a small bowl, stir together the honey, Dijon mustard, melted butter and pepper.'),(943755,3,'Place chicken in the greased baking dish, and pour the honey mustard sauce over it.'),(943755,4,'Bake for 45 minutes in the preheated oven, basting frequently with the sauce, until chicken is firm and juices run clear.'),(945031,1,'Spray a 9-inch square baking dish with cooking spray and line with parchment paper.'),(945031,2,'Spread the chopped pecans in a single layer on top of the parchment.'),(945031,3,'Add butter, sugar, and salt to a heavy bottomed 3 quart pot'),(945031,4,'Bring to a boil over medium low heat, stirring frequently.Once the candy is boiling, stir frequently, slowly and evenly, until the candy has reached 290F to 300F, or \"hard crack\" on a candy thermometer.Once the candy has reached 290F-300F, remove from heat and gently pour over the chopped pecans.'),(945031,5,'Let the candy sit for a few minute, undisturbed, before sprinkling the chocolate chips over the top.Cover the baking dish with foil and let sit for 5 minutes or until the chocolate has softened.'),(945031,6,'Remove the foil and gently spread the softened chocolate into an even layer. An offset spatula works best for this.'),(945031,7,'Place the candy in the refrigerator and let cool completely. Give it at least 2 hours.Lift the parchment out of the baking dish and place the toffee on a cutting board or solid surface.Use a knife to gently break it into smaller pieces.Store in an airtight container in a cool place.'),(945776,1,'To make cookie crust, combine cookie crumbs, sugar, salt and butter together in small bowl and mix with fork. Press into buttered 8-inch tart pan.'),(945776,2,'Bake at 350F for 10 minutes. Set crust aside. To make filling, combine eggs, brown sugar, pumpkin pie spice and salt in bowl of stand mixer fitted with whisk attachment.'),(945776,3,'Add pumpkin puree and heavy cream and mix until incorporated. Measure 1 cup of mixture and set aside. Set baked crust on sheet pan.'),(945776,4,'Pour filling into crust. In bowl, combine melted chocolate with reserved filling. Spoon on top of tart and swirl into filling.'),(945776,5,'Bake until center is set and no longer appears shiny, 40-45 minutes.'),(945776,6,'Let tart cool to room temperature and store in fridge until ready to serve.'),(945829,1,'Heat a large skillet or medium saucepan over medium-high heat.'),(945829,2,'Add the oil and onions and cook onions down until lightly golden, about 3-4 minutes.'),(945829,3,'Add ginger and garlic and let cook for 30 seconds, stirring so it doesnt burn.'),(945829,4,'Add the chicken, tomato paste, and spices. Cook for 5-6 minutes or until everything is cooked through.'),(946645,1,'Make the muffins by combining 2 tablespoons of brown sugar together with  teaspoon of cinnamon and the diced apples; mix well then set aside.Using a hand mixer, beat together the oil, white sugar, and remaining brown sugar until well combined.'),(946645,2,'Add the sour cream, egg, and vanilla; beat well until creamy.In a separate bowl, combine the flour together with the baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt until well combined.Slowly add the flour mixture to the wet mixture until just combined.'),(946645,3,'Add the cinnamon apples and liquid to the batter; stir to combine.'),(946645,4,'Place into the refrigerator for 10-15 minutes.Preheat the oven to 425 degrees. Line a muffin tin with muffin liners.Prepare the topping while the batter is in the refrigerator and the oven is preheating, by combining the diced butter, white sugar, flour, and cinnamon together until crumbly.Spoon the batter evenly into the muffin liners (I only had enough batter for 11).'),(946645,5,'Sprinkle the topping evenly over the muffins.'),(946645,6,'Place the muffins into the oven and bake for 5 minutes. Without opening the oven door, lower the temperature to 375 degrees and continue to bake for 9-11 minutes, or until a tester inserted into the muffin comes out clean.'),(946645,7,'Remove from the oven and allow to cool in the pan for a few minutes before moving to wire racks placed over parchment paper (for easier cleanup later after glazing).While the muffins are cooling make the glaze by combining the powdered sugar together with a bit of milk and mix until creamy and smooth.'),(946645,8,'Drizzle the glaze on top of the cooled muffins.'),(946645,9,'Serve and enjoy.'),(946774,1,'In medium saucepan over moderate low heat, melt butter.'),(946774,2,'Whisk in flour and cook, whisking, for 5 minutes.'),(946774,3,'Add broth in a stream, whisking to boil. Simmer for 5 minutes.'),(946774,4,'Let gravy cool, transfer to a bowl and cover and chill overnight. Platter your cooked turkey and cover it loosely with foil.'),(946774,5,'Pour drippings into a fat separator and discard fat.'),(946774,6,'Place bird roasting pan on two burners of the stovetop and use medium heat. (Make sure your roasting pan is stove top safe. Do NOT do this with a glass roasting pan.)'),(946774,7,'Add wine and reserved drippings, scraping up the brown bits on bottom of pan.'),(946774,8,'Whisk in premade gravy and any juices from resting turkey.'),(946774,9,'Add salt and pepper to taste, cooking until hot, and serve with your bird.'),(946966,1,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.Pat turkey completely dry.Melt butter in a small saucepan.'),(946966,2,'Add sage and let cook for 5 minutes.'),(946966,3,'Add garlic and cook one more minute.'),(946966,4,'Remove from heat and let cool for 10 minutes.Rub sage butter over the skin of the turkey, as well as pushing it under the skin over the meat.Season with salt and pepper.'),(946966,5,'Place quartered onion and apple into the cavity of the turkey.'),(946966,6,'Place turkey in a roasting pan UPSIDE DOWN (breast side down).Roast in preheated oven for 1 hour.Carefully turn turkey over and roast another 60-90 minutes, or until thermometer placed in thick part of the thigh reads 165 degrees F.'),(946966,7,'Remove from oven and let rest for one hour. This ensures the turkey stays super moist so this step is very important!Carve, serve, and enjoy!'),(947845,1,'CRUSTPreheat oven to 350F. Have a deep-dish pie plate ready to go.'),(947845,2,'Place the bread mix into the bowl of a food processor or electric mixer. Scatter the cubed butter over the bread mix. Pulse, if using food processor, about 10 times to work the butter into the flour. If using a mixer, turn on to low speed to work the butter into the flour. It will resemble cornmeal with larger, pea-sized pieces of butter remaining. This can also be done by hand using a pastry cutter and gentle hand.With the processor or mixer running on low speed, add the ice water to the bowl a little at a time. You may not need all of it. When the dough comes together into a ball, stop the motor. Use a spatula to scrape down the sides. Check to see if it\'s too dry. If so, add a little more water. It should be soft and pliable, like cookie dough, without being too sticky. Form dough into two small disks. Wrap both and refrigerate for 20-30 minutes to make it easier to work with. (Note: you only need one crust. The other can be frozen or used for another pie.)'),(947845,3,'Place the chilled dough onto a piece of parchment paper.'),(947845,4,'Place another sheet of parchment paper on top and use a rolling pin to roll the dough into a large round about \" thick.Carefully transfer the dough to the pie plate. If it cracks or breaks, no worries. Just press it back together and continue. Trim off the excess dough from around the edge. Decorate the edge all the way around by pinching it between two fingers, or using another method. Chill until ready to fill and bake. (The pie dough scraps can be saved and rolled out to form pie crust cookies.)Preheat oven to 400F. Prick the bottom of the crust with a fork a few times.'),(947845,5,'Place crust in oven and bake for 15-20 minutes, or just until golden on the edges.'),(947845,6,'Let cool for 10-15 minutes.Lower heat to 350F. Prepare filling.FILLING'),(947845,7,'Whisk together egg yolks, brown sugar, maple syrup, and cornstarch until the sugar has mostly dissolved.'),(947845,8,'Add the remaining ingredients and whisk well.'),(947845,9,'Pour filling into the partially baked crust.'),(947845,10,'Bake for 45-50 minutes, or until the filling is set, but still jiggles a little in the center. (It may take as long as an hour)'),(947845,11,'Let cool completely. Refrigerate, if desired, or serve at room temperature. Store any leftover pie in an airtight container in the fridge.WHIPPED CREAMBeat the heavy cream with an electric mixer, or by hand with a whisk, until soft peaks form.'),(947845,12,'Add the molasses and vanilla extract. Continue beating or whisking until medium peaks form. Dollop on top of pie.'),(947885,1,'Combine dry ingredients, stirring to mix well.'),(947885,2,'Pour egg whites into dry ingredients. Stir with a spoon or small spatula until you have an even, lump free batter. Batter should be very pourable, like a thin crepe batter. If its not thin enough, add more egg white. Do NOT add water or any other liquidthey will stick and turn brittle.'),(947885,3,'Heat a nonstick skillet over medium high heat. Spray pan with olive oil spray. Measure 2 Tbsp of batter at a time, into a small cup.'),(947885,4,'Pour batter into the pan all at once. Swirl quickly to distribute batter like a round crepe. Cook until set on one side. Edges will begin to curl slightly. Flip and cook on the second side. Each tortilla takes about 90 seconds to fully cook.'),(947885,5,'Once both sides are set, flip back and forth in the pan, until you see brown spots on each side. The texture changes from semi-moist and dries out like a tortilla. Cool on a clean dish towel.'),(947885,6,'Store cooled tortillas in an airtight container in the fridge up to a week, or freezer up to 1 month.'),(947893,1,'Roughly chop the pecans, almonds, and prunes.Chop the onion, apple, and celery into 1/4\" pieces.Chop the hotdogs and bacon into 1/4\" pieces.Finely chop the garlic. Leave the raisins whole.Over medium heat, fry the bacon until it starts to brown. (About 5 minutes)'),(947893,2,'Add the chopped onions. Cook until the onions until they just start to brown. (About 5 minutes)'),(947893,3,'Add the ground meats to the pan. Break up the meat with a spatula.Cook the meat until it is no longer pink then add the chopped hotdogs.'),(947893,4,'Mix and cook for 5 minutes.'),(947893,5,'Add the chopped celery and garlic.'),(947893,6,'Mix and cook for 5 minutes.'),(947893,7,'Add all of the remaining ingredients to the pan.'),(947893,8,'Mix well.Cover your pan with aluminum foil or a lid. Cook for 15 minutes over medium heat.'),(947893,9,'Remove the foil but don\'t discard.'),(947893,10,'Mix the stuffing well.'),(947893,11,'Add 1/4 white wine or water if the stuffing is getting dry.Cover again with the lid or aluminum foil and cook for another 15 minutes.Turn off the heat and let rest for 10 minutes.'),(947893,12,'Remove the foil and check the salt.'),(947893,13,'Add more salt if needed.'),(948052,1,'Preheat oven to 350F. Line two large baking sheets with parchment paper or silicone baking mats and set aside.In a mixing bowl, whisk together the Pillsbury BEST All Purpose Flour, baking powder, and salt. Set aside.In a large mixing bowl using an electric mixer, cream together the Crisco All-Vegetable Shortening and sugar until well combined.'),(948052,2,'Mix in the egg, milk, and vanilla extract until fully combined.Slowly add the dry ingredients and mix until just combined.Divide the dough in half.'),(948052,3,'Roll out each half on a lightly floured surface to -inch thickness for crisp cookies or -inch thickness for softer cookies.'),(948052,4,'Cut with 2 to 3-inch cookie cutters.'),(948052,5,'Place 2 inches apart on baking sheet. Re-roll any scrap pieces of sugar cookie dough and cut out more cookies as needed.'),(948052,6,'Bake in separate batches at 350 for 8-13 minutes or until the tops of the cookies are set and lightly browned. Baking time will vary based on how thick you roll the cookie dough and the size of your cookie cutter.Cool on the baking sheet for 5-10 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to finish cooling.Beat the cream cheese and Crisco All-Vegetable Shortening until well combined, then mix in the powdered sugar and vanilla until fully combined.Frost the cooled sugar cookies and top with sprinkles if desired.'),(948274,1,'Before You Cook  Preheat oven to 450 degrees  Thoroughly rinse produce and pat dry  Prepare a baking sheet with foil and cooking spray1Prepare the Ingredients'),(948274,2,'Peel, trim, and cut carrot into \" pieces on an angle. Trim bottoms off Brussels sprouts and halve (quarter if larger than ping-pong balls). Pat pork tenderloin dry, and season all sides with a pinch of salt and pepper.2Roast the Vegetables'),(948274,3,'Toss carrot pieces and Brussels sprouts with 2 tsp. olive oil,  tsp. salt, and  tsp. pepper on prepared baking sheet.'),(948274,4,'Spread into a single layer, leaving room to add pork tenderloin later. Roast 7 minutes.'),(948274,5,'Remove from oven. Vegetables will finish cooking in a later step. While vegetables roast, sear pork tenderloin.3Sear the Pork Tenderloin'),(948274,6,'Place a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.'),(948274,7,'Add 2 tsp. olive oil and pork tenderloin to hot pan. Sear until lightly browned on three sides, 2-3 minutes per side.'),(948274,8,'Remove pan from burner and transfer pork to baking sheet with vegetables. Reserve pan; no need to wipe clean. 4Finish the Vegetables and Pork Tenderloin'),(948274,9,'Roast until vegetables are tender and pork tenderloin reaches a minimum internal temperature of 145 degrees, 8-12 minutes. Rest pork tenderloin at least 5 minutes before slicing.While vegetables and pork roast, make glaze.5Make the Glaze'),(948274,10,'Return pan used to sear pork tenderloin to medium-high heat.'),(948274,11,'Add red cooking wine and fig preserves and stir occasionally until it thickens into a thin syrup, 1-2 minutes. If glaze reduces too much or thickens too much as it cools, stir in water 1 Tbsp. at a time until desired thickness is reached.Plate dish as pictured on front of card, garnishing vegetables with goat cheese (crumbling with your hands if needed). Bon apptit!'),(948417,1,'Place the cashews in a bowl and cover them with boiling water. Soak for 1 hour.Bring a large pot of water to a boil and add the spinach. Cook until bright green and wilted, about 2 minutes. (If using frozen spinach, it might take a few more minutes to thaw.)'),(948417,2,'Pour the spinach into a colander and apply pressure to the top to remove all of the liquid.'),(948417,3,'Transfer the spinach to a cutting board and coarsely chop it. If theres still a lot of liquid coming out, place a towel over the top and apply pressure to soak up any remaining water.'),(948417,4,'Heat the olive oil in the same pot over medium-high heat.'),(948417,5,'Add the onion and garlic and saut for 5 minutes.'),(948417,6,'Add the spinach and cook for 5 minutes more.Meanwhile, drain the cashews and add them to a blender with the water, lemon juice, vinegar, salt, and nutmeg. Blend on high for about 1 minute, until very smooth.Stir the cashew cream into the spinach mixture, then remove from the heat.'),(948417,7,'Serve immediately.Make It Ahead'),(948417,8,'This dish can be made up to 3 days in advance and stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator. Return the mixture to a skillet over medium-low heat and stir until heated through.'),(948727,1,'Place a steamer basket in a large pot, fill with water to just below the bottom of steamer basket. Bring water to a boil.'),(948727,2,'Add cauliflower florets and celery root pieces. Steam until vegetables are tender and easily pierced with a fork (about 12-15 minutes).'),(948727,3,'Drain, reserving  cup of cooking water .*'),(948727,4,'Place cauliflower and celery root back in pot.'),(948727,5,'Add butter and sour cream. Use and immersion blender to combine ingredients.'),(948727,6,'Add necessary amount of reserved cooking liquid to bring to desired consistency.'),(948727,7,'Add salt and pepper to taste. **'),(948727,8,'Place in serving bowl and top with fresh chives.'),(948887,1,'Add turkey, pecans, celery, cranberries and grapes to a mixing bowl. In another bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise and sour cream or yogurt, curry, lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste. Taste and adjust seasonings.'),(948887,2,'Add about half to the turkey mixture and mix to combine.'),(948887,3,'Add as much of the remaining dressing to the turkey as desired.Chill.'),(948887,4,'Serve on lightly buttered rolls with a leaf of lettuce if desired.'),(949106,1,'Instead of Turkey: Lemon and Herb Roasted Chicken1 roasting chicken, about 4 to 5 lbjuice of 1/2 lemonsalt and pepper to taste1 onion, peeled and quartered1 rib celery, cut into large chunksfew sprigs fresh parsley4 tbs melted butter3 tbs coarsely chopped fresh parsley1/4 tsp dried rosemary, crumbled1/2 tsp dried leaf thyme'),(949106,2,'Preheat oven to 350.Rub inside of chicken with lemon juice.'),(949106,3,'Sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),(949106,4,'Add the onion quarters, celery, and a few sprigs of parsley to chicken cavity.'),(949106,5,'Combine the melted butter with the chopped parsley, rosemary, and thyme.'),(949106,6,'Brush some of the butter mixture over the chicken.'),(949106,7,'Place chicken in a shallow roasting pan and roast at 350 for about 20 min per pound.Baste with melted butter and herb mixture several times.'),(949106,8,'Serves 4'),(949274,1,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).'),(949274,2,'Heat 2 teaspoons olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat, and cook and stir the sausage until browned.'),(949274,3,'Transfer the cooked sausage to a large baking dish.'),(949274,4,'Pour 1/4 cup of olive oil into the skillet, and cook the potatoes, stirring occasionally, until browned, about 10 minutes.'),(949274,5,'Place the potatoes into the baking dish, leaving some oil. Cook and stir the green and red peppers and onions in the hot skillet until they are beginning to soften, about 5 minutes.'),(949274,6,'Add the vegetables to the baking dish.'),(949274,7,'Pour wine and chicken stock over the vegetables and sausage, and sprinkle with Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper. Gently stir the sausage, potatoes, and vegetables together.'),(949274,8,'Bake in the preheated oven until hot and bubbling, 20 to 25 minutes.'),(949274,9,'Serve hot.To continue, See the next page (Click the red Next button below)Like this article on Facebook:Facebook'),(949274,10,'Pinterest'),(949274,11,'Print'),(949274,12,'Messenger'),(949274,13,'Next'),(949558,1,'In a medium saucepan, bring the coconut milk up to a simmer on low to medium heat.Stir in the vanilla extract before adding the white chocolate. Turn the heat to low and stir until the chocolate is completely melted.'),(949558,2,'Add the sea salt and stir.'),(949558,3,'Remove from the heat and slowly stir in the coconut and almond meal. Press the mixture in to a bowl or lunch box and cover.'),(949558,4,'Place in the fridge to firm for around 90 minutes.'),(949558,5,'Place the remaining coconut in a bowl and using a teaspoon scoop out a heaped spoon of the truffle mixture.'),(949558,6,'Roll the truffle in to a ball before rolling it through the coconut. Repeat with remaining mixture'),(949558,7,'Place the truffles in the fridge, covered, for at least one hour and up to two days before serving.  Take the truffles from the fridge and sit at room temperature for 15 minutes before serving.'),(949558,8,'Combine the sugar and water in a small saucepan over low to medium heat and stir until the sugar dissolves completely. Allow the mixture to come to a simmer and reduce the hea