rigerated until needed.Pre-heat oven to 400F. Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper.With a floured rolling-pin roll out each chilled dough round into a 1/8 thick sheet, then cut each into a 12 circle with a pizza cutter, using a sturdy dinner plate or bottom of a springform pan as your guide.'),(956327,2,'Transfer one round to the parchment-lined baking sheet.Use a spatula to evenly spread the spinach & artichoke filling into a thick layer atop the dough, leaving a 1/2 border around the edges. Top with the remaining dough round, pinching along the edges to create a loose seal. Next, set a small glass upside down in the middle. Use a pizza cutter to slice away from glass (i.e. not through center), cutting the dough into quarters.'),(956327,3,'Cut through each quarter again, making 8 strips, and again, making 16 strips, and one last time so that you have 32 strips of pastry emanating from the center. Lastly twist each strip a few times, then use a pastry brush to coat the entire wreath with whipped egg.'),(956327,4,'Bake on oven middle rack for 30 minutes until golden all over, then immediately plate and serve! Pair with marinara sauce for dipping.'),(956641,1,'Heat oil in a pan.'),(956641,2,'Add Kalonji, dry red chilies, and Hing.'),(956641,3,'Saute for few seconds.'),(956641,4,'Add chopped Tomatoes and salt.'),(956641,5,'Mix well.(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});Cover it and cook it for 3 to 4 minutes on medium flame.Now open the lid, add chili powder, sugar, and jaggery.'),(956641,6,'Mix very well.Cover it again and cook it for 2 to 3 minutes more.Open the lid and stir once. Again cover it and cook it for 4 to 5 minutes or until it thickens a little bit.That\'s it!! Sweet, Sour and Spicy Tomato Chutney is ready.'),(956641,7,'Serve it with Paratha, Idli, Dosa, Pakora or use it as a spread.'),(957346,1,'Stir together powdered sugar, peanut butter and butter until well mixed.Shape peanut butter mixture into 1 inch balls, placing them on a baking sheet covered with waxed paper.'),(957346,2,'Let balls stand for 20 minutes until dry.Melt the dipping chocolate or confectioners coating.Drop balls one at a time in melted chocolate.Using a fork, remove from the chocolate, letting excess chocolate drip off.'),(957346,3,'Place back on the waxed paper.'),(957346,4,'Let stand until dry.Store tightly covered in a cool dry place.Nutrition Info :Servings: 30 pieces'),(957346,5,'Smartpoints: 5Calories 51Total Fat 3.3 gSaturated Fat 1.2 gTotal Carbohydrate 4.8 gDietary Fiber 0.3 gSugars 4.3 gProtein 1.1 gTo continue, See the next page (Click the red Next button below)Like this article on Facebook:Facebook'),(957346,6,'Pinterest'),(957346,7,'Print'),(957346,8,'Messenger'),(957346,9,'Next'),(957542,1,'Place the first four ingredients in a large bowl.'),(957542,2,'Cut organic extra virgin coconut oil into the dry ingredients until large crumbs form.In a small mixing bowl, beat the egg and add the remaining ingredients. Stir until well incorporated.'),(957542,3,'Add the wet mixture to the dry mixture. Stir until a sticky dough forms. Cover and refrigerate the dough for 30 minutes.'),(957542,4,'Remove from refrigerator and slice the dough in half. Rewrap and refrigerate one of the halves.'),(957542,5,'Roll the portion of dough into uniform,  inch sheet.'),(957542,6,'Cut out shapes or traditional round cookies.'),(957542,7,'Transfer to a lightly oiled cookie sheet.'),(957542,8,'Bake in a preheated 350-degree oven for approximately 13 minutes or until cookies turn slightly golden and become firm. Allow to cool on the cookie sheet for one to two minutes before transferring to a cooking rack. Repeat with the second batch of dough.'),(957845,1,'Stir 3 tablespoons oil, parsley, coarsely chopped rosemary, chopped sage, zest, fennel seeds, chile, and garlic in a bowl. Rub all over turkey, and season with salt and pepper.'),(957845,2,'Place in a shallow, nonreactive baking pan; cover. Refrigerate at least 4 hours (or overnight).'),(