t is very tender, 5 to 6 hours. Reduce to warm and remove lid.Meanwhile, place potatoes, rosemary, remaining 2 cloves garlic, and 2 tablespoons salt in a stockpot; add water to cover. Bring to a boil over high. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until potatoes are very tender, about 15 minutes.'),(958739,3,'Remove from heat.'),(958739,4,'Remove rosemary and garlic, then drain.Reserving cooking liquid, remove short ribs and vegetables from slow cooker. Skim fat from liquid, then transfer to a blender; add remaining  teaspoon salt. With center piece of blender lid removed, secure lid on blender.'),(958739,5,'Place a clean dish towel over lid opening. Puree on medium-high until smooth.'),(958739,6,'Serve potatoes and short ribs with vegetables and sauce.'),(958739,7,'Garnish with parsley leaves and pepper.'),(958880,1,'For the Brownies:Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Grease a 913\'\' inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.Chop the butter and the unsweetened chocolate into chunks and place together in a microwave safe bowl. Microwave on low power in 30 second intervals, stirring in between, until melted. (You could also melt them over LOW heat in a saucepan, stirring constantly). Set aside to cool, stirring occasionally.In a large bowl beat together the eggs, sugar, and vanilla.  Slowly add the melted chocolate, while stirring.In a separate small bowl combine the flour and baking powder. Stir the flour into the chocolate batter, just until combined. Don\'t over-mix.'),(958880,2,'Pour batter into greased pan and bake for 20-30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.'),(959662,1,'Add everything to a large crockpot.Set the slow cooker to low and cook for 8-10 hours.Stir well before serving to shred the chicken.'),(959662,2,'Add in cooked noodles and gently stir together.'),(959662,3,'Serve and enjoy!'),(961458,1,'In a 6 quart Instant Pot, place chicken, onion, carrots, bay leaves and peppercorns.'),(961458,2,'Add cold water enough to fill up to 2/3 full line or approximately 10 cups.***Close the lid, set pressure vent to Sealing and press Pressure Cooking for 30 minutes. Display will say ON, Instant Pot will take about 30-40 minutes to come to pressure, you will see a bit of steam coming out from a valve, then float valve will rise and countdown from 30 minutes will begin.After, your Instant Pot needs to bring pressure down before you can open it, which will be indicated by a dropped down float valve. You can let it do it on its own which will take at least 30 minutes - Natural Release. OR you can do Quick Release by turning pressure valve to Venting position, which takes 3-4 minutes. I recommend doing so with a long wooden spoon and outside. Trust me, its a messy process but I usually do not have time to wait.Open the lid and using a mesh strainer discard any foam, onion, bay leaves and peppercorns. At this point chicken is so cooked, you can  easily break it into pieces with a long utensil right inside the pot.'),(961458,3,'Remove bones if you wish (they are super soft, so I take out only big ones).'),(961458,4,'Add salt, oregano, basil, garlic powder and pasta. Stir, close lid, turn on Keep Warm and let pasta cook for 15 minutes if using gluten free or egg noodles, and 25 minutes if using whole wheat pasta. Open, add dill and serve hot. That was easy dinner in one pot.In an 8 quart Instant Pot, place chicken, onion, carrots, bay leaves and peppercorns.'),(961458,5,'Add cold water enough to fill up to 2/3 full line or approximately 15 cups.***Close the lid, set pressure vent to Sealing and press Pressure Cooking for 30 minutes. Display will say ON, Instant Pot will take about 40 minutes to come to pressure, you will see a bit of steam coming out from a valve, then float valve will rise and countdown from 30 minutes will begin.After, your Instant Pot needs to bring pressure down before you can open it, which will be indicated by a dropped down float valve. You can let it do it on its own which will take at least an hour - Natural Release. OR you can do Quick Release by turning pressure valve to Venting position, which takes 4-5 minutes. I recommend doing so with a long wooden spoon and outside. Trust me, its a messy process but I usually do not have time to wait.Open the lid and using a mesh strainer discard any foam, onion, bay leaves and peppercorns. At this point chicken is so cooked, you can  easily break it into pieces with a long utensil right inside the pot.'),(961458,6,'Remove bones if you wish (they are super soft, so I take out only big ones).'),(961458,7,'Add salt, oregano, basil, garlic powder and pasta. Stir, close lid, turn on Keep Warm and let pasta cook for 15 minutes if using gluten free or egg noodles, and 25 minutes if using whole wheat pasta. Open, add dill and serve hot. That was easy dinner in one pot.'),(962294,1,'Line two baking sheets with parchment paper and set aside.'),(962294,2,'Add the water and 4 cups sugar to a large pot or Dutch oven. Bring the mixture to a boil, stirring to help dissolve the water.'),(962294,3,'Add the orange slices and use a spoon to press them down a bit into the water. Reduce to a simmer, and cook for 20 minutes.Carefully remove each slice from the water and lay flat on the baking pans.Allow the slices to sit for several hours.'),(962294,4,'Add the extra sugar to a shallow bowl and lightly coat both sides of each slice in the sugar.'),(962294,5,'Place the slices on a wire rack overnight.The slices will be slightly sticky, but not dried completely.Store the slices in an airtight container with a lid, separated between sheets of parchment paper.'),(962569,1,'Step 1'),(962569,2,'To prepare the filling, rub five-spice powder evenly over pork.'),(962569,3,'Heat a grill pan over medium-high heat. Coat the pan with cooking spray.'),(962569,4,'Add pork to pan; cook 18 minutes or until a thermometer registers 155, turning pork occasionally.'),(962569,5,'Remove pork from pan, and let stand 15 minutes.'),(962569,6,'Step 2'),(962569,7,'Cut pork crosswise into thin slices; cut slices into thin strips.'),(962569,8,'Place pork in a medium bowl.'),(962569,9,'Add onions and next 7 ingredients (through 1/4 teaspoon salt); stir well to combine. Cover and refrigerate.'),(962569,10,'Step 3'),(962569,11,'To prepare dough, combine 1 cup warm water, sugar, and yeast in a large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.'),(962569,12,'Step 4'),(962569,13,'Lightly spoon flour into dry measuring cups; level with a knife.'),(962569,14,'Add flour, oil, and 1/4 teaspoon salt to yeast mixture; stir until a soft dough forms. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface. Knead until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes).'),(962569,15,'Place dough in a large bowl coated with cooking spray, turning to coat top. Cover and let rise in a warm place (85), free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in size. (Gently press two fingers into dough. If indentation remains, dough has risen enough.)'),(962569,16,'Step 5'),(962569,17,'Punch dough down; let rest 5 minutes. Turn dough out onto a clean surface; knead in baking powder.'),(962569,18,'Let dough rest 5 minutes.'),(962569,19,'Step 6'),(962569,20,'Divide dough into 10 equal portions, forming each into a ball. Working with one dough ball at a time (cover remaining dough balls to keep from drying), roll ball into a 5-inch circle.'),(962569,21,'Place 1/4 cup filling in center of dough circle. Bring up sides to cover filling and meet on top. Pinch and seal closed with a twist. Repeat procedure with remaining dough balls and filling.'),(962569,22,'Step 7'),(962569,23,'Arrange 5 buns seam side down, 1 inch apart, in each tier of a 2-tiered bamboo steamer. Stack tiers; cover with lid.'),(962569,24,'Step 8'),(962569,25,'Add water to a large skillet to a depth of 1 inch; bring to a boil over medium-high heat.'),(962569,26,'Place steamer in pan; steam 15 minutes or until puffed and set. Cool 10 minutes before serving.'),(962569,27,'Chef\'s Notes'),(962569,28,'Kick up the spice level with some red chili peppers, cilantro, or jalapeos. Tiny cubed cucumbers make a fresh, crunchy addition to this Asian favorite. Hint: The beauty of this recipe is that you don\'t have to stick with pork. Make it a veggie, bean or even seafood bun.'),(962923,1,'Press the Saut function on the control panel of the Instant Pot. Click the Adjust key and you can choose less, normal or more- heat setting. I selected the normal, it will start to heat up and you will see ON sign on the LED display. After the pot has turned hot, you will see the HOT sign on the display. Now, you can start sauting. Important: While sauting do not close the pot with the instant pot lid.'),(962923,2,'Add 1 tablespoon oil, let it turn hot.'),(962923,3,'Add onion, season with salt and saut for a few minutes till light golden.'),(962923,4,'Add ground beef, break the ground beef using an wooden spoon to avoid formation of lumps. Saut for a few minutes till the pink color has faded.'),(962923,5,'Add garlic powder, chili powder, cumin powder, coriander powder, dried oregano and salt.'),(962923,6,'Combine well.'),(962923,7,'Add green pepper, red pepper and chopped tomato.'),(962923,8,'Combine well.'),(962923,9,'Add tomato sauce, soy sauce and water, combine well.Close the lid. Click on the Cancel key to cancel the saut mode. Make sure the pressure release valve on the lid is in the sealing position.Click on Manual function first and then click on Pressure, select high pressure. (there are 2 options: low and high pressure). Click the + button and set the time to 15 minutes and walk away. After 15 minutes of pressure cooking, it will beep.You can either have the steam release naturally, it will take around 20 minutes. Or after 10 minutes, turn the pressure release valve on the lid to venting and you can see the steam releasing. Be careful as the steam is very hot. After the pressure has released completely, open the lid.If the stew is watery, you can cook for a few more minutes by turning on the saut function. Saut, Adjust to normal and let cook for a few more minutes.'),(962923,10,'Add cilantro and corn if adding at this point, combine well and let cook for a few minutes.I served this with pasta, add pasta into a bowl, top with ground beef stew and add cheddar cheese on top and serve. Enjoy!'),(963291,1,'In a small bowl, mix together the fish sauce, oyster sauce, and sugar. Keep near the stove, along with the chicken and vegetables.'),(963291,2,'Heat a wok or large skillet over high heat until very hot.'),(963291,3,'Add the oil and swirl the pan to coat the bottom.'),(963291,4,'Add the chicken in an even layer and sear, undisturbed, for about 1 minute.'),(963291,5,'Add garlic, stir, and continue cooking for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Chicken will be lightly browned, but not cooked through.'),(963291,6,'Add the green onions, bell pepper, onions, ginger, and sauce. Stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes, until the chicken is cooked through and the bell peppers and onions are crisp-tender.'),(963291,7,'Serve immediately, with plain white or brown rice.'),(963379,1,'Wash and peel the potatoes.'),(963379,2,'Cut them into 1/4th inch thick pieces and place in a cold bowl of water for about 30 minutes. (If you plan on soaking longer than 30 minutes, place in the fridge covered)Adjust the oven rack to be the 2nd from the top. Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F. Line a large pan with parchment paper (do not skip the parchment) and set aside.'),(963379,3,'Remove the fries from the water and dry VERY thoroughly.Toss together seasoned salt (1/2 tablespoon), pepper (pinch), chili powder, garlic powder, and cumin.'),(963379,4,'Remove 1 teaspoon of these spices.'),(963379,5,'Place the COMPLETELY dried fries on the prepared sheet pan. Cover with 1 to 2 tablespoons olive oil and the 1 teaspoon of spices. Toss and then quickly separate to be in one layer.'),(963379,6,'Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes, remove, flip, and bake for another 15 minutes.MEANWHILE, prepare the fish. Take the Panko, dried thyme, minced garlic, and 2 tablespoons olive oil and place in a large pan over medium to medium high heat. Stir pretty constantly for 4-6 minutes or until the Panko is toasted.'),(963379,7,'Remove from the heat and set aside.Grab 2 other bowls. Put flour in one bowl.'),(963379,8,'Place the egg and Dijon mustard in the last bowl. Briskly whisk the egg and mustard until well combined.'),(963379,9,'Cut the 10 ounces of cod into 6 equal sized pieces. Generously salt (about 1 teaspoon) and pepper (about 1/2 teaspoon) both sides of each of the cod pieces.Being gentle, dredge each piece in flour. Be generous you should use up most of the flour. Then dredge each piece is the mustard + egg mixture.Finally dredge each piece in the panko. All 3 of the mixtures should be all used up.'),(963379,10,'Remove the fries from the oven and separate them to either side of the pan so there is a section in the center.'),(963379,11,'Place the 6 pieces of fish in the center and put back in the oven for 9-13 minutes or until the fish is cooked through and the fries are crispy. Broil for 30 seconds if desired.'),(963379,12,'Remove from the oven and toss the fries with another teaspoon (or to taste) of the fry seasoning mix. Toss with the Parmesan cheese if desired.Enjoy immediately with tartar sauce and fresh lemon.'),(963427,1,'Turn on the saute function, melt the butter in your pot and cook the onions and carrots in the butter until they start to soften (no need to cook all the way, the IP will do the rest!).'),(963427,2,'Next, add the roughly chopped broccoli (DO NOT add the broccoli that you chopped into small pieces yet!), the cauliflower, 1/2 tsp salt and the broth.'),(963427,3,'Put the lid on and set on manual for 3 minutes, quick release when it\'s finished.'),(963427,4,'You can either use an immersion blender to blend everything right in the pot, or blend in batches in a regular blender.'),(963427,5,'Add in the finely chopped broccoli, put back on saute mode and cook until the broccoli has softened (should just take a few minutes). Stir in the cheese, add pepper to taste and serve!'),(963427,6,'In a large pot, melt the butter over medium heat, then add the onions and carrots. Cook, stirring occasionally until they start to soften (they will finish cooking later, so don\'t worry about trying to make them super soft).'),(963427,7,'Next, add the roughly chopped broccoli (DO NOT add the broccoli that you chopped into small pieces yet!), the cauliflower, 1/2 tsp salt and the broth. Cover and simmer until veggies are all VERY soft. You should be able to mash them against the side of the pot with the back of a spoon.'),(963427,8,'Meanwhile, cook the broccoli that\'s been chopped small in the microwave. I put them in a glass casserole dish with a lid and a couple of tablespoons of water, then cooked until very soft. It took about 5 minutes or so, but all microwaves are different so keep an eye on yours the first time you make this.'),(963427,9,'Once veggies from the pot (with the chicken broth) are soft, puree the mixture in the blender in batches until all of the contents of the pot are pureed. Return to pot.'),(963427,10,'Heat pot on low heat. Stir in the shredded cheddar cheese and the cooked finely chopped broccoli until all of the cheese is melted.'),(963427,11,'Add pepper to taste.'),(963427,12,'Serve!'),(963427,13,'*Just a little note - this makes a pretty thick soup, that\'s how my family likes it, but if your family likes it thinner, by all means, add some extra broth until it\'s the way you want.'),(963470,1,'To Make The Chicken Salad:Toss all ingredients together in a large bowl until combined.'),(963735,1,'Preheat the oven to 325 degrees.In a large cast iron skillet melt the butter on medium heat and add in the onions and half the salt.'),(963735,2,'Let cook for 15-20 minutes stirring every few minutes.Once they start caramelizing remove them from the pan.'),(963735,3,'Add in the canola oil and turn the heat up to medium-high.Season the brisket with the remaining salt and pepper.Brown on both sides for 3-5 minutes on each side.'),(963735,4,'Remove the beef and add the garlic, Worcestershire sauce, beef broth and beef base (if using).Stir well and add the brisket back in fat side up.Top with the onions and tent tightly with foil or a lid.Cook for 3-4 hours.'),(963829,1,'In a large deep skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.'),(963829,2,'Add onions, mushrooms, and jalapeno and cook until onions are softened, 7-10 minutes.'),(963829,3,'Add tomatoes with their juices, bell pepper strips, broth, cumin, paprika, oregano, salt, and pepper. Lower the heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until thickened.Crack each egg on top of the tomatoes. Cover and cook for 6-8 minutes or until the whites are set and the yolks are still runny.'),(963829,4,'Remove from the heat and top with basil and goat cheese.'),(963829,5,'Serve immediately (the eggs will still cook if you leave them in the tomatoes).'),(964157,1,'In a large, heavy-bottomed pot, bring the vegetable oil to optimum frying temperature - aim for 350 degrees.In a large bowl, toss the chicken with the corn starch until well coated.Fry the chicken in batches - do not overcrowd the fryer.  Fry each batch for 5-6 minutes.  (The chicken pieces should be a light golden brown colour.)'),(964157,2,'Remove from oil and place chicken on a baking sheet.When all the chicken has been fried, move on to the sauce.In a large skillet, add all of the sauce ingredients and bring to a boil.'),(964157,3,'Whisk the sauce occasionally until the desired thickness has been achieved.  The thicker the sauce, the better it will coat the chicken.Once the sauce has thickened, add the cooked chicken and toss to coat.  Cook for 5 minutes, tossing regularly.'),(964157,4,'Transfer the chicken to a serving platter.'),(964157,5,'Garnish with fresh parsley or green onions and serve immediately.'),(964506,1,'Preheat oven to 350F. Spray a jumbo muffin tin with nonstick spray, and set aside.First, cook the Morning'),(964506,2,'Star Farms sausage patties and bacon.'),(964506,3,'Heat a medium nonstick pan over medium-high heat, add the olive oil, and cook until sausage and bacon are warmed through.In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, and spices. Divide the egg mixture evenly among the 6 jumbo muffin cavities.To make 3 sausage and 3 bacon egg patties, crumble 1 sausage patty in each of 3 muffin cavities, then crumble 2 bacon strips in each of the remaining 3 cavities.'),(964506,4,'Bake in preheated oven for 15-18 minutes, until golden brown on top and no longer jiggly.'),(964506,5,'Serve immediately by themselves or inside a sandwich, or refrigerate leftovers. To freeze, let egg patties cool to room temperature, then wrap tightly in plastic wrap, place in freezer zip-top bag, and microwave when needed.*NOTE: if you don\'t have a jumbo muffin pan, you can make these in a normal muffin pan but cook time may vary as they will be thicker*'),(964694,1,'Preheat an oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).'),(964694,2,'Place the ground turkey, onion, garlic, egg, bread crumbs, Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese, parsley, pesto, milk, salt, and black pepper in a bowl.'),(964694,3,'Mix until evenly blended, then form into 1 3/4-inch meatballs. Make a hole in the meatball with your finger and place a cheese cube in the hole. Seal the meatball around the cheese and place on a nonstick baking sheet.'),(964694,4,'Drizzle the olive oil over the meatballs.'),(964694,5,'Bake in the preheated oven until the meatballs are no longer pink in the center, about 30 minutes.'),(964694,6,'Heat the marinara sauce in a saucepan over low heat. Bring to a simmer, and place the baked meatballs in the marinara sauce for about 2 minutes.'),(964845,1,'Pour all ingredients into a lidded container.Seal and shake to combine.Refrigerate leftover dressing, use within 7 days.'),(965037,1,'Combine the drained tuna with chopped celery and mayonnaise. Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper.'),(965037,2,'Serve over the baby spinach. Dress the baby spinach first if desired with a small amount of lemon juice and olive oil (1 tsp each), remember to include the additional NC for the lemon juice (about 0.3g NC per tsp).'),(965279,1,'This soup is best if made the day before serving.In stock pot sweat onions in olive oil, when soft add carrots, salt and pepper to taste. Cook for 2-3 minutes over medium heat. Then add in lentils and stir for 1-2 minutes.'),(965279,2,'Add broth and bring to a vigerous boil, slightly covered for 15-20 minutes.'),(965279,3,'Add 4 cups water, salt and pepper to taste and simmer on low for a few hours. When reheating add in 1/4 cup grated Parmesan or Romano cheese. A little extra cheese can be added when serving and if you want you can also make and add some small macaroni pasta to the soup. Enjoy!'),(965873,1,'Im Heidi  This site celebrates cooking, and aspires to help you integrate the power of lots of vegetables and whole foods into your everyday meals. The recipes youll find here are vegetarian, often vegan, written with the home cook in mind.Follow Heidi'),(965873,2,'Instagram'),(965873,3,'Youtube'),(965873,4,'Facebook'),(965873,5,'PinterestRSS Feed'),(965873,6,'My Cookbooks'),(965873,7,'Near & FarSuper Natural Every DaySuper Natural Cooking'),(965914,1,'Whisk together buttermilk, minced garlic, salt, chili powder, sugar, and ground pepper.'),(965914,2,'Place chicken pieces in a large gallon size ziplock back (or a large mixing bowl), then pour the buttermilk mixture over the chicken, make sure the chicken are all fully covered.'),(965914,3,'Let the chicken marinate in the fridge for at least 4 hours, preferably overnight.When ready to roast, return the chicken to room temperature.Line a baking dish with aluminum foil, and preheat oven to 220 Celsius (425 Fahrenheit).Arrange chicken pieces on prepared baking dish, drizzle with some olive oil, and sprinkle with some chili powder (or paprika powder).Roast for 50-60 minutes, or until fully cooked and the skin develops some charred spots. If you wish, you can baste the chicken with more oil midway of roasting.Best when serve immediately.'),(965991,1,'Heat oven to 450F. Pre-bake 9\" pie crust until lightly golden, 10-12 minutes.Cook turkey bacon. Cool and chop into small pieces.'),(965991,2,'Add olive oil to the pan and heat over medium heat.'),(965991,3,'Add the leeks and mushrooms, and cook for 5-8 minutes, until soft and cooked through.In a large measuring glass or bowl, beat together the eggs and milk.'),(965991,4,'Add the salt, pepper, turkey bacon, leeks and mushrooms.When pie crust is done, reduce oven heat to 350F.'),(965991,5,'Pour egg mixture into the pre-baked pie crust and bake for 40-50 minutes, until middle is cooked through (it won\'t jiggle and inserting a knife into the middle shouldn\'t leak any liquid).To Freeze:Allow baked quiche to cool completely.Cover with plastic wrap, and then aluminum foil. Label with the name, date, and re-heating instructions using a sharpie.Freeze for up to 3 months.To reheat thawed quiche:Thaw completely.'),(965991,6,'Heat in a 350F oven for 30 minutes, until heated through.To reheat from frozen (note: if you used a glass pie dish, thaw completely before placing in the oven)'),(965991,7,'Place frozen quiche (covered with foil) in a 350F oven for 30 minutes-1 hour (depending on the size of your quiche), until heated through.'),(966048,1,'Cut florets from the head of broccoli and place in the bowl of a food processor. Pulse until the broccoli florets are broken up into tiny pieces resembling rice, and then add riced broccoli to a large mixing bowl. Repeat this step in batches until all of the broccoli is pulsed. Wipe out food processor to use later on.'),(966048,2,'Add 1 tbsp of olive oil to a large skillet set over medium heat.'),(966048,3,'Add broccoli rice and stir. Cover the skillet and cook for about 5 minutes, stirring until the broccoli has softened a bit.'),(966048,4,'Remove the skillet from the heat.'),(966048,5,'Add basil leaves, remaining 1/4 cup (4 tbsp) olive oil, nuts, garlic, 2 tbsp Parmesan, lemon juice, salt, and pepper to the food processor and pulse until the basil and nuts are broken up into small pieces and the ingredients are combined.Fold the basil mixture and remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan into the sauteed broccoli rice. Season with additional salt, pepper, lemon juice, Parmesan, etc. to your taste.'),(966300,1,'Turn oven to 325oFLine baking dish (9'),(966300,2,'with parchment paper to allow for easy release'),(966300,3,'Melt butter in microwave safe bowl or microwave safe measuring cup'),(966300,4,'In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients, sifting flour and cocoa powder, and transfer to food processor'),(966300,5,'Combine eggs, vanilla and instant coffee / espresso in a small bowl and add to dry ingredients, turning on food processor to combine'),(966300,6,'Keeping food processor on, slowly add melted butter to mixture'),(966300,7,'Transfer mixture evenly to your baking dish and bake at 325oF for 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean (check starting at 30 mins)Set aside in baking dish to cool'),(966687,1,'Beat whipping cream, sugar, and vanilla until soft peaks form.'),(966687,2,'Add in mascarpone cheese and amaretto and continue to whip to stiff peaks.Dip lady fingers in coffee (and brandy if using) and place in an 88 pan to make the first layer  you can fit about 7 cookies in each layer. Don\'t let them soak as the will fall apart, just a quick dunk in the coffee is enough.'),(966687,3,'Spread half of the whipped cream mixture on top of first layer of lady fingers. Repeat process with second layer of lady fingers and cream mixture.Dust the top of dessert with cocoa powder using a sieve. Refrigerate for about 2-4 hours (it gets even better in the fridge and is a perfect make-ahead dessert).'),(968879,1,'Add all the ingredients to a blender.'),(968879,2,'Blend until smooth. (Duh.)'),(969189,1,'Pre-heat the oven to 37'),(969189,2,'L