o pot, season with salt and pepper to taste and cook, stirring occasionally until browned.'),(981996,2,'Drain majority of fat from beef and set aside (you can drain it all if you want it to be healthier I just like the little bit of flavor a small amount of the fat gives).'),(981996,3,'Heat remaining 1 Tbsp olive oil in pot, add chopped yellow onion and saute until it begins to soften, about 3 minutes.'),(981996,4,'Add in garlic and saute 30 seconds longer.'),(981996,5,'Add in chicken broth, diced tomatoes, crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, oregano, rosemary, fennel seeds, thyme, sugar, parsley, the cooked ground beef and season with salt and pepper to taste. Bring just to a boil, then reduce heat to medium-low, cover and simmer 20 minutes.'),(981996,6,'Meanwhile, prepare lasagna noodles according to directions listed on package, reserving 1 cup pasta water before draining pasta.'),(981996,7,'Add cooked pasta to soup along with 1/2 cup  1 cup pasta water as desired. In a mixing bowl, using a fork, stir together mozzarella, parmesan and ricotta.'),(981996,8,'Ladle soup into bowls, dollop with a large scoop of the cheese mixture and sprinkle with chopped parsley (you can help the cheese melt better by cooking in the microwave after dolloping over soup for a bit or you could put the soup in oven safe bowl, top with cheese mixture and set under broiler to melt well. Or just stir into very hot soup and it should melt well).'),(981996,9,'To continue, See the next page (Click the red Next button below)'),(982274,1,'Preheat the oven to 35'),(982274,2,'Put cheese in a microwave safe bowl. Microwave one minute. Stir. Microwave 30 seconds. Stir. At this point all the cheese should be melted. Microwave 30 more seconds until uniform and gloopy (it should look like cheese fondue at this point).'),(982274,3,'Add the rest of the dough ingredients and the cheese to a food processor.'),(982274,4,'Mix using the dough blade until a uniform color. If you do not have a food processor you can mix in a medium bowl with a wooden spoon but you may need to dump it onto wax paper and knead it by hand to thoroughly incorporate the ingredients. Once it is a uniform color wet your hands and press it out into a 912 ish rectangle on a parchment lined baking sheet.'),(982274,5,'To make the cream cheese filling you can add the cream cheese, vanilla, egg, and sweetener to the food processor (no need to wash) or to the bowl you were using.'),(982274,6,'Mix until smooth in the food processor or with an electric mixer.'),(982274,7,'Put the filling down the center of the dough. Mine was spreading out a bit so I just pushed it back to the middle with a rubber spatula.'),(982274,8,'Sprinkle the blueberries on top.'),(982274,9,'Cut one inch strips down the edges of the dough as shown in the photo. Criss cross one over the other, braiding as you go down.'),(982274,10,'Bake for 40-45 min until the dough is golden and the cheese filling no longer jiggles.'),(982962,1,'Saute onions in olive oil on medium-high heat until browned and translucent, approx. 10 minutes.'),(982962,2,'Add minced garlic and saute for another minute.'),(982962,3,'Add wine, stir to life any browned onions/garlic from bottom of the pot, and simmer for a couple of minutes.'),(982962,4,'Add tomatoes, half of the herbs, salt, pepper, and crushed red pepper. Stir, and let simmer on low heat for 3 hours, stirring and tasting occasionally.'),(982962,5,'Add seasoning as needed.'),(982962,6,'If sauce is looking too thin, leave lid ajar for a while.'),(982962,7,'During the last 10 minutes of cooking, add rest of the herbs.'),(983344,1,'Heat the oil in a large nonstick pot over medium high heat.'),(983344,2,'Add the onion and saute until softened, about 5 minutes.'),(983344,3,'Add 2 teaspoons of the garlic and saute for 1 minute, stirring constantly to prevent burning.'),(983344,4,'Add the uncooked quinoa and 1/2 teaspoon chili powder.'),(983344,5,'Sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),(983344,6,'Saute for another 1 minute to add flavor to the quinoa.'),(983344,7,'Add the broth, bring to a boil, cover and cook for 15-20 minutes. When the quinoa is done, it will be soft throughout. Fluff with a fork and toss with fresh minced parsley.'),(983344,8,'While the quinoa is cooking, heat 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet over medium high heat. When the pan is hot and the butter is melted, add the shrimp and sprinkle with the remaining 1/2 teaspoon chili powder directly in the pan. Season with salt and pepper and saute until no longer translucent and golden brown on the outside. Just at the end of the saute, add 1 teaspoon garlic and swirl around in the pan until the garlic is very fragrant.'),(983344,9,'Melt the remaining 5 tablespoons butter with the 2 teaspoons garlic to make a sauce for drizzling (for this, crushed garlic or garlic paste would work really well but minced is also fine).'),(983344,10,'Serve the quinoa and shrimp together in one dish, topping with fresh chopped parsley and lemon juice if desired. When the butter is melted and cooled slightly, drizzle over the shrimp and quinoa.'),(983344,11,'Serve immediately, while still hot.'),(983547,1,'Heat a Dutch oven or large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook and stir beef and onion in the hot Dutch oven until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes; drain and discard grease.'),(983547,2,'Add cabbage, tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, garlic, salt, and pepper and bring to a boil. Cover Dutch oven, reduce heat, and simmer until cabbage is tender, about 30 minutes.'),(984315,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.'),(984315,2,'In a food processor add garlic and walnuts and pulse. Then add in the spinach, salt, cheese and olive oil. Process until it all comest together.'),(984315,3,'Spray a baking dish with cooking spray and lay out your tilapia filets. Take a paper towel and dry off the filets.'),(984315,4,'Spread the pesto over the filets. I only used half of the pesto to make 4 filets.'),(984315,5,'Place in the oven and bake for 12 minutes. Then set under the broiler for 3 minutes or until bubbly and a little browned.'),(984315,6,'Serve immediately.'),(984786,1,'Preheat oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Grease and flour a 10 inch Bundt pan.'),(984786,2,'In a large bowl, mix the flour, 2 cups sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Blend in buttermilk, 1 cup of butter, 2 teaspoons of vanilla and 4 eggs. Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.'),(984786,3,'Pour batter into prepared pan.'),(984786,4,'Bake in preheated oven for 60 minutes, or until a wooden toothpick inserted into center of cake comes out clean. Prick holes in the still warm cake. Slowly pour sauce over cake.'),(984786,5,'Let cake cool before removing from pan.'),(984786,6,'To Make Butter Sauce: In a saucepan combine the remaining 3/4 cups sugar, 1/3 cup butter, 2 teaspoons vanilla, and the water. Cook over medium heat, until fully melted and combined, but do not boil.'),(985109,1,'Whisk to blend. Set aside.   In the bowl of an electric stand mixer, on medium speed, whip together butter, shortening and sugar until very pale and fluffy, about 4 minutes, scrapping down the sides of the bowl as needed.'),(985109,2,'Add the egg and mix to combine.'),(985109,3,'Add the egg white, vanilla and almond extract and mix until well combined.   With the mixer running on the lowest setting, slowly add in dry ingredients and mix just until combined.'),(985109,4,'Transfer dough to an airtight container and refrigerate 1 1/2 - 2 hours or until the dough is firm. (I refrigerated the dough overnight because that is what worked best for my schedule.)   When ready to bake, preheat oven to 37'),(985109,5,'Prepare cookie pans by either using a Silpat or parchment paper. Set aside.   While the oven is heating, sprinkle a clean work surface with cake flour. Turn out half of the dough onto the work surface. Lightly sprinkle the surface of the dough with cake flour.   Evenly roll dough out to a generous 1/4-inch thickness (that means bigger than 1/4-inch but less than 1/2-inch  ), or up to 1/2-inch for thicker cookies. (The pictured cookies were about 1/2-inch in thickness because I ate all of the thinner ones. Yum.)'),(985109,6,'Cut into desired shapes. (I used a medium heart cookie cutter and got 20 cookies).'),(985109,7,'Transfer to Silpat or parchment paper lined baking sheets.'),(985109,8,'Bake in preheated oven 8 - 11 minutes ( The cookies should be a pale color, not brown. Overcooking will cause a crispy cookie, which totally defeats the purpose of a soft cookie, right? ).'),(985109,9,'Remove from oven and allow to cool on baking sheet several minutes before transferring to wire rack to cool.   Repeat the cookie process with the remainder of the cookie dough and as much of the dough scraps as you can use. The cookies that are made out of the dough scraps will still taste very good, but they may not be as soft as the cookies which were cut from the first pass.   Cool completely then frost with Vanilla Frosting and add sprinkles if desired. If using sprinkles, be sure to sprinkle immediately after frosting each cookie so that the sprinkles will stick before the frosting sets.   Store in an airtight container at room temperature.'),(985109,10,'For the vanilla frosting:   Put all of the frosting ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Using an electric hand mixer, mix on low speed until ingredients are combined.   Increase mixer to medium-high speed and whip until frosting is pale, smooth and fluffy.'),(985880,1,'Heat oven to 375 degrees. In a small bowl, stir together chili powder, paprika, garlic powder, pepper,  teaspoon salt, and red pepper flake.'),(985880,2,'Drizzle pork roast with 1 tablespoon olive oil. Rub seasoning onto roast.'),(985880,3,'Roast for 50-60 minutes, until internal temperature reaches 160 degrees.'),(985880,4,'Stir together black beans, avocado, cilantro, scallions, lime juice, 3 tablespoons olive oil, and  teaspoon salt.'),(985880,5,'Serve salad with roast.'),(986054,1,'Pound chicken breasts thin.'),(986054,2,'Cut into large stips. Season one side of chicken with all-purpose seasoning.'),(986054,3,'Turn an electric pressure cooker to browning setting.'),(986054,4,'Add canola oil and heat until very hot.'),(986054,5,'Place seasoned side of chicken facing down and season another side.'),(986054,6,'Bronw chicken breasts on both sides, turning once or twice.'),(986054,7,'Pour chicken broth over browned chicken.'),(986054,8,'Set the machine to high pressure.'),(986054,9,'Set timer to cook for 12 minutes.'),(986054,10,'Open pressure cooker, using Quick Release method.'),(986054,11,'Remove cooked chicken breasts from the cooker and transfer to serving plates.'),(986054,12,'Serve hot!'),(986619,1,'Reduce heat to low, cover, and allow to simmer, stirring occasionally, for about 30 minutes.'),(986619,2,'Just before serving, mix the bacon into the cooked cabbage.'),(986619,3,'Serve immediately.'),(986803,1,'Begin by making the stew. Coat the bottom of a large pot with 2 tablespoons of oil and place it over medium heat. When the oil is hot, add the mushrooms in an even layer. Avoid crowding the pan and cook them in batches if needed. Allow the mushrooms to cook for about 5 minutes, flip, and cook 5 minutes more, until lightly browned on both sides.'),(986803,2,'Remove them from the pot and transfer to a plate.'),(986803,3,'Add the remaining oil to the pot. When the oil is hot, add the celery, carrot, and onion. Saut for about 10 minutes, until the veggies begin to soften.Stir in the garlic and flour. Saut about 2 minutes more, until the garlic is very fragrant and the flour evenly coats the veggies.Stir in the stout, broth, tomato paste, cabbage, potato and thyme. Return the mushrooms to the pot. Raise the heat and bring the liquid to a boil. Lower the heat and allow the mixture to simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. The veggies should be a bit firm at this point. You can add up to a cup of water during simmering if the broth reduces too much.While the stew simmers, make the dumpling dough. Stir the flour, nutritional yeast, baking powder, salt, thyme and chives together in a medium mixing bowl. Stir in the milk and oil to form a soft and sticky dough. Be careful not to overmix.After the stew has simmered for 10 minutes, taste test the broth and season it with salt and pepper to taste. Then drop 2-3 tablespoon dollops of the dough into the stew. Make sure you\'ve got plenty of room, as the dumplings will expand as they cook.Cover the pot and lower the heat. Allow to simmer for about 15 minutes more, until the veggies are tender and the dumplings are fluffy.Ladle into bowls and serve.'),(986847,1,'In a large mixing bowl, sift together flour, sugar baking powder, baking soda, and salt.'),(986847,2,'Whisk in buttermilk, eggs, and melted butter just until combined.'),(986847,3,'Preheat a flat griddle over medium-high heat.'),(986847,4,'Scoop  cup of pancake batter onto griddle.'),(986847,5,'Let pancakes cook until bubbles form before flipping.'),(986847,6,'Cook other side until golden brown.'),(986847,7,'Serve hot with syrup.'),(986985,1,'Heat a large pot over medium heat and add diced onion and peppers.  Cook until softened, 5-7 minutes.Next, add the butternut squash and garlic and cook for another 2-3 minutes.'),(986985,2,'Add all the remaining ingredients, stir until combined, cover and let simmer until butternut squash is fork tender, about 40 minutes.Carefully (you may want to wait until its cooled) add about 3/4 of the soup to a blender or food processor and blend until smooth.  You could add the entire thing if you dont want any chunks.'),(986985,3,'Add the pureed soup back to the pot and mix until combined.'),(986985,4,'Serve immediately or store in the refrigerator up to 4 days.'),(987561,1,'Place yeast and sugar in a large mixing bowl.'),(987561,2,'Mix melted butter and milk in a small bowl. The mixture should feel warm to the touch, but not too hot to touch (110-115F).'),(987561,3,'Pour over yeast/sugar and stir 