n making Kashmiri Paneer Gravy, we need to make sure we have the homemade tomato puree.'),(987916,2,'Here\'s how to make homemade tomato puree.'),(987916,3,'Next we boil 2 cups of water with a pinch of turmeric. Once the water is boiled, turn off the heat. We will use this water to place fried paneer pieces.'),(987916,4,'Place a kadai on medium heat and add 2 tablespoons mustard oil.'),(987916,5,'Add the cut paneer pieces into the pan and shallow fry the paneer until you get a nice golden brown on all sides. Turn off the heat.'),(987916,6,'Drop the paneer pieces for the Kashmiri gravy, into the prepared hot turmeric water for few minutes. It will prevent the paneer for being chewy.'),(987916,7,'Into the same pan, add one tablespoon oil.'),(987916,8,'Add badi elaichi, green cardamom, bay leaf, hing and cinnamon stick.'),(987916,9,'Saute for a minute until the aromas of the spices wafts in the air.'),(987916,10,'Next add the homemade tomato puree along with red chilli powder and dry ginger powder.'),(987916,11,'Stir well until all the masalas are well combined and the masala easily comes off from the sides of the kadai.'),(987916,12,'Add in the powdered saunf to the Kashmiri Paneer gravy and mix well'),(987916,13,'Add 1/2 cup water, mix well and simmer for a few minutes.'),(987916,14,'Finally add the fried paneer cubes, garam masala powder and ghee, cover the kadai with the lid and allow it to cook for 2 minutes. After a few minutes, switch off the heat.'),(987916,15,'Garnish with chopped coriander leaves and your Kashmiri Paneer Gravy is ready to be served.'),(987916,16,'Serve Kashmiri Paneer Gravy along with Roti, Naan or Kulcha for a delicious weekend meal.'),(988513,1,'To a small bowl, add garlic powder, dry basil leaves, black pepper and salt.'),(988513,2,'Mix together and season both sides of the chicken breast with the spice blend.'),(988513,3,'Heat large skillet to medium high heat.'),(988513,4,'Add avocado oil to the pan and then add seasoned chicken breasts.'),(988513,5,'Saute each side for 4-6 minutes. Until both sides have a nice sear on them and they are no longer pink when cut into them.'),(988513,6,'Remove from pan and let rest for 3 minutes. Slice the chicken and set aside.'),(988513,7,'To a medium bowl, add balsamic vinegar, olive oil, dijon mustard, honey, dry basil leaves, garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.'),(988513,8,'Whisk together until the vinegar and honey no longer separate and dressing becomes thick.'),(988513,9,'Assemble the salad: to a large bowl add spinach, blackberries, kiwi, red onion, avocado, feta cheese, walnuts and sliced chicken.'),(988513,10,'Serve with balsamic dressing on the side.'),(989078,1,'Wear rubber gloves'),(989078,2,'Dont mix the colors too much into the shaving cream.  The brightest colored eggs happened in the areas where the dye was sitting on top of the shaving cream.'),(989078,3,'Lining the pan with aluminum foil will bake for easier cleanup.'),(989636,1,'Before You Cook'),(989636,2,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees'),(989636,3,'Thoroughly rinse produce and pat dry'),(989636,4,'Prepare a baking sheet with foil and cooking spray'),(989636,5,'Prepare the Ingredients'),(989636,6,'Trim stems off Brussels sprouts and halve vertically (quarter if larger than a ping-pong ball).'),(989636,7,'Peel, trim, and cut carrot into \" slices on an angle.'),(989636,8,'Pat pork tenderloin dry and, on a separate cutting board, cut into \"-thick medallions. Season both sides of medallions with  tsp. salt and a pinch of pepper.'),(989636,9,'Roast the Vegetables'),(989636,10,'Place Brussels sprouts and carrot on prepared baking sheet. Toss with 1 Tbsp. olive oil,  tsp. salt, and a pinch of pepper. Massage oil into vegetables.'),(989636,11,'Spread into a single layer and roast in hot oven until tender and lightly browned, 15-17 minutes.'),(989636,12,'While vegetables roast, cook medallions.'),(989636,13,'Cook the Medallions'),(989636,14,'Place a medium non-stick pan over medium-high heat and add 2