vegetables.'),(990340,5,'Add the rice, moong dal, vegetable broth, and water. Bring everything to a boil, then reduce the heat to low. Cover the pot and simmer the kitchari for about 20 minutes. After 15 minutes of cooking, check to see if there are still enough liquids in the pot. If you notice that the liquids are completely absorbed by the rice and beans, add 1/2 to 1 cup of water and stir to incorporate.'),(990340,6,'Remove the lid and check to see if the rice is tender. If the kitchari is looking too runny, let it simmer, uncovered, for a few more minutes. If the kitchari is too thick, turn off the heat and add 1/2 to 1 cup of water and stir. Taste and see if you need to add a small pinch of salt.'),(990340,7,'Serve the kitchari in bowls, along with chili oil, cilantro, and lemon wedges, if you like.'),(990378,1,'Preheat oven to 350F. Spray a 9-by-5-inch loaf pan with floured cooking spray, or grease and flour the pan; set aside (dont use an 8-by-4-inch pan; its too small)'),(990378,2,'In a small bowl, combine 1/3 cup granulated sugar with the cinnamon and stir to incorporate; set aside.'),(990378,3,'In a large microwave-safe bowl, melt the butter, about 1 minute. After the butter has cooled momentarily (so you dont scramble the egg), add the egg, brown sugar, oil, vanilla, and whisk to combine.'),(990378,4,'Add the buttermilk and whisk to incorporate.'),(990378,5,'Add the flour, nutmeg, baking soda, optional salt, and stir until just combined; dont overmix. Batter will be thick and lumpy. Dont try to stir the lumps smooth.'),(990378,6,'Pour half the batter into prepared pan, smoothing it lightly with a spatula.'),(990378,7,'Sprinkle three-fourths (75%) of the cinnamon-sugar mixture (just eyeball it), distributed evenly over the surface of the batter. This creates the cinnamon ribbon.'),(990378,8,'Top with remaining half of the batter, smoothing it lightly with a spatula.'),(990378,9,'Sprinkle remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture, distributed evenly over the top. It looks like a lot, but its necessary to form the crust, and not all of it aheres.'),(990378,10,'Bake for 45 to 55 minutes (mine took 50), or until top is set and firm, and a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, or with a few moist crumbs, but no batter. Allow bread to cool in pan for about 15 minutes before inverting.'),(990378,11,'Invert bread over the sink or a paper towel to catch some of the non-adhered cinnamon-sugar and sprinkle it back on the bread.'),(990378,12,'Place bread on wire rack to cool completely. Bread will keep airtight at room temperature for up to 5 days, or may be frozen for up to 3 months. Makes wonderful toast.'),(990424,1,'For the cupcakes'),(990424,2,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line cupcake tins with paper liners or spray with non-stick cooking spray.'),(990424,3,'In a large bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.'),(990424,4,'In a medium bowl, whisk together the buttermilk and egg whites.'),(990424,5,'Place the sugar and lemon zest in the bowl of your mixer or another large bowl and rub them together with your fingers until the sugar is moist and fragrant.'),(990424,6,'Add the butter and, working with the paddle or whisk attachment, or with a hand mixer, beat at medium speed for 3 minutes, until the butter and sugar are light and fluffy. Beat in the vanilla, then add one third of the flour mixture, still beating on medium speed. Beat in half of the milk-egg mixture, then beat in half of the remaining dry ingredients until incorporated.'),(990424,7,'Add the rest of the milk and eggs, beating until the batter is thoroughly combined.'),(990424,8,'Add the last of the dry ingredients. Finally, give the batter a good 2-minute beating to ensure that it is thoroughly mixed and well aerated.'),(990424,9,'Using a large scoop (about 3 tablespoons), distribute the batter between 24 muffin wells, filling each well 2/3 full.'),(990424,10,'Bake for 18-22 minutes, or until the cupcakes are springy to the touch and a toothpick inserted into the centers come out clean. Cool on wire rack.'),(990424,11,'Once cupcakes have cooled, hollow out a small circle in the center of each cupcake; I use an apple corer because I am little OCD and obsessed with symmetry. Spoon or pipe in a dollop of lemon curd.'),(990424,12,'For the frosting'),(990424,13,'In a small saucepan, combine 1 1/2 cups sugar with the water and corn syrup; clip a candy thermometer to side of pan. Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves. Continue boiling, without stirring, until syrup reaches 230 degrees.'),(990424,14,'Meawhile, in the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the whisk attachment, whisk egg whites on medium-high speed until soft peaks form. With mixer running, add remaining 2 tablespoons sugar, beating to combine.'),(990424,15,'As soon as sugar syrup reaches 230 degrees, remove from heat. With mixer on medium-low speed, pour syrup down side of bowl in a slow, steady stream. Raise speed to medium-high; whisk until mixture is completely cool (test by touching the bottom of the bowl) and stiff (but not dry) peaks form, about 7 minutes. Use immediately.'),(990424,16,'Frost cooled cupcakes. Use a kitchen torch to lightly brown the meringue frosting.'),(990595,1,'Add peeled and scooped avocado to a blender. It\'s okay to use overripe avocados that are beginning to turn brown in this recipe - in fact, this is a great way to use those up!'),(990595,2,'Add almond milk, spinach, date syrup, cocoa powder, sea salt, and vanilla to the blender, and blend until the mixture is very smooth and creamy.Melt the dark chocolate bar in a small bowl in the microwave. Alternatively, use a double boiler to melt the bar.'),(990595,3,'Add the dark chocolate to the blender, and blend into the pudding mixture.Fully cool for the thickest and richest pudding.Top with berries, coconut whipped cream, or toasted coconut, if desired.'),(991164,1,'In a large pan (see note), heat the olive oil over medium heat.'),(991164,2,'Add the ground beef and sausage and cook it, breaking it apart with a spatula, until its no longer pink.'),(991164,3,'Add the onion, garlic, tomatoes, and red pepper flakes and cook them with the meat for two to three minutes.'),(991164,4,'Add the marinara sauce, water, and salt and stir to combine. Bring the pan to a boil and add the spaghetti. Adjust the heat to maintain a strong simmer and cook the pasta in the sauce for 20 minutes, stirring frequently, or until the pasta is tender.'),(991164,5,'Add the herbs and stir. Top each serving with grated parmesan cheese if using.'),(991494,1,'Stir together all the ingredients except the chicken breasts and pour into a large Ziploc bag.'),(991494,2,'Add the chicken breasts and marinate in the fridge for a couple of hours or overnight.'),(991494,3,'Place the marinaded chicken breasts on an aluminum foil lined cookie sheet and bake at 375 degrees F, uncovered, for about 45 minutes or until the chicken is fully cooked. I use a meat thermometer to make sure the internal temperature is between 170 and 180 degrees F.'),(991494,4,'Do not throw out the marinade. While the chicken is cooking simmer it over low heat and brush it on the chicken about every 10 minutes as it cooks.'),(991494,5,'The nutritional information provided is automatically calculated by third party software and is meant as a guideline only. Exact accuracy is not guaranteed. For recipes where all ingredients may not be used entirely, such as those with coatings on meats, or with sauces or dressings for example, calorie & nutritional values per serving will likely be somewhat lower than indicated.'),(991505,1,'In a large pan, melt butter and stir in riced cauliflower on medium heat.'),(991505,2,'Add seasoning. Continue to cook the cauliflower for 7-8 minutes until the color of the cauliflower is less solid opaque. Turn down heat and stir in cream cheese and cheddar cheese until melted.'),(991505,3,'Sprinkle pepper and green onions and bacon if desired.'),(991794,1,'Preheat oven to 350F. Spray a 9x13 baking pan with non-stick cooking spray and set aside.'),(991794,2,'In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, and salt until well combined. Set aside.'),(991794,3,'In a separate large mixing bowl, whisk together the oil, eggs, brown sugar, granulated sugar, crushed pineapple, and vanilla extract until fully combined.'),(991794,4,'Add the grated carrots and chopped walnuts to the wet ingredients and stir until well combined.'),(991794,5,'Add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients and mix with a whisk or rubber spatula until just combined, making sure not to over mix the batter.'),(991794,6,'Pour the cake batter into the prepared baking pan and spread around into one even layer.'),(991794,7,'Bake at 350F for 35-45 minutes or until the top of the cake is set and a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean. If needed, tent with foil for the last 15-20 minutes of baking to prevent excess browning on top of the cake.'),(991794,8,'Remove from the oven, transfer to a wire rack, and allow to cool completely in the pan.'),(991794,9,'In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, or in a large mixing bowl using a hand-held mixer, beat the cream cheese until smooth.'),(991794,10,'Add the butter and mix for about 30 seconds-1 minute until well combined and smooth.'),(991794,11,'Add the powdered sugar and vanilla extract and continue mixing until fully combined, scraping down the sides of the bowl as needed.'),(991794,12,'Using a knife or an offset spatula, top the cooled carrot cake with the cream cheese frosting. Slice into pieces, serve, and enjoy!'),(991818,1,'In a large jar add berries, vanilla beans, and peppercorns. For a more intense vanilla bean flavor scrape out 1 of the halved beans.'),(991818,2,'In a medium-sized saucepan add apple cider vinegar, water, honey and kosher salt. Bring to a boil over high heat and pour over the berries.'),(991818,3,'Put the lid on the berries and cool to room temperature.'),(991818,4,'Place in the refrigerator and let sit overnight.'),(991818,5,'Enjoy over ice cream, yogurt or in a salad.'),(992173,1,'Blend the beet, berries, banana, avocado, honey, collagen, and almond milk until smooth. Divide between two glasses and garnish with the chocolate and coconut.'),(992173,2,'Enjoy!'),(992905,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour two 8 or 9-inch round cake pans. Set aside.'),(992905,2,'In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Set aside.'),(992905,3,'In the bowl of an electric stand mixer fitted with a paddle attachment, cream together peanut butter, butter and'),(992905,4,'sugars until fluffy, about 3 minutes.'),(992905,5,'Add eggs, one at a time, beating at medium speed for 1 minute between each addition. Stop mixer and scrape down'),(992905,6,'the sides of the bowl as necessary.'),(992905,7,'With the mixer on low speed, add half of the flour mixture to the butter mixture. Slowly add all of the buttermilk.'),(993015,1,'Preheat hte oven to 425 degrees. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.'),(993015,2,'Slice the ends off of the russet potato. Then, slice the sides off so that all sides are flat. Slice the potato lengthwise to get 4 slabs, about 1/4\" thick. Slice these slabs in half lengthwise to yield 8 dippers.'),(993015,3,'Place the potato dippers on the baking sheet and brush with olive oil.'),(993015,4,'Bake for 25-30 minutes or until browned and crispy on the edges.'),(993015,5,'Smear the top 1/3 of each dipper with your desired dip: hummus, avocado, marinara sauce, etc.'),(993173,1,'Hot Cross Buns'),(993173,2,'Place all of your dried fruit (cranberries, raisins, cherries) in a Pyrex or microwave safe measuring cup and pour the rum or apple juice over your mixed fruit. Cover with cling film and microwave in 30 second intervals until the cling film is shrink fit to the top of your measuring cup (usually 1-2 minutes total). Set the heated measuring cup of fruit aside and allow to cool for 20-30 minutes.'),(993173,3,'In a large bowl, or the bowl of your stand mixer, combine the flour (all purpose and bread flour, or use only all purpose flour if you don\'t have bread flour on hand).'),(993173,4,'Add spices (cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg - allspice or cardamom can be substituted if needed), salt, baking powder, and brown sugar. Use a whisk or fork to quickly combine the dry ingredients.'),(993173,5,'Add the wet ingredients (butter, eggs, egg yolk, and milk) and combine, kneading until an elastic dough is formed (about 3 minutes with a stand mixer).'),(993173,6,'Mix in the cooled fruit and all of the rum or apple juice that was in your measuring cup.'),(993173,7,'Cover the dough with cling film or a warmed tea towel and allow to rise for an hour (your dough may not double during that rise, but will increase in bulk).'),(993173,8,'Turn your dough out onto a lightly floured work surface and knead until smooth. Divide your dough into approximately 12 portions (I usually fill my 9 x 13 pan with rows of 3 x 4 buns for my 12 portions). Round each portion into a nice bun, placing the buns seams side down in your lightly greased pan.'),(993173,9,'Cover the buns with cling film or your warmed tea towel again, and allow to rise for an additional hour. Or until they have increased in size enough that they are touching each other in the pan.'),(993173,10,'(When your dough is almost completely risen) Preheat your oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).'),(993173,11,'Mix the reserved egg white with milk, whisk and then brush over the tops of each of the buns.'),(993173,12,'Bake the hot cross buns for 25-30 minutes for a dozen, or 20-25 minutes if you have made 14 portions (or more). The buns will be golden brown when done.'),(993173,13,'Remove from the oven and turn out onto a wire cooling rack (the buns will pop out as one sheet of buns). Allow your hot cross buns to cool completely before making the cross with your icing.'),(993173,14,'Hot Cross Bun Icing'),(993173,15,'In a small mixing bowl, combine confectioners sugar, salt, vanilla (or almond) extract and 1 Tbsp heavy cream. Stir until you have a nice thick icing (using more heavy cream if needed).'),(993173,16,'Transfer icing into a piping bag with a small round piping tip, or into a ziploc baggie and snip a small tip off to pipe through. Make a cross on top of each of your buns.'),(993461,1,'Whiskey Glazed'),(993461,2,'Baked Ham'),(993461,3,'From the Kitchen of Deep South Dish'),(993461,4,'Prep time: 10 min |Cook time: 2 hours 40 min |'),(993848,1,'Before You Cook'),(993848,2,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees'),(993848,3,'Thoroughly rinse produce and pat dry'),(993848,4,'Prepare a baking sheet with foil and cooking spray'),(993848,5,'Ingredient(s) used more than once: Parmesan'),(993848,6,'Roast the Broccoli'),(993848,7,'Toss broccoli florets with 2 tsp. olive oil,  tsp. salt, and a pinch of pepper on prepared baking sheet. Massage oil into broccoli.'),(993848,8,'Spread into a single layer and roast in hot oven until lightly browned, 18-20 minutes.'),(993848,9,'While broccoli roasts, toast panko.'),(993848,10,'Toast the Panko'),(993848,11,'Place a medium non-stick pan over medium-high heat.'),(993848,12,'Add 1 tsp. olive oil and panko hot pan. Stir constantly until toasted, 30-90 seconds.'),(993848,13,'Transfer panko to a plate.'),(993848,14,'Wipe pan clean and reserve.'),(993848,15,'Cook the Chicken'),(993848,16,'Pat chicken breasts dry, and season both sides with a pinch of salt and pepper.'),(993848,17,'Return pan used to toast panko to medium heat.'),(993848,18,'Add 1 tsp. olive oil and chicken to hot pan.'),(993848,19,'Cook until chicken is golden brown and reaches a minimum internal temperature of 165 degrees, 5-7 minutes per side.'),(993848,20,'Remove chicken to a plate.'),(993848,21,'Wipe pan clean and reserve.'),(993848,22,'Make the Sauce'),(993848,23,'Return pan used to cook chicken to medium-high heat.'),(993848,24,'Add cream to pan and bring to a rolling boil.'),(993848,25,'Rolling means more than a few bubbles; a rolling boil means water is boiling vigorously, 20-30 seconds.'),(993848,26,'Remove from burner.'),(993848,27,'Stir in butter, half the Parmesan (reserve remaining for broccoli), and green peppercorns. Season with a pinch of salt.'),(993848,28,'Finish the Dish'),(993848,29,'Sprinkle toasted panko over broccoli.'),(993848,30,'Plate dish as pictured on front of card, serving sauce on top of chicken and garnishing broccoli with remaining Parmesan. Bon appetit!'),(993892,1,'For the crust:Preheat the oven to 350 degrees (F)'),(993892,2,'Combine the crust ingredients in a medium bowl and mix well with a fork until a dough forms.Press into an 8 inch springform pan or pie plate.'),(993954,1,'Heat olive oil in 6-quart (6 l0 electric pressure cooker turned to browning functions.'),(993954,2,'Add chunked beef, season with salt and black pepper, and cook stirring occasionally, until browned on all sides, for about 8 minutes.'),(993954,3,'Remove cooked meat from the pot and transfer to a large bowl.'),(993954,4,'Pour the brandy into the instant pot and stir up any browned bits on the bottom.'),(993954,5,'Stir in dry red wine.'),(993954,6,'Return cooked beef with any accumulated juices to the pot.'),(993954,7,'In a medium mixing bowl, combine beef broth and all-purpose flour.'),(993954,8,'Whisk until the flour dissolves completely. Stir broth mixture into the pot.'),(993954,9,'Stir in green olives, thyme, sage, and bay leaves.'),(993954,10,'Close pressure cooker and lock the lid.'),(993954,11,'Set the machine to cook at high pressure.'),(993954,12,'Set timer to cook for 30 minutes.'),(993954,13,'Meanwhile, melt butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium-low heat.'),(993954,14,'Add pearl onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until they are soft and lightly browned, for about 10 minutes.'),(993954,15,'Remove the skillet from the heat.'),(993954,16,'Using the Quick Release method, bring the instant pot to normal.'),(993954,17,'Unlock and open the lid.'),(993954,18,'Scrape browned onions with any accumulated juices of the skillet into the stew. Stir well.'),(993954,19,'Close pressure cooker and lock the lid.'),(993954,20,'Set machine to cook at high pressure.'),(993954,21,'Set timer to cook for 7 minutes.'),(993954,22,'Turn off the electric instant pot and let pressure fall back to normal naturally, 15-20 minutes.'),(993954,23,'Unlock and open the lid.'),(993954,24,'Discard bay leaves.'),(993954,25,'Stir stew well before serving.'),(993985,1,'Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F. Line a large sheet pan with parchment paper and set aside.'),(993985,2,'Grab three bowls.'),(993985,3,'Add the flour to one bowl.'),(993985,4,'Combine panko, 1/2 cup freshly grated parmesan cheese, dried parsley, garlic powder, about 1/2 teaspoon each of salt (I use seasoned salt) and pepper. Stir.'),(993985,5,'In the final bowl, add 1-2 teaspoons lemon zest, 4-5 tablespoons lemon juice (depending on lemon flavor intensity desired), minced garlic, and 5 tablespoons melted butter. Stir.'),(993985,6,'Remove 4 tablespoons of this mixture and set aside.'),(993985,7,'Slice chicken breasts to the size of tenders (about 1 and 1/4th inch strips) or use chicken tenders.'),(993985,8,'Coat in flour, heavily dredge in garlic lemon mixture, and then coat in the Parmesan panko mixture.'),(993985,9,'Place on prepared sheet pan. Use any remaining Parmesan panko mixture and sprinkle over tenders.'),(993985,10,'Sprinkle lemon pepper seasoning over the tenders (I use Mrs. Dash lemon pepper)'),(993985,11,'Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes and remove.'),(993985,12,'Flip the tenders to the other side.'),(993985,13,'Place the asparagus next to the tenders and drizzle the reserved lemon butter sauce.'),(993985,14,'Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese over the asparagus and toss with tongs.'),(993985,15,'If desired place lemon slices over the chicken (optional)'),(993985,16,'Return to the oven and bake for another 10-12 minutes or until the internal temperature of the chicken has reached 165 degrees F.'),(993985,17,'Meanwhile, whisk remaining 3 tablespoons melted butter, 3 tablespoons lemon juice, 1-2 teaspoons lemon zest, 3 tablespoons olive oil, and 3 tablespoons honey in a small bowl.'),(993985,18,'Add some pepper and parsley if desired.'),(993985,19,'Remove from the oven and top with the honey lemon mixture and fresh parsley if desired and enjoy immediately.'),(993985,20,'Do not top chicken breasts with the honey lemon mixture unless eating immediately and aren\'t planning on having leftovers since it will make it soggy.'),(994306,1,'In a large bowl, combine the cooked noodles, bacon, tomatoes, and romaine lettuce and toss.In a smaller bowl, combine the mayonnaise, sour cream, yellow mustard, salt, and pepper.'),(994306,2,'Whisk together and pour into the large bowl.Stir until everything is evenly coated and serve! Top with extra bacon, lettuce, and tomatoes.'),(994495,1,'Preheat oven to 200 degrees and preheat a Belgian waffle iron (or standard waffle iron).'),(994495,2,'In a mixing bowl whisk together flour, cornstarch, baking powder, baking soda and salt for 20 seconds, make a well in center of mixture and set aside.'),(994495,3,'In a separate mixing bowl whisk together buttermilk, milk, vegetable oil, vanilla extract and egg yolks until combined.'),(994495,4,'In a separate bowl, using an electric hand mixer set on high speed, whip egg whites (make sure there isn\'t a drop of yolk or they\'ll never fluff up) until soft peaks form.'),(994495,5,'Add sugar and whip until stiff glossy peaks form.'),(994495,6,'While whisking, pour buttermilk mixture into well in flour mixture and mix just until combined (batter should be slightly lumpy). Fold in egg white mixture.'),(994495,7,'Cook batter in waffle iron according to manufactures directions. Once each waffle is done, transfer to warm oven and allow to rest until crisp.'),(994495,8,'Serve warm with butter and maple syrup.'),(994495,9,'Variations - serve with sweetened whipped cream, fresh berries and fresh fruit syrup. For churro waffles brush top of waffle with melted butter (be sure to get in each square) then pour a generous amount of cinnamon sugar into a 9-inch pie dish and dunk butter coated side in cinnamon sugar mixture.'),(994495,10,'Recipe source: inspired by Fifteen Spatulas and Fine Cooking'),(994589,1,'Preheat Oven to 450'),(994589,2,'Wash and destem the Portobello Mushrooms'),(994589,3,'Place the mushrooms cap side down on a foil-lined sheet and drizzle with olive oil'),(994589,4,'Sprinkle with Pizza seasoning'),(994589,5,'Layer spinach, tomato, cheese and another round of seasoning'),(994589,6,'Cook in oven until cheese has melted or around 6 minutes'),(994589,7,'Add the pepperoni and cook until the pepperoni is crispy'),(995020,1,'In a large skillet, melt butter with olive oil.'),(995020,2,'Add garlic and saut until fragrant, about 1 minute.'),(995020,3,'Add wine or broth, salt, red pepper flakes and plenty of black pepper and bring to a simmer.'),(995020,4,'Let wine reduce by half, about 2 minutes.'),(995020,5,'Add shrimp and saut until they just turn pink, 2 to 4 minutes depending upon their size. Stir in the parsley and lemon juice and serve over pasta or accompanied by crusty bread.'),(996399,1,'Place broccoli, blueberries, red onion, cranberries, and sunflower seeds in a large bowl. In a small bowl, toss apple with 1 tablespoon lemon juice.'),(996399,2,'Add to the big bowl with the salad.'),(996399,3,'In a small bowl, whisk together all dressing ingredients.'),(996399,4,'Pour dressing over the salad and toss gently to combine. Salad may be served immediately or refrigerated until serving. It will last for 2-3 days in the refrigerator.'),(996901,1,'Make the rice: In a small saucepan, cook the rice according to the package instructions, adding the butter and salt.'),(997077,1,'Cook florets in a large pot of lightly salted water 5-7 minutes, until tender.'),(997077,2,'Drain; return to pot to keep warm while you prepare sauce.'),(997077,3,'Place shallots, 2 tbsp wine and 1 tablespoon lemon juice in a small saucepan over medium heat. Simmer until reduced to 1 tablespoon. Reduce heat to very low; stir in a few small pieces of butter, swirling with a wire whisk until mostly melted.'),(997077,4,'Gradually add the remaining butter, whisking constantly until sauce is smooth. Season with 1/8 tsp salt, 1/8 tsp white pepper and remaining lemon juice to taste. Do not allow sauce to boil.'),(997077,5,'Pour sauce over broccoli. Enjoy!'),(997078,1,'Steam broccoli florets in a steamer basket set in a medium pot over lightly salted boiling water for 5 minutes until crisp-tender.'),(997078,2,'Drain and rinse under cold water.'),(997078,3,'In a blender or food processor, pure garlic, vinegar, capers, salt, and pepper. With motor running, add oil in a thin, steady stream; blend until smooth.'),(997078,4,'Pour dressing into a large salad bowl. Thinly slice broccoli florets and add to dressing.'),(997078,5,'Mix in celery, scallions and olives. Toss gently to coat evenly with dressing and serve.'),(997860,1,'Chop strawberries into small cubes and add them to a mixing bowl.'),(997860,2,'Peel the skin off kiwis and chop them into small cubes as well.'),(997860,3,'Add kiwi to strawberries.'),(997860,4,'Add honey, minced mint, and lime juice.'),(997860,5,'Gently mix everything together until evenly incorporated. Be gently, you don\'t want to bruise or mash the fruit.'),(997860,6,'Serve right away or store in the refrigerator for a few hours before serving.'),(998213,1,'Cut each Brussels sprout in half through the root, then slice thinly.'),(998213,2,'Heat 1 teaspoon of olive oil in a large skillet set over medium heat.'),(998213,3,'Add the onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until the onions are soft, 4 to 5 minutes.'),(998213,4,'Add the remaining 1 teaspoon of olive oil to the skillet, then add the Brussels sprouts. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the Brussels sprouts are tender, but still bright green.'),(998213,5,'Stir in the pistachios, dried cranberries, Parmesan cheese and pepper. Taste and season with additional salt, if desired.'),(998213,6,'Transfer to a serving dish and keep warm until ready to serve.'),(998318,1,'Heat a pan with the oil over a low heat. Stir-fry garlic and onion for five minutes.'),(998318,2,'Add the mushrooms and saut for five minutes.'),(998318,3,'Add the carrot and courgette and cook for a further few minutes.'),(998318,4,'Add the tins of tomato and tomato paste and mix well. Open the can of lentils and drain liquid. Give them a good rinse under the tap and then add to the sauce.'),(998318,5,'Mix again.'),(998318,6,'Sprinkle over the dried oregano and a small handful of chopped parsley/basil.'),(998318,7,'Turn up the heat up until the sauce begins to boil, then turn down the heat and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. The sauce will thicken as it cooks. If it gets too stiff add  cup water and mix well.'),(998318,8,'Serve on top of spaghetti or courgette noodles.'),(998426,1,'Remove from heat and add butter and lemon extract.'),(998426,2,'Sprinkle with xanthan gum and whisk quickly to combine. Stir in sweetener to taste (I like mine rather tart).'),(998426,3,'Whisk in sour cream until no lumps remain.'),(998426,4,'Pour into pie shell and refrigerate for at least 4 hours to set - the longer, the better, so overnight is best if you can wait that long. (It\'s also awesome if you pop it in the freezer for an hour after being refrigerated).   Top with lightly sweetened whipped cream.'),(999278,1,'Preheat oven to 32'),(999278,2,'Spray a 10-inch cast-iron skillet with baking spray with flour.'),(999278,3,'In a large bowl, beat butter and brown sugar with a mixer at medium speed until fluffy, 3 to 4 minutes, stopping to scrape sides of bowl.'),(999278,4,'Add egg and vanilla; beat until combined.'),(999278,5,'In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, and salt. With mixer on low speed, gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture, beating just until combined. Beat in  cup oats and milk.'),(999278,6,'With dampened hands, press half of dough into bottom of prepared skillet.'),(999278,7,'Spread peanut butter onto dough. Drop heaping tablespoonfuls of remaining dough over peanut butter.'),(999278,8,'Sprinkle with chocolate morsels and remaining  cup oats.'),(999278,9,'Bake until golden brown, about 45 minutes, covering loosely with foil during last 10 minutes of baking to prevent excess browning, if necessary.'),(999278,10,'Let cool for 15 minutes.'),(999278,11,'Serve with vanilla ice cream, if desired.'),(999602,1,'In a large mixing bowl, lightly beat egg (s).'),(999602,2,'Add flax seed (if using), applesauce, milk, maple syrup, vanilla, baking soda and salt; whisk until well combined.'),(999602,3,'Add oat flour and almond meal, mix well.'),(999602,4,'Preheat waffle maker. Spray top and bottom griddles with cooking spray each time and make waffles according to your waffle makers instructions. Amount of batter depends on the size of your waffle maker. I have similar to this one and used about 1/3 cup batter per waffle.'),(999602,5,'Store: Refrigerate in air circulating container for up to a week or freeze for up to 6 months.');
